name: HAYDEN
description: I'm HAYDEN, a very smart black and white border collie mix. I'm nine years old (born Aug. 21, 2009) and weigh about 85 pounds. I've been microchipped and have received my rabies and distemper\/parvo\/parainfluenza shots. I've been neutered. I have diabetes and require two insulin injections each day -- the cost per month for this treatment is about $300. I have been treated with monthly flea and tick drops and am on monthly heartworm preventive. My mom was dumped at the Smithville Animal Shelter and was taken home by Blue Sky Animal Rescue just one day before I and my six brothers and sisters were born. I'm happy and am housebroken. I need to be an only dog because I tend to try to protect my family against any other animals. I'd be a good fit with an individual or family who loves to jog or walk. I have too much energy for very small children but would love to play with older kids. I love to cuddle and have a funny fondness for eating ice cubes -- I run to the refrigerator when i hear the ice machine being used. Each animal at Blue Sky Animal Rescue is spayed or neutered, fully vaccinated, heartworm tested, heartworm treated if applicable, de-wormed, given monthly heartworm prevention medication and monthly flea\/tick prevention, and dental care as needed. In many cases, the cost of vetting services is greater than the adoption contribution. The adoption contributions (cash only) help defray the costs of vetting services, but rarely, if ever, cover all expenses. Additional donations are welcomed and much appreciated. Hayden's adoption contribution is $80, and additional donations are welcomed. If you're interested in sharing a loving forever home with him, please E-mail bsarescue@prodigy.net or call Blue Sky Animal Rescue at 512-360-4814 and schedule a visit! Thank you!

name: Charlie Brown
description: <p>Charlie Brown is an American Staffordshire Terrier that is\u00a05 yrs old\/50lbs. He is a very sweet boy who just wants to love and be loved. He came to us with a badly injured leg which required life threatening surgery due to a bad infection. A Good Samaritan saved Charlie and donated the funds for his surgery. His amputated left rear leg does not slow him down one bit. He has a good personality, loves people and gets along well with most dogs in play group. Charlie Brown has no abandonment issues and relishes the love and affection from people. He has not been introduced to cats. He is UTD on vaccinations and Rabies, Neutered, Current on HW Prevention, Microchipped, and Kennel Trained<\/p>

name: Patty
description: Patty is a 6YR old\/76lb Golden Ret\/Chow Mix that was dumped at a business where a Good Samaritan brought her to Kim Acres.  Upon intake we had to assess Patty's limp in her right front leg.  X-Ray showed she has limited mobility due to old ligament tears that had not healed properly; we were told she would have a limp.  Instead of amputation we choose to give Patty months of rehabilitation and after 7 months she has learned to walk on her leg.  We have no way of knowing if this is permanent, she has lots of energy and never once let her leg injury slow her down.  Her personality is very sweet; she loves play group\/other dogs.  She will need someone that will be very patient with her.  She has not been introduced to cats.  She is UTD on vaccinations and Rabies, Spayed, Current on HW Prevention, Microchipped and Kennel Trained.

name: Stella
description:
Amber and Stella were left chained and noosed to a fence bordering a vacant lot in Houston, Texas in the heat of the summer. Stella's ears had been butchered off with blood running down the sides of her head.

We raised enough money to get them into boarding, but are still struggling to pay the vet bill for spay procedures. 

Please consider visiting www.reunionrescue.com and donating via the Paypal button to help fix these girls so they can go to their forever homes.

Amber and Stella were let down by society, but they are wonderful girls. They are very social and friendly, but we're seeking homes without other female dogs. 

Contact us today to ask about our foster to adopt program, raw feeding and homeopathic treatment. Learn to feed your dog for 25 cents a day and never have to go to the vet.

description:

This little darling is bit barrel-chested and just a gorgeous shade of chocolate!  He loves to cuddle and exchange affections, preferably with women, as he is a true ladies man!

Frankie does well with other dogs as well as cats.  He loves his foster mom’s teenaged daughter and sleeps with her every night.  Frankie needs a loving forever home where he can cuddle and be loved on and feel like he's doing his job as a loverboy!  

Do you have room in your heart and your home for a chivalrous guy like Frankie? The blessing will be mutual indeed!

name: Fiona
description:
Hi! My name is Fiona and I am a redheaded brindle Staffordshire terrier. I am about 2 years old and weigh in at 50 pounds.

I was rescued from a hoarder who had me crated 24/7 with a dog that bullied me and stole my dignity and sense of security for over a year.

When I arrived at my foster’s home, I was in horrible condition and in desperate need of love and attention. My years of being bullied made me scared of dogs and humans, so naturally, I am slow to trust. But my three women fosters have worked very hard and gradually gained my trust. Even when I was afraid of my foster moms, I was never aggressive.

Now I even run and play in the yard with my foster brothers and sisters! Men still kinda intimidate me, but I am beginning to trust the human hand to be gentle and the voice to be tender.

I am looking for a forever home of my own that is willing to see past my shyness and see the true love and gentleness in my soul. Is your heart big enough to accommodate a special girl like me? 

I am spayed, up to date on all vaccines, microchipped and heartworm negative.

name: Oreo
description:
Meet Oreo! She is the sweetest lab/pitty mix you would ever want to know!
<p>
She is 7 years old and has been spayed, she lives inside and is house trained, extremely well-mannered, and as friendly and affectionate as the summer day is long!
<p>
Oreo is very good with kids and most other animals.  As you can see from the
pictures she loves to cuddle!  For her entire 7 year life she has lived with other dogs and cats.  
<p>
She will lay down, dance, shake hands and turn in circles for treats. She loves to play and have fun, she is in very good health. She is an incredible dog, and it is with a very heavy heart that we must give her away.  She is a beloved part of our family, but because of circumstances we must find a new home for her.
<p>
Won't you please give Oreo a chance to show you what a wonderful companion she can be!
<p>

name: Fay
description:
Hi, my name s Faith, and my mama calls me Fay! :)  I was found in
front of a school playing with some kids..  The officer that found me kept
looking for my puppies and no sign of them...  They took me to this awful
outside kennel that they call a pound..  I only had 3 days, but the lady
that saved me kept begging and begging for more time to find my owners..  No
luck, so I guess she thought I was sweet enough to take home with her..  and
she did!  I get along with all of the other 20+ dogs at our place, and I
adore their little girl Kayla, who is 3 1/2..  She likes to rub on my ears
and I LOVE that!
<p>
I have recently been spayed and am now UTD on all of my
shots.  I like to stay in my doghouse most of the time and lay around, I ma
a very mellow girl, my mom has to literally get the excitement going in her
voice before I get the hint that she wants to play with me :)  But, I am
fun, spunky, well mannered, and short she says :)  I am about 38 pounds and
approx 2-3 years old..  I am a pitbull terrier and I would love to meet you!
<p>

name: Cinnamon Girl
description:
Cinnamon Girl is a 10 year old female, spayed, house-trained pit bull--six ?generations gentle-bred--that needs a home. Cinnamon was raised with a? smaller rat terrier mix dog and socializes well with other dogs--she? actually lets smaller dogs boss her around.
<p>
Her owners cannot keep Cinnamon in their ?apartment, and they have not been able to find anyone who can take her in. She ?was staying with a friend of theirs in Fort Stockton, but she got out of his? yard a couple of times already, and he was warned that the next time they ?catch her, they are going to euthanize her.
<p>
She rode side by side with her ownder ?for 9 years in a truck--she is a big baby! She is a wonderful companion and we wish we could?keep her.?? Her owner is beside himself about what to do with her. He knows we can't keep? her now, but we are both trying to find a place for her--if you know of? anybody at all that can take her in and give her a good home, we will be? more than happy to feed her, pay for any vet bills, etc., if they can just? give her a good home.
<p>

name: Lilly Lou
description:
This is Lilly Lou aka Momma Dog. She was found at a gas station in Houston with her three pups. The vet says she is about 1-1/2 years old (06/2012). ??Very sweet and affectionate, she loves to get in your lap and has no idea how big she really is. She loves to play with little dogs and big dogs too, but she is also very content just sitting beside you or lying down in the kitchen if you are cooking. ??Lilly should go to a home with no cats, but loves kids and other dogs. She does like a dog bed, but loves to sleep in a people bed too. ?

name: Tito
description: <p>Tito is an exuberant, active, friendly young lab who has had a hard time catching a break in life.<br \/><br \/>This boy was brought to the shelter in July with a broken front leg, after a Good Samaritan found him. Tito was lucky enough to find a foster home so he could heal -- but came back to the shelter after eating some de-greaser. Lab pups in general need a lot of exercise and they need to be kept away from things they can damage when their person is gone, because they tend to get into things and chew. Tito did that.<br \/><br \/>He is also a smart boy who adores training -- he loves earning treats and toys. He likes puzzle toys, too. He is friendly and can be super-affectionate, but he also can be rambunctious and jump up on people, so he needs someone who is used to handling big dogs and can help this boy grow into the model canine citizen he was meant to be. <br \/><br \/>Tito needs a home that will give him the mental and physical activity and loving structure that he craves. To help with that, Tito's adopter will get a $250 voucher toward training to make sure he gets a good start in his new life. <br \/><br \/>His time is running out quickly to find a forever home. Please visit Tito at Austin Animal Center in East Austin on Levander Loop if you think you may have room in your home and heart for him. His animal ID # is 632753, and he is in Kennel 209. Feel free to email or to call volunteer Peggy with any questions, 512 496-7090.<br \/><br \/>Tito is a bit over a year old now, and he is neutered. <br \/><br \/>Information on this animal is posted as a courtesy. name: Miley
description: Hi, My name is Miley and I'm a very sweet girl. Believe it or not, I was born at the shelter. I was brought back because they forgot how much time a puppy requires. I need to find a family that really wants me for who I am. I get along well with other dogs, love playing in the baby pool in our play yard and even know how to jump hurdles and travel through an agility tunnel. I'm a great climber too and would love to take hikes in the Hill Country. I'm sure I would love taking trips down to the river and beach since I love water. As you can see, I have many talents! I'm pretty good on a leash and know Sit and Down. I promise to be a wonderful companion if you just give me a chance. I hope you'll come and meet me at the shelter. I need to be an inside dog so I can learn to be a part of the family.

description: <p>"Buster" is a Ridgeback\/mix, born in February 2010.\u00a0\u00a0 He was rescued from Houston animal control and is neutered, current on shots and micro-chipped.\u00a0\u00a0 Buster has a great temperament and is good with children and a variety of pets, but no cats please.<\/p>

name: Cupcake
description: Cupcake is one of our dogs that represents exactly what we do and why we do it. Cupcake was a breeding machine, and had a neglectful owner. She was pulled from living in a shed with her new born pups, half of them dead. There was a group of kids threatening to kill her and her pups so thats when we stepped in. She was so happy to see a kind face she ran right to the rescuer, she did not hesitate to jump in the car. The surviving pups were saved and Cupcake was very mothering. She is an awesome girl, gives great hugs and kisses and loves her toys. She is very smart, knows commands, walks great on a leash and listens well. Cupcake would be the perfect dog for the right person or family, she is very loyal; but does need an experienced handler. She has shown aggression to certain other dogs but seems ok with others, and certain men do put her off at first. Give a call if you would like more information.

name: Baron
description:
Est. DOB: 1/1/2005.  Baron is a great dog.  We actually witnessed his  "dumping."  I was so mad, I told my husband to follow Baron and the car who sped  away when he saw us coming.  They pulled in to a driveway and denied dumping the  dog, but Baron was sitting outside his door with his paw up looking right in the  window at this man!  They finally told us that Baron is a fence jumper and that  he is mean and aggressive and bites people so they no longer wanted him.   However, none of that is true!  The fence jumping might be true, we have no way  of knowing that because our kennels are all covered but Baron is not aggressive  at all and has never tried to bite any of us since he has been at our shelter.   He is very loving and gentle and likes to be right next to you

Baron has recently had surgery to remove 4 mass cell tumors.  Bless his heart, he is doing great!  He is such a happy dog and never knew he had cancer.  Fortunately, the pathology reports came back showing it is a low grade cancer!  We are so happy because the prognosis is much better than we thought!   

.  Click here to complete the adoption questionnaire (link at the top of the page) and email it to: kim@dogsrus.org
Visit our Website for more information about our shelter, adoption policies, and procedures.

description: Gracie makes us smile all the time. She is a super sweet, happy, loving girl and she is just beautiful to watch at play or curled up at rest. This sweet girl is just dying for affection and a family to love. Gracie loves giving kisses, playing chase with you and just knowing that you are there for her. Left behind when her beloved family moved away and could not to take her, Gracie hopes to find that true forever home this time. She is such a good girl, she is house trained, crate trained and would make a great addition to almost any home so call us today to meet her.

name: Prince Romeo
description: Just look at this face and tell me your heart doesn't melt-  Born at our shelter, with 9 siblings, Prince is just the sweetest boy. Prince was the little guy of the group so he quickly became the favorite of the shelter staff. He is very affectionate once he warms up to you and is very smart. Prince is a good boy who loves to play with other dogs and toys and likes water. His favorite thing to do is give you hugs and try to lay across your lap while gazing into your eyes. He is a big love bug that would like nothing better than to have someone he can trust and be his best friend. He is about 60 lbs, has long legs and a great smile. Come visit this sweet boy and you will melt. Was also call him our little Romeo.

description: <p>Today I am sending out a plea with the hope of finding a forever home for Maximus (aka Max), a very eligible, tall, dark and handsome young man in his early 20\u2019s (the vet who neutered, vaccinated and treated Max for heartworms a couple of months ago estimated that Max is about three years old).<br \/>\u00a0<br \/>Max was rescued by Col. Stan Horton (Retired USMC), animal lover and rescuer this past March in a not so nice neighborhood in the Alief area of Houston where Max had been dumped by his former owners.\u00a0 I am the one who took the pictures of Max and I\u00a0 think that he may be a Weimaraner\/Staffie mix who has a real zest for life and is full of energy. Max has a beautiful coat that has recovered nicely from the condition it was in when he was rescued by Col. Stan back in March.<br \/>\u00a0<br \/>Unfortunately, the wonderful couple who has been fostering Max since he was rescued will be moving soon, and must find homes for Max and others before moving. So Max needs to find another foster home (Col. Stan\u2019s wife has already told him not to even think about bringing another Dog home to foster) or even better a forever home where he will be an integral part of the family.<br \/>\u00a0<br \/>According to Col. Stan, Max loves people and gets along great with his two other foster dogs. Max may be a little shy at first with both dogs and people but then really opens up once he gets to know that person\/persons or dog\/dogs and loves to run and play.<br \/>Col. I enjoy rompin’ and stompin’ with my foster brothers and sisters in my foster mom’s huge backyard. One dog I particularly like is also for adoption on this website and his name is Red. I am spayed, up-to-date on all my vaccines, microchipped, house trained and crate-trained. What’s not to love? name: KYLE
description: **This dog is being fostered in North Houston.**\n\nMy rescue story begins with my trying to walk into a local grocery store.  I was just outside the door and trying to walk in after customers when two nice ladies stopped to check on me.  Since the \u201clost-dog\u201d signs they put up all around the area did not locate my owner, I am now looking for a loving forever home. I am playful and love other dogs.  I will run, run, and run and really enjoy their company. My weight is just under 50 pounds and my age is possibly three years.  Guesses have been made as to my primary breed, but I\u2019m possibly Border Collie mixed in with some Siberian Husky.  My fur is a beautiful, charcoal gray. I am fully vaccinated, neutered and microchipped. I am housetrained and crate trained. What more could you ask for? I am eager to please, easily trained and just an all around good boy. I am seeking a forever home to call my very own. Could that home be with you and your family? I promise to lavish you with my love and loyalty all the days of my life. If you would like to apply for me, please e-mail caninecompassion@yahoo.com for an application.

name: Charity
description:
Charity was rescued this past May from the streets in SE Houston-TX. She was roaming near a busy street and my friend was able to get her into her truck. She was not wearing any collar, nor microchipped, she had to be in boarding for almost 4 months at our vet so we could keep her safe. We're asking for a foster but we know they are hard to find. Charity is a very sweet dog, 3 years old, Mix breed, we guess maybe some kind White German shepherd with Bull terrier, she is white with some cute black spots in her ears, weighs 48 lbs, she is HW positive, but she got her treatment and is only waiting until next year when she can be tested again. Other wise she is a perfectly healthy, happy and friendly dog. She is fully vetted, spayed and now microchipped. She gets along with other dogs and also loves people and kids, but not cat friendly.
Charity is searching for a forever home after being rescued, now all she wants is be loved forever and be a loyal companion for any owner or family.
She is in Houston-TX.

name: Emmie
description:
Emmie is a petite, sassy, loving, professionally trained two-year-old red Staffordshire terrier who adores people of all ages and is a terrific companion, both on the go and on the couch.

She has been living and training since late last year with one of Austin's top dog trainers. Emmie is house-trained, crate-trained and knows 20 commands, including sit, down, look away, wait, drop it and even doggie pushups. She has her foundation training under her belt. 

Emmie goes on field trips every weeks. She enjoys downtown, Mueller Park and Lady Bird Lake trail. She loves the vibe of South Congress and gets excited when we drive up (her dearest wish is to be the shop dog for Hudson's smoked meats). She rides nicely in the car. 

Emmie was saved from the shelter minutes before she was due to be euthanized -- we couldn't stand the idea of this bright light not getting a chance to shine. 

She is an affectionate girl who pays close attention to her person. She loves petting and will sit close, leaning into you. She looks back over her shoulder at you on walks to be sure she's doing what you want her to do. 

She would be a perfect running or walking buddy. She has shown an interest in agility training -- a real self-starter, she started using the equipment at the shelter as soon as she saw it. The whole crew loves her at her trainer's place. 

She is still learning to be calm around other dogs so she's not recommended to go to a home with another dog at this point. And she wants to chase cats, so a cat-free household would be best for her. 

She is not reactive to all other dogs -- on the trail and at the farmers' market, she will walk calmly by some dogs but bark at others. We think she wants to play. But we are teaching her that she needs to be calm around other pets until it's playtime. 

Emmie has heartworms, but the treatment cost will be covered. She has already started on the medication that she must take before treatment. After treatment and a period of rest, she will be cured and healthy. 

Emmie could be the best gift you ever give yourself!  :-)

Both Cupid and Champ have been to obedience training.

name: India
description: India and her sister, Ireland, came into rescue together. While Ireland is very outgoing, India is a bit on the shy side and takes awhile to warm up. She is playful with other dogs and especially enjoys being with her sister.  Masticatory muscle myositis. Huh? That's what we said too! Our first indication that something was wrong with India was when her eye started to droop and the inner eyelid was protruding. We immediately thought she had been stung by something and rushed her to the vet. The diagnosis was much worse than an insect sting. Little issues she had been having over the past weeks began to make sense. She was refusing to eat her kibble and preferred softer food. We thought it might be a dental issue, but her teeth looked good.  We soon learned that one of the main symptoms of MMM is difficulty opening the jaw and chewing without pain. This is why she was having trouble eating. Further testing confirmed that India was indeed suffering from MMM, an auto immune disease, which usually affects larger breed dogs. The only treatment is long-term prednisone. She successfully came through the first flare up and began eating normally again. She's had a couple of subsequent flare ups since she was first diagnosed that seem to resolve with prednisone. During these flares she shows the classic concave skull associated with MMM, which is indicative of the masticatory muscles contracting. While India's condition does not seem to be life threatening, it is a known disorder that any adopters will have to watch for and make sure she receives prompt vet care whenever it presents itself. She's a little shy around people, but really loves playing with other dogs. \n\nIf you are interested in adopting India please visit our website at www.omcr.org and click on "How to Adopt" to download an application.

name: BLEU
description:
**This dog is being fostered in North Houston.**

Hi! My name is Bleu. I am a medium-energy, cute, adorable, cuddly, and very sweet runt of the litter with eyes that really sparkle and that is waiting feverishly for you!! I was born on November 12, 2013. My siblings have all been adopted and I am the lone ranger. But I am the cutest of them all, my foster mama says, and when I am excited, my whole body wiggles. I guess I get that from Mom who can also be seen and adopted right here! Her name is Bella and she is very smart and playful just like me!. Right now, I live at a foster home. It is nice and my foster mom is so cool. She is the nicest foster mom ever, and I will hate to say goodbye, but what my little heart longs for is to wake up one morning to find out that YOU’RE HERE!!!! You finally found me and you hug and cuddle me all the way to my very own home. Wow, my very own family who will love me forever and ever! Now, that is a doggy's hugest dream in the whole, wide world!! I know you will love and protect me just as I will love and protect you. I will be your bestest friend!! When you do arrive, you will find out that I love to play, jump and run, run, run around in a yard. I love lots of snuggles and hugs and I love to give kisses in return. If you have a little girl or boy that I could grow up with, we would be the best of pals and it would be so cool to have someone who would have as much energy as I do and would want to run and play with me. Maybe he/she could teach me some tricks (you know, I am at that perfect age for training). That would be so much fun!! If you have other pets, I am cool with that, too!  Another of my faves at my foster home is playing with my foster brothers and sisters. I sure will miss them. Well, I will go for now, but don’t take too long okay? It is really, really hard to wait for things. I am just so excited that I can hardly wait. My very own family! Love you soon! If you would like to apply for me, please e-mail debravan@yahoo.com for an application.

name: Zoey
description: Hi, my name is Zoey! I'm as cute as button and ready for a new home.  I love people, animals, and toys.  I am as sweet as they come, so don't miss out on getting to know me. I need a large area where I can play. Love people and kids. I am fixed and current on all shots and heart worm preventative.  Call 979-280-0505 and fill out my adoption papers and we are ready to go home!!
label: not-adopted

name: Elvis
description: ETOSHA WEBSITE HOME PAGE\nAdoption ApplicationThere are many ways you can help. Click HERE to find out how.\n"Elvis" is a Ridgeback\/Redbone cross, although it boggles the mind why such a mixture of breeds would have been done intentionally. (We know his origins because we also rescued his mother and three siblings.) He isn't camera shy, by the way, just unable to stand still for more than two minutes. Elvis was born in March of 2010 and is neutered, heartworm negative, up to date on shots, x-rayed clear of hip dysplasia and micro-chipped. He doesn't have a ridge and exhibits more Redbone characteristics than Ridgeback, including an intense love for water. Like the entertainer he was named for, Elvis is a born showman. His antics are legendary here at Etosha and make us laugh every day. He is great with dogs his own size but a little hard on the wee ones. Elvis is looking for a good home with plenty of room to run, an olympic-sized pool or lake within hiking distance, another dog to play with, sturdy children over eight and no furry critters (like cats) to contend with. He is crate trained and will snooze away most of a hot afternoon indoors -- OR clear all the kitchen counters if someone forgets and leaves him loose in the house (pesky Ridgeback influence there).
label: not-adopted

name: Repo
description: ETOSHA WEBSITE HOME PAGE\nAdoption ApplicationThere are many ways you can help. Click HERE to find out how.\n"Repo" is a purebred Walker Hound male, born in January of 2009. He is neutered, heartworm negative, micro-chipped and up to date on shots. This boy is a blast for anyone with a sense of humor. Repo thinks his food bowl is a hockey puck, and he treats it accordingly. He can amuse himself for hours, playing with his bowl, tossing it up in the air or scooting it along the ground. Repo would be happy as a little clam to be adopted by someone with a good arm and several Frisbees at his disposal. Repo came to us from San Antonio. Breeder unknown.
label: not-adopted

name: Victor
description: ETOSHA WEBSITE HOME PAGE\nAdoption ApplicationThere are many ways you can help. Click HERE to find out how.\n"Victor" is a purebred Walker hound. He was born in 2007 and rescued from an abusive situation in San Antonio, Tx. Victor is neutered, current on vaccinations, micro-chipped and crate trained. He's good with most other dogs, not cats, and great with children of all ages. Victor would like a home in the country where he can exercise his vocal cords and scare off predators that typically raid chicken coops during the night. He absolutely must have a fenced yard of his own, however, because he's a scent hound, born to track hot or cold and not stop until overcome by exhaustion. Victor's breeder is unknown.

name: Reno
description: ETOSHA WEBSITE HOME PAGE\nAdoption ApplicationThere are many ways you can help. Click HERE to find out how.\n"Reno" is from Louisiana, not Nevada, we're not sure what breed-or combination of breeds- he is, but it has been suggested by someone familiar with Azawakhs that he might be a mix of this ancient breed. He definitely has a personality unlike any dog we've ever rescued- reserved and quiet one minute, and bounding across the lawn and barking at the clouds overhead in the next. He doesn't bay, or howl, not even when he hears a siren or other hounds singing at the top of their lungs. Reno is fully vetted and looking for a home where he can get plenty of exercise. No cats or small children please.

name: John Watson
description:
Adoption Fee: $125
Adoption fee includes spay/neuter and rabies certificate, first vaccinations, deworming and a one year TBAR membership. 

John Watson has come a long way to be your best friend. Check out his before and after pictures to see how much he has improved at his current foster home. John Watson is friendly and loves to play. He gets along well with other animals and walks on a leash. He is crate trained and housebroken too. 

John Watson came to TBAR starving and needing lots of TLC. He has since put on plenty of weight and enjoys his foster home. But he would be so happy to finally have a family of his own that will love him every single day.

Please contact True Blue Animal Rescue at help@t-bar.org or (936)878-2349 if you are interested in meeting this sweet boy!

label: not-adopted

name: Miley
description:
Meet Miley! She is a one and a half year old American Bulldog mix, She is one of the sweetest most affectionate dogs we have ever known! She was brought in to the Midland Animal Shelter with a prolapsed uterus. We took her to Tall City Vet to get her all fixed up. After about two weeks at Tall City, they gave us the OK to pick her up!

Miley went to her foster home and that is where we discovered she needs to be an ONLY PET. Miley does not do well with any other animal and must go to a single pet household!

Miley is now currently being boarded at Tall City. This is not a life we want for her, to be kenneled 24 hours a day, 7 days a week. Miley needs to find her forever home where she can be the one and only as soon as possible. 

Won't you PLEASE give Miley the chance to show you what a wonderful companion she can be> YOU WON'T REGRET IT!!  :-)

name: Duke
description:
FOUND in Gleannloch Farms 2 months ago. Below is what his foster family has to say about Duke: 
Duke is a large mixed breed dog weighing about 65 pounds. No heartworm, fully vetted, loves kids/dogs. 
Duke is a sweetheart of a dog and has a calm submissive personality; and this makes him a delightful companion for a family of any age or size. While he enjoys walks and frisking in the yard, he is very polite indoors and is excellent company when I am working at home or watching tv. He settles down very quickly when guests arrive. He rarely barks. I do not think he will do well with a cat; he has treed our "visiting neighbor cats" several times. Duke sleeps well at night; not waking until I get up (which is NOT early). Duke is completely housetrained and does not beg for food or grab food that is on the counters. He does not get on the furniture or the beds. Duke allows me to clean his feet by rolling on his back as soon as I grab a towel. I find him to be very intelligent; learning quickly and responding well to correction and positive reinforcement. He does not have any food or bowl aggression issues. 
I have thoroughly enjoyed this dog and know that the right home is out there. He needs activity and a loving owner. 
He needs training in walking and staying in the crate when home alone. (He is an escape artist I have learned today - got out twice by squeezing through the top of the crate. On a personal note I have found him to be the best behaved new pet we have ever had. 

Here is a wonderful video of Duke in all his glory!  http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=l6Tbx_rpEZ4&fmt=37

name: Bleu
description:
Hi! My name is Bleu. I am a medium-energy, cute, adorable, cuddly, and very sweet runt of the litter with eyes that really sparkle and that is waiting feverishly for you!! I was born on November 12, 2013. My siblings have all been adopted and I am the lone ranger. But I am the cutest of them all, my foster mama says, and when I am excited, my whole body wiggles. I guess I get that from Mom who can also be seen and adopted right here! Her name is Bella and she is very smart and playful just like me!. Right now, I live at a foster home. It is nice and my foster mom is so cool. She is the nicest foster mom ever, and I will hate to say goodbye, but what my little heart longs for is to wake up one morning to find out that YOU’RE HERE!!!! You finally found me and you hug and cuddle me all the way to my very own home. Wow, my very own family who will love me forever and ever! Now, that is a puppy's hugest dream in the whole, wide world!! I know you will love and protect me just as I will love and protect you. I will be your bestest friend!! When you do arrive, you will find out that I love to play, jump and run, run, run around in a yard. I love lots of snuggles and hugs and I love to give doggie kisses in return. If you have a little girl or boy that I could grow up with, we would be the best of pals and it would be so cool to have someone who would have as much energy as I do and would want to run and play with me. Maybe he/she could teach me some tricks (you know, I am at that perfect age for training). That would be so much fun!! If you have other pets, I am cool with that, too!  Another of my faves at my foster home is playing with my foster brothers and sisters. I sure will miss them. Well, I will go for now, but don’t take too long okay? I am a young and it is really, really hard to wait for things. I am just so excited that I can hardly wait. My very own family! Love you soon!

name: Kevin Bacon
description:
MISSYS HAVEN CANINE Rescue, in San Antonio TX, does not have a shelter - ALL of our dogs are raised in foster homes in the San Antonio area. Each dog comes spayed or neutered, up-to-date on vaccinations that are appropriate for their age, microchipped, heartworm tested and on current on monthly flea/tick and heartworm preventative. 

ALL OF THIS IS INCLUDED IN THE ADOPTION FEE OF $200.00 FOR LOCAL DOGS AND $250.00 FOR PUPPIES. ( Local is in the state of Texas)! Medical records will come with each dog at the time of adoption.

IF THIS IS AN OUT OF STATE ADOPTION, TRANSPORT TO YOU is included in the adoption fee of $400.00 for adult dogs and $500.00 for puppies. We transport all over the country!!

All our dogs are socialized and we try to provide you a good understanding of the dog’s personality. Please visit our website for more information about what we do; http://www.missyshavencr.org. You will also find helpful our adoption application and pictures of our all our dogs/pups looking for homes!!

Don’t forget to like and share us at http://Facebook.com/missyshavencr

If you are interested in adopting, please fill out an application, once submitted we will contact you for a meeting. Also, we only adopt young puppies out of area once they reach 10 weeks old. OUT OF STATE ADOPTIONS: We do allow out-of-state adoptions for dogs, however, the adopter MUST pay for all transportation fees. NOTE: As we believe proper healthcare of one's pet is a requirement of good ownership, MHCR only adopts out dogs that have been fully vetted and altered. Thanks!

Please apply http://www.missyshavencr.org if you are interested in adopting from Missy’s Haven Canine Rescue. More information available by contacting info@missyshavencr.org

name: Angel
description:
Angel was found after being hit by a car. We were asked to rescue this poor girl and over time she has fully recovered from her injuries. She is coming along very nicely and bonding with her foster mom.  However, with anyone new, she still runs from them until she has time to get to know them. She gets very excited when she sees the volunteer who comes out weekly to walk the dogs and has warmed up to some volunteers after only two visits. That is a lot of progress for this sweet girl.

She loves to play with all the dogs and has a great little personality. She is sneaky at times and will wait by the other dog's crates and go in to steal their treats if she feels they don't eat them in time. She has never had a problem with any of the friendly dogs she meets. She is not pushy or hyper so she would make a great quiet house companion.

Name: Angel
Age: 1-2 yrs. old
Gender: Female
Mix/Purebred: Small shepherd mix
Weight: 40-50 lbs.
Housetrained: 99%
Crate trained: crate trained but enjoys being out and can be trusted
Heartworm Negative/Positive: Negative
Spayed/Neutered: Spayed
Micro chipped: Yes
Good with other dogs: Yes, playful
Good with cats: Doesn't seem to mind foster cat
Good with children: Timid with all people

We feel like she would be ideal for a small family or single person who works from home with whom she can bond with without having to share affection or worry about new people coming and going.  She needs a very calm home. She might even work best in an apartment setting where the home was not too big and she could be closer to her person without feeling overwhelmed by large spaces. She would enjoy having a furry friend who could show her what trust and relaxation looks like. She needs someone who can understand her limits and is extremely patient. They also need to understand that fearful dogs work on their timeline and not any one person's.  She is totally capable of bonding with a new owner ( like she has with her foster mom), taking walks together, and she enjoys being petted after she learns to trust you. She wants to be a lap dog but she doesn't realize how much she has grown. She is a medium size dog who weighs about 45-50 lbs.

Angel had a really rough start in life. She has not had any applications on her since she came to rescue so if you feel like you might be right for her needs please apply and come out and meet her.
come out and say HI!

name: Camry
description:
CAMRY & CAYENNE - Lab Mixes - Spayed

Birthday:  27 April 2010

Camry and Cayenne are just 2 of 18 dogs that we rescued from a field.  They are feral dogs and have never had any human contact until we came along.  We fed them for over a year and still couldn't gain their trust.  We had to enlist help in trapping them, one at a time.  The puppies were adopted out and most of the adults ended up with good neighbors who are taking care of them and giving them a good life even though they may never be able to touch them.  These two ended up here at Las Lomas.  They are still very shy and afraid of people but have never been aggressive.  It is so much fun to watch them play together and finally see their tails wagging!  They love to talk to us while we clean and feed and they seem very content.  We continue to work with them as best we can but they are going to need someone with experience in handling fearful dogs.

CAMRY & CAYENNE - Lab Mixes - Spayed

Birthday:  27 April 2010

Camry and Cayenne are just 2 of 18 dogs that we rescued from a field.  They are feral dogs and have never had any human contact until we came along.  We fed them for over a year and still couldn't gain their trust.  We had to enlist help in trapping them, one at a time.  The puppies were adopted out and most of the adults ended up with good neighbors who are taking care of them and giving them a good life even though they may never be able to touch them.  These two ended up here at Las Lomas.  They are still very shy and afraid of people but have never been aggressive.  It is so much fun to watch them play together and finally see their tails wagging!  They love to talk to us while we clean and feed and they seem very content.  We continue to work with them as best we can but they are going to need someone with experience in handling fearful dogs.

name: Mojo
description: Mojo is a 5 year old Boxer mix. He has the cutest pink nose and smile that we have ever seen. Mojo has been looking for his forever home for some time now so please share him. Mojo needs some training, but he's a very smart guy and learns quickly. He loves people of all sizes, but we think it's best that Mojo go to a home without any small children under 12 years old. He also gets along fine with other dogs in public, but doesn't usually accept them in his home, so we recommend he be your one and only. Mojo is crate trained, fully vetted, neutered and ready to go. He's been waiting so long for someone nice to come and take him home.
label: not-adopted

name: Copper
description:
We want to take a minute to shine the spotlight on one of our love muffins who has been with us for awhile, but has not given up hope.

This handsome gentleman was brought to CASI as a baby in 2012 with his 2 sisters, Penny and Coral. Him and Penny got adopted together, and later Coral found her home. A little while later in 2014, Copper and Penny, due to no fault of their own, found their way back to us. They both had Heartworm Disease- but thanks to your donations they were able to be treated. After treatment, sister Penny found a wonderful furever home. Copper thought he found a family, but chemistry is everything, and it just wasn't a fit. So here he is, still continuing to search for the one.

This guy needs adventures, someone to explore the unknown with and play countless hours of fetch. He's so sweet and fun! Spend a few minutes with him and you'll fall in love! He's a wise man who has been through some hard knocks in his short 5 1/2 years of life, but we know there is someone out there that is the perfect match for Copper! 

Please help us find this guy a home! We love all of our babies to pieces, and we enjoy nothing more than seeing them get homes of their own and being spoiled like they deserve! Copper deserves it!

#adopt #CASIpets #mynewbestfriend

name: Ari
description:
1,275. (as of February 14, 2018)

That is how many days Ari has been looking for a forever home. To be perfectly honest some of us at GAO had no idea what Ari's full story was. We learned a little bit more about her recently. 
Ari was adopted as a puppy around 8 weeks old. She was surrendered to Williamson County Regional Animal Shelter in August of 2014 when she was about a year and a half old because her people were moving. How sad for Ari to be left at a shelter as a one and a half year old dog who (at that point in time) had spent her entire life in their home? She was then pulled into rescue by GAO to find her forever home. 

Ari has touched the hearts of many people within the rescue community and, though GAO loves her dearly, we believe she deserves more than what she has currently. The owners and staff of Happy Trails Kennels are the most amazing and wonderful people who treat our dogs who reside there like royalty, but that is not a place for a dog to spend their entire life. Ari is deserving of a home, a family, and love. 
Ari is an amazing girl with tremendous potential, but she also lacks confidence with other dogs which makes her seem unfriendly during meet & greets. But with patience and the proper introduction, she quickly becomes curious and even submissive to more confident dogs. She lived with two other dogs in a previous foster home. Ari just needs time and patience to integrate her into a new home, but she'll definitely be worth it. There are several of us who know and love Ari as our own who would be more than happy to help make this transition easier if it meant she would officially be "HOME". 
Ari is one of the smartest dogs that has ever been in the care of our rescue and is highly treat motivated! Her previous fosters were AMAZING and taught her to have great manners! She knows a long list of commands like sit, stay, kennel up, settle, and more. She would make a wonderful running partner for anyone looking for a friend on the trails! She is house trained, kennel trained, up to date on vaccines, and spayed. She does very well with older children and loves all people she meets! She is big and strong and loves to play, so we would mainly recommend her for children over 12 yrs old. She can be energetic but also knows how to be a great big cuddle bug.

Please help us share this amazing girl and let’s help her find her forever home. If you're interested in her or have any additional questions, please feel free to shoot us a message! Otherwise, our adoption application can be found at www.georgetownanimaloutreach.org/adoption-application

name: Scarlet Rogue
description:
Scarlet Rogue absolutely loves her toys; balls, tugs, stuffed or squeaky and they are especially appealing when a human wants the toy too. This 6 year old lady loves to play with toys and people. Scarlet is blind, but she is otherwise healthy and heartworm negative. She is an energetic flashy fawn lady.

Scarlet Rogue is house, crate and leash trained; she needs access to a dog door and a handler that recognizes when her visual impairment makes her stop on a walk. Calm reassurance gets her started again. She has become friends with all 5 of her furry foster friends (except the Jack Russell doesn’t know it yet) and especially likes to play with the Schnauzer mix. She has not chased the cats she has met but that may be due to her sight issues. She has been good with children, but just as with our deaf dogs who can be unwittingly startled, she cannot be placed with children under 10.

This pretty, healthy, happy lady is all Boxer. Sure, she has a glitch, but that hasn’t stopped her from loving people and toys and dogs and being a terrific buddy. She’ll reward your patience with wiggles and snuggles and offer you her toy. Scarlet is a Permanent Foster with no adoption fee who will receive support similar to one of ABR’s Silverhearts.

Won't you give me a chance to be your friend?  I am a fun boy\n\nPotty\/crate training\/basic obedience and maybe a few tricks too!

name: Majestic
description:
My name is Majestic, and I need a home with lots of love, room to play and treats for my tummy.  I am a mix of pit bull and American bulldog which makes people afraid of me, but I am a loving puppy.  I was meant to be a breeding dog, but I was placed too young with an American bulldog who was 2 years older than me.  

He didn't like me very much, and now I'm afraid of dogs; but my foster mom is training me to become more used to them, and I am doing very well!  I also am learning to be well behaved, as my age is only 6 months.  I've also been spayed along with deworming, rabies, bordetella (which means I can be around other dogs, and not become sick), distemper and parvo, along with heart worm medicine.  I weigh 42 lbs, and am leash training plus, I know when to go outside.  

P.S. My mom has puppy food, and my toys if you adopt me.  

Thank you,

Majestic and my foster mom, Tessa

name: Nate
description:
Nate is an amazing dog and a kissaholic. . Nate gets very excited when you pick up his leash. He is so happy about food he dances when you are getting it ready. He loves to just lay his head in your lap. Nate has discovered toys and nylabones are his favorite. He is a protective dog and will keep you and your home safe.
A good Samaritan found Nate and Bastrop Animal Rescue arrived on the scene as soon as we heard about him. He was in terrible shape from head to toe. He was covered in puncture wounds, green goo was oozing from an infected ear and half the ear was missing, his eye was ulcerated, he was skeletal, had demodex mange, a broken infected toe and broken leg that was never set. He doesn't care about any of the pain and suffering from his past. Nate is a sweet, gentle and loving dog with people and dogs, though he hasn't met any cats. For Christmas, Nate wants a family of his very own. He does have a protective side.

Nate is fixed, microchipped and up to date on vaccinations. His adoption fee is $150.Interested in adopting a pet from Bastrop Animal Rescue? To start the adoption process, please go to www.BastropAnimalRescue.org/adopt to complete an adoption application. Thank you!

name: Scooter
description:
Please contact Jamesa (roxysrescue@yahoo.com), 713-882-2610 for more information about this pet.

Border Collie Male

SCOOTER

 This guy has my respect. I pulled him from a high kill shelter in San Antonio, Texas. He was very emaciated and had a rear leg with a bone sticking out and broken in several places. Someone had abused him. But Scooter was still happy and loved to be held and his spirits had not been broken. He has been a trooper from day one, never making a sound even though he was in a lot of pain.

 His leg was so bad; the vet considered amputation but decided to watch the bones heal. And heal they did until he grew. The bone in one leg doesn't bend but that doesn't stop Scooter he jumps on the deck, runs upstairs to his room, plays chase with this foster brothers & sisters and gets around normally just like the other dogs.

 His complete medical records and x-rays will come with him at the time of adoption.

 Someone else named him early on but his name Scooter so deserves, he is a SCOOTER. He only barks when he is talking to you. He bounces around still like a puppy and just a very happy guy. He gets along with everyone.

 He runs and plays with his foster brothers and sisters and he is just a sweet dog. Scooter is 1 1/2 years old now; I got him when he was 2 months old. He weighs 47 pounds and has reached his adult height & weight. 

 He has a beautiful black wavy coat and he does not shed. His best friend is Bradley, a bigger white border collie who only has 3 legs. Bradley was hit by a car but when he came to my house and Scooter was so small, Bradley treated Scooter as if he were his child. He cleaned him, cuddled with him and just watched over him like a mother would. It would be nice if they could go to a home together because Bradley is completely deaf and Scooter is his ears. Bradley is extremely friendly, loves to play, chases the ball and gets along with everyone. He loves his toys and belly rubs, Bradley is very gentle. 

 You can view his bio on the same site or our website www.roxysk9rescue.org

name: Logan
description:
Please contact Jamesa (roxysrescue@yahoo.com), 713-882-2610 for more information about this pet.

Calm Border Collie loves being a dog!

LOGAN

 This crazy little boy Logan is a special one for me. His mother belonged to a family who could no longer care for them so I fed them and took care of them but they stayed with the family. Then the family tired of them and didn't want them around anymore.

 I got his mother spayed, his sister spayed and adopted into a wonderful home. When we reached the clinic for his surgery Logan just lost it. He was so afraid; the clinic asks me to bring him back at a later time. Well that trip spooked Logan and he would not let me touch him ever again. He ran to me when I showed up to feed him, he knew the sound of my car and he knew his name.

 Since he was not neutered, he traveled the streets to get with any female in heat. I'm sure Logan has several kids out there :) One night Logan was experiencing some pleasure with one of his girlfriends (Ruby, also for adoption) when he was attacked by 2 vicious stray pit bulls who wanted Ruby for themselves.

 Logan had his testicles pulled right out by those pit bulls. So now Logan had no problem with me touching him and putting him in the car, he needed my help. His surgery went well, just a normal neutering as it turned out. He had some bite wounds on his legs but they healed well.

 Unfortunately Logan has heartworms and will need to have the 2 day treatment at the vet's office to get rid of them. After than Logan will be heartworm free and available for adoption.

 We are trying to raise funds for his surgery $400. Please consider donating towards his Heartworm treatment, no amount is too small we would very much appreciate it. You can donate on our website or directly to Callaghan Road Animal Hospital to Roxy's K-9 Rescue/Logan's Heartworm Treatment. (210) 647-1101

 And of course if you would like to adopt Logan once his treatment is complete, please email me. Logan would love to have a home of his own so he can be spoiled even more.

 Logan came into my home as if he had always lived here, he loves some love. He is quiet, plays very well with my personal dogs and he LOVES his bed. I just laugh at him and tell him, he could have been living inside the life of luxury 2 years ago if he hadn't decided against being fixed!!!!

 I loved his entire family from the time I met them. His mother was extremely sweet and calm and he is just like her.

  

 Please consider sharing Logan's story with your friends, family and co-workers on Facebook, Instrgram, Twitter or any social media. Thank you.

 gofund.me/9sgymshg

 You can view more pictures of Logan on our website under the TUFF TAILS button: www.roxysk9rescue.org

name: Hickory
description:
If ever there was a name with a perfect fit, it’s got to be Hickory. Ol’ Hickory… Just look at that face and you can see so many adventures and memories. Ol’ Hickory is around 6 or 7 years old; young enough to keep you company and old enough to stay by you. His beautiful fawn coat and just-beginning-to-gray muzzle are distinguished. He’s a healthy boy although he is heartworm positive. As always, ABR will work with his adoptive family for treatment.

Hickory’s best friend is Benny Pointer. The live in a house full of Boxers and get on well with all of them. Hickory is calmer than Beny and they usually takes naps together in an open kennel. He likes to run around the yard and play with the others and Benny. He is terrific with his crate; going in is a breeze and he’s so quiet you could forget him in there. He’s house trained and not destructive and not really interested in toys. He does fine with kids and would do well with a fur buddy.

This sweet, gentle soul would do fine in most families, and would do well in an apartment with someone who needs a walking companion. Maybe he can share some stories with you.

name: Houla
description:
Houla is our 3 year old mixed breed dog.  She has been spayed, microchipped, and is current on all vaccines.  She has been with our family for 2.5 years now and is fully house trained and crate trained. She is an inside and outdoor dog, since we have a dog door, and she sleeps inside. She is friendly and sweet. She interacts great with our 19 month old twins boys; licking their feet and letting them pet her. She's always gotten along well with other dogs, however recently our older dog has been aggressive towards her. There have been no signs of her instigating this behavior. We are truly saddened at the prospect of losing Houla, but because she is the younger dog and good with other pets and children, we feel that she would be the easier of the two dogs to rehome.  We did not come to this discussion lightly, and we have tried modifications in the home and continue to separate the two dogs.

description: This adorable little guy is a young Chihuahua mix who loves to cuddle and give kisses.   He is a little shy at first (but aren't most of us) but he does well with other small dogs.  A perfect companion for a person or another small dog.  His foster mom reports that he is crate trained and potty trained to puppy pads .   \nA SWEET BOY !
label: not-adopted

name: Oshie
description:
Oshie is a 2-3yr old American Staffordshire Terrier. He has a had a rough start to life and has spent almost 2yrs in the "shelter/rescue system". Oshie is a very focused, loyal, and loving boy. In the house Oshie likes to have a toy or bone that he can chew on while you watch TV. If he doesn't have something to chew on he will get into mischief and steal shoes or other items on the floor to tease you into a game of keep-away. Oshie loves to snuggle on the couch and has a big happy smile when he gets loved on. Oshie is house broken and crate trained and is quiet in his kennel when you are at work or out of the house.

Oshie has an obsession with balls and toys that would make him a great detection or sport candidate. Oshie has videos showing his ball/toy and hunt drive for any handlers or working homes that would like to adopt him. Oshie is not fazed by new places and has no concerns for loud noises like fireworks or thunder storms. Oshie will even dive into a pool for his toys and would likely make a fun dock diving partner. He is very intense with his toys and will snatch toys out of hands. He is still working on his out command and does not release toys easily. Oshie is working on obedience and agility skills in his foster home.

Oshie is dog selective and would do best as an only dog or in a home willing to rotate him with other dogs. He would do OK with another dog if the owner is local to San Antonio and willing to work with the MMK9 trainers to help him settle in. Oshie is also not recommended for homes with children under 13yrs because of his tendency to snatch anything that might be a toy out of peoples' hands.

description: Everyone loves Buddy when meeting this sweet fella!! He is very loyal, a gentle leash walker, and crate trained!\n\nThis boy is an inside doggy and sleeps on the couch every night although he would gladly sleep in bed if there was room for him.  When he gets excited, he hops around like a deer, especially when he knows his dinner is coming. He is excellent around children, cats, and other dogs - Buddy just loves everyone! *Buddy is a gold-medal high jumper; therefore, he will need a secure, fenced area if left unattended* This won't be a problem if Buddy is allowed to run, and boy can he run! Fully house-trained and ready to share his love and great personality with that special person!

She has the amazing ability to move even the biggest of objects when she gets excited, and her strong will can be a challenge at times, but Lisa is the sweetest most loyal girl who will love you forever. She will do excellent on fenced acreage where she will excel as an inside and outside family member. Lisa is a large, strong bundle of energy, just waiting for that right, forever home!

description: Penny is a loving girl, and she's the newest member here at Acres of Love Animal Rescue.  \n\nShe's learning to leash walk and picking up her skills fast.  She learns commands quickly - sit, shake, etc - and is very eager to please.  She keeps her kennel very clean and shows no signs of food aggression.  She not only loves her dog igloo to sleep in, but enjoys standing on top as well!
label: not-adopted

name: Bear
description:
Bear is an extremely independent guy; yet so dependent on his human for companionship.  He is so appreciative of just the littlest of things!  He gets excited over playing ball, or playing in his water trough, which he absolutely loves!  

Bear was found living on his own on a vacant lot where trash was being dumped.  He was emaciated and had no food or water.  For almost 6 wks, food and water was hauled to him twice daily until his trust was gained.  He made his freedom ride to Acres of Love Animal Rescue fairly well and now has his own yard, and even comes inside when weather conditions get extreme.  Bear is just the happiest boy I've ever seen with personality plus.  Loves to be groomed, bathed and smooched on!

**Bear MUST BE NEUTERED BEFORE ADOPTED**

He is HW positive and on a proven, slow kill treatment for heartworms. For more information on this happy guy, please call Carla at 979.877.8597. Joker's adoption fee is $75.00.

name: Nona
description: Nona has had quite the life. She ran free in a neighborhood on her own, had a litter of pups who were saved on New Years Day and a few months later she was finally caught and fixed and taken to a foster home. After a few days she escaped. A few days later she rethought her position in life and went back to the fosters front door and barked to go back inside. She's been there since. We figure after being back on the streets a few days she decided inside living with food, water and love was much better. Since, Nona has really adapted to the family living. She is house trained, loves to play with her toys and the other dogs, loves belly rubs and even nudges for attention. When going for walks, she stays with her foster siblings but she will not allow a leash to be put on - it simply scares her too much. So she will either need a lot of patience in training or she needs a secured home and back yard big enough to get some exercise. Nona deserves a chance to have a permanent home and a great life like all dogs do. Will it be with you?

label: not-adopted

name: Buddy PH
description:
My Foster Mom told me one day we were jumping in the car to go for a "snip snip", surely she meant haircut right, her friend even said "hair cut right? Giggle giggle".  But I'm no Poodle or Toto guy I'm smooth coat so why would I need a hair cut? Let me tell ya....snip snip meant losing my thingamagiggies, my man stuff, my you knows! It's actually a good deal though, because now I'm not a breeder machine anymore, now I'm a bed snuggling, kid licking, lady kissing BUDDY dog!

I am a Pit/Cuddle Bug mix muscley hunk at the ripe mid age of 6-7 years. The only thing bigger than my 85 pound bod is my HEART, I'm not even sure how it fits in my chest. I enjoy going on walks, but doing the cuddles with my foster people, that's my main hobby. My first 5/6 years were forgettable, it wasn't a waggy lifestyle, I was tied and crated 24/7 and my only free time was to breed. I never got the people cuddles that my heart yearned for.

I had mange, heartworms, and malnourishes, but now I'm on the medicine and almost completely better.  True to a dog's spirit, I hold zero grrrrudges and love dogs and humans. Sometimes small humans age 3 and 8 come over and they rub all over me, I love that, it's like where have you been my whole life??? I met a cat one time and had to get real close to sniff and figure out what it was, you see I'm partially blind so my sniffer is my best way to "see". My eyes have to be cleaned daily, but Foster Mom says I'm the good boy for my drops. I'm also potty trained and crate trained. Sometimes I eat my toys, so you'll need to get very strong toys that don't fit all the way in my mouth. I do have scars on my neck that are reminders of my sad times, but my spirit is fully intact (unlike my you know parts) and I want to share my loves and kisses with you. Adopt me!

special_needs_notes: Shiloh has a severe heart murmur and cannot be spayed or put under anesthesia because of it. She needs a long-term medical foster.

name: Carl Fredricksen
description:
Silverheart pair with Ellie Fredricksen

Carl and Ellie Fredrickson are an older couple looking for a retirement home. It can be a “55 and older” community with other more spry residents as they (Carl especially) don’t act their age. Carl is about 10 and Ellie’s about 13 and of course they are Silverhearts. Ellie doesn’t get out and dance as she once did, but she still gets around. She and Carl, their foster mom and grandma and all the other big and small dogs like to sit out back and enjoy the sunsets together.

They get along fine with big and small dogs and cats too. There aren’t any small kids in this menagerie so we’re not sure how they do with kids. Both of them have been dieting because foster mom said so, and they are feeling much better. Carl and Ellie are real sweethearts who would love to fill your home with warmth and laughter and smiles and a few sunsets while they can.

Am totally trained in obedience, potty and crate trained, and know. Few tricks.

Trained by the female inmates in the Paws in Prison Program.

www.pawsinprison.com for adoption guidelines and information

name: Ramps
description: from owner who surrendered him: Rampage we found while visiting my sister in San Antonio. We went to a San Antonio Rampage hockey game, and there he was, under our car at the SBC Center when we went to leave. We just had to take him home. He was very skinny and hungry and very scared. We brought him home October 26, 2013. He looks like a lab, but is not quite as big as most of the labs I have had. and his is brown with a white patch on his tummy. But my guess would be he has some lab in him. When we took him to the vet the following week, he estimated he was probably around 4 months old. So we approximate his birthday July-ish of 2013. Rampage still shows some signs of being abandoned or hurt by whomever left him in the SBC center parking lot. It took him a while to get used to people, and he scarfs down every drop of food when it hits the bowl. After being with us for almost 4 years, he has become very loving and comfortable. He is still scared of new people. He does not show aggression toward them at all, he just runs away and hides. However, he does show affection toward frequent visitors, such as our parents, siblings, and nieces & nephews. So we are confident he will become comfortable is his new home quickly. He does still eat all his food immediately, so we do not free feed him. He eats once a day and eats every drop immediately.  He is great with other dogs- submissive

name: Chin
description:
I am an American Bull dog.  My name is Chin.  I am neutered, almost 4 years old now.  I have a large personality with so much love to share. 
I look small in my pictures but I am a very large strong boy.  I do love to ride in the truck, and I get along with most other dogs…. I did get along with dogs I met at the vets but I come from a home I was an only dog. 

My rescue person had me neutered, and I am heart worm positive but I am started on slow kill and I look forward to having a new happy home of my own.  

My rescue person says I am a bit to large to go into a home without small kids because of my size. So if you have little ones I am not the dog for you.  For you as well as for me.

I have a heart on my side, and I am hoping someone will fall in love with my handsomeness and adopt me.
Adoption fee is $250 and I come with a year of meds for my heart worms.    

Oh I do not like cats.  Just saying so you know I need a home without cats.

I really am a love and want a special loving home to live out my years.  It is tough losing your home and I do not want to ever go through this again as I am a Good Boy.

Please fill out an application if you would like to meet me and or talk to my rescue person.  

Information on this animal is posted as a courtesy. This animal is NOT part of the
Vision Hills rescue animal population, and is not a Vision Hills foster animal. 
Vision Hills makes NO guarantees, and is not responsible for the health and 
temperament screening of this animal. If you adopt this animal the contract will 
be between you and the person who has the animal, not between you and Vision

health status and behavioral tendencies. Ask for verification of vaccination and

problems, be an informed adopter and ask your vet about important health and
temperament issues before adopting an animal.

name: Nilla
description: This is Nilla, yes like the cookie. She is a very sweet girl who had a rocky start to life. Pulled from her Mom way too early this sweet girl was lucky the person who had her did not keep her. Nilla could barely eat on her own, was full of intestinal worms and covered in fleas when she arrived. She was placed into a foster home to receive the care she needed to get her ready for the world. Nilla is very smart, very much on the skittish side with people and new things, loves other dogs but will test them, she loves toys, and does have a bit of separation anxiety. She doesn't really like walking on a leash so will need some work, she does not like water. She probably would do best in a home without children or alot of action, and with someone willing to work with her fears and shyness. name: Grant
description: Rescued from a rural animal control shelter, Grant is now almost 4 years old as of April 2019. Grant is a mix breed dog that includes almost equal portions of  American Staffordshire Terrier, Chow Chow and companion breed dogs--this is NOT a guess! Grant was DNA tested. This awesome and obedient dog is house trained, crate trained, walks well on a leash and is a wonderful companion to children, other dogs and cats. Grant has been in a foster home for approximately one year while he underwent "soft" heartworm treatment. He is now negative for heartworms and never wants to go through this again. Grant's new owner must be committed to making sure Grant receives a heartworm preventative each month for the rest of his life. Grant is neutered, microchipped, up to date on vaccinations and ready for a permanent home. He currently lives with 2 dogs and 3 cats and has been a great companion and playmate to numerous other foster dogs that have come and gone in this foster home. Serious adopters can call Dianna at 281.797.4681 or email katyrescue@ymail.com for more information. Grant's adoption fee is $75.00.\n\n

name: Turbo- San Antonio area
description: Viva Fiesta!!!!  Hi my name is Turbo and I live in San Antonio.  Would you believe that I am 11 years old and this is the first time I\u2019ve been to Fiesta?  Well I love it and I\u2019ve sent pictures to all my friends and family.  I\u2019m a compact little guy about 10 lbs. I only have 3 teeth left but it doesn\u2019t slow down my eating at all.   My family and I lived outside for quite a while, but all that changed since New Years Day.  We have nice warm beds and blankets and good food now.  I love food!  I can be very determined when food is around.  I have improved tremendously in my housebreaking skills and my pet sitter says I have done really well with no accidents the last time I stayed at her house.  I do wear a belly band but am slowly learning not to mark.  She didn\u2019t have to change it all day because I didn\u2019t have any accidents.  I love to play and run around the house like a 4 year old.  I love to snuggle and sit on laps.  If my forever home would like to take me out and about I would really like that.  I\u2019m a really friendly guy and like having tons of friends.

name: Maxwell
description: Hi guys! My name is Maxwell.  My brother Cody and I had a good life in north Texas, but then our mom got sick and passed away. We are pretty broken up about it. Her amazing daughter came and got us, though, and brought us home with her. She was really worried we would end up in a bad, scary shelter! We are so grateful to her for that. We are easy going, loveable, fluffy guys who are looking for a home where we can lay around, maybe play a little, and go for walks. As you can tell, we didn't miss any meals, and need a bit of a diet. Our doctor doesn't think it's "thyroid", whatever that means. I think that's a good thing?  Anyway, if you are looking for a laid back companion (or two?), all you need to do is fill out the application and someone will be in touch!  P.S.  My adoption fee is only $250!\n\nTexas Great Pyrenees Rescue, Inc. is a 501(c)(3) organization dedicated to Great Pyrs.  We have the best selection of pyrs in Texas and we do home checks and vet checks before placement.  We start with adoption applications (no cost\/obligation) and we make placements on a first submitted-first approved basis.  If you are interested in giving this dog a new home, please complete an adoption form found at http:\/\/www.txpyrs.org

name: Hope
description: Hope is another CASI pup that your donations help support. This festive gal was brought to us last spring. Hope loved to play with her doggie friends, but we soon realized that she would always get cut up and her skin seemed stretchier than it should be. We took her to the doggie doctor and was told Ehlers-Danlos Syndrome. This basically means Hope has an abnormal production or breakdown of collagen and, as a result, the skin is weaker and may tear easily. The mildest amount of trauma may cause a large wound. Hope isn't on any long-term medications, and otherwise she is your normal great girl, but because of this she seems to get overlooked in the kennels. Hope doesn't have to live in a bubble, just a home where she can be allowed to be herself with a family that understands a small scratch for some can be a bigger issue for Hope.

name: Cooper
description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Cooper doesn't look it, but he is 12 years old. He came to us when he was 10 years old. I felt sorry for him and his owner. The guy that owned him had him since he was a puppy. He had recently gotten married and Cooper was unable to transition into a family with two small children. He was totally stressed out and snapping. Now I know what my answer would have been, but the guy was committed to making his marriage work, so Cooper had to go.

He had a real rough transition at first. He hated being at the facility. I took him my house, and he still wasn't happy. For the first six months he barked constantly. One day he followed me to the kennel and met the puppies. From then on he found his place in the world. He rules the quarantine room. He set up shop in a bottom kennel and he supervises al the workers and volunteers. He is happy as a lark. He loves the new puppies. He wants to babysit. When I was taking pictures, he kept getting on the table to make sure the babies were ok.

I'm not sure that Cooper would be a good candidate at this point for a new home, unless the person had a lot of patience and love to give him. He would really appreciate people sponsoring him. He still gets all the special treatment our adoptable dogs get. Every month he gets heartworm preventative, he gets a Bravecto pill every 90 days and he gets treats and toys. We are committed to letting him have a happy life, but as he ages his care will be more costly.

Hi! I am Dexter! Sometimes I am called Dex, sometimes I only answer to Mr. Handsome. I am a cuddly, fun guy who has recovered from paralysis. I had a back injury, likely due to genetics, and I had the surgery to fix it. After I rehabbed, I can walk again. I love to rip apart my stuffed toys, run around with the other foster dogs and sit on my foster parent's laps. As if my good looks weren't enough, I am pretty well housetrained. I am quiet and easy going. My favorite place to hang out is in the kitchen because that is where the snacks live. Meeting new people is no problem for me because I am friendly and charming. Having someone home with me all the time would be a dream come true, but I can certainly nap while you go to work if that means more snacks and toys, but I will need attention and love when you come home. I enjoy the company of other dogs and pretty much ignore the cat.

Love dachshunds and not ready to adopt or circumstances won't permit having a dog? How about being a sponsor or making a donation. Every one of our dachshunds receives excellent medical care along with day to day food, love and housing. Being non-profit, we rely on generous individuals like yourselves to help save these fur babies. You can do this specifically for one dog with the sponsor button on their webpage or a general donation on our “How To Help” page. Easy and quick through Pay Pal or your debit/credit card. You generosity is sincerely appreciated by all and is tax deductable. Need other ideas? You'll find tons of them on the How to Help tab. All contributions are tax deductable.

Diamond Dachshund Rescue of Texas is a non-profit 501(c)(3) volunteer organization with focus on rescue and adoption of pure breed Dachshunds. Hello! I'm Romeo. I came to DDRT in 2017 when my parent got sick and couldn't take care of me any longer. My current foster family has taken great care of me but I am looking for my forever home.

Most of my day is keeping company with the humans in the house. I like to sit in laps while they read or watch TV. I will "talk" to them and let them know if I need to go out, or when I'm ready to come back in, if my water bowl is empty, or if I want to play. I'd rather be the only dog in the house and keep the humans all to myself, but if I do have to share the home with another dog, they need to be little like me.

See, there are things in my life that scare me just a little - like big dogs, certain noises, and laminate or hardwood floors. The noise and texture on my feet doesn't feel so good. I prefer the carpet and tile. I know that sounds kinda silly, but at my age, a guy knows what he wants!

I would love to spend my days on the couch snoozing and taking naps, watching TV with you, and getting belly rubs! If you are older, like me, at home most of the time, or like watching TV too - you could be my forever home!

If you would like to meet this handsome, snuggly, lap guy, please fill out an application for Romeo Too today!
