name: Tyson
description:
Please contact Jamesa (roxysrescue@yahoo.com), 713-882-2610 for more information about this pet.Gorgeous guy blended Beagle, American Stafforshire, Bassett Hound & LabTYSON
Low Rider was his birth name because of his appearance, short legs with body very low to the ground and he is a mixture of a few different things. And boy does he have a story behind him. Tyson and his 9 siblings were born in my home after I rescued his very pregnant mother, her very pregnant daughter and another daughter just 6 months old. They had been dumped in a local park here in San Antonio, Texas. It was freezing cold and raining outside.
His mother gave birth about 3 days after I got her and her daughter gave birth the very next week. A different rescue took in the pregnant daughter and the 6 month old daughter.
All of the puppies came out very different but healthy and happy. You know a female dog can become impregnated by up to 7 different males and surely this is what happened to Tyson's mother Paris. Miss Paris really had a diverse group of babies!!!!
Tyson was adopted out by a family with kids and even though he was raised inside my home, they kept him outside. He escaped his fence and got hit by a car. Sadly the car that hit him left him there until Animal Control Services (ACS) our city shelter picked him up very injured. He lay all evening and night in a bed of ants that bite him all over. That car really hit him hard.
Thank goodness for microchips, ACS notified me that they had one of my dogs. When I went to pick up Tyson, I was shocked at his injuries. I immediately took him to my vet and he spent a week there before coming home to heal even more.
Tyson endured several surgeries and he is back to being a normal dog. He is happy, friendly and loving, also very obedient. Tyson was not returned to his adoptive family because they were not able to pay the enormous vet fees for his surgeries and care. So I am trying to find the right forever home for Tyson.
Tyson does run and jump, plays chase, wrestles and has no limitations. His back leg is does not bend completely because he had a steel rod in place for longer than normal to help the bones heal to prevent amputation.
This is a dog with a very playful and sweet personality; he loves everyone and gets along with other dogs very well.
I have attached pictures of his injuries, his mother & litter mates and current pictures of Tyson. I plan on posting a video of him soon so you can see him in action and know he has no limitations. Most of all Tyson loves kids and some human attention.
He loves the camera; he weighs 37 pounds and a mixture of basset hound, beagle and who knows what else.
You can view more pictures on our website: www.roxysk9rescue.org

name: Prince Charming
description:
LOVEABLE, Big-headed, sweetest boy EVER!!!!!Prince came to us to stay temporarily until he could be transferred to a rescue. WELLLLL, we just fell absolutely in love with him and committed to keep him with us, until he finds his forever home.
This is one special guy. He's soooooo unbelievably loving and affectionate!!! He's also super quiet & well-behaved. We envy the family who ends up with this love muffin! ♥
Mr Charming is around 6-8 years old. The perfect age to share love and couch potato time and lots of walks. He also LOVES to jog. He's a lovely, graceful runner and soooo fun to be around!!!
He LOVES walks and is perfect on a leash. He's super with other dogs and all people. He rests his great big head on your lap and you feel his beautiful, loving, gratitude!!! 4/12/19 4:14 PM
organization: I Once Was Lost Animal Advocacy
label: not-adopted

name: Charlie
description:
3 year old cutie in need of a special homeCharlie was living with a family for the first 3 years of his life. He was in a great deal of pain yet put in prozac, instead of getting the care for his back he needed. After he started acting out, due to pain, his 'family' got rid of him. How very sad for this little boy.

UPDATE from Charlie's foster Mama 2.28.2017 "
Charlie is still looking for his forever home. He needs a very special, patient, super duper doggie knowledgeable human. He gets along great with other dogs and doesn't mind cats. Because Charlie's medical condition went neglected for so long, he has conditioned himself to act out a little. He wants love and cuddles on his terms. Please share this boy, or make a donation to

#

IOnceWasLostAnimalAdvocacy

because they've taken on Charlie full time. I can only foster him every once in a while. If we could send him to more heat therapy sessions that would help him. He also needs supplements for his skin allergies. Poor little pumpkin, he really is a good boy. He minds so well.
"

We are happy we have him because it turns out he has bone spurs in his back so he was in a bunch of pain. He is regularly seeing a chiropractor and is making good progress.

Because of this pain, Charlie can sometimes be a little naughty toward strangers or towards commotion. If his needs are understood, Charlie will be a fantastic little buddy.

Charlie needs a home that will be devoted to his special needs and will understand who he is. If this is all in place, Charlie is a little sweet cutie pie who is a pleasure to be around.

Charlie LOVES other doggies and really really LOVES car rides!!!!

Charlie's trainer says he's "very smart" Charlie's foster mom says Charlie says "

I LOVE car rides they bring me such joy. I want the whole world to see. I am learning that this world has so much love to offer and that I don't have to be so unsure about everyone." & "I'm learning so much thanks to all my angels for making sure I am given another chance."

If you might be the special home Charlie needs, please message us to schedule a time to meet this little boy. ♥♥

Additional Information:

Charlie seriously needs a home that can respect and understand his back issues. He has bone spurs that cause him pain.

For the most part he's adorable, not to mention the cutest thing ever :o), but he will bite if his space isn't respected. He truly needs a home that will give him space and only pet him when he requests it.

In other words, he isn't a snuggly little thing. He simply needs a home that will give him kindness, love, healthy food, gentle care and understanding. Also, no kiddos.

He LOVES other dogs and would also be good with cats. The best home for him would have another dog, who the humans can snuggle with and pet, along with Charlie, who would be in a home where he feels safe but can kind of be on the outskirts of the family unit.

We would be ecstatic to find a home for him. It just needs to be the right home.

We do have other small adoptables, who Charlie regularly hangs out with. Adopting him along with one of his friends would be a win-win. The new family would have a doggie they could snuggle with, Charlie would have his buddy AND he would have a safe, loving home to call his.

label: not-adopted

name: Major JuM
description:
YOU SHALL NOT PASS! My colon was acting just like Gandalf from Lord of the Rings and not letting my uh……..waste product go through due to a colon stricture. Stricture, fancy Dogtor word for a narrowing of part of the colon. So even though my entire family, even my fur Mama was rescued and adopted out early last year, I have been hanging around God’s Dogs Rescue home base getting my colon fixed. That’s right Major had a MAJOR medical issue and now I am fixed after weekly dilations for about 7 months. 

It’s about time! Now I am completely healed and ready to pawty at a new house. I am a MALE about 1.5 yrs old and fully grown at mid-sized 45 pounds.  My litter was a Brittany Spaniel/Pittie mix.  My spaniel genes gifted me the stunning white coat contrasted perfectly with my liver colored spots.  Liver! What a gross, yet delicious way to describe my patch color, but not as gross as colon strictures, that’s for sure. 

I have fun around other dogs and my temperament is SWEET mixed with LOVING. I can be a bit shy at first, since I have been sick and not allowed to go out and about the town for months, but I warm up like butter on the pan. You will be enchanted by the way my light hazel eyes jump out from my handsomely gorgeous red liver mask. I am a smart, playful and happy guy just so excited to finally be better and I can’t wait to meet my new family, is it you?

GOD'S DOGS Rescue, in San Antonio TX, does not have a shelter - ALL of our dogs are raised in foster homes in the San Antonio area. Each dog comes spayed or neutered, up-to-date on vaccinations that are appropriate for their age, microchipped, heartworm tested and on current on monthly flea/tick and heartworm preventative. 

 ALL OF THIS IS INCLUDED IN THE ADOPTION FEE OF $200.00 FOR LOCAL DOGS AND $250.00 FOR PUPPIES.   ( Local is in the state of Texas)! Medical records will come with each dog at the time of adoption.

IF THIS IS AN OUT OF STATE ADOPTION, TRANSPORT TO YOU is included in the adoption fee of $400.00 for adult dogs and $500.00 for puppies. We transport all over the country!!

All our dogs are socialized and we try to provide you a good understanding of the dog’s personality. Please visit our website for more information about what we do; http://www.yourtxrescueconnection.org/. You will also find helpful information about transport, our adoption application and pictures of our all our dogs/pups looking for homes!!

 Please contact us at adoptions@godsdogsrescue.org for more information about adopting one of our dogs and puppies or fill out an adoption application at http://www.godsdogsrescue.org/adopt/adoption-application/

Thank you for wanting to adopt a rescued dog, their LIVES depend on it!
label: not-adopted

name: TIMMY
description:
My name is Timmy and believe it or not, my foster mom says I am a Chippet. She thinks I am a Chippet because she says I have a lean body, long legs and the personality of a Whippet but my face looks like a Chihuahua. I think I am more like a short Whippet because I am quiet and docile and I am quite content to curl up on the couch all day. But when I get out in the yard, I come alive and have lots of energy and I can run really fast. I am a little shy and it takes me some time to familiarize with a stranger but, once acquainted, I will be my usual friendly and social self. I have a very sensitive nature so I would be unhappy in a large family with lots of children as chaos makes me anxious. My foster mom says I would be a perfect dog for a single person or empty nesters because I am not rowdy and rambunctious like some other dogs. Because I have a very thin coat and not much body fat, I like to find a warm spot in the house and will settle in as long as it is close enough to you. I don’t mind being out in the cold as long as I am moving or running, but it would certainly be cruel to leave me outside for extended periods of time in cold weather.

Timmy is available for adoption with Saving Grace Dog Rescue of San Antonio. The adoption fee is $150.00. An adoption application, home visit and adoption contract are all required. All dogs are spayed/neutered, up to date on vaccinations appropriate for their age, microchipped, and wormed for internal and external parasites. If you would like more information or an adoption application, please email us at sgdrsa@outlook.com.

Please note that visual breed identification in rescue dogs is unreliable so for most of our dogs we are only GUESSING at predominant breed or breed mix. We get to know each dog as an individual and will do our best to describe each of our dogs based on personality, not by breed label.

name: Sparky
description: Short, stocky and totally adorable, Sparky is a loyal and affectionate friend who would love to be the next resident of your household. He's currently living in a foster home and they can attest that he'll make a lucky family very happy when he moves in! Sparky's foster mom says he's one of the most cuddly dogs she's ever known and has the perfect activity level. He enjoys long walks or short jogs, but he doesn't need to be constantly burning off extra energy. He can also entertain himself and he loves to toss his toys in the air and then go track them down. He also enjoys a round of tug of war and kind of playing fetch - Sparky will bring you a toy, you throw it, he will go sit with it for a while, then bring you a different toy, or just throw the toy to himself because why not? Feel free to try to teach him the rest of the rules of the game! Sparky also has excellent manners in the home. He's house and crate-trained but does great left alone outside of one and hasn't show any destructive tendencies. But he really prefers having his favorite people around, even if he's just chilling nearby while they work. Sparky takes some time to warm up to new people, but once he trusts you, he's as loyal and kind as can be. He's very affectionate and loves to curl up with his favorite humans and definitely thinks he's a lap dog. He loves to lay his head in his person's lap while they stroke his head or just snuggle on the bed or couch. If there's only a tiny little space there for him, Sparky says he can make it work! He also walks well on leash and knows 'sit' and 'come'. Sparky will make a fantastic companion to the right family. Come meet him and see if this big cuddlebug is right for yours! 4\/23\/19 4:41 AM
label: not-adopted

name: Rio
description: This handsome tall drink of water is Rio! His interests include fetch, swimming, fetch, treats, fetch, and gently leaning into your leg for pets. We should also mention that he loves playing fetch and will regularly do leaps and flips in the air trying to catch the ball. And he's really great at bringing the ball back to you and dropping it. If he thinks you don't see the ball on the ground, he'll politely pick it up and set it in your lap. Rio manages to keep the game going with even the laziest of tennis ball throwers! True to his name, Rio also really LOVES being in the water! Whether you're hosing him off or taking him for a dip in a pool or creek, he'll take all the water time he can get. And while he is incredibly energetic when playing with a ball or in the water, when he's all tuckered out, he's happy to hang out with his person and snuggling. Rio can be aloof with people he doesn't know, but he warms up quickly and before long he's asking for belly rubs and cuddles. Rio's a big guy, but he is very easy to walk on leash and enjoys going a nice quiet walk around the neighborhood, taking in all the sights and smells while staying by your side at a nice pace. He's also a smart pup who sits politely for treats and recently became TOP Dog Ready, which means he has already learned all the skills in his training plan in APA!'s Total Obedience Program. The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Rio has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! Dogs in the program learn skills including sitting calmly when approached by strangers, calmly walking past another dog, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' and coming when called. In addition, Rio has also learned 'Place'. Rio has worked hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with Rio after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 Rio's an easy friend who's easy to please and he's more than ready to move on to his forever home. Come meet this handsome guy today!

name: Josephine
description:
Josie is a volunteer favorite who is very photogenic and appreciates nature.

She is a sweetheart who doesn't need a protector, she can take care of herself. What she needs is a soft place to land, someone who will treat her kindly and give her all the love she could ever want. She prefers people who are soft and gentle souls, who can appreciate a dose or 10 of nature therapy.

She knows all of her basic commands, is an active playful dog who loves water, diving for leaves and long walks in nature.

Josie does not do well around children and small animals. She is selective with dogs but has successfully played with other dogs. A meet and greet with your dog is recommended on shelter property. But she may be better as an only pet.

name: Socks
description:
Leggy, affectionate trail dog looking for just the right soulhuman!Hello friends! My name is Socks and I am a leggy, loving, adorable boy who loves to hit the trail and snuggle with my humans. I was found abandoned at only 5 months old and have lived at a rescue kennel ever since.

I'll tell you a secret. When my trainer lady sat down to make this post, she was a little inspired by a hilarious and heartwarming page called The Least Adoptable Dog in the World. You see, I'm a bit of a handful.

BUT, I'm also a total catch in a lot of ways. In fact, she's known much more difficult dogs than me and they're all happy and thriving in h
omes now. I just need the right human who sees the exceptional boy I am and realizes I'm their souldog. We both feel very confident that I am absolutely someone's souldog.

<3

So to start, here are some AWESOME things about me:

*Rockstar trail dog & running buddy. For real, I'm an active Austinite's dream boy!

*No reactivity issues to people, dogs, cats, small mammals - I wanna be social!

*Super affectionate and loving, affection calms me down when I have my moments.

<3

*I love toys. I love fetch. I love gnawables. I'm learning puzzle toys. I love you.

*I ride nicely in the car.

*I'm working on being an adventure boy and think water is pretty sweet.

*I come with training support.

Now why do I need a special home?

*I am genuinely high energy. Couple that with the fact that I'm a young adult male and have lived in a kennel environment for way too long and I'm now also a guy with some arousal issues and stress related acting out.

*I can be mouthy. I have gotten SO much better with this but see above, overarousal, be it stress or excitement or anxiousness, brings it out. Usually it's no biggie to redirect now, I often even redirect myself, but the stickier the situation, the more mouthiness you might see and moving to a new home is pretty sticky!

*I'm not exactly a pro at indoor life but I am coachable. During my life indoors practice, I've responded super well to potty training and hey, paws don't go on the counter type stuff. I also overcame something really scary called stairs. But I definitely need more practice and may still do stuff like steal a hat off the shelf bc it looks like a toy.

*I've lived my young life out in the country so sometimes new experiences and city life make me nervous. I'm resilient though and I look to my human for cues so I know this won't be a biggie. I'm already going to more adventurous places and doing great!

My trainer lady with
Dog Possible
is helping find my human so you can email her at amy@dogpossibleaustin.com and she will hook us up!

You can also visit my very own Facebook page, A Special Home for a Dog Named Socks and click on my photo story to learn more about me: https://www.facebook.com/SocksMcGruff/

I hope I steal your heart!

name: Whiskey
description: Like a fine spirit, Whiskey just keeps getting better with age! Whiskey is full of boundless love, loyalty, and affection. He is constantly rolling on the ground for belly rubs, especially if he can you think he's been a good boy about something - he rolls right over to get his reward. And you'd be doing that a lot because he IS a good boy. Whiskey is really smart and has a lot of skills under his belt - sit, down, place, come - he knows them all! Whiskey is also house-trained and does well in his crate. When out of the crate, he knows what toys he can play with and what things are off limits. Though he loves a good romp or a game of fetch, he is equally fond of naps and lounging on the couch. Really, just being with his people is his favorite thing. He's just the most affectionate little love muffin you'll ever meet. Need a partner for outdoor adventures? Whiskey is ready to explore the hidden gems of Austin for hiking and swimming. He really likes to get away from the excitement of Lady Bird Lake to see what else is out there. He's also game for a good game of fetch as long as every adventure ends with a nice long nap on the couch, snuggled next to his number one buddy. With his smoky brown eyes, he looks up to you for guidance in every situation. With a subtle cue from you, he'll show you all his skills. This sweet boy will keep you balanced - lots of one-on-one time snuggling on the couch and a fond farewell when you go out to visit with friends. He will always be waiting for you when you come back - holding down the home front while you're away. Whether you leave him in his crate or asleep on the couch, he knows what's his and what's yours. Whiskey is also in the Total Obedience Program. The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Whiskey has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! Whiskey is now TOP Dog Ready, which means he has already learned all the skills in his training plan, including walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers, calmly walking past another dog, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'Place', which means Whiskey will go to a special place in your home on command. Whiskey has worked hard to become a wonderful pet and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with Whiskey after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 Whiskey's the type of dog who totally knows when you had a bad day, and will up his snuggle game accordingly. He is for someone who is looking for a soulmate. If you think you're in the market, you should come meet him!

Please note that visual breed identification in rescue dogs is unreliable so for most of our dogs we are only GUESSING at predominant breed or breed mix. We get to know each dog as an individual and will do our best to describe each of our dogs based on personality, not by breed label.\n

name: Oscar
description:
Meet Oscar!  He is a sponge for love, attention, and socialization, and he's ready for a forever home and family!

He is affectionate (but not needy) and loves walks and pats. 

Being eleven years young and experienced canine, he takes a relaxed approach to life, spending his days lounging and sleeping. 

Friday movie night?  Oscar is ready to join in!

But, when you need a great wing man to have by your side for Sunday Funday, Oscar is that friend.  Hiking Barton Creek trails or Zilker Park?  Oscar is more than excited to share adventures of all kinds!  Splashing in the water, walking nicely on leash, and friendliness toward other humans and pets make him your dream dog

Oscar is scared of men and will bark at them.  We can’t explain it, it’s just a thing, but potential adopters need to be aware of that.

Oscar is up to date on vaccines, neutered, and healthy!

Did we mention that he is extraordinarily handsome, too!??

ATXcatsdogs@gmail.com is contact for potential fosters or adopters!

For more photos and info:

Follow us on Facebook https://www.facebook.com/austincatsanddogsrescue/

Follow us on Instagram https://www.instagram.com/austin.catsanddogs.rescue
label: not-adopted

name: Ginger and Sandy CB
description:
What would you do? Say you are at the Vet’s office and you hear a person crying that they lost their home and can’t keep their two beautiful loving 10 year old and 15 year old dogs and have run out of options.

What would you do? And this was not a made up pretend scenario on the John Quinones show this was our real life.  Lucky for us, a fella was there and said he would foster us so that we could find a new place to call home instead of the eeeek alternative.

My name is Sandy, I am the one with the flappy ears and dabbles of grey fur on my muzzle, I am 10 years old and mostly golden Labrador Retriever mixed with Shepherd weigh about 60 pounds.  I earned each of my gray whiskers, I got a new one each time I did something sweet for my human, so there are LOTS there.  I am daughter to the smaller of us. My Mommy is named Ginger, obviously, named for her pretty color.  She is my actual blood Mommy and 15 years old. 

We have been twogether for 10 whole years, so God’s Dogs Rescue very much wants us to be adopted as a package deal, since our world has already been turned inside out, they want us to have some consistency. We are sweet sweet gals, easy on a leash, very soft to touch, and already house trained. We do wonderful around other dogs and really just want a soft place to spend the time we have left.  I want to continue earning my gray muzzle whiskers and show you just how much sweetness I have to offer.

Ginger CB- new dog, female, 15 years, Shepherd/Lab mix, about 50 pounds, slightly perky ears

Sandy CB- new dog, female, 10 years, Lab/Shepherd mix, about 60 pounds, longer flappy ears

GOD'S DOGS Rescue, in San Antonio TX, does not have a shelter - ALL of our dogs are raised in foster homes in the San Antonio area. Each dog comes spayed or neutered, up-to-date on vaccinations that are appropriate for their age, microchipped, heartworm tested and on current on monthly flea/tick and heartworm preventative. 

 ALL OF THIS IS INCLUDED IN THE ADOPTION FEE OF $200.00 FOR LOCAL DOGS AND $250.00 FOR PUPPIES.   ( Local is in the state of Texas)! Medical records will come with each dog at the time of adoption.

IF THIS IS AN OUT OF STATE ADOPTION, TRANSPORT TO YOU is included in the adoption fee of $400.00 for adult dogs and $500.00 for puppies. We transport all over the country!!

All our dogs are socialized and we try to provide you a good understanding of the dog’s personality. Please visit our website for more information about what we do; http://www.yourtxrescueconnection.org/. You will also find helpful information about transport, our adoption application and pictures of our all our dogs/pups looking for homes!!

Please contact us at adoptions@godsdogsrescue.org for more information about adopting one of our dogs and puppies or fill out an adoption application at http://www.godsdogsrescue.org/adopt/adoption-application/

Thank you for wanting to adopt a rescued dog, their LIVES depend on it!

name: Navi
description:
Navi may be a bit older than some of the dogs, but don't let that fool you! She still has plenty of life and energy and a lot of love to give. She loves affection and chasing a ball, and enjoys her daily walks. Navi is fine with some dogs, as long as she can be the boss. She and Kaiser walk together and get along fine, as long as she thinks she is in charge. She would not do well with another dominant or alpha dog, but a friendly submissive one might work.

Spayed female 
6 years old approximately
House and crate trained 
Ok with some dogs but prefers to be only dog 
Micro chipped 
Heartworm negative 
Good with people but needs strong leader
Not good with cats

Cats are to be chased and she has a high prey drive so a no cat household is a must. She does love to go for car rides, walks, and loves to play ball. She loves tummy rubs and petting and is very affectionate.

Navi does need a very strong leader that she respects or she will not do well and she will take charge and that is not good. She seems to like women better than men too but does respect an alpha of either gender. She takes treats gently and gives kisses to her human.
 
If you can be the kind of leader Navi will thrive with please go to our website and fill out an application for her.

name: Lady Red
description: We don't know much about Lady Red's past, but we are certain that her future is sunny, with a 100% chance of a forever family! Lady Red currently resides in a very special and loving foster home, where she has proven over and over how perfect she is. A low maintenance gal, she is house and crate-trained and she loves nothing more than to meet and greet new people. With her striking beauty and soft manners, she'd be a good addition to most families. Lady Red's favorite activities are playing with toys, car rides and napping under the sun. She absolutely loves the feeling of soft wind and the shiny sun on her sweet face, and she can often be seen around town walking and exploring with her foster family. She has good leash manners and is learning basic commands. Just like us humans, our beautiful Lady comes with some quirks. She is partially blind, possibly due to having Canine Diabetes, which is managed by diet and insulin shots (watch her video - we promise it's really easy). This beauty is so intuitive that it took her no time to memorize her foster home's layout and breezes around the furniture with no problems. As you watch her navigate her environment, you'd swear she had no sight issues at all. Lady Red has come a long way to find her place in this world. If you'd like to walk this earth right next to her, don't delay!

name: Derby
description:
This dog is located at the Hearne animal control facility in Robertson country, TX.  This is not a shelter and does not have regular open hours.  You must contact Debbie at 979-279-6388 to discuss or meet the dogs here.  Until a few months ago, this was just a catch and kill facility with no adoption program and virtually no hope for the dogs that were impounded here.  A local resident (Debbie) and other concerned volunteers are leading a grassroots effort to save as many of these dogs as we can.  If you are interested in one of the dogs here, call Debbie immediately at 979-279-6388.  These dogs do not have the luxury of time.  The urgency can't be overstated.  
Unfortunately, in most cases we know nothing about the dogs' histories....medical or otherwise.  We do our best to learn about their personalities and will always be completely honest based on our observations.
Please visit our facebook page at https://www.facebook.com/pages/Urgent-Animals-of-Hearne-Robertson-County-Texas/472642442810842
A vet reference is necessary to adopt an animal from this facility.  To discuss fees and the adoption process, call Debbie immediately at 979-279-6388.

name: Elizabeth
description:
Elizabeth is a sweet shy girl rescued in rural South Texas.  She would do best in a low key home with patient and compassionate humans that make her feel secure.  She loves to play outside and loves toys.  She does well with other friendly dogs and ignores cats.  

Once she feels secure, Elizabeth enjoys gentle human interaction. She is more comfortable with women than men and is still very afraid of a leash attached to her collar as it must remind her of being trapped and dragged with the catchpole used by the animal control officer.    

Elizabeth needs an owner with a great deal of empathy and compassion to whom she can bond.  Ideally her new owner would be interested in slowly expanding Elizabeth's social experiences and building her confidence.  

Elizabeth is spayed, up to date on shots and hw negative.  She is also microchipped and current on preventatives.
special_needs_notes: Very shy due to being under-socialized with diverse humans.  She is very shy with strangers and afraid of men.  She is not fear aggressive or a bite risk but she would be a flight risk until she is comfortable and secure.  She will also not walk on a leash attached to a collar.  She will need someone with experience to bring her out of her shell and build her confidence.  She does great with other dogs.

name: Rocco
description: Rocco's the complete package - a goofy, beautiful, intelligent dog and an absolute sweetheart. Rocco loves his people and always wants to be near them and making them proud. Rocco's favorite game is 'fetch', and while bringing the ball back is not Rocco's strong suit, he'll happily chase it nonstop. He makes up for not returning it by being adorable in the way he pounces on it before it gets away! This smart cookie would thrive in a home where he'll get a lot of exercise and mental stimulation. In fact, Rocco is so smart that we've put him in APA!'s Total Obedience Program. The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Rocco has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! Rocco is learning skills like sit and down, walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' and coming when called. Once Rocco successfully completes all the skills on his training plan, he will be considered TOP Dog Ready! Rocco is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with Rocco after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 One look at Rocco's gorgeous eyes, and goofy smile, and you'll fall in love. Come meet him and see for yourself!

Desmond has been doing really well in his foster home and gets along great with the little dogs he lives with. He's house-trained, isn't jumpy and doesn't counter-surf. Desmond prefers to spend as much time with his people as possible, and he also enjoys getting lots of mental stimulation. He does great with puzzle toys, Kongs and Kong wobblers - anything to keep that big brain occupied. This smart pup is also thriving in APA!'s Total Obedience Program, which is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Desmond has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! Desmond is learning skills like walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'place', which means Desmond will go to a special place in your home on command. Once Desmond successfully completes all the skills on his training plan, he will be considered TOP Dog Ready! Desmond is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with Desmond after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 Desmond doesn't ask for much - just a family that will give him a lot of attention and possibly one with older teenagers and a well-matched doggie sibling. name: Tiki AH
description:
I am just a wittle waggy Weenie/Beagle mix.  Weenie is like an easier way to say Dachshund.  I have only been on this earth for a couple of months, so you will have to start from scratch and teach me like everything.  Chew this, don’t chew this.  Pee on this, don’t pee on this. You know?

I am a girl puppy and one of 5 puppies found under a shed when we were two weeks old. Since then I have been at a foster house spending most of my free time playing and snoozing. The Dogtor said we are going to be small breed dogs maybe 20 pounds once we grow up. Do you want to adopt me? And also, please can you explain what adopt means? They keep saying it, but not explaining it!

GOD'S DOGS Rescue, in San Antonio TX, does not have a shelter - ALL of our dogs are raised in foster homes in the San Antonio area.. Each dog comes spayed or neutered, up-to-date on vaccinations that are appropriate for their age, microchipped, heartworm tested and on current on monthly flea/tick and heartworm preventative. ALL OF THIS IS INCLUDED IN THE ADOPTION FEE OF $200.00 FOR LOCAL DOGS AND PUPPIES( Local is in the state of Texas)! Medical records will come with each dog at the time of adoption.

IF THIS IS AN OUT OF STATE ADOPTION, TRANSPORT TO YOU is included in the adoption fee of $400.00 for adult dogs and $450.00 for puppies. We transport all over the country!!

All our dogs are socialized and we try to provide you a good understanding of the dog’s personality. Please visit our website for more information about what we do; http://www.yourtxrescueconnection.org/. You will also find helpful information about transport, our adoption application and pictures of our all our dogs/pups looking for homes!!

 Please contact us at adoptions@godsdogsrescue.org for more information about adopting one of our dogs and puppies or fill out an adoption application at http://www.godsdogsrescue.org/adopt/adoption-application/

Thank you for wanting to adopt a rescued dog, their LIVES depend on it!
label: not-adopted

name: Fredrick
description: Fredrick has a sweet, bashful smile that sums up his entire being. He can act like a delicate wallflower when you first meet him, but once he is comfortable, he is all about being up in your personal space. He is a pro-level cuddler. Fredrick walks great on a leash. He has good manners and is very focused on his person. Which is fortunate, because taking walks is his favorite thing. He'd rather do that than fetch or wrestle with other dogs. He would do best in a home with a yard, as he loves being outside. He'd like to split his time equally between the grass and your lap, if he could. He learned sit, and has proven to be smart and eager to please. All you really need to fall in love with Fredrick is to look into his eyes. He just has the warmest, most soulful eyes. When he gives you a little hopeful tail wag, it'll be all over. If you're ready, come meet him!
label: not-adopted

name: Brooks
description: Brooks is a happy, spirited and very talkative pup. A first-rate conversationalist, if you say something to Brooks, he will answer you! This boy's got opinions and he's not shy about sharing them. Though he's not much of a barker, Brooks will go around harrumphing and grumbling and huffing his opinion on every situation. His expressive eyes also have a lot to say: 'You're my best friend,' 'Where's the treat?' and 'Let's go jump in the lake!' A sporty senior, Brooks is usually pretty mellow in the home, but he perks up on walks and loves when they go for a long time. He's also 100% water bug and he will launch himself into the lake fearlessly and without hesitation. He loves to retrieve sticks and especially loves it when you jump into the lake with him. Whether it's swimming, hiking or jogging, Brooks is happy to match your pace. He just loves to be outside in the sunshine and he relishes every moment adventuring with his person. As athletic as he is, Brooks is also the perfect, chilled-out house guest. Calm, house-trained and all around well-behaved in the home, Brooks is very good at keeping himself occupied, content to settle in with a good rawhide and some toys. But his favorite activity at home is getting scratches, particularly butt scratches, and you can easily buy his loyalty with them. And treats. Brooks will do just about anything for a treat. Brooks adores attention, and when his person greets houseguests warmly and invites them inside, Brooks takes a couple of sniffs, then expects them to give him butt scratches too. He also enjoys playing tug of war, and when he gets excited, he'll jump around on his hind legs and howl a little bit. He's up for playing with toys if you are, but otherwise is very content to snooze for hours at a time, especially if he is curled up next to you. This spirited guy is also thriving in APA!'s Total Obedience Program. The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Brooks has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! Brooks is learning skills like sit and down, walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'Place', which means he will go to a specific place in your home on command. Once he successfully completes all the skills on his training plan, Brooks will be considered TOP Dog Ready! Brooks is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with him after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 This adorable, athletic cuddlebug is sure to bring lots of love and laughter to your home. Come meet him and we promise you'll have plenty to talk about!

name: Thor
description:
Heartworm Prevention is given on the 14th of each month

UPDATE:

Thor is progressing, but it's a slow work in progress. He's not marking as much, and he's very slowly learning to stand down when he's overwhelmed by the urge to protect. He's definitely not the dog for your average family, but in a home with no or few other animals (no alphas) he could be someone's best buddy forever. He does have a very sweet and cuddly side, and we're continuing to work to let that shine through. If you've ever wanted to rescue an animal purely for the sake of the animal, and are willing to work to save this boy, then he would love you for it for the rest of his days.

Thor's come a long way since being pulled off the streets of San Antonio. He's had a heart workup to make sure he's OK for anesthesia (neuter), and he's put on a little bit of weight so he's not just skin and bones.
This boy's had a rough life, and he still has some aggression issues with my pig, but he's learned to accept and interact with other dogs and people. He still requires careful observation, but he really has come so far!
We're still working on marking, although he's improving. Whomever adopts him needs to understand he requires some patience and understanding. If you can offer him those, then you'll have a dog who loves and adores you!

name: Olive
description: Hi, I\u2019m Olive! Can you believe I\u2019ve been at ADL for over a year? Crazy, right! I know my person is out there somewhere! Please tell me it could possibly be you! A little about me\u2026I can be a bit shy around new people and places so I may need some time to adjust to my new home. Please don\u2019t let that worry you because before you know it, I am as playful as can be! I love running, exploring, and enjoying my time outdoors. You might catch me rolling around in the grass with a squeaky toy in my mouth because I LOVE to play with toys! I also enjoy a good game of fetch and have impressive skills at catching tennis balls in midair. I\u2019m very treat motivated! I\u2019ll sit for treats and happily stare at you with puppy dog eyes as I wait for the treat. I would fit in best in a home with older considerate children and although I\u2019d prefer to be the only furbaby, I might consider a dog-sibling too. So if you have any potential dog-siblings for me, then let\u2019s set up a meet-and-greet! Overall, I\u2019m a friendly and playful gal who just needs a special person who\u2019ll love me no matter what. I may have a very serious expression when you see me at ADL but there is a silly side to me that you must see! Please give me a chance to show you how fun I can be!\n

name: BUCK
description:
Meet Buck! Buck is estimated to be about 1 1/2 yrs old with some rough times behind him- obvious from his embedded collar injury and the possible burn scar on his rear leg. Our best guess at breed is a Lab/Hound mix. Buck is 60 lbs of happy energy and he gets along well with other dogs and is potty trained and crate trained. Buck loves to meet new people! His enthusiasm leads him to jump up to greet people so we are working on manners. He would be perfect for an active person and would be a great running partner! He is a very smart dog so he needs to keep his mind stimulated. He has already learned sit and down and we are working on roll over. He is easily motivated so additional training or training classes would be perfect for him! He needs a secure fence and supervision while outside. Because he is a big puppy he would do best in a home with no small kids and other medium to large dogs. While he is good with other dogs he does bark when on a leash at unfamiliar dogs which can sound a little intimidating, but he is just so excited and wants to play. He has a goofy personality. His favorite snack is bananas and he likes to play in the bathtub!

Buck is available for adoption with Saving Grace Dog Rescue of San Antonio. The adoption fee is $150.00. An adoption application, home visit and adoption contract are all required. All dogs are spayed/neutered, up to date on vaccinations appropriate for their age, microchipped, and wormed for internal and external parasites. If you would like more information or an adoption application, please email us at sgdrsa@outlook.com.

Please note that visual breed identification in rescue dogs is unreliable so for most of our dogs we are only GUESSING at predominant breed or breed mix. We get to know each dog as an individual and will do our best to describe each of our dogs based on personality, not by breed label.
organization: Saving Grace Dog Rescue of San Antonio

name: Esther
description: Esther came to our rescue with a huge hernia, mammoth tumors and needed to be spayed. She struggled with gaining weight and an infection but now she has healed and is at a healthy weight! \nEsther loves to lay around and cuddle on the sofa. She would love to meet a new companion and have a forever home. She is so cute with her big airplane ears when she looks up and is very sweet. She doesn't bark or whine only grunts and moans.  She just is not a complainer. She is working on her potty training and will go potty outside when taken out. She loves to go for walks and walks good on a leash. Esther is fine with other dogs and cats around as long as she can sit with you too. She does have some seeing issues but finds her way around the house and outside just fine.

name: Mulberry
description:
Petite, sweet, loving little Mulberry finally has a family that is kind to her and expects her to be part of what they do. No more outside in a kennel, raising pups or anxiously anticipating the next forced breeding. This little fawn sweetheart is only 4 or 5 years old and this world of touches and treats and laps is brand new. She has been fully vetted, spayed and finished the routine preventive medications for dogs like her from the Palm Valley area. Remarkably she is heartworm negative.

Mulberry soaks up love and attention like a sponge. She loves people, even little people, and cuddling is about as good as it gets. Mulberry did not need to develop social skills with dogs or people in the puppy mill, but she is catching up quickly in her foster home. She does not like dominant male dogs (no surprise there) but is learning that some dogs are OK, like the submissive male Boxer she lives with now.

Mulberry is house, crate and leash trained. Her experienced foster mom explains “ It is hard not to give in to her soulful brown eyes and pixie face when it is time for discipline but she responds well when told no. She does have a stubborn streak so repetition and patience are key.” This little darling needs a loving family who can say no when needed and still shower her with love, attention, inclusion and security. Goodness knows she earned it.


More info coming soon

name: Ziggy
description: Ziggy is a spunky, young pup with a desire to learn. He's also a very playful guy, and loves to run, run, and run some more. If Ziggy was a muppet, he'd definitely be the Cookie Monster! This guy lives for treats. He'll do just about anything for one and because he's so incredibly smart, we do mean just about anything. We're convinced that Ziggy can learn anything that doesn't require opposable thumbs. And he's so good on leash that sometimes he's so focused on his handler (and the treats), that he'll walk right into fences. Ziggy watches his person closely to figure out what game they can play next or what will be asked of him. He's currently learning to play a 'shell game' of finding a treat in various containers. This game is particularly fun for him because he has to use his nose. That's another thing that Ziggy likes - he loves to follow his nose to make sure that he smells all the smells!! This smart pup is also thriving in APA!'s Total Obdience Program and recently became TOP Dog Ready, which means he has already learned all the skills in his training plan. The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP Dog, Ziggy has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! Dogs in the program learn skills including sit and down, walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers, calmly walking past another dog, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' and coming when called. In addition, Ziggy has also learned 'Place'. Ziggy has worked hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with Ziggy after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 Ziggy is a great example of what training and love can do for a dog. Because Ziggy is so smart, he can sometimes get himself into trouble and needs a home with someone who is comfortable setting boundaries. In return, this goofy boy will melt your heart and empty your treat pouch. Come meet him!

name: Princess Margaret
description:
Princess Margaret is a lady of a certain age (9, but we’re not telling) who gets along with her younger fur friends and 2 little skin kids just fine. That doesn’t mean she hasn’t earned a bit of respect, like “get the heck out of my quiet spot, NOW” kind of respect. A glance and a low comment is all that’s needed for the youngsters to get the message. It’s quiet time inside after all. Outside, well, she can still run with the best of them; and slow down for play time with the skin kids too.

This lady sports a fawn coat with a white chest and just a dash of white on her neck, pretty elegant. You don’t even have to ask if she is house trained, I mean, really how embarrassing. She’s fine outside a crate too. When she’s not napping in her quiet spot you’ll find her right by your side. Princess Margaret likes her humans, big and small.

This lady has had a few litters, of course, and she is heartworm positive. ABR will discuss the options for treatment and help with it too. This sweet, dignified lady has some years left in her journey. She’d love to have her quiet spot next to you while you read a book, or watch tv, or take a nap with her.

name: Lily
description:
Please contact Anne (abaumgartner2008@yahoo.com) for more information about this pet.Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

70 lb perfect house dogLily (70 lbs, 3 yrs) is a super sweet bully who came up to a rescuer trapping another and asked to come home. All she wants is to be a house dog and part of the family. It's evident Lily was hit, so raised arms or swiping motions make her duck and freeze. Lily needs a good mommy or daddy to let her be their lap dog with plenty of belly rubs and hugs given. Lily is crate and house trained and knows the sit and shake commands. Lily does fine with dogs that don't over-react to her out-going, in your face attitude; she does well with tiny to huge dogs, but is too excitable for cats. Lily runs errands and goes to the park and pet stores, but is still working on her leash skills when she gets excited. Her sweet personality is definitely worth it! For more information, please contact her foster mom, Anne. 210-887-8041 or abaumgartner2008@yahoo.com

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.

Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and a 30-day trial of 24PetWatch Pet Insurance. Adopters will also receive a Petco Pet Parent Savings Books that contain:• $100s in savings plus a coupon for a free 6 lb. bag of WholeHearted dog food.• Thoughtful care tips.• Online resources and support.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved and you are traveling from out-of-town, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time.

We do try to schedule bi-monthly meet-and-greets in Austin as interested is generated.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

name: Louie Luckenbach
description:
Welcome to the Wonderful World of Rescue Dachshunds. Look around and read their bios. Find a few whose personality seems to fit well. Consider one of our Well Seasoned Seniors who are truly wonderful and have so much to offer. Need help finding the best fit? We'll help with that too. Please fill out an application and let’s get you all matched up with a loving new “furever’ companion and friend. You’ll find the application on the “Available Dogs” page.
NOTE:

Adoptions to Texas residents only

.

Standard Adoption Fee Adult Dog: $250 ea. Puppy Adoption Fee: $300 ea. Reduced rates for Seniors dogs (10 and up). Reduced rates for pairs (when adopted together).

Email: ddrtxinfo@gmail.com Primary Website: www.DDRTX.org
Mr. Louie Luckenbach is a big boy at almost 35 pounds. Louie has suffered a lifetime of abuse and neglect and while he is very sweet and loving, he can be unpredictable and would need an experienced home. He is very sensitive about his amputated toe even though it has healed; it caused him a great deal of pain for possibly a very long time. He has some permanent hair loss due to food allergies. He is food aggressive but his foster mom is working with him on it. He is perfectly house trained.
Love dachshunds and not ready to adopt or circumstances won't permit having a dog? How about being a sponsor or making a donation. Every one of our dachshunds receives excellent medical care along with day to day food, love and housing. Being non-profit, we rely on generous individuals like yourselves to help save these fur babies. You can do this specifically for one dog with the sponsor button on their webpage or a general donation on our “How To Help” page. Easy and quick through Pay Pal or your debit/credit card. You generosity is sincerely appreciated by all and is tax deductable. Need other ideas? You'll find tons of them on the How to Help tab. All contributions are tax deductable.

Diamond Dachshund Rescue of Texas is a non-profit 501(c)(3) volunteer organization with focus on rescue and adoption of pure breed Dachshunds. All dogs are fully vetted and housed on private property. Meetings are scheduled upon adoption approval. Thank you for your continued support to the rescue and shelter communities!
Opt to Adopt!

name: Mickey and Petey
description:
4 yr old Chihuahua-Shih Tzus (Chi-Tzus), bonded brothers, neutered, Rabies and DHPP vaccinations current, heartworm positive, but on Moxy-Doxy slow kill method with supplies for 6 month treatment, crate trained, and so stinking sweet they will melt your heart. 
Mickey looks like a scruffy Chi and Petey looks like long legged Shih Tzu. Both about 7-8 pounds. According to former owner Petey was attacked by a raccoon at his feeding bowl as a young pup. Vet says his eye is healthy, doesn't need to be removed, but obviously there is sight loss. They were raised in a pack situation (are in one here), so do well with other dogs. They are also good with cats (caveat is my cats DO NOT RUN... they rule the house with iron paws). 
Both are very affectionate, but Petey is the shy one. Former owner told a vague story of Petey missing for three minths and some getting him back in rough shape. He was matted and will slink around army crawling if he is unsure. Otherwise he will roll on you like a cat and beg to be held. Mickey is quite feisty and will make sure he gets his attention. I crate and feed them together. They are pretty easy. 
I am afraid small/rowdy toddlers and children may be too much for Petey. Both cannot tolerate rough handling. 
Both acted as if I were drowning them during possible first bath of their lives, and being groomed is also daunting. They need patient handling. Both were good for nail trims.

label: Achilles
column26: Achilles was found as a stray, but he has so much affection for people that we think he may not have always been on his own. He constantly wants to snuggle and when he sees his people coming, he wags his little tail with all his might! He loves to be by your side and will lay his big adorable head on your leg Or lean his whole body against you. His APA! friends rave about his kisses and how speedy and sneaky he is with them. Achilles is great on leash and loves to go on long walks. He's also a very patient guy and is perfectly content to let you stop and chat with people along the way. He's not particularly interested in other dogs and seems to prefer just spending his time with his people, but he has become enamored with playing fetch, if fetch means running around with the ball in his mouth. He hasn't figured out the other half of fetch yet, but we're working on it. Achilles is also working on being the best dog he can be in APA!'s Total Obedience Program. The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Achilles has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn skills like sit and down, walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' and coming when called. Once Achilles successfully completes all the skills on his training plan he will be considered TOP Dog Ready. Achilles is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA! staff to continue to build a training relationship with Achilles after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 This easy-going pooch is a joy to be around and can't wait to meet his family. A more loyal companion you'll never find. Come meet him! Follow Achilles on Instragram @achilles_austin

name: Pearl
description:
Hi there - my name is Pearl and I am a loving lady-pug.  Well, I'm at least half pug, that is! But because I'm larger than your average pug, we are not sure what the other 50% is.

More about me:  I'm only 8 years old, and I am so good with people of all kinds, including children.  Because I have issues with other dogs, I would thrive as the only dog in a house.

I would make a wonderful family dog because I'm very smart, know some commands, and love to snuggle. I appreciate strong guidance and will also let you know when I need "me-time"!

I'm pretty much the whole package, and I am so excited about meeting you at the next adoption event or during a trial visit.

name: Sofia
description:
Sofia is a gorgeous girl in search of a forever home. She was surrendered to a high kill shelter because her owner said they could no longer care for her, and was terrified. She has come a long way but is still a work in progress. Sofia was probably an only dog and does not seem to have been around people much. She bonded to her foster Mom immediately, but is very leary of other people, but with some work should be fine. 

Spayed 3 year old female
Current on shots
Heartworm negative
House and crate trained
Micro chipped
Still learning social skills
Weight 70 lbs

Sofia probably needs an experience and patient owner, and for now would NOT do well in a home with children. This could change, but for now we think it best she go to a quieter home. Sofia is doing well learning to interact with other dogs, so would be fine as a single dog or with another confident good natured one. 

If you think you could provide the right home for this gorgeous girl, please apply.

I like to play with toys and I really enjoy splashing around in the kiddie pool! All I want is to be around people and I would especially love to be around you. name: Caleb
description:
Caleb is a staffordshire terrior mix about 1.5 years old. He weighs about 55 lbs but could still stand to gain a few more since he still looks a little underweight. 

He is a young boy with an old soul, very affectionate and eager to please. He gets along with all the female dogs his size that are low energy here at the shelter but does not do well with male dogs. He doesn't need a lot of exercise but would probably enjoy a walk in the park every now and then. He is currently being treated for heart worms and will be ready for his new home in just a few weeks. 

He is in a small shelter in Lytle, TX and can be transported to your area once adopted. His adoption fee is $185 and transport fee is $185. If you are interested in adopting Caleb, please contact Lytle Animal Care and Control at 830-709-3832 and request an application.

name: Thaddeus
description: Thaddeus is an older gentlemen, but you can see he still has a youthful spirit. Not a sporting spirit though - he's pretty much just here for the naps and bully sticks. But a sparkle in his eye, a winning smile and a willingness to meet new friends. Thaddeus loves meeting people and always greets them gently and politely. For as much as he loves treats, he is sure to take those gently too. There is not too much Type A in his personality. He loves to go on walks and is great on leash. He is well-behaved in the home and knows how to use a doggie door. He is not super cuddly but he will occasionally lay his head in your lap. And don't be terribly surprised if you find he's crawled into bed with you in the middle of the night. Although he spends most of his time napping, he's still up for some leisurely adventures at the lake or park. He's a great swimmer. Thaddeus is the ultimate low-maintenance dog. Super chill, but still fun to hang out with, he's just looking for a comfy couch and some good friends. Is there room in your heart and living room?

name: Schone
description: Schone is a People Pup! This sweet, mature lady is a social butterfly who is always excited to meet new people when she's cruising around her neighborhood. She walks right up to strangers, tail wagging. At home, she'll sleep next to her foster mom's desk or cuddle on the couch, always wanting to be with her person. Schone is easygoing and fully house-trained. She makes few demands other than letting you know when she needs to go outside. She walks well on her leash and is quiet and well-behaved when left alone at home, so no crate required! Though she's easy to care for, Schone has been diagnosed with Cushing's disease, which is managed with medication. Schone would love a home with older kids, and she's fine with either a house or an apartment. She just wants to be with her people, staying close to them and taking those fun walks. Come meet this sweet lady!

name: Molly Chi
description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Hi. My name is Molly. My brother Tanner and I were adopted out together when we were puppies. Unfortunately our mommy got a bad sickness and could no longer take care of us. We were very lucky. A Doggie 4 You always takes back their babies, so Tanner and I were safe. We were very scared for our big sister Mollie Two. She came from off the street and we were afraid she would be left behind, plus she wasn't very friendly. Boy were we happy when she got to come with us.

When our mommy got sick, she quit going outside. So we were confined indoors and I am afraid we gained alot of weight. I came in weighing over 20 pounds and I could barely walk. All three of us were in really bad shape. Over the past year we all have been gradually losing weight and I can walk and play again. I even play with toys again. I am a little older and wiser than some of the other dogs but I have alot of love left.

I wish I could go with Tanner. We have never been apart.

If you are interested in adopting this dog, send an email to adoggie4you@yahoo.com.
Adoption Fee is $150.00. If Tanner and Molly go together the total adoption fee is $200.

name: Jordan
description:
Jordan is a female, year old, brindle American Staffordshire Terrier blend looking for her forever home. 

Jordan first entered our program in January 2017 after she had been owner surrendered to a local veterinary clinic with a broken femur. We brought her under our wing, repaired her leg, and found a home for her. 

Unfortunately, in October 2017, an animal shelter called us and said a female pit bull had turned up with a microchip associated with our program. It was Jordan, except...now she is an adult with cropped ears. While she had been picked up as a "stray," her owners went ahead and relinquished her to the shelter, allowing us to go and reclaim her. 

Jordan is a sweet, smart girl but she has to be the *only* animal in a home with a securely fenced yard. She has a strong prey drive, so open property and/or ranch style housing will not be an option. Jordan has been exposed to children, but she is young with lots of energy, so if the home has children, they need to be at least 10 years of age. 

Jordan is very smart and learns commands easily. She is eager to please and absolutely LOVES toys. We know she will make a lucky family or individual very happy. 

For more information or to adopt, please visit www.mylongwayhome.org/pitbulls/adopt
label: not-adopted

name: Motley
description:
Motley is a 2 year old white male American Pit Bull Terrier/Lab Blend (best guess) looking for his forever home. He and his brother Bon Jovi first entered our program as a litter of 8 in January 2016.

After being adopted together in 2016, both boys grew up in a loving home. After multiple tragedies struck the family, the owner felt the best option for the boys - setting emotions aside - was to return them for the opportunity to find a new home that could continue to provide the level of care we seek for each of our dogs.

Heartbroken and devastated, the family returned both boys to us earlier this January.

Motley is very social with dogs, livestock, and horses and loves people. Motley is kennel trained and potty trained. Motley is healthy, heartworm negative, and ready to be adopted!

To apply to adopt Motley, please visit https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSf7lEM04PZS_5DKKYpB1zvzwCtxlCAOgd-MEfMerdG8Q9yByQ/viewform

She is always up for any activity and especially loves car rides and napping on the couch with her human. She is house-trained and does extremely well in the crate when she's home alone. Jasmine is quiet, affectionate and extremely treat-motivated, which makes training easy. Jasmine is also in APA!'s Total Obedience Program. The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Jasmine has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help her learn the skills to become the best dog she can be! Jasmine is learning skills like sit and down, walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' and coming when called. Jasmine is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with Jasmine after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. name: Scooter
description:
Please contact Jamesa (roxysrescue@yahoo.com), 713-882-2610 for more information about this pet.A Real TrooperScooter is a 3.5 year old Border Collie, weighing 45 lbs. He has reached his adult weight and height. This guy has my respect. I pulled him from a high kill shelter in San Antonio, Texas when he was almost 3 months old. He was very emaciated and his rear leg had with a bone sticking out and broken in several places. Someone had abused him. But Scooter was still happy and loved to be held and his sprits had not been broken. He has been a trooper from day one, never making a sound even though he was in a lot of pain.
Even though his leg was so bad; the vet considered amputation but decided to watch the bones heal. They leg healed but he has a limp that doesn’t stop him from running and jumping. His room is upstairs and he bounces up the stairs all the time. And he loves for me to play chase with him in the backyard. His complete medical records and x-rays will come with him at the time of adoption.
Someone else named him early on but his name Scooter so deserves, he is a SCOOTER. He only barks when he is talking to you or to alert me that someone is near our gate in the backyard. He bounces around still like a puppy and just a very happy guy. He gets along with everyone.
Scooter will let a dog cuddle with him, eat out of his bowl and share his toys. To sum Scooter up, he is just a fun loving guys who smiles all the time and gives you love every day. You cannot help but smile back at him and laugh because he sits there with a goofy grin on his face looking at you until you do smile and tell him something good. This is the type of dog that you want to come home to, he is a best friend best buddy pal for sure.
He has a beautiful black wavy coat and he does not tend to shed with regular baths, he will sit still for a bath, then he goes and takes a long nap. J There is nothing better to Scooter than having his head scratched and getting some attention from him human. And a rawhide, he chews on them and plays with them! He is not demanding and very low maintenance. He eats regular dry food but he watches to see if you might share your food with him!!!! While he has been in my care, he has helped heal the soul of other rescue dogs brought into my home that didn’t have the best start in life. Scooter just seems to know what is going on.
His best friend was another bigger white border collie who only has 3 legs. Bradley was hit by a car. Scooter instantly took to him and became his hearing dog and totally took care of Bradley. Sadly Bradley got adopted and Scooter has been searching for another best buddy.

name: Kaily
description:
She smiles when she is with youHER STORY
This girl is super sweet, please meet her and let her melt your heart.
Kaily gave birth to 8 puppies on November 17, 2015; 4 girls & 4 boys. All have been adopted. Kaily appears to be a true Labrador Retriever but mixed with something. Kaily had no microchip and I guess she ran away for a better life. Kaily ate through her rope and tie-down from her home and ended up at one of my feeding stations very pregnant. She gave birth to 9 puppies almost 1 week later. Very smart girl, I guess Kaily decided she would not give birth while tied up. She had on a huge black collar and chain that she broke to escape her previous home. That awful collar has been removed for a more stylist one. As soon as she had her babies, I climbed the fence and found her 2 day old babies laying filth, dirt, trash, it was not very nice and they were covered already with fleas. This may have been Kaily's first litter, she tried to hide them from the elements but she didn't do a very good job, they were completely exposed to the wind and rain. 1 little puppy didn't make it. But the other 8 looked good.
Kaily ended up being very happy to be rescued, loaded up and taken to a clean, safe home where she could receive love & attention.
Kaily is 2.5 years old and currently weighs 68 lbs but she could stand to lose a few pounds. I’m sure with regular walks she would probably lose 10 pounds easily. Kaily has a great personalities, she is very quiet, friendly and gets along with all humans and dogs. Actually her entire litter of puppies were all very quiet, quiet when they played, ate, wrestled, they were just a very calm, chill bunch. Kaily does not get upset, nor is she destructive. She will sleep in her crate but she is fine just sleeping on her doggy bed, she is not destructive. She will play with toys but she would rather have some ear scratches and love from her human and cuddle besides you. She is not a shadow dog, very independent but she keeps an eye on you to make sure you are still there. Her solemn look turns into a smile while she is following you around and she is just close to you, all she wants s to share her love. Kaily is a great, very calm, well behaved young lady and will make a great family pet.
She also communicates with you like if she wants to watch TV and it is off she will just sit and stare at the TV until you turn it on. She will also cuddle with you and watch TV together.
Kaily is a Labrador Retriever mix with a bronzy brown coat with black going doing the middle. Now that she knows she is safe and not chained up, she is the perfect little lady. She requires very little maintenance and just wants to be loved. She has 1 male playmate that she is fond of but she is in a home with a variety of foster brothers and sisters. She gets along with small and big dogs, her first roommate upon arriving here was a 4 pound Maltese and he made sure she knew who was boss!! Kaily has a mild demeanor; not aggressive in any area and likes to get out for walks but not demanding of them. Nor does her behavior require that she be walked on a daily basis. Kaily's coat looks a lot better now than when she was first rescued. Please consider giving Kaily her chance at a forever home. You would be getting a prized family pet by adopting this girl into your home.
PLEASE VISIT OUR WEBSITE FOR MORE PICTURES: roxysk9rescue.org

name: Roxy
description:
Up for adoption in Texas and New England: Roxy and Kia, a bonded pair, a mother and daughter!  



These two sweet adorable girls are a dynamic duo.

Kia, who is 12-years-old, is Roxy’s mother. Roxy is 9-years-old and lost her right hind leg to cancer. This does not phase her whatsoever, and she can run up and down stairs without issues.  

Kia weighs about 60lbs and Roxy weighs about 70lbs. 

These poor girls were left behind when their owner was sent to a nursing home.  

They are very well behaved, housebroken, calm, and excellent with other dogs and are friendly with cats.  

They have to stay together.  Is there someone out there who can provide them a loving home to live out their golden years?  

Kia has darker eyes and shorter ears, compared to Roxy. 

They are spayed, vaccinated, microchipped and housebroken. 



Apply at www.luckylabrescue.com

name: Juliet
description: Meet Juliet!  This fun little girl is looking for someone to run and play with, relax and watch movies, shows, commercials, etc ...mainly, just someone to love on her forever and show her she can trust them to keep her safe so she will never be left to fend for herself again!\nJuliet is a 6 yr old chihuahua mix.  Don't let her age fool you though... she runs and plays like she is half her age!  At only 6.8 lbs, she would be a wonderful addition to the right home.  With her small build, she will be best in a home without really young or very active children though.  She is very curious and loves to find out what is behind every door and in every corner!  She is currently living in a home with lots of playmates close to her own size, a 7 yr old little girl and two adults.  Her favorite way to spend her day is relaxing after chasing her playmates around the yard... more relaxing than chasing, but no one is keeping track!  She is kennel trained (although would probably prefer a couch or bed to call her own), housebroken and learned how to use the doggie door the first day (although with everyone's small size, is only open during the day when their people are home and can make sure nothing happens while they are outside). Her adoption fee is $90 and includes her shots, spay and a box of heartgard.  If you are interested in this wonderfully sweet girl, please send your application to myhappytail@yahoo.com.  Applications are found by clicking on the More about Us button on her profile.

name: Cecily
description:
Someone once described a dog as a “Family Dog in a Box”. That description fits Cecily to a T. She is a beautiful 6 year old with patience and grace. She plays with one of her host dogs and politely lets him know when she’s done. Her other host dog doesn’t like other dogs much and she respects his distance. The cats still refuse to play and she lets them slide. She is very loving and patient with the toddler and early schooler in her home too.

Cecily curls up in her crate for a nap or quiet time whenever she’s ready. She loves laying in the sun, walks, and being near her people and she has great recall. Cecily is eager to please and learn new things. 

Cecily is a very well balanced lady who is easy to live with. She is heartworm positive and not symptomatic. ABR will explain treatment options and help with it; treatment need not be difficult now. She is otherwise healthy, happy and steady. You will wonder where she’s been all this time when you see her napping in her crate in your home.



More info coming soon
