name: Munchkin
description:
There are times when want-to and can-do just don’t match. Such is the case with our little Munchkin. She was adopted in 2015 as a puppy and has lived a pretty happy, easy life. But sometimes declining health or dear relatives who need increasing care just overwhelm the can-do and the beloved Boxer’s welfare has to be addressed. You see, Munchkin likes to explore, and when a gate is accidentally left open, well, heaven knows she’s going to see what’s beyond. But she doesn’t understand cars and roads and mean people, and that brings us back to what is best for her.

She is small at about 45 pounds, with a docked tail, natural ears, a fawn coat, black mask and white chest. She gets along with dogs just fine but is pretty shy overall and very timid with men. She’s between 3 and 4 years old now and completely up to date on her vaccinations, including rattlesnake (it needs an annual booster), heartworm medication and flea and tick meds. She is house, crate and leash trained and does not jump up or get on furniture.

Munchkin is still a bit high energy girl with a high  prey drive: no cats, but she is sweet and cuddly too. It is never easy to let go of a loved one, but sometimes doing what is best for them is the right thing to do. Our Munchkin needs a family where she can be safe and secure. 



More info coming soon

name: Cricket
description: We hope you don't mind if we chirp about our Cricket. Besides the adorable way she tilts her head as she waits for a treat, the most important thing to know about Cricket is that she is an admirer and collector of toys. Cricket LOVES toys and she always keeps several in her kennel. And she often proudly shows off one to her volunteer visitors. If she passes a toy while on a walk at APA! she must investigate and evaluate. If she were a human, she'd have a whole room 'mint in box.' Cricket is good with people of every type, big and small, and is great at meeting strangers. She will walk right up to them for pets but doesn't jump up on them. Cricket has lived with kids (aged 7 and 10) in foster, and she was very gentle and patient with them. She loved being petted and playing fetch and tug-of-war and also met a lot of the kids' friends and was great with meeting all of them. Cricket's just a great pup to have around - she's affectionate without being needy and high energy and playful when you want her to be. She will put her paw up on your to get attention or just lay her head on your lap to let you know it's time for pets. When indoors, she naps a lot and is happy to relax and lounge about. She has a tendency to sleep in really funny poses - curled up as small as possible like a cat, or on a chair with her head hanging off or sprawled out with her paws daintily crossed, or on her back with her paws in the air. But once she gets outside, her high-energy side comes out, and she loves to go on long hikes or runs or play fetch for as long as you can stand it. With her expressive eyes, constant wagging tail and big floppy funny ears, Cricket has a lot of personality and seems to exude gratitude anytime her people come near her. Cricket has great manners at home and quickly learned and obeyed which pieces of furniture she was and wasn't allowed on. She almost never barks in any situation and sleeps through the might in her crate. She walks pretty well with a gentle leader and gives great eye contract to keep those treats coming. In fact, Cricket is such a good training buddy that she recently became CGC Ready, which means she successfully passed the American Kennel Club's CGC test with her volunteer trainer! To pass the CGC test, a dog must demonstrate obedience and general reliability in real world situations. A CGC-Ready dog knows sit and down, walks nicely on leash, will sit calmly when approached by strangers or another dog, won't approach people or dogs without permission, greets people appropriately, stays in a sit or down until told 'free,' and comes when called. Cricket has been working hard to be a dog you can take anywhere with pride, and as part of APA!'s CGC program you can work with APA to continue to build a training relationship with her after adoption and get officially CGC certified for free! Check out a video about CGC: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 Cricket but would be great for a single person, couple or family with kids. She would love a backyard romp around in as long as the fence is tall because this Cricket can jump! Cricket has got a lot of love to give, so if you're looking for a smart, happy, affectionate pup who's eager to learn and eager to please, come meet her!
label: not-adopted

name: Brindle
description: The name 'Brindle' might seem generic, but we couldn't think of a better name for such a stunningly handsome boy with the most perfect chevron markings. In a word, Brindle is gorgeous! He's also incredibly sweet and has the most soulful eyes to go with his amazing good looks and personality. If that's not reason enough to meet him, you should know that Brindle is a model houseguest with A+ ratings in the home. This elegant, long-legged boy really knows how to mind his manners. He's potty-trained, happy to go in his crate and a is good boy left on his own while his people are out doing human things. Though he loves his couch time, Brindle enjoys stretching those long legs out on the trail, where he will happily walk right by your side at a leisurely pace. And bust out the rope toy and he'll morph into a giant puppy - you'll know it's game time when he strikes his adorable play-bow! If you've got treats, Brindle will show you his tricks! This boy is super smart, already knows some some impressive skills and is very eager to please. He's also thriving in APA!'s Total Obedience Program. The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Brindle has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! Brindle is learning skills like sit and down, walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'place', which means he will go to a special place in your home on command. Once Brindle successfully completes all the skills on his training plan, he will be considered TOP Dog Ready! Brindle is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with Brindle after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 Trust us, when you meet Brindle you'll see he's all the dog you'll ever need. Come meet this handsome guy! Follow Brindle on Instagram @adoptbrindle

name: Cody
description:
Hi!  My name is Cody! I'm a sweet, loveable guy who just had a run of back luck.
 I had it pretty good... you can see I didn't miss any meals! 

A while ago, my mom got sick and passed away. 
I'm pretty sad about it, but her daughter was amazing and brought me home with her. 
She can't keep me forever, but wanted to be sure I got a good "forever" home with a family who understand the needs of a  bigger guy like me.

If  you think a big, fluffy love-bug might be missing from your life, please fill out the application! I'd love to meet you!  

P.S. as a bonus, my adoption fee is only $250!

name: China
description: China is an spirited girl who LOVES playing fetch. China bounces from one end of the play yard to the other, so happy she's getting to chase after tennis balls. And if her person doesn't throw that first ball fast enough, she'll run to the bucket holding the balls and paw at it to say 'Right here, human!' China doesn't have much hair, but she has a big heart and loves all her human friends at the shelter. If China's experienced a lack of kindness in her past, she doesn't hold it against anyone. She just wants to find her humans and play play play! China settles down nicely in her kennel and waits patiently for someone to take her out, but once she's out, this energetic girl is rarin' to go. China's also gotten along well with the dogs in playgroup and should be able to go home with a well-matched doggie sibling. Sweet and fun-loving, China would make a wonderful companion to any number of loving homes. She doesn't ask for much - a nice walk, a game of fetch, some TLC and this precious lady will love you forever. Come meet China!
label: not-adopted

name: Mueller
description: An emotional support animal for his previous owner, Mueller is incredibly loyal to his human friends. You'll never question how much he loves you as this highly affectionate guy will nuzzle his head underneath your head and give you soft little side kisses from the corner of his mouth. His favorite place to be is in your lap, and he's described by his friends as having a very comforting presence. He seems very in tune with how his people are feeling and will offer kisses if he thinks you need them. As cuddly and loving as Mueller is, it does take him some time to warm up to new people, but once he trusts you, you become everything to Mueller and a more loyal friend you'll never find. Mueller is also super low-maintenance - he likes to play in short bursts, but overall has a pretty low energy level. He likes to play tug of war and roughhouse with his people and also enjoys his toys, especially ones with bumps and nubs that he can chew on. But what Mueller really enjoys are his walks. He loves to get out on the trail, his floppy ears bouncing along happily, before he's back at home chilling with his people. This smart pup and enjoys showing off his skills and he's got quite a few. He already knows 'sit', 'stay', 'come' 'lay down' and 'shake'. He walks well on leash, is fully house and crate-trained and is good at keeping himself entertained when his people are busy, either laying on his back, enjoying the breeze or giving his chew toys some attention. Loving and loyal and a pleasure to have around, Mueller would make a wonderful addition to your home. Come meet him!
label: not-adopted

name: Vegas
description: Vegas is the best of both worlds! A relaxed cuddlebug in the home and a playful, silly boy in the yard. This sweet, imaginative boy loves his downtime, but he also loves to make up his own quirky games, entertaining his human friends to no end! You should see him when he's out in the yard putting on a show! Living up to his name, Vegas is quite the acrobat. His performance includes running, jumping, rolling and spinning. It's hard not to laugh when he's tossing toys in the air or scampering after balls. Since he likes to include the audience in his act, he prefers to let the humans do the retrieving. You know he's really happy when he jumps into the air and spins in a tight circle. Once the performance is over, Vegas is ready to chill inside. He's content to lay right by your side with his big ol' head in your lap. When he looks up at you with those soulful eyes, it's impossible to not fall in love. Vegas is fully house-trained and is making good progress on crate-training, though he's so well-behaved when left alone, it isn't really necessary. And he's great at letting you know when he needs to go outside. So what do you say? Are you ready for a new best friend who will give you a free Vegas show every day? Visit Vegas today and see how much he has to offer!

name: LIANA
description:
Hi there!  My name is LIANA.  What’s yours?  Nice to meet ya!  

Hey!  Before you get attached to me, read all the way to the bottom.  You will see that I am still in Houston, TX but I want to get OUT of Houston and OUT of Texas so I can have a really good life.  I want to see Texas in my rear view mirror. A nice person came along and took me in and, now, I am ready to hit the road to your house!  Uh, make that “our” house, OK? (You may see me listed in numerous cities looking for my new home.)


I am a Bulldog/Pittie mix and I am 3.5 old and I weigh 50 pounds.  I have had all of my shots and have been spayed so I can go to my new home with YOU!  Those funny-looking 2-legged creatures said I’m also microchipped – whatever THAT is.  At any rate, I will be fully vetted.  Is that anything close to petted?  I love to be petted!  


Wanna hear some more good stuff about me?  OK, here goes.  I like my peeps - PERIOD - Just you and me, kid, OK? - no other doggies -  I love chew toys. I love to cuddle with my peeps - playing or couch-sitting when we get tired.  Let's be a team, OK?



If you would like to take me home (and you know you do), please email doggydarlings12@gmail.com  and she can get me on my way to a new and loving home!  My adoption fee is $650 USD and includes my vetting, spaying, microchip, health certificate, travel crate AND air transportation from Houston, TX to areas in the Northeast U. S., North Central U. S., Northwest U. S., and Canada and will be arranged by the rescue group.  (This is a courtesy posting.  Doggy Darlings is not the rescue.)  

Watch this segment from the TODAY show:  http://www.today.com/news/puppy-rescuer-takes-dogs-4-200-mile-odyssey-loving-arms-2D79517768

name: Charlie Brown
description: Charlie Brown came to me when he was about 9 months old and it became clear very quickly that he had been badly mistreated by someone already in his young life. He was extremely skittish and untrusting and I worked very hard with him to bring him along to where he is now. It makes me so happy to see how far he has come along. He has blossomed from a scared, sad, little dog into a happy, trusting, and extremely affectionate companion. He is still wary of new people (especially men), but quickly warms up and wants to be petted by everyone. He thinks he is a lap dog, and if you will let him he will get up on the bed or couch with you and snuggle for hours! He also loves other dogs. Playing and running in the yard with his buddies brings out the puppy in him! He deserves a home with someone who has the time to give him all the love that he craves and I know that he will be an amazing friend. I am currently located at San Antonio Pets Alive!, and I am in a foster home. By adopting me, you not only give me a new leash on life; you also save the life of the additional dog who can be rescued from euthanasia and placed in foster care. name: Penny Lane
description:
Penny Lane was named through ABR’s Name-A-Boxer program to honor a dear friend, a very fitting tribute for a dog loving friend. This little bundle of fawn energy is about 2, maybe 3 years old but still acts like a puppy. At about 40 pounds she’s tiny for a female and even though her broken front leg never healed quite right, she’s game for whatever comes her way. 

Penny Lane lives with a couple older kids and regularly entertains her neighbor preschooler. She is dog friendly but needs a little time to get to know them first. She is good with her host male Boxer but we don’t know how she is with cats. Once she knows her fur buddies it’s playtime! Penny Lane is house, crate and leash trained and short walks are fine but she tires on longer walks. Penny is a bit shy with strangers but her fur buddies show her the way so she would do best with a fur buddie or two.  

Penny Lane is a kisser once she gets to know you and be sure she’s safe. She is heartworm positive but routine medication that she has been on for 9 months can take care of that and ABR will help with treatment. She loves her people, her dog buddy, her toys and Boxer burns. So, let her add some joy and smiles to your family. It’ll only take a few minutes and she’ll be showering you with kisses.

name: Kya
description:
This little bit of brindle is new to rescue and just beginning to get her feet under her and be comfortable enough to be herself. Fortunately she has a 2 year old skin kid to read stories to her, pet her and snuggle up all safe and warm. Kya is 5 years old with just a touch of gray on her muzzle. She is heartworm positive, as many rescues are, but treatment need not be difficult with ABR’s help. She is, as all ABR rescues, taking monthly medication to prevent additional heartworms.

Kya lives with 3 other Boxers and a Chiweenie and they all get along. She’s still a little hesitant to go into the backyard alone, but her love of a sunbath and a stroll around the yard with the oldest Boxer host help her overcome that.  She loves a good rub and grunts her approval for things she likes. Kya is house trained.

This gentle little girl needs a patient, loving family to help continue her healing. It takes time, structure, love and reassurance to help her learn to trust again so she can blossom into the beautiful, sweet girl she is. It’s normal for her to be a little cautious as she makes all the adjustments in her new life. Are you ready to guide her in exchange for grunts, snuggles, smiles and loyalty?

name: Tavish- DFW AREA
description:
If you’re looking for a very loving, calm IG in his middle years, Tavish is your lad. Tavi (also known as Butterbean) is a charmer and whip-smart. He already knows many commands/words and learns more as his foster mom teaches him.

Tavi loves a routine and finds it comforting to know what’s happening (and when) as regards to walks, potty breaks and feeding. This is partly the breed and also due to his blindness, caused by cataracts. 

Please don’t think of Tavi as a “special needs” dog; his foster mom believes he has been blind for quite awhile, since he’s very comfortable with his sight loss. He gets to know his home pretty quickly to make his way around and will zero in on your location when you say, “come” and clap hands. He’s just a regular dog who happens to be blind.

Tavish is low energy indoors and sleeps quite a bit. He’s been living in a condominium with his foster mom and is content to sleep in his little bed beside her desk at home during the day with a potty break in early afternoon. (He has also gone to the office with his vacation foster mom and she says he did great there.) He sleeps in his crate/pen at night for 8+ hours. If you’re gone for a few hours during the day, he’s content to be crated as well.

Outdoors, Tavish is always on a lead and is well-behaved. He loves to walk in the morning after breakfast and again in the early evening for 20-30 minutes. His long legs can keep up with you and being blind, he never bolts. He has a cold weather coat and a rain coat, loves to wear them and isn’t afraid of a bit of weather. Tavi is very comfortable with all of the dogs at the park and in the condo community and their owners remark on how calm Tavish stays around other dogs. Rambunctious puppies who jump on him make Tavi a bit grouchy but he has good boundaries and lets them know to back off. 

He travels well in a car, going to outdoor cafés and happy hour and isn’t bothered by noise like music or cars. He’s traveled on a road trip with his foster family, stayed in a hotel for a week and was a perfect guest.

His teeth were extracted at intake, but he eats small kibble very well. He has been eating a low-fat, high-calorie kibble for several months and is in great health with the softest coat.

Tavish has transformed from a malnourished, frightened dog to a beautiful, healthy boy with a sweet personality. He is easy to care for and bonds well to a loving person. He loves to sit beside you on the sofa with his blanket and snooze while you read or watch TV. He’ll be a charming companion beside you for years to come.
special_needs_notes: No medical issues. Blindness due to cataracts but my foster mom thinks I must have been blind for quite some time because I'm comfortable with the blindness; it's not a big deal to me.

description: Hey, humans! Echo here. How's it hanging? Well, a little about me: I\u2019m only a year old and pretty new to this place. I\u2019m into walks, humans, and other doggos. I\u2019m neither an extrovert nor an introvert. I\u2019m what they call an "ambivert." Yup, you guessed it, I took a personality quiz online! I\u2019m shy at first and warm up quickly. Plus, not to toot my own horn or anything, but people keep saying I\u2019m sweet as apple pie -- which just so happens to be my favorite pie in the WHOLE WIDE WAGGIN' world!\n\nIf you\u2019d like to have some fun with me -- or simply chillax in the summer heat -- contact the City Of Taylor, Texas Animal Shelter at 512-352-5483 for more information.

name: Brad
description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Hi guys. My name is Brad. I came to A Doggie 4 You on March 17, 2018. I was born late January or early February 2018. I was so excited. Didn't like all the shots very much. But we had toys and all the food we could eat. We were so excited.

On March 18th I broke with Parvo and felt really bad. I didn't think I was going to make it. They took me and my siblings to something called a hospital. They made me feel all better.

I went home and had to stay in something called quarantine. When I finally got to go to adoptions and find my family I kept hearing people say I was too old. I don't understand. I am not even a year old.

My foster mom says there is a family out there looking for me. Are you that family?

name: Dodger
description:
Up for adoption in Texas and New England:  Dodger. 





This cute pup has a message for you:





"Hi friends!  I'm Dodger and am an energetic and fun 7 month old Lab-mix.   I currently weigh about 55 lbs and I still have some growing to do.   





I love to play with all of the dogs in my foster home.  I have a ton of energy, so a doggie friend in my new home would be nice with a large place to run and play.  I am too energetic for cats and small children.  In fact, small kids make me nervous, and I tend to get grumbly, so I need to go to a home where there are none.  I am shy when I first meet someone new, but I do warm up pretty quickly.  





My favorite things are Nylabone chew toys and squeaky toys.  I also occasionally will fetch a tennis ball.  But wrestling with my doggie siblings is my favorite.   





When inside, I like to just chill on my dog bed or hang out in my crate.  I am crate trained, house trained, up to date on vaccines, microchipped and neutered.  I walk well on a leash and ride quietly in the car.  





I really would love a home of my own with an active family who will take me on walks or on fun adventures.  Is that with ?you?"





This beautiful boy is neutered, vaccinated and microchipped. 





Apply at www.luckylabrescue.com

name: Toro
description: Toro is a real dog's dog. He loves to run and jump and sniff and swim and fetch and do all of the wonderful things dogs do. If you are looking to get the most out of all the things Austin has to offer, Toro would be an excellent wing man. Toro gets along well with most of the other dogs in playgroup and is friendly with new people. He's house-trained, knows sit and is very attentive to everything happening around him. He gives that classic inquisitive head tilt to let you know he is really paying attention. He can be a bit amped when he is first let out of his kennel, because as you can imagine, he doesn't care to be cooped up. Once he gets some time to stretch his legs, he settles into a more medium pace. And he's got a sensitive side and isn't above leaning into you for some pets and loving. The ideal home for Toro would be one with a yard he could chase down lizards in and perhaps another well-matched canine companion to pal around with. Toro has been thriving in APA!'s Total Obedience Program and recently became TOP Dog Ready, which means he has already learned all the skills in his customized training plan. The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP Dog, Toro works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him become the best dog he can be! Dogs in the program learn skills including sit and down, walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers, calmly walking past another dog, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'Place', which means he will go to a specific place in your home on command. Toro has worked hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with him after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 Toro is for the true dog people out there. Those who appreciate man's best friend in their full water-splashing, stick-fetching, squirrel-chasing glory. If that's you, you should definitely meet him!
label: not-adopted

name: Reno
description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.I am Reno and I don't understand why they have to take my picture. Jeez.

On March 17, 2018 my whole world changed. You see, we were owned by an older gentleman who kinda was like the old lady and the shoe, but instead of kids, he had us dogs. We were allowed to run loose and we kinda populated the neighborhood.

He had 21 of us stashed at his house when he got sick and had to go to the hospital. He thought his son would take care of us, but he didn't. Lucky for us the mailman realized we were on our own without food or water. The nice people from the Waco shelter came and rescued us.

We were very scared and didn't act very nice. They were very concerned and knew we needed help adjusting to our new situation. They called the girls at the ranch and they came in this big bus and got us. All of us. No one was left behind. We were terrified, but very greatful to stay together during the transition. Then we got home and realized we had food and toys, Wow.

I take a little longer to get to know, but I really like attention. I am very loving to the people at the ranch who take care of me. I like treats and will be your best bud if you give me treats. I need a special family with people that will give me time to be the great dog I am. I am very smart and agile.

I'd love to find a forever home, so why don't you fill out an application for me today?

name: Daisy Flower JuM
description:
My name is Daisy Flower, the volunteer added the middle name Flower because there is another dog named Daisy, you should check her out, she is wearing a blue flower hat.  I am not wearing any hats, unless you count the metafurical hats that I will wear once you adopt me I will wear the hat of your bfff (best furry friend furrever), your therapist, life coach, ball coach, coach potato, muttivational speaker, kissing bandit (is that a hat or a mask for that one?).

I am a silly goofy gal who loves everybuddy and everything, so really in the realm of dogs, I am fairly bleh…no issues, no aggression to word smith, no sugar coating of unwanted behaviors, I am an ordinary good girl. Just a good dog, down on her luck in the big city of San Antone, looking to move on up to the big leagues.

My age is a bit of a question mark, they think I have the vitality of a 1 year old, but the yellow on my teeth says I might be 3 or 4 years, or….I have a major coffee drinking problem. I enjoy to play with dogs that are big, small, or in between size like me, I am about 40 lbs, but could stand to gain a bit.  I am still waiting for the fur on my ears to grow back after a run in with fleas and ticks.  They are gone now. 

 I love to run, play and wrestle with friends in the pasture. I might just be an ordinary Shepherd mix named Daisy, but I plan to add extra-ordinary LOVE to your life.

GOD'S DOGS Rescue, in San Antonio TX, does not have a shelter - ALL of our dogs are raised in foster homes in the San Antonio area. Each dog comes spayed or neutered, up-to-date on vaccinations that are appropriate for their age, microchipped, heartworm tested and on current on monthly flea/tick and heartworm preventative. 

 ALL OF THIS IS INCLUDED IN THE ADOPTION FEE OF $200.00 FOR LOCAL DOGS AND $250.00 FOR PUPPIES.   ( Local is in the state of Texas)! Medical records will come with each dog at the time of adoption.

IF THIS IS AN OUT OF STATE ADOPTION, TRANSPORT TO YOU is included in the adoption fee of $400.00 for adult dogs and $500.00 for puppies. We transport all over the country!!

All our dogs are socialized and we try to provide you a good understanding of the dog’s personality. Please visit our website for more information about what we do; http://www.yourtxrescueconnection.org/. You will also find helpful information about transport, our adoption application and pictures of our all our dogs/pups looking for homes!!

 Please contact us at adoptions@godsdogsrescue.org for more information about adopting one of our dogs and puppies or fill out an adoption application at http://www.godsdogsrescue.org/adopt/adoption-application/

Thank you for wanting to adopt a rescued dog, their LIVES depend on it!

label: Bertie
column26:
THIS IS A COURTESY LISTING. ADR is not responsible for the health, temperament, behavior or placement of this dog. Listings are done at the request of the dog's owner and as an outreach and community service in hopes of finding these dogs a loving, stable forever home. Placement decisions are made solely at the discretion of the owner and not Austin Dog Rescue. Owners are required to ask for an adoption fee from adopters.

This is the information that we received from Bertie's current owner:

Bertie is a 7-year-old Boxer/Bulldog mix, and is a total sweetheart. She is a bit of a bull in a china cabinet at 85 lbs. Bertie came from a home with 5 children, and has been known to adore them, but due to her rehome she has shown a bit of aggression toward children that don't live in her home. She gets along well with other dogs, but needs a bit of time to adjust to them at first. Her behavior towards cats is unknown. Bertie is trained on the commands to sit, lay down, stay, too far (when off leash and too far away), come, leave it, kennel, bone and dinner. Bertie loves walks, playing ball, her favorite tug of war and riding in the car or golf cart.

If you are interested in meeting this sweetheart, please contact Jennifer at: japrocessing@yahoo.com

name: Dakota
description:
Please contact Jamesa (roxysrescue@yahoo.com), 713-882-2610 for more information about this pet.Dancing Husky Looking for her New HomeThis gentle girl is looking for a home where she can be your best friend. Dakota is 80 lbs and needs to walk to drop at least 15 lbs off of her. She would love to walk as she is very friendly and likes meeting new people. YES, She likes to get on her hind legs and try to dance, twirling around with a big grin on her face!!!
The vet has described her breed as mostly Husky with some Labrador Retriever mixed in and the vet puts her age at 5 years old. She has good solid teeth. There are no medical problems with her and she tested NEGATIVE on her heartworm test -- YIPPEE!!!
Dakota is up to date on her vaccination and rabies shots, she will not need anything until this time 2019, She has also been de-wormed. She is microchipped and her medical records will come with her at the time of adoption. She will need to be on monthly Heartworm Preventative and we can sell you a 6 month supply for $47 so you do not need to pay to have her tested again. Her test results will come in her medical records.
Dakota is in a foster home with 2 other big dogs, a cat and a rabbit and little kids. She gets along with everyone, she has not had 1 incident with any of them. She is low energy and will lay there and watch everyone doing their thing and she is totally fine with that. Give her a chewbone and that has made her day! I'm not too sure about her playing with toys, you'll have to speak to her foster mom about that.
Dakota would love to find her forever home. Dakota is such a sweetheart and always full of smiles but most of all she gets along with adults and children of all ages. Every night she tucks my school age boys into bed and sleeps next to them all night.
She is brownish-red in color with white paws and white face. When it's feeding time she gets very excited and loves to show it with her friendly dances. She also shows excitement when you put water inside her small pool that she plays in. Dakota enjoys playing fetch, having her belly rubbed, going for walks and loves to cuddle.
When she goes out to potty she walks the yard, sometimes lays out there to sunbath and comes back to the sliding glass door to be let in. She is completely house trained and trustworthy to be left alone without having to be crated. She is crate trained but she doesn't bother anything that is not hers.
She is house trained and will go to the back door letting you know that it is potty time. When Dakota is outside during the night she gets scared and will cry until brought inside. She is strictly an indoor family pet type of dog.
Overall, Dakota is a friendly, sweet and loving older dog who wants to share this with a good forever family.
Dakota rides good in the car, doesn't mind getting her nails done or taking a bath. Surprisingly for her breed, there is very little shedding.
Dakota would do good in an apartment because she is so calm, a non barker and just a gentle girl. She would love to have her owner human person to love her so she doesn't have to share the love.
Dakota is a great companion, she is best friends with a female German Shepherd who had to go to the vet and Dakota was sad all day until her friend came home. She is also kind of motherly with other dogs.
Please email us at roxysrescue@yahoo.com if you'd like to speak to her foster mom, set up a meet and greet for adoption or have any interest in her. Her foster mom can tell you so much more about her personality.

description: You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Let me introduce myself, I am Brock! I am a pure bred Boxer. I am about 3 yrs old. There were some people that used me for breeding. They put me in a pen with these other male dogs and they beat me up bad. It was so terrible. So they turned me in to ACS. Then this nice rescue saved me. I was so scared when I saw all these other dogs. I was so afraid they would beat me up too, that I growled and barked at the dogs especially the other boys. I am now learning that not all the other dogs are mean. I keep hearing the people say how sweet I am and how proud of me they are. They say I am a big teddy bear whatever that is. I do know I quit barking at the other dogs. I would prefer to be the only dog in the house but might get along with a large female. I would want to meet her first. I have all my vaccinations, neutered,and microchipped. I am HW negative. If you would like to fill out an application on me go to our website www.adoggie4you.org. I would really love a home of my own. If you can\u2019t adopt but would like to sponsor me, you can donate below.

name: Sebastian
description: Sebastian loves going on adventures, car rides, taking long walks, or simply being a couch potato and chilling with his person. He's sweet and playful like a puppy, but mature enough to listen quite well to directions and walks nicely on leash. He loves learning new tricks and one of his specialties is giving on-demand kisses! Sebastian is the ultimate cuddle bug and promises to let you sleep in if you'll let him share your bed! He's also content to snuggle up in a comfy crate or dog bed if that's your preference. Sebastian perfected his home skills in foster where he had a doggie foster sibling, a social female pup, who slowly taught him how to dog. Now he may be able to live with a well-matched doggy sibling. He's crate-trained and was very well-behaved in the home once he understood the rules. Squeaky toys are his absolute favorite, but Sebastian also likes sturdy chew toys, food puzzles - pretty much anything he can play with he's a big fan of. This easy-going pup loves soaking up all the pets and attention from his humans and warms up quickly to new people, revealing his wiggly side once they show him some affection. Sebastian has a ton of spunk and is eager learn what tricks you have up your sleeve, especially if treats are involved! In fact, Sebastian is such a smart pup that he's part of the Total Obedience Program. The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, he has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! He's learning skills like sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' and coming when called. Once Sebastian successfully complete all the skills on his training plan, he will be considered TOP Dog Ready! As a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with him after adoption and we can master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 Sebastian can't wait to find his special someone to take him home. Come meet this sweet pup today! You can follow Sebastian on Instagram @sebastian_the_adoptable

Meet our beautiful Daphne! Daphne is a Labrador Retriever and Rottweiler blend and is approximately 1-year-old.
Daphne was adopted as a puppy from a local shelter and raised by a family with children. At age 6-months-old, Daphne was surrendered to our rescue.
Daphne has matured into an obedient and loving dog who lives to please! She enjoys playtime with her foster brothers and sisters, splashing in her wading pool, walks around the neighborhood and area parks. Her prospective owner ideally would include Daphne in a similar active lifestyle. Daphne is house and crate trained, walks great on a leash, and sits on command. Her Labrador personality makes her super outgoing and friendly!Please understand you are commiting to providing a good home for her entire life (up to 15+ years or more) - not just until her puppy cuteness wears off. You must also be committed to housebreaking, age-appropiate enrichment and exercise, leash training, grooming needs, and positive socialization. Her adoption fee is $175. This includes her spay surgery, DhPPv vaccination, bordetella vaccination, rabies vaccination, deworming, one month of flea and heartworm preventative, microchip, leash and collar, Petco coupon book, and 30-days of pet health insurance. Please be aware that puppies, small breeds, and pure breed dogs do get adopted quickly so interested parties are encouraged to apply online at www.saspca.org. Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m. Additional questions may be directed to Anne at 210-887-8041 or abaumgartner2008@yahoo.com.

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.

Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and a 30-day trial of 24PetWatch Pet Insurance. Adopters will also receive a Petco Pet Parent Savings Books that contain:• $100s in savings plus a coupon for a free 6 lb. bag of WholeHearted dog food.• Thoughtful care tips.• Online resources and support.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

name: Boxy
description:
Boxy is a beautiful 5-6 year old flashy fawn who is a love bug to everyone she meets.  ABR was notified about her by a shelter volunteer who acted as her advocate, knowing what a tremendous dog she is.  She was surrendered to the shelter by a family who was moving out of state and didn't take her.  While her life with them was hardly ideal, she was initially very sad and it took some TLC to bring her out of her shell.   

Foxy Boxy is now living happily with two male boxers in her foster home and eager to make friends with every human she's met.   At recent fundraising events for ABR she won lots of hearts for her sweet, calm demeanor with everyone ages 15 months to 88 years.   We were especially touched at how she bonded with some teens and young adults with developmental differences -- she was so patient and gave them the love and acceptance that they deserve.  While Boxy does not currently live with children, she did live with children in her former home and clearly misses them.  She is extremely maternal which often manifests in her wanting to lick the faces of children she meets, so any potential adopters should be aware of that in case that might be startling to their child.  In terms of other dogs, Foxy Boxy needs slow introductions to feel safe with new dogs.  ABR volunteers are happy to work with potential adopters on the best way to introduce dogs.  Boxy was wary of the dogs in her foster home for the first few hours but since then it's been nothing but domestic bliss!  Boxy does fixate on cats during walks and likely would not be ideal for a home with cats. 

This lovely girl is a great choice for someone who wants the sweet loving nature of a boxer but whose life is not compatible with the needs of an active young boxer.  Perhaps that is a retired person, someone who works from home or even a family with kids who want a dog who doesn't need to be front and center.   Once she's had one short to moderate walk a day,  Foxy Boxy is happy to lounge around the house and keep watch.  She loves affection and will give as good as she gets. Her foster brothers mentored her on how to be a house pet (read: Grade A Couch Potato) and she likes lying next to them and watching the happenings of the neighborhood from the front window. Her foster mom taught her how to ring a bell at the backdoor when she needs to go outside. Her former owners had not maintained medical care but she has now been spayed and has all her shots. She tested positive for heartworms and has been on a "slow kill" method since coming to ABR so she might not need the traditional treatment.  ABR will work with Boxy's adopters to discern the best course of action and pay for treatment if that is what is best for her.

name: Achilles
description:
Achilles was rescued by his military family 4 years ago from a neighbor. His life has been pretty great so far; he’s helped raise two kids who are now a preschooler and a young teen. He’s been part of a loving family who has cared for him and kept him safe. He has returned their care and kept them safe too. But, now duty calls again and his family will not be able to fulfill their duty and continue to care for Achilles. And so, ABR will help them find a new, loving family for Achilles.

He’s about 5 years old with a gorgeous fawn coat and white bib and that champion’s stance. He is one handsome boy. He knows a lot of commands and loves to do everything his family does so leaping into the car is just the beginning of a great adventure. His teenage boy gets to go on walks with him every day. He loves to play and nap. He’s not fond of baths but he tolerates them OK. Achilles is prone to upset tummies so his diet is pretty important. His family feeds him a special diet and ABR has volunteers who are very knowledgeable about diet ready to help.

Achilles needs a new family. His family had to make the best of a difficult situation and asked ABR for help. Now ABR is asking you to help Achilles make as easy a transition as possible so his family can make their transition knowing he is safe and loved. He’s trained in raising kids, so maybe...

name: Migos
description: This handsome guy is one of our TOP dogs in training, a rockstar in our Rufftail Runners program and just an all-around fun and affectionate pup. Migos' default position is upside down, wiggling around like a goofball. He gets really excited over big plastic balls and rope toys, but also tends to make strange things his 'precious' like stumps or rocks - he will leave them if asked, but sometimes he just has a thing for that random brick laying around. Another of Migo's standout quirks is he likes to go 'grass swimming,' - he lays on the grass and scooches around on his belly to swim! He enjoys that almost as much as real-life belly rubs and he'll make fast friends with anyone willing to give them (He has a perfectly smooth belly so it's impossible to resist). Migos has a lot of energy to burn and likes to stay on the move. He loves his time on the trail, and then when he's all tuckered out, he becomes very snuggly with his friends. He also loves going to playgroup and enjoys playing with his canine buddies, and he may get along with a well-matched doggie sibling. A quick learner, Migos already knows 'sit' and 'down', he walks well on leash and is learning a bunch of new skills in APA!'s Total Obedience Program. The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Migos has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! Migos is learning skills like sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'Place', which means he will go to a specific place in your home on command. Once Migos successfully completes all the skills on his training plan, he will be considered TOP Dog Ready! Migos is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with Migos after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 Migos would be perfect for someone who likes to hike or run the trails and he'd love a yard with some grass to swim around in (Hopefully he'll leave the bricks alone). Come meet this great pup!

name: Lily
description:
Adoption applications should be filled out to expedite the process:
http://www.lilpaws-malteserescue.org/joomla/adoption/adoption-application.html

Monthly Meet & Greets 
Petco (in Leander) every 1st Saturday of the month
Pet Supplies Plus (Parmer & Mopac) every third Saturday of the month

Lily is an 8year old special needs female Yorkie, a very sweet girl who weighs about 8 pounds. She is spayed, microchipped, and current on vaccinations.  Lily did not receive adequate health care earlier in her life. In spite of her lack of care she is currently healthy. 

  An Xray shows an old hip fracture that was never treated and has caused a stiffening in her right rear leg.  Her front left leg is missing some bone (probably congenital) and she cannot use it.  

To add to her physical woes, in the past 8 months she suddenly went blind probably due to a condition called SARDS.  Even with her physical challenges, she learned to move around the house and yard at her new foster home.  She is housetrained but requires assistance to go outside.  She loves hanging out on the couch with her person.  Would you like to be Lily's hero or heroine?  This girl is a survivor but we want to see her safe and secure for the rest of her life.  It's time, she needs a forever home where she can be safe and secure forever.  She is very trusting and gives everyone kisses when she first meets you.  

Adoption Fee $300

** Please note: Due to their size, our dogs are not suitable for homes with children under 5..

We do not have a facility, all dogs are fostered in the homes of our volunteers. If you are interested in adopting a dog from Lil' Paws Maltese Rescue and other Petite Paws, please visit our website at www.lilpaws-malteserescue.org and fill out an adoption application. This is the first step in our adoption process.  Our goal is to place our dogs in safe, stable and loving homes in the Austin Metropolitan area. Thanks for looking!

Lil' Paws Maltese Rescue and other Petite Paws depends on donations to keep the dogs in our program healthy. Many health issues are taken care of before a dog leaves a rescue: spaying, neutering, immunizations, dental care, and in some cases major surgery. Because of the cost of this care, donations are essential to enable us to continue our work. If you would like to show appreciation for what we do and help us continue to do it please go to our website homepage and click the donate button. We thank you in advance for your support.
organization: Lil Paws Maltese Rescue and other Petite Paws

name: Brother
description: With his goofy charm and ridiculous amount of enthusiasm, Brother is ready to be your workout buddy, adventurer and loyal friend. Brother is looking for someone who will team up with him and explore all that Texas has to offer. His favorite activities include always wagging his tail, swimming, hiking, running in circles and playing the barking game at shadows and skateboarders going TOO fast! He's an active pup but isn't opposed to curing up and watching some Netflix (preferably with his favorite toy, Teddy), and in his downtime he excels in snuggling, licking faces\/ears and being your #1 fan! Brother doesn't chew things he shouldn't (with the expectation of paper bags, because who can resist?) and he sleeps quietly in his crate through the night. He's a smart pup and already knows 'sit,' 'stay,' 'back up,' 'lay down' and 'vacuum' (where he cleans up all the yummy snacks off the floor, except carrots, gross). Brother really seems to love learning and is thriving in APA!'s Total Obedience Program. The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Brother has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! He is learning more skills like 'leave it', walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'Place', which means he will go to a specific place in your home on command. Once he successfully completes all the skills on his training plan, Brother will be considered TOP Dog Ready! Brother is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with Brother after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 Brother is buckets of fun and will win you over with his passion for living life to the fullest. He has a ridiculous amounts of enthusiasm and more than anything is looking for a home where he can be speedy and active. If that sounds like yours, come make Brother your playmate for life! Follow Brother on Instagram @brother_atx

name: Zoey
description:
Zoey was adopted from ABR (Atlanta Boxer Rescue) 6 years ago and now ABR, Austin Boxer Rescue, is helping her family find Zoey a new family who will love and protect her like they have. Zoey’s family is a military family and this time she just can’t go where they have to go. Zoey has always live with her family and she is a very gentle, well trained sweetheart at 9 years old. She is house, crate and leash trained and can entertain herself with a chew toy for hours. She is dog friendly and is very sympathetic to adults who are not feeling well. She’s been fine with kids, but after proper greetings she’d rather go where they aren’t.

She is a very pretty fawn girl with a white muzzle and graying eyebrows. She likes car rides and people and play time of course. But mostly, she likes being part of the family, doing what they do, being nearby. She’s pretty low key, easy going, sweet and even keeled. She’d love to go with her family of course, but sometimes finding a new family can be almost as great. Zoey could fit in your family pretty easily.

name: Manning
description:
Hi, i’m Manning!  I’ve been at Missy’s Haven for about 18 months now but I don’t complain.  See I’m not very fond of others, they make me nervous.  I love my foster mommy, she gives me kisses, belly rubs, treats every day, and even hangs out with us and watches tv.  

If you want to come read to me, see if we may be a match let the wonderful people at MHCR know.  If not it’s okay, like I said they take great care of me and I even have a bunch of new friends.  

I’ve We don’t get the chance to meet, You can help by sponsoring me and all us old timers here, Monetary donations are nice but they always need used or gently used towels, rub a dub dub!  Paper towels, bleach, I love Science Diet small bites, and oh yea, those soft doggy treats.  

- - Manning - - 

If you are interested in adopting, please fill out an application, once submitted we will contact you for a meeting.  Also, we only adopt young puppies out of area once they reach 10 weeks old. name: Tyler
description: Tyler loves belly rubs, playing 24\/7 with his doggie foster sibling, taking long naps, and Kong toys. This feisty boy loves everyone, and if he can lay on them to take his naps, that makes his day! Tyler really loves snuggling with his people. Tyler also really wants your attention, so ignore him and he'll give a little bark to remind you that he's there and also may need a treat. When he gets excited, his ears flop around and he sticks his butt in the air. His foster mom says his facial expressions are to die for! His eyes are the color of amber and green and he makes you fall in love with him every time you make eye contact. Tyler loves playing with his large foster doggie sibling, and they're really good about sharing their toys. He has a lot of energy, but he gets it all out playing with his doggie buddy. And once he's all tuckered out, he's ready to crash and naps frequently throughout the day. You'll always know when Tyler's napping because he's quite the snorer. You'll also know because he'll probably be sleeping on top of you. Tyler is very well-mannered for a young pup and is making good progress on his house-training. His crate-training is also going well as long as toys and treats are part of the bargain, and he sleeps quietly through the night. Chill and playful all in one little baby, Tyler would make a wonderful addition to any number of loving homes, preferably one with a yard for him to run circles in and keep your kids entertained all day. Come meet this perfect pup!

name: Mr. Wilson
description:
Please contact Jamesa (roxysrescue@yahoo.com), 713-882-2610 for more information about this pet.Meet this fun shy guy who LOVES to play in the pool, that is his favorite toy. I know it is hot outside but I have a feeling Mr. Wilson would be playing in water if it was not hot.
If you are looking for a typical puppy with a little shyness to him then you need to meet Mr, Wilson. Give him a little time to warm up to you as he has been protected and spoiled and babied. But if you have toys and lots of toys so he can run around and try to play with all of them then Mr. Wilson is your guy. He plays gentle with his 2 sisters who are also for adoption.
Mr. Wilson's coat is medium to long, shiny and wavy and does not seem to shed, we have had him since he was 3 months old and not detected any black fur laying around. He is crate trained, sleeps in his crate with the door open.
Mr. Wilson was rescued from his pure breed black Labrador Retriever mother as she lives on the streets. He gets his smarts from her as he watches everything you do and follows you around. He is also independent and not under your feet at all times. Not a barker unless there are stranger coming, then he will run so do not expect him to protect your house, expect him to be your friend and cuddle with you.
7 months old, quiet, playful, loves people and other dogs and cats, I think that gets him a gold star! He would be great as a companion pet or your sidekick who gazes at your with his pretty eyes. Although he is an inside dog, I hope you can provide a puppy pool for him, I swear it is his favorite toys. He runs and jumps in the pool often and when the water gets dirty, he looks at you sadly until you refill it again then he is just the happiest dog.

name: Fridge
description: Don't let his name fool you because Fridge is anything but cold! When you first look at Fridge, he might seem so stoic and serious, but when he flashes that ear-to-ear grin, your heart will melt like a scoop of ice cream on a hot summer's day! This sweet boy is the perfect dog for those of us who enjoy our quiet time. He is happy to lay right under your feet while chewing on his favorite toy, offering the quiet comfort that only dogs can provide. In the home, Fridge proved to be the perfect houseguest, potty-trained and non-destructive. Give him a squeaky toy and he'll happily trot around the house like a playful puppy. During his sleepovers, he does great on his own, with minimal barking and lots of napping! In fact, his sleepover friend described him as a 'lovely, easy dog.' Fridge can be shy with new people at first, but when he leans in for a pet you know you've got a friend for life. He intuitively knows exactly what his human friends need, whether it's a kiss on the cheek, a soothing lean against your leg, or playful antics that will make you laugh. Fridge is as loyal as they come and prefers to be as close to his people as possible and likes looking into their eyes as they stroke his soft velvety fur. Fridge really seems to enjoys observing his people, and human companionship (and head pets!) are his favorite things. Oh, and tennis balls. Fridge's fetch game is on point and he has an A+ in 'Drop'. Fridge has a moderate energy level - not too lazy, not too playful. He's mastered his basic commands and is thriving in APA!'s Total Obedience Program. The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Fridge has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! Fridge is learning skills like walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' and coming when called. His greatest skill, however, is scoring bonus treats from his trainer when he flashes his trademark puppy-dog eyes. Once Fridge successfully completes all the skills on his training plan, he will be considered TOP Dog Ready! Fridge is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with Fridge after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 Fridge is a gem of a dog and he's looking for that special person to make his own. We have no doubt he will make his forever family very happy, so if you're in need of a loyal and loving best friend, come meet Fridge today!

name: Samantha Lynn
description:
Welcome to the Wonderful World of Rescue Dachshunds. Look around and read their bios. Find a few whose personality seems to fit well. Consider one of our Well Seasoned Seniors who are truly wonderful and have so much to offer. Need help finding the best fit? We'll help with that too. Please fill out an application and let’s get you all matched up with a loving new “furever’ companion and friend. You’ll find the application on the “Available Dogs” page.
NOTE:

Adoptions to Texas residents only

.

Standard Adoption Fee Adult Dog: $250 ea. Puppy Adoption Fee: $300 ea. Reduced rates for Seniors dogs (10 and up). Reduced rates for pairs (when adopted together).

Email: ddrtxinfo@gmail.com Primary Website: www.DDRTX.org
You know that feeling of instant gratitude when you know you made somebody happy? That's what you get every time you give Samantha Lynn even just a little bit of attention. When you speak to her, the tail wags. When you pet her she gives the most beautiful smile. She's that good girl you've been looking for. Her inability to see doesn't hinder her much at all. She learns her environment quickly and then nothing is in her way. Give your heart to her and she will give you her all. She will listen to you on walks, but will need your guidance for the bigger obstacles. If you have a step up to the couch she will even figure that out and join you! Intelligent, amazing, and beautiful – that is how her foster dad would describe her. Samantha gets along well with her Dachshund friend. So if you're looking for a wonderful soul look no further. Fill out that paperwork and let yourself be part of her life! Samantha Lynn is blind in the right eye and may possibly have extremely limited vision in the left. She will require some patience and assistance from time to time. She would do best in a home free of clutter and with a yard without many obstacles. She is an extremely quick learner who gets along with other dogs.
Love dachshunds and not ready to adopt or circumstances won't permit having a dog? How about being a sponsor or making a donation. Every one of our dachshunds receives excellent medical care along with day to day food, love and housing. Being non-profit, we rely on generous individuals like yourselves to help save these fur babies. You can do this specifically for one dog with the sponsor button on their webpage or a general donation on our “How To Help” page. Easy and quick through Pay Pal or your debit/credit card. You generosity is sincerely appreciated by all and is tax deductable. Need other ideas? You'll find tons of them on the How to Help tab. All contributions are tax deductable.

Diamond Dachshund Rescue of Texas is a non-profit 501(c)(3) volunteer organization with focus on rescue and adoption of pure breed Dachshunds. All dogs are fully vetted and housed on private property. Meetings are scheduled upon adoption approval. Thank you for your continued support to the rescue and shelter communities!
Opt to Adopt!

name: Puppy Gypsy
description:
Up for adoption in Texas: Puppy Gypsy. 


She is 11 weeks old and 17lbs. 





Gypsy is very happy and will run to great you.  She does like to jump but we are working on that. She is great with other dogs.  





She is medium energy and almost housebroken. She is crate trained and can go five hours without an accident. 





Gypsy is very friendly with everyone and knows her name and responds. She loves to chase you or steal her brother's toy.





Her foster family is working on the sit and down commands.





Cutest behavior: She will give you her deep bark when she is needing a little extra attention.  If I look at her right after she always is just waiting for you to pick her up.  She also loves to sleep under things so her foster mom will usually find her back end sticking out!





Gypsy is a love bug!  She loves to play and have fun but she really enjoys sitting with you on the couch or taking a nap with you!  She is very gentle in her play but is a normal puppy and loves to chew.  She enjoys stealing shoes when she thinks you are not looking.  She happily gives them up when you redirect to a toy!  





Apply at www.luckylabrescue.com

name: Rory
description:
Rory’s alias is “the heart thief.” He came from the bad part of the valley for Boxers and was hand fed for his first several weeks in his foster home. But now this handsome fawn guy is headed to a healthy 70 pounds of kisses, wiggles and play bows. He even manned a kissing booth for 8 hours and never missed a kiss. Rory figured out the dog door in 5 minutes and does not fear doing his business in the rain. He has 2 foster Boxer sisters to play with or nap with and he is at ease at whatever speed the house is moving.

Rory is about 7 years old but has the activity and curiosity of a 5 to 6 year old. He takes his human for walks and nicely explores along the way. Rory is very dog friendly and loves his humans, and now he’s discovered toys. Rory is almost completely healed from the non-contagious demodex mange he came in with, and his foster mom has him on the slow-kill method for his heartworms. He has completed the routine course of preventives for tick borne illnesses so common to the part of the valley he escaped.

Of course Rory is house, crate and leash trained and just easy to live with. He seems to know he got a chance at a good life and he’s going for it in a calm, loving, gentle way. His foster mom feeds her dogs and Rory a raw diet and she offers to take as much time as needed to explain it and it’s benefits. Like most Boxers, Rory is very social and likes to have friends around so he would do best with a fur buddy or 2. This guy is an absolute gem; calm and confident enough to make friends and let the world come to him.

name: Savannah
description:
Savannah is only 7 weeks old and will not be ready to go to her forever home until August 30. I will be spayed, microchipped, have all of my vaccinations, dewormed 3 times; I will be on monthly flea/tick preventative because you know those little critters are plentiful in Texas and my foster mom makes sure we are fresh and clean all the time.
I have a twin brother named Buster but when you look at us closely you can see the difference. I look more like my daddy and Buster has some of my mom's markings on his ears and paws, We had a sister that looked my mom but some rescue group took her before my foster mom could get back and now they won't give her back.
So my mom is a Basenji/Shepherd mix and my dad is a Hound/Shepherd mix. Dad was so sweet. Both of my parents were dumped in a bad neighborhood by their owners and they started hanging with the strays in the area that my mom feeds daily. Those strays do not want to get caught so my mom just takes care of them.
You can see my parents on Facebook Page: Roxy's K-9 Rescue under the album MOVING COMPANY PUPPIES.
My foster mom saved us from under those heavy steel beams, there were only 3 of us hanging on in the 100 degree weather. But we are happy now, we play with tennis balls that are almost bigger than us and we have BIG stuffed animals that we fight over and the toy is much bigger that both of us put together. We have a spunky survival spirit and we love being in a home. Although we miss our mom and sister.
We are not barkers, we are quiet and being spoiled and we love being held and carried around. When you get us, we will be spoiled rotten. They are trying to potty train us but we are resisting right now, I guess we'll give in to what they want us to do in about 2 weeks.
I like playing with toys but I live playing with my brother Buster best of all. And when we hear our foster mom come home, she yell for joy because we know she is going to pick us up! My personality is still developing but you can say I am independent and can keep myself company playing with things.
Right now we are at a different home and we will be going to the home of the lady who saved us and we heard she really gets puppies in shape before they go to their new home. Don't worry you will love us!!!!
Mom isn't sure if we are going to stay small since we were deprived of nutrients early in our young lives or if we'll reach the size of our parents. Our mother weighed about 40 lbs and dad weighed about 55 lbs.
Don't you want to adopt us? We are in San Antonio, Tx but they transport dogs every month across the U.S.
PLEASE VISIT OUR WEBSITE FOR MORE PICTURES: roxxysk9rescue.org or Facebook page: Roxy’s K9 Rescue

name: Polk
description: Friendly, rambunctious and very curious, Polk has a real zest for life and is ready to take on the world. He loves to try new experiences and has the most positive attitude. Polk was surrendered by his previous owners because he was kept tied up in the backyard and kept chewing through his leash. We guess it worked because now Polk is living it up at the shelter where he has human and canine friends alike and gets to go to playgroup every day. Polk loves every new person he meets and always acts like he just found his new best friend. Polk loves going on long walks, is great on leash and is very in tune with whoever's walking him. He has an exuberant play style and he thinks everything's a toy, but even if it's not, he will happily trade you for an appropriate one. A real outdoorsy pup, Polk likes getting his paws wet and sniffing all the new smells. And he's a great car passenger too - 'Adventure time?! Let's go!' An ideal day for Polk would start with a nice hike, then back home for a romp around the yard and a game of fetch, then settling down and being brushed and eating yummy treats. As much as Polk loves to run around and have fun, he's also ready to chill with his people for a quiet night in. Polk also enjoys learning new things in APA!'s Total Obedience Program. The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Polk has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! He is learning skills like sit and down, walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'Place', which means he\/she will go to a specific place in your home on command. Once Polk successfully completes all the skills on his training plan, he will be considered TOP Dog Ready! He is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with Polk after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 An all around happy dude, Polk is more than ready to be a part of family that will include them in their activities and give him a nice soft bed to sleep in (He wouldn't say no to a backyard with a kiddie pool either). In return, he promises to be your best buddy in the world. Come meet this great pup!

description:
There once was a dog named Emmett 
He was an expert at Fetch It! 
He ran and he played 
Any toy, any game 
Adopt him and you won’t regret it! 

Emmett loves toys. Limericks? Maybe not so much. ;) He’d definitely love his own family and home of his own. Emmett is an extremely friendly dog who is brimming with a truly joyful energy that will keep you laughing. Trust us, silly antics WILL ensue! If possible, Emmett loves treats even more than toys, and he enjoys showing off his smarts to earn all you’re willing to give. He’s got lots of energy to run and play, but he enjoys his people too, so we suspect he’ll make a great couch critic of your favorite binge-worthy TV show. 

Emmett is eagerly waiting for you to come take him for a stroll around the shelter so he can earn his spot as your new lucky charm. We think you’ll be the lucky ones, though, if you adopt him. Emmett has an Adoption Angel, so leave your pot of gold at home. His fee has already been paid.

name: Rosanna
description: Rosanna is a low-key lady who has plenty of love to give, and she's looking to bring her relaxed lifestyle to a lucky family. Rosanna gives kisses and likes when you talk to her. Her foster mom says she has a calming presence in the home, and that along with her excellent manners make her a joy to have around. While she does plenty of lazing around and seems happiest just sitting beside you, she also enjoys toys, playing tug of war and getting out for short walks. This friendly lady enjoys meeting new people and likes getting pets from strangers on her trips to Home Depot. Rosanna's one of those dogs everyone at the vet office loves to fuss over, and she wiggles her butt when she sees familiar faces coming. She's gotten along with dogs in the past and could go home with a well-matched doggie sibling. Rosanna is quiet in the home, fully house-trained and non-destructive when left alone. She sleeps quietly through the night on her doggie bed, she knows 'sit' and will wait patiently before you release her to go for a walk or eat her meal. She also knows 'down' and 'speak' and is an excellent car passenger. Rosanna does have some arthritis and would appreciate a home or ground floor apartment with few steps to go up and down. Loyal, affectionate, curious and friendly, Rosanna would make a wonderful addition to just about any family. Come meet this great pup!

name: Missy
description:
Up for adoption in Texas: Missy.





Missy is a very sweet girl who is about 2 years old and 50 lbs.





This girl has quite a story! The poor thing has quite a story, she was stuck in the shelter for five months, through no fault of her own.  Then Lucky Lab saved her. 





Missy has been living in a foster home and doing very well. She’s a love bug and loves, loves, loves to cuddle. She also loves the water! So if you've got a pool or a lake, she's "in!" 





We think having another dog in the home would be an ideal match for Missy, she really seems to blossom with another pooch around, she loves other dogs.  She is afraid of cats. 





Missy walks well on a leash and rides well in the car. 





We'd recommend a home with older kids and adults. 


Missy is shy at first and can even cower a bit when she meets new people, then she comes out of her shell. Loud voices and noises frighten her. 





Missy isn't a fan of going in the crate, we think it's because she was in a cage in the shelter for so long.  But once she's coaxed in with treats she does pretty well.





She is spayed, vaccinated, microchipped and housebroken.  Missy is a gem of a dog and we really want her to have an amazing home after all she's been through.  We think she's a diamond in the rough and with some love and care she will be a spunky incredible best friend! 





Apply for Missy at www.luckylabrescue.com

description: A note from Duncan's foster mom:   Duncan is a goofy, happy black lab that has some mobility issues. He has no idea that he's not your typical dog, though! He is potty trained, loves cuddles, loves playing with other dogs, enjoys chews, and is really gentle with his stuffed animal toys. The previous owner thinks he may have been kicked by a horse, leading to his mobility issues. Outside, he walks around but does flop over and is unsteady, but loves exploring the yard and has no issues going potty by himself. Inside I have wood floors, so he doesn't have a whole lot of traction so has learned to crawl around the living room. He's great with all of the foster puppies I've had and is really gentle with them. He loves napping on the couch while I'm watching TV. If you are a bit of a couch potato with no back issues, this happy, snuggly boy may be the right guy for you!

description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.My name is Rusti. I never had a name before. The lady at the ranch said I am being named after a very special dog that recently became a guardian angel for the pups. He was their first rescue.

My brother and I are very lucky. Our mommy lost her life in front of us when we were on Hwy 37 eating roadkill. We were very hungry and I guess mommy didn't realize people would not slow down.

When she got hit we were very scared, so we froze right in the middle of the highway. Lucky for us a very nice lady who rescues dogs in Corpus Christi risked her life to save us. We are very grateful to her for saving us.

We were pretty sick earlier. The dead animal we ate made us sick. The nice ladies at the ranch gave us fresh water, food and a bath. They even took off all those nasty ticks we had in our ears.

description:
We’re not called Austin Boxer Rescue by accident; even though we take the vast majority of our Boxers from high-kill shelters across Texas, we still welcome Boxers that were rescued by good samaritans. And so we welcome Bruno on his journey from forgotten to family. We know he is a very handsome flashy fawn boy who lived outside and needs to learn about life inside; but he is good with other dogs and good with kids. 

His owner taught him commands in Spanish, and fed him well as he appears to be in good shape. We don’t know his age although he appears to be fairly young, and he will be fully vetted before he is adopted. The young man who rescued him took him home where he loves to play with the family dog, but they cannot keep him and asked ABR to find him a proper family, one where he will be part of the family. Welcome Bruno, your forever family is looking for you.
