name: Manning
description: When Manning sits at your feet and looks at you with those stunning blue eyes, you can't help but be mesmerized. When he gives you his paw, he's letting you know that it's okay, he knows he's beautiful and you can be friends now. Energetic, smart and extremely playful, Manning loves rope toys and anything that bounces (the bigger the ball the better). He'll fetch but he would really prefer that you to chase him around the yard. You'll always know when it's playtime when Manning's around because you'll catch those intense blue eyes staring intently at you while he wiggles with excitement: 'Come chase me, human!'. Manning really hates it when play time is over will wait until you're just about to grab his leash, then he'll play bow and run circles around you hoping that you'll chase him again. Manning can be a little shy with new people, but the best way to break the ice is to break out a giant ball or a rope toy. If your taste in toys is that good, Manning figures you must be okay. Manning enjoys going to playgroup and hanging out with his canine friends and should do well with a well-matched doggie sibling. He'd also obviously love a yard to romp in with his favorite people. When you call his name, Manning will come right over, look up and hand you his paw. He's house-trained, knows 'sit,' and with his great eye contact and how focused he is on his person, he's doing great in APA!'s Total Obedience Program. The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Manning has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! He is learning more skills like down, walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'Place', which means he will go to a specific place in your home on command. Once he successfully completes all the skills on his training plan, he will be considered TOP Dog Ready! Manning is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with Manning after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 This spirited pup will make a wonderful companion to the right family. Come meet Manning and prepared to be dazzled!

name: Fanta
description:
Please contact Jamesa (roxysrescue@yahoo.com), 713-882-2610 for more information about this pet.Fanta is a 7 month old Labrador Retriever who is seeking her forever home. True to her Lab traits and characteristics, Fanta loves the water and can sit there and play with her toys in peace.
Fanta can be a big baby at time and just likes to lay with you and cuddle.
Fanta was part of a litter of 9 born to a stray mom on the street. We were able to save all of them except 2. Fanta loves toys and playing with her brother and sister. But her brother has bren adopted and Fanta is a bit lonely as her sister Sprite is a bit shy.

As you can see Fanta is very comfortable being a cuddle baby but she is growing so she won't be a lap dog much longer. Fanta's mother is about 50 lbs so Fanta is expected to not become bigger than that as an adult.
Included in the adoption fee of $150, she is current on all vaccinations including rabies, she has been de wormed several times, Fanta is microchipped and spayed already. Her medical records will come with her at the time of adoption.
ADOPTION FEE & APPLICATION REQUIRED

Roxy's K-9 Rescue does not have a shelter, all of our dogs are raised in foster homes. Each dog comes spay/neutered (fixed), rabies shots appropriate for their age, and dewormed twice. The dogs are up to date on vaccinations according to their age at the time of adoption. They are microchipped, heartworm tested and on monthly flea/tick and heartworm preventative. ALL OF THIS IS INCLUDED IN THE ADOPTION FEE.
Medical records will come with each dog at the time of adoption.
Our organization is run by volunteers/foster parents, please be patient to give us time to respond to your emails and/or phone calls. We will reply to you. Thank you.

name: Saturn
description: Saturn is a smart, energetic lovebug who likes to play play play! This goofy guy came into the shelter as a stray, and now he's eager to make being a beloved family dog his full time job! Saturn is basically like a big puppy, except he won't pee on the carpet or chew on your shoes. He's a great alarm clock - he wakes up every morning so happy and ready to take on the day. And he's extra cuddly in the mornings, which makes waking up that much nicer. He'll also keep you company in the bathroom and check on you in the shower to make sure you're ok. Saturn absolutely adores his people, is very affectionate with them and LOVES to cuddle. He prefers to get his ya-yas out through high energy play, so he can spend the evening curled up with you for snuggles. If you sit down, he'll crawl right into your lap and smoosh his face into your chest. He just wants to be as close to you as possible, and you'll know how relaxed he is when the snoring starts (it's loud but adorable)! Saturn has a rough and rowdy play style and generally gets along with other dogs as long as they like to play and wrestle, and he may be able to go home with a well-matched doggie sibling. He's also a total water bug and loves to play in the kiddie pool and chase water from the hose. He makes for a great trail buddy and he absolutely loves playing tug of war, but he's also happy to entertain himself with toys or sunbathe while his people are doing people things. Saturn's a smart pup too and has an adorable eagerness to please his people. He knows sit, down, and shake, he's fully house-trained, can be left home alone without getting into any trouble, is easy to bathe and great in the car. He also loves to run around and show off all the skills he's learning in APA!'s Total Obedience Program! The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Saturn has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! Saturn is learning skills like sit and down, walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'Place', which means he will go to a specific place in your home on command. Once Saturn successfully completes all the skills on his training plan, he will be considered TOP Dog Ready! Saturn is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with Saturn after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 Saturn connects so deeply with his people and can't wait to find his forever lap to rest his head in. Come meet him!
label: not-adopted

name: Bogart
description:
Bogart is still pretty new to ABR in mid September and just settling into his new environment. You see, Bogart came to us with some sight in his right eye and none in his left eye. His right eye was swollen and had to be removed, so this 2 year old guy is now learning his way around completely blind. He’s doing remarkably well considering the obstacles; he finds his way around the house and uses the dog door to go outside. He loves attention and obviously likes to be near his humans. He is not comfortable with other dogs yet but that may change as he gains confidence and finds a gentle friend.

Bogart has a fawn, almost honey, coat with a handsome black mask. He’s a quiet lap dog who gives lots of kisses and hopes for lots of pets. He is heartworm positive but treatment may not be difficult with ABR’s help. He’s a special guy waiting for a special family to guide him.

October 21 and Bogart is fitting in nicely. He loves to play “I’m gonna getcha” with a blanket, and howls in delight when his humans squeak a toy. He follows their voices and footsteps around the house and yard. He loves to be petted and talked too. What a sweet boy!
label: not-adopted

name: Humphrey
description:
I can’t speak for anyone else, but my heart just melts when I see this guy and hear his story. Humphrey is about 8 years old, around 50 pounds (on the small side for a male), with a fawn coat and white on his chest and all 4 feet, a black mask, docked tail and floppy ears, and he’s blind. Probably been blind for a while as he masters his new environments within 2 to 3 days, with patient help of course. He has a permanent smile and a permanent wink. Humphrey has about the best attitude you can imagine.

Humphrey is heartworm negative and healthy and always on the up side. His butt wiggles so hard when his foster mom gets home you just don’t know where he’ll wind up. He loves his Boxer female host, and probably ought to be with a Boxer who looks out for him, lets him follow them. Humphrey is house trained and he loves his toys that keep him entertained during the day while his foster mom works. Neither he nor his foster sister are kenneled and neither of them are destructive.

Humphrey is dog friendly, but like deaf Boxers, the introductions need to be closely supervised until the other dogs understand the difference; Humphrey’s not being rude, he just needs extra sniffs and reassurance. It’s best for Humphrey that he not live with little kids as they may not understand one another, but older kids with patience and empathy would be OK. We don’t know how he relates to cats. He sticks to his foster mom when she’s home and he could learn to stick with you too. You will never forget Humphrey once you meet him.

name: Herbert
description: With his soft fur, compact body and sweet, smooshable face, Herbert has been described as a 'stuffed animal made of velvet. At first glance he may look like a lazy dog, just sitting there without a care in the world, but then he'll bust out in zoomies, do playbows and flop over to get some belly rubs. It turns out Herbert has quite a bit of energy, though he is known to play up his low key appearance. His trainer says he's very intelligent and learns things quickly, but he may not always DO them quickly. Herbert is very affectionate once he gets to know someone, and his friends say he's always ready for cuddles and giving kisses. He's lived with dogs in the past, enjoys going to playgroup to see his doggie pals and could go home with a well-matched doggie sibling. He's also completely house and crate-trained. Herbert has proved to be an impressive scholar in APA!'s Total Obedience Program and now that he's learned all the skills in his training plan, he is TOP Dog Ready! The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. Dogs in the program learn skills including walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers, calmly walking past another dog, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'Place', which means Herbert will go to a specific place in your home on command. Herbert has worked hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with him after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 Herbert doesn't ask for much, but he'd love a home with an active person to help him get his zoomies out and continue his training. In return he'll let you smoosh that amazing face all you want. Come meet him!
label: not-adopted

name: Deegan
description:
Up for adoption in Texas and New England: Deegan.
He is about 5 years old and weighs about 35lbs. 
Deegan is very sweet with people. He is sweet, affectionate and thrives on praise. 
He is GREAT on a leash and loves walks.
Deegan already knows the commands, "sit," "down," and "shake." 
Deegan can be picky about his dog friends, so if you have another dog in your household we'd recommend a meet and greet first. 
We would not recommend Deegan be placed in a home with cats or young kids. 
We think Deegan would blossom in a loving home with lots of positive reinforcement. 
He is neutered, vaccinated, microchipped and housebroken. 
Apply at www.luckylabrescue.com

name: ENYA
description: Enya is sweet girl with lots of energy and love. She is house trained and sleeps in a crate at night and while we are gone with no problems. She enjoys playing outside with other dogs or playing fetch with balls and toys. She is a great snuggler and loves to shower others with endless kisses. She has been living in a foster home with a cat, and is highly interested in him, but doesn't hurt him. She has also been living with two other dogs and gets along great with them. Enya would do best with a family who can match her energy, but at the end of the day won't mind some couch cuddling.

name: Koba
description: Koba is a happy, smart, loving pup with an adventurous spirit and a gorgeous brindle coat. This handsome fella loves being loved on and will follow you around the house like an adorable shadow. But he isn't pushy about asking for affection - as long as he can be nearby, Koba's one happy little camper. He can be shy with new people, but once he warms up, he becomes the most loyal and loving companion. Medium to high-energy, Koba is still a youngster and likes getting plenty of exercise. He's lived with a dog in the past and enjoys mixing it up in playgroup with his canine friends at the shelter. He's a big fan of playing tug of war and fetch (with two balls though - you've got to trade him for the one he's got). He also has a goofy streak and likes jumping into empty bathtubs and will even help out with the yard work, breaking up all those big sticks. But Koba's not just a good time Charlie. He's extremely smart and well-trained, so much so that he recently became TOP Dog Ready! This means he has already learned all the skills in APA's Total Obedience Program, which is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP Dog, Koba has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to practice the skills to be the best dog he can be! Dogs in the program learn skills including sit and down, walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers, calmly walking past another dog, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'place', which means Koba will go to a specific place in your home on command. Koba has worked hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with him after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 Koba doesn't ask for much - just a home with a yard, a doggie playmate to help him get his ya-yas out and a person to call his own. If that sounds like yours, come meet this amazing pup!
label: not-adopted

name: Eli
description: Eli is really good at being a dog. He does all the dog stuff. He is truly excellent at playing fetch. He'll bring it right back to you and drop the ball right in your hand. You don't have to wrestle it out of his mouth or anything. He makes an excellent trail runner\/jogging partner. He chases cats, just a little, but what full blooded dog doesn't? He loves to get pets, he loves to sniff things, he loves to wag his tail and looks adoringly at you. He barks at the mailmen and he loves to roll in the grass outside... You know, dog stuff. Eli is good with meeting new people - he will jump up on them once or twice, then proceed to rub his butt against their knees. He likes to kiss his foster mom's face when she's laying on the couch and loves a good butt scratch. He also barks if you hug someone in front of him - he gets a little jealous and wants to be included in the love. Eli loves toys, but his favorite is his ball that he will lovingly fetch and return for HOURS. He is also a talker when he plays and will make cute growly\/whiny noises waiting for you to throw the ball or tug on the other end of his rope. Overall, he has medium energy and a few hours a day of play is enough for him. Mostly, Eli just wants to be loved and accepted. He follows his foster mom around and lays next to the shower and couch or at the entrance to the kitchen. But he is definitely a major talker. He will make noises at you as if he's trying to have a conversation. His foster mom often responds just to make him feel heard. He talks at you when he wants to play, when he's hungry, when he wants out, when he wants pets, etc. But he will quiet down if you tell him 'hush'. Eli is also very well-trained. He is house and crate-trained and knows sit, shake, come and lay down. He walks well on a leash and rarely pulls. And he has done fine with the 2 year-old staffy mix in his foster home. In fact, Eli is so well-trained, he recently became TOP Dog Ready, which means he has already learned all the skills in his training plan. The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test, and as a TOP Dog, Eli has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him become the best dog he can be! Dogs in the program learn skills like sitting calmly when approached by strangers, calmly walking past another dog, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'place', which means Eli will go to a specific place in your home on command. Eli has worked hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with him after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 Loving and playful, well-trained and goofy, Eli is going to make some lucky person very happy. If you're looking for a tiny dog you can put in your bag and take to brunch, keep looking. But if you're looking for the full dog experience, if you want to run and jump and sniff, then you can't do better then Eli. Come meet him!

name: St. Patrick
description: When you look into his eyes, St. Patrick says: 'I love you and I will protect you from all the scary things out there in the world! Also, may I have some treats?' St. Patrick is a highly affectionate and clumsy little goofball who's chock full of quirks. He'll trip over and fall off things just from the excitement of seeing you. He loves to show off to make you proud and even taught himself crawl, which is beyond adorable. He also sits side-saddle and only likes to roll over in one direction and will sit on your feet for kisses. He loves playing fetch and working on puzzle toys - any sort of work-learning seems to please him the most. He has lots of energy to burn and likes to put it to work learning and playing. Very attentive and eager to please, St. Patrick picks up new tricks in a hurry. Sometimes he's so focused on performing that he will 'sit,' 'down' and 'shake' in quick succession just to get your attention. While learning 'place,' he was so excited that he sat on the edge of the platform before he was all the way on, tried to recover, then rolled right on off. St. Patrick is learning all these new tricks in APA!'s Total Obedience Program (TOP), which is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, St. Patrick has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! He is learning skills like walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'Place', which means he will go to a specific place in your home on command. St. Patrick is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with him after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 St. Patrick's loving eyes, big smile and stellar personality are sure to win you over. He genuinely seems to thrive on the laughter and praise he gets from his people. If he had a yard to romp in and show off his skills and goofy antics, he'd be the happiest guy in the world. Come meet this amazing pup!

name: Bethany
description: Bethany is a sweet, happy, loving angel, and we think you'll fall in love with her as quickly as she falls in love with you! Bethany's tail is always wagging and she's great with meeting strangers. She's a very affectionate pup and will accept their love and pets for as long as they're willing to give them. In between asking for pets by sweetly sliding her head into your hands, Bethany enthusiastically and fearlessly explores any new environment. Don't be fooled by her grey whiskers, because Bethany still knows how to play like a puppy. She's very spunky and likes running around the yard to burn off energy and gets hilariously rowdy when she hops into bed for the night. Then she'll flop right down at the end of the bed to settle in for some sweet dreams. This is not the dog who will be in your face waking you up before the sun either; she's perfectly content to get up when you are. But when she does hear you get up, you'll be treated to the THUMP THUMP THUMP THUMP of her tail wagging against the bed. After a good play session or a long walk, Bethany is happy to entertain herself or just take a nap. She's not that interested in toys - when she's offered a tennis ball, she takes this as an offer to be loved on. But she does have one favorite stuffed toy she likes to chomp on and enjoys Kongs stuffed with treats. Smart and very trainable, Bethany LOVES treats, which makes working with her a breeze. She sits perfectly while she waits to be leashed up, she's 100% house-trained and has been left successfully in her crate. She also does well left home outside of one without getting into any trouble. She won't chew on anything but her Kong or favorite toy and doesn't get in the trash or anything that isn't hers. She does great on car rides and is just so happy for any chance to pal around with you. It's hard not to fall in love with Bethany's inquisitive, loving and joyful nature. Come meet this sweet girl!
label: not-adopted

name: Wyatt
description: This smooshy people-pleaser is more than happy to cuddle the day away with his human friends. Wyatt may be a big boy, but that doesn't stop him from climbing right into their laps to get some affection. In fact he 'sings' when he sees his favorite people coming and he is very keen on making them happy. Happy people mean cuddling and toys, and Wyatt loves all kinds - ropes, balls, squeakies, stuffies, you name it. While Wyatt's perfectly capable of keeping himself entertained if he has a toy to roll around with, he much prefers if you play tug of war with him. But Wyatt would give it all up for some pets. This boy loves intense scritchy sessions more than anything. Wyatt's a smart pup too, and he works diligently during his training sessions because he wants to be a good boy for his people. He's already mastered sit, down and recall and he's crate and house-trained! Wyatt is also thriving in APA!'s Total Obedience Program and recently became TOP Dog Ready, which means he has already learned all the skills in his training plan. The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP Dog, Wyatt has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! Dogs in the program learn skills including sit and down, walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers, calmly walking past another dog, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' and coming when called. In addition, Wyatt has also learned 'Place'. Wyatt has worked hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with Wyatt after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 Wyatt doesn't ask for much - just a home a giant sofa and a bin full of toys and humans who he can cuddle with. Come meet this sweet pup!

description: If we were putting together a yearbook, Rocky would be named \u201cBiggest Sweetheart!\u201d Rocky\u2019s foster mom says he is a first-class cuddler who loves walks, rubs and snuggles, and to play with other dogs! She says Rocky is very loyal, laid back and sometimes goofy, but he shows his smarts by aceing food-puzzle games she gives him. Rocky has shown he is very sweet with children and loves when they pet him.  If you think Rocky may be a perfect fit for your family, reach out to meet him by emailing his foster mom at sarahkantzseu@gmail.com.

name: Zucy
description: Zucy is so pretty! This sweet girl is smart, friendly, and has lived with kids and other dogs. She has been kept outdoors most of her life, so Zucy is really wishing and hoping for a new forever home where she will truly be a member of the family. She will be a wonderful friend and companion for many years to come! She's peppy and playful and ready to have fun with you.\n
label: not-adopted

name: Joel
description: Hi, I\u2019m Joel! Some of us dogs just can\u2019t get into hanging out in our kennels because we find kennels boring! I\u2019d much rather be outside where all the action is! Give me a chance to meet you outside and you\u2019ll see what a happy boy I am! I walk well on a leash and will smile for you. Sometimes I\u2019m on alert for squirrels and will scope out my surroundings. I can be charming and I love attention, especially when attention involves me receiving treats! I love treats and I learn very quickly. Once I get to know you, I might turn into a lap dog. I have to admit that I may get excitable during playtime, so it would be best that I go to a home with older children. I also get along great with dogs but I\u2019d rather hang out with the calm ones. I\u2019m ready to find my home soon! Please give me a chance to go on a stroll in the dog park with you!
label: not-adopted

name: Breeze
description: An energetic and affectionate gal with perfect perky ears, Breeze is a pup who's up for anything, and she lives to be her person's sidekick. Breeze's ideal date would be a walk or run around the park, maybe a dip in the lake (she loves water), followed by relaxing with some head scratches and snuggles. When she's not burning off energy, Breeze LOVES being close to her human, resting her head on their shoulder or chest. And if you sit on the ground with her, she'll do the same thing and push you right over. There's no such thing as too close for this sweet girl. Breeze does fine meeting strangers - she's a bit aloof with new people at first, but warms up quickly, and once you have a relationship with her, she will stick by your side forever! Breeze gets along well with her doggie pals in playgroup, likes playing chase with them and has a rowdy play style that would be a good match with a doggie sibling who likes to mix it up as much as she does. She also really enjoys rope and puzzle toys to keep her mind occupied. Breeze is fully house-trained, walks well on leash, already knows 'sit' and 'down' and comes when you call. Smart as a whip, she's very treat-motivated, eager to please and is breezing through her training in APA!'s Total Obedience Program. The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Breeze has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help her learn the skills to become the best dog she can be! Breeze is learning skills like walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free' and 'place', which means she will go to a specific place in your home on command. Once Breeze successfully completes all the skills on her training plan, she will be considered TOP Dog Ready! Breeze is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with her after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 Breeze would love a home with active people who will include her in their adventures and ideally a doggie playmate to help get all that energy out. She can't wait to start playing and bonding with her forever family. Come meet her!

name: Boomer
description:
Shy and delightful, and easy to walk on a leash is our Boomer! At four years old he is past the puppy crazies and in his Prime! This extra-large guy has a gorgeous chestnut coat and is a mixed breed.

Boomer is neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, tested negative for heartworm and is on heartworm prevention. All our animals must be indoor pets. Dogs are very social animals; there's really no such thing as a "good outdoor dog".

name: Shasta
description:
Shasta is a 5-6 year old dog from animal control in El Campo. She is spayed/vaccinated/microchipped.  Shasta is a terrier mix and weighs 28 pounds.
She has a mast cell tumor on her back leg. There is not enough skin to remove the tumor and close the surgical wound. Shasta is on Benadryl twice a day to slow the spread of the cancer.
She also has heartworms.  We are doing the “slow kill” treatment: Heartgard every month and Doxycycline, an antibiotic, every six months as long as she is positive.
Shasta is very food/toy/territory possessive so needs to be an only dog.
Yes, she has issues, but she’s a fun dog for a person or couple that can give her a good life for as long as possible.
For adoption information please call Cheryl at 979-732-5591.  Shasta's adoption fee is $75.00.

name: Miguelito
description: Miguelito was rescued from a hoarding situation and he's still trying to figure this beloved family dog thing out. Miguelito has a very distinctive look to him with his big radar ears and long legs that make him look more like a fawn than a dog, and he has the same bashful, delicate personality. He likes having his crate as a safe space, and during the day he roams the house and follows his foster mom from room to room. If he loses sight of her he'll bark to say 'Mom! Where you at?' He likes to sit in the chair next to her for brushing and pets and 'cookies'. He is turning into very much a lap dog and has also learned to play and has a favorite stuffed animal that he carries around everywhere with him like it's his baby. Miguelito is very a low maintenance guy and smart too. He already knows 'crate', 'no' and 'quiet', is working on 'come' and 'out', and he's really good at 'cookie' and 'treat'. He's making excellent progress on his house-training and has proven to be a good watch dog and barks when anyone is at door or in the yard. Miguelito will make a wonderful addition to a household that's looking for a sweet and gentle companion. Come meet him!

name: MERLIN
description: Merlin says Let's get out of here and make some memories!. This spritely senior boy is housetrained, knows sit\/stay\/down and loves treats! He's ready to go running, play fetch, take a dip in the creek, then lounge at your feet until you're ready to do it all again. And he's super photogenic!   Merlin got to go to foster for a weekend and came back with this report: Merlin is very eager to please. He is smart and well behaved. Come visit Merlin or email caring@classiccanines.org for more information.

name: Hope
description: UPDATE: Hope is doing really well. She will do best in a home without other dogs or small children. Because she is blind, she can be frightened by too much commotion or noise and she's not able to tell when another dog just wants to play, or not. Hope is a female, 2-year old Labrador Retriever blend. She is a complete sweetheart! She is great with other dogs and loves to play with them and loves her toys too. Hope was saved from euthanasia at the city shelter by San Antonio Pets Alive. Hope had been shot and had a severely injured hip. She was also malnourished. She went to a San Antonio Pets Alive foster home to gain needed weight. Once her bloodwork improved, along with gaining 15 lbs and energy, the veterinarian cleared Hope for surgery. She underwent a Femoral Head Ostectomy (FHO) - an orthopedic surgical procedure that helps restore pain-free mobility to her damaged hip due to the bullet that was found. She is recovering wonderfully and now looking for her forever home! Updates from her foster home: - She is a great eater and doesn't bark- she's a quiet one :) - She has learned to walk on a lead well, and she loves sleeping on her bed or in the sunshine - Her sight is not restored, but she does follow hand claps and comes when her name is called- very well! - She is housebroken and enjoys relaxing in her kennel. - She gets along great with the dogs in her foster home and would do wonderful with a "guide" dog friend of her own! I am currently located in a San Antonio Pets Alive! foster home. By adopting me, you not only give me a new leash on life; you also save the life of an additional pet who can be rescued from euthanasia and placed in foster care. If you are interested in adopting me, please email adopt@sanantoniopetsalive.org with my name and ID#. Please allow up to 24 hours to respond, as all fosters work on a volunteer basis. To find out how you can get involved and help turn San Antonio into a no-kill city, please visit www.sanantoniopetsalive.org

name: Jackie
description: Jackie has been an amazing foster dog. She's very social, does great with kids, adults, and other dogs. Jackie does like to rough play and can sometimes be a little too rough but listens well when is told to be gentle. She vibes well with her human. She does jump a little but she it very tender when she does. Small dogs tend to be a little scared of how forward she is but once she understands not to play rough with one she won't both doing it again. I've taken here on hikes, runs and dog parks are her favorite. She loves meeting new dogs and gets a little anxious when she doesn't get to greet them. So far I haven't had a chance to socialize her with house cats but she does bark and chase neighborhood cats if they come in to our yard. Jackie definitely loves the outdoors and being out of the house and enjoying nature is her calling. I am currently located in a San Antonio Pets Alive! foster home. By adopting me, you not only give me a new leash on life; you also save the life of an additional pet who can be rescued from euthanasia and placed in foster care. name: Spoodoo
description: Spoodoo is a speedy boy! He loves doing zoomies, then will sprawl out on the ground, pop up and zoom again! After he gets the zoomies out of his system, Spoodoo likes to come hang out with his friends, leaning in for pets petting and ear scratches and getting some nice quality snuggle time in while his humans enjoys that beautiful smooshy face. Spoodoo is getting along nicely in playgroup with his dog buddies at the shelter and we think he could go home with a well-matched doggie sibling. He's also reported to have done great with the resident cat in a previous foster home. Spoodoo loves playing with rope toys and especially enjoys scent games. He's a smart pup too and is eager to please his people. He's already house and crate-trained and is learning all kinds of great skills in APA!'s Total Obedience Program. The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Spoodoo has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! Spoodoo is learning skills like sit and down, walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'Place', which means he will go to a specific place in your home on command. Once he successfully completes all the skills on his training plan, Spoodoo will be considered TOP Dog Ready! Spoodoo is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with him after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 Spunky, cuddly, silly and just an all around fun pup, Spoodoo is more than ready to move to a forever home where he can get all the love he so deserves. Come meet this sweet guy!

name: Sadi
description: Sadi is a well-behaved and happy girl who likes to be where her humans or canine friends are, following them around the house to see what everybody's up to. Sadi seeks out attention but is always polite about it. She excitedly accepts pets when offered and will climb into her foster dad's lap when invited. While Sadi can be very playful and prances adorably when she gets excited, she overall has a pretty medium energy level. Sadi gets along beautifully with the resident 75 lb pittie mix - they love to roughhouse or just follow each other around the house or yard. There's also a beagle in her foster home, but she told Sadi to leave her alone and Sadi's happy to oblige, because that's the kind of girl Sadi is. She just wants everybody to be happy. It's no surprise that Sadi has excellent manners in the home - she's house-trained, knows 'sit' and 'no' and does wonderfully in her crate and will go right in when you say 'kennel'. If there's no room on the couch for Sadi because it's full of people and beagles, she's happy to go chill in her crate until a spot opens up. If allowed on the bed, she'll stay out of your way, sleeping politely at the foot of it, but she'll also sleep through the night in her crate without any fuss. Sadi can be a little shy with new people, but she warms up quickly because Sadi really loves humans. She gives gentle kisses, and if you say 'kiss kiss', Sadi is happy to oblige. She'll lay her head in your lap to ask for pets, but she isn't pushy about seeking out affection - as long as she can be close to her people, she's a happy girl. Sadi also LOVES going for walks and would thrive with a family that will include her in their adventures. Throw in a doggie companion and a backyard to romp around in and Sadi's the happiest pup in the world. If you're looking for a loving companion for the entire family, come meet sweet Sadi!

He exhibits Alpha Male behavior and therefore must be the only animal in the household (spayed female dogs may be ok). 
HE IS NOT A DOG PARK KIND OF DOG!
He does have a chase instinct so I recomnend a leash at all times when outdoors. I am no longer able to provide for his needs. I am disabled and physically am unable. He will remain with me until a satisfactory home meeting his needs is found. 
If interested in this sweet boy Pls call me, Jenna, at (217)714-3914 with questions. I may also be reached by email: txscorpio79@yahoo.com

name: Josie
description:
Please contact JoEllen (sagdinfo@aol.com) for more information about this pet.Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

Josie is a super sweet little 1 yr old Min Pin / Doxie mix that loves everyone! She is one of her foster mom’s favorite pups, because she gets along so well with everyone and is just so easy going. Josie is spayed, current on all vaccinations, microchipped and housebroken with the aid of the dog door.

Josie’s adoption fee is $150 and an online application can be completed at www.saspca.com.

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.

Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and a 30-day trial of 24PetWatch Pet Insurance. Adopters will also receive a Petco Pet Parent Savings Books that contain:• $100s in savings plus a coupon for a free 6 lb. bag of WholeHearted dog food.• Thoughtful care tips.• Online resources and support.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved and you are traveling from out-of-town, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time.

We do try to schedule bi-monthly meet-and-greets in Austin as interested is generated.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

name: Stella
description:
Stella is a tall 5 year old, 60 pound female with a fawn coat and white flash on her face, chest and paws. She is quite the looker. She is heartworm negative and healthy. Stella currently lives with a foster mom and her dogs, and after slow introductions, she does well with all. ABR always encourages slow, supervised introductions for new dogs into new settings, allowing them time to observe and learn the surroundings, hierarchy, rules and rhythms of their new home from the safety of their crate.

Stella is a lover with her people and will snuggle whenever possible. She loves to play and loves her walks, but like many rescued dogs, she is currently leash reactive. Consistent redirection, reassurance, and appropriate reaction (like moving to the other side of the street, retreating to a lawn so Stella can sit while the other dogs pass, offering a treat each time Stella looks to her handler rather than the other dog…) will gradually help her gain confidence and trust in her handler. She does well at home with her fur friends.

Stella is house, crate and leash trained and sweet and loving at home. I’ll add a personal note: my personal dog has been leash reactive for all of his 12 years; much less so now he’s a terrific loose-leash walker. He has also welcomed 42 Boxers in to his pack to foster and mentor, play and snuggle with. Each dog has a comfort zone we just need to help them find.
label: not-adopted

name: Bulldozer
description:
Bulldozer is a terrific name for a terrific guy who plows ahead regardless of the obstacles. He is a flashy brindle male about 4 years old. He is one handsome guy.
He has been in a foster home with Boxers and small dogs and they all run the fence together, just in case something is there. Bulldozer keeps up easily even though his back left leg has atrophied due to a neurological issue. No problem for him.

Bulldozer is a small male who is cute, cute, cute. He’s healthy and not in any pain. He is heartworm positive, but that doesn’t interfere with his activities, and it need not be a difficult treatment with ABR’s help. The sweet, polite little guy is house, crate and leash trained; and he doesn’t mind sharing the couch.

Unfortunately, Bulldozer’s house includes cats; and he’s easily fast enough to catch them. So, he really needs a forever family, or a foster family until his forever finds him. It’s best for him to have a fur buddy to keep him active and not be crated so he can exercise his working leg as much as possible. He’s not into mischief, he really loves his people, and he needs someone special, without cats.
label: not-adopted

name: Chickadee
description:
Chickadee is a lady who’s been around the block and checks to make sure who is in charge, just in case she needs to pick up the slack as usual. She’s about 7 now and a bit thin from her travails, but life hasn’t slowed her down much; at least not much more than anyone else with her experience. She’s gaining the weight back in her foster home, and she’s already checked out her male Boxer host, just in case he’s not up to the task of keeping things in order. So far, so good.

Chickadee is heartworm positive but ABR always helps with treatment and can explain the options. It doesn’t seem to bother her at all. As you might imagine, Chickadee is not a high energy gal now, she’d like to play some, nap some, lay in the sun a bit and get a few pets. She usually sleeps with her stuffed animal toy. She is house and crate trained and does fine with other dogs, especially if they pass the test of “who’s in charge”. Chickadee is not OK with cats and we do not know how she relates to kids.

Chickadee still has lots of walks and play time, naps and sun baths on her dance card. She’d probably be happy to teach a young boy about being in charge, you know, for when she can’t anymore.

I had heartworms when I first came into HSNBA but my friends sent me to a sleepover for a while until the doctor said they were all gone! Now I am heartworm free and SO ready to find a friend to play with. I don't like cats very much but I would still be the best cuddle buddy around. If you are interested in meeting me come on by HSNBA and see if I would be perfect for YOU!HSNBA lists all animals online from the moment of intake, and our listings are updated automatically every midnight. name: TAWNY
description: What is happiness? Happiness surely is a loving, devoted, doggy pal to join you on this crazy journey we call life. Meet Tawny - the prettiest girl to walk this earth and one pooch you are going to want to have by your side. Tawny is an absolute treasure with a sweet, lovable personality. She is young at only ~ 2 years old and has a beautiful light fawn coat that sparkles. She may be Labrador Retriever mixed with something smaller like Australian Cattle Dog or terrier. She is nearly pint-sized, weighing only ~ 41lbs on a fat day.  Tawny currently lives with dogs of all sizes in her foster home and she loves them all, sometimes even climbing into a crate with her best doggy pals to take a nap. (She does seem a little too interested in the cats around her foster home to live with cats.) Because she is a proper lady, Tawny is already crate-trained, she knows how to sit on command, and she likes going for car rides. She has a very good nose and loves to sniff around to discover new things. This girl is beauty, brains, and grace all wrapped into one gorgeous package. Tawny enjoys the wide open spaces at her foster home and will run around with pure joy in her heart. You can\u2019t help but smile. But, she also enjoys couch time and won\u2019t hesitate to climb into your lap for pets and affection. Tawny\u2019s other favorite things include sleeping like a human with her head on her own pillow, laying on the floor with her legs spread out like a frog, and telling you about her day. She is a world-class dog.  Likes: friendly wrestling with other dogs, grandpas who always have the good treats, being a free spirit  Dislikes: when people forget to refill the ice tray, zombies, TV finales that are \u2018to be continued\u2026'  Tawny is only $50 to adopt. Adoption includes spay, current vaccination, and microchip. Give us a call to meet her!

name: Maggie
description: Meet Maggie. That's her sister in the picture with her - they were abandon at a local business in the middle of the night. In the morning the business owners fed them and gave them water, then called us. The girls were timid but welcomed the kind touch and have come out of their shell nicely. They were full of intestinal parasites and very thin but never stopped wagging their tails. Maggie is very playful, love toys, love giving kisses, is smart and likes getting a good belly rub. The girls are crate trained, know sit and definitely love dinner time. Both girls are so affectionate. Either Cassie and\/or Maggie would make a great addition to the family.

name: Chico
description: Chico is a chill and loving pup with the sweetest face and softest fur. He's one of those dogs that seems exists just to make your life better, and he's comically low maintenance. His energy level is described as 'low low low', he doesn't need a lot of attention and has amazing manners in the home. He's fully house-trained, does just fine alone and will happily chew on his Kong in his crate while you're at work. Chico's so low key that he doesn't even bark at the doorbell, although he's always happy to see who's on the other side. He's quick to curl up next to new people, and if they come bearing treats, they have a friend for life! Chico LOVES treats and takes them very gently, and he shows people how much he loves them by giving gentle kisses. His calm and cheerful demeanor would probably make him a good companion to children as well. There's not a lot of toy playing going on with Chico, but this boy definitely likes his naps. If Chico had a favorite activity it's probably stretching out on the couch for belly rubs. He sleeps quietly through the night on his bed or the couch, and while he isn't a fan of getting up in the morning, he'll begrudgingly get up, eat some breakfast, then go back to bed. As lazy as he is most of the time, Chico is always up for taking long leisurely walks where he can stop and sniff the roses. Despite his chill demeanor, Chico is eager to please his people. This sweet guy adores home life and really just wants one that's willing to love on him and show him he's a part of the family. In return, he promises to love you forever. Come meet this beautiful couch potato!

name: Emma Rose - Austin
description:
I'm a chill girl just looking for someone to snuggle with. I love laying outside in the grass just soaking up the sun and am very comfortable with using a supervised doggie door.  I walk very well on a leash and enjoy going for walk.

I'm patient with my hyper foster sister and have never had a single issue with food aggression, even when foster sister tries to steal my treats! 

I bark but only occasionally and only when startled by the mail man or after other dogs have been barking for a while. I stop quickly with redirection.

I am available for inquiry but won't be available for adoption until after October 15.

I am currently symptom free.  The vet found a mass during a routine visit.  She is expected to have a good quality of life for at least the coming year if not longer.

name: Dallas Maverick
description:
Up for adoption in Texas: Dallas Maverick. 





This boy is literally too good to be true! Sweet, adorable Maverick is about 1 year old and 55 lbs.





Dallas Maverick has a very sweet demeanor and loves people and other dogs.  He hasn't been around cats in his foster home. 





He is a very happy boy and loves attention from everyone.  In fact, he will nudge his nose under your arm when he wants you to pet him.  





He loves to play fetch and has wonderful recall.  He is great on the leash and loves going for walks.  He does pull a little when he sees other dogs because he gets excited and wants to meet them.  





He knows "sit" and "down" and is currently trying to master "stay".  Dallas Maverick is not fond of the crate, so his foster does not crate him.  He is trustworthy in the house and displays no negative behaviors when left out of the crate.  His foster reports that he is a great dog.  





He is up to date on routine vaccines, is neutered, housetrained. microchipped, heartworm negative and ready for his forever home.   





Apply at www.luckylabrescue.com

name: Czar
description:
This handsome, energetic guy is looking for his forever home! His name is Czar and he’s probably about a year old. Our guess is he’s a lab, pit bull terrier and possibly some Rottweiler blend.

Czar is an active boy and love all kinds of toys. He likes to be cuddled but is also eager to play and explore. He would make a good running/hiking/adventure buddy. He loves to be with his foster mom and insists he must lay rightnexttoher when they’re watching TV.

He would do well as an only dog or in a home with another female dog his size that is also high energy. He’s currently in a foster home with several other dogs but no cats, so not sure how he is with them. He doesn’t get along with other male dogs or dominate females. He'll need a secure fenced-in yard over 4 feet high to help run out his energy. He’s fully housebroken and is food motivated so training is easy. He’s very intelligent and a fast learner.

If you are interested in adopting Czar, please contact Lytle Animal Allies at lytleanimalallies@yahoo.com for more info.

name: SANDRA
description: Once every now and then a dog comes along who just completely wows you. Totally stops you in your tracks. That dog is Sandra.   Sandra is simply lovely and we don't know any other way to say it. You have to meet this dog in person to experience her true awesomeness. She is a 5-star dog who lights up rooms with her calm, easy-going temperament. Someone surely told Sandra it was her duty in life to make people happy and she does this very well. Sandra has been EXCELLENT with kids and currently lives and does fantastic with cats and other dogs. Because she is a proper lady, she is leash-trained, house-trained, knows how to SIT on command, and is quickly learning other commands. Sandra is eager to please and has a nice, pleasant, lower energy level that will match almost any home. She would love to accompany you on an easy-going walk but is just as happy to crash with you on the sofa with some snacks (but, watch out, she may steal your spot).   Likes:  Stuffed animal toys, snoring, cuddling with her foster dad. Dislikes: Folding laundry, cold feet, pyramid schemes.  This girl is exceptional. We know there is a family or individual out there with a Sandra-shaped hole in their heart - is it yours? Sandra is only $50 to adopt. She is spayed, current on vaccinations, and microchipped. If you are thinking Sandra sounds like the dog you've been searching for a very long time to find, please contact us to meet her!

name: Starling and Rex
description:
Up for adoption in Texas and New England: An amazing bonded pair: Rex and Starling. They love one another and want a home where they can be adopted together and bestow love on YOU! 



We will tell you about each dog: 



Starling


Gender: Female


Breed: Black Lab Mix


Age: 5 Years Old 


Weight:  45 LBS



Starling (Star Bar, Ling-Ling, Bruce Lingstein or Agent Starling as she is known) is a very sweet and well behaved girl.  She loves to get pets and is a very gentle soul.  



She isn't a high energy dog, but will sometimes get a little wild hair and stand on her hind legs like a circus elephant.  It is really cute and something that will crack you up the first time you see it.  



She is so low maintenance that her fosters often forget she is home until she walks up and presses her nose into their hand asking for attention.  You can usually find her curled up by their feet or at the foot of their bed. She is a super easy going dog and just wants to be loved.  She will make a great pet for a family who can give her the love and attention she deserves.



Starling is very gentle when taking food by hand, and obeys all commands to sit, lay down and  shake.  She also knows “levanta te” which is the command to stand up. She is very sweet to the foster's dog and will often give kisses to her “brother” and her foster brother dog.  She is not aggressive in any way.

Cats are unknown. 

She loves walks.

Starling is very well behaved when home alone.  Both fosters work outside of the home, and there have been no accidents or other behavioral issues while they are away.

So far she has been great with everyone.  There is not a mean bone in her body.  She is a little shy at first, but warms quickly to those who give her love. She will respond well to a little light play.  Likes to get belly rubs.



She is an allstar on a leash but squirrels are of keen interest to her, so you may want to tighten your grip if she sees one.



She is VERY obedient.  She listens very well.  She knows sit, stay, shake, down, etc.  She is extremely gentle when taking treats of food from hands.



She is adorable.  Starling loves human attention.  Starling will stand on her back legs and put her front paws up like she is reaching out for a hug.  It is so funny and cute.  She is also a great cuddle buddy.





Name of Dog: Rex


Gender: Male


Breed: Black Lab Mix


Age: Apx 7 Years Old 



Weight:  55 LBS


Rex (Mr. Rex, Rexus-Plexus, Plaxico Burres or T-Rex) is a very sweet and well behaved boy.  He loves to get pets and is a very gentle soul. He isn't a high energy dog, but will sometimes catch a glimpse of his tail and give it a good chase.  It is really cute and something that will crack you up the first time you see it.  He is so low maintenance that his fosters often forget he is around until he walks up and lays his head on your lap letting you know that he wants some love.  You can usually find him curled up by his foster's feet or at the foot of their bed. He is a super easy going dog and just wants to be loved.  





Rex is very gentle when taking food by hand, and obeys all commands to sit, lay down and  shake.  He's chill but love walks.




We don't know how he is with cats, but he loves dogs. He is very sweet to his foster's other dog and will often give kisses to his “sister” and their dog.  He is not aggressive in any way.




He is very well behaved when home alone.  Both his fosters work outside of the home, and there have been no accidents or behavioral issues while they are away.





Rex is great with everyone he meets, there is not a mean bone in his body.  He is a little shy at first, but warms quickly to those who give his love.




He isn't that into fetch, but will respond well to a little light play.  Likes to get belly rubs.





Like his "sister" he is an allstar on a leash but squirrels are of keen interest to him, so you may want to tighten your grip if he sees one.




He is also VERY obedient. He listens very well. He knows sit, stay, shake, down, etc.  Rex is extremely gentle when taking treats of food from our hands.




Rex is adorable. He loves human attention.  The first time Rex places his big head on your lap, and looks up at you with his big brown eyes asking for love, your heart will melt .







Starling and Rex are great dogs, they are a great pair, very well behaved and super obedient.  These two would be best friends for a kid or single man / woman looking for a pair of loving and loyal companions.  We really hope they get a great home where they can be the center of attention because they deserve it. 


They are both spayed, neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, housebroken and ready to find their forever home! 


Apply at www.luckylabrescue.com  Let's get this great pair a fabulous home!

name: Sofi2 HH
description:
Interview with Sofi2….

YOUR NAME IS INTERESTING, HOW DID THAT COME ABOUT?

Whelp, auto correct was spell correcting my name to SciFi 2 as if I was the sequel to a Science Fiction film, but it is actually Sofi2. My Foster Mommy found me on what would have been her first rescue doggie’s 10th birfday. That doggie’s name was Sofia, Sofi for short.  So I am the sequel or Junior to the first Sofi.  Hence the name. I even fit into to Sofi’s collar. It is nice that my Foster Mommy thinks highly enough of me to name me after her bestest dog.

WHERE DID YOU COME FROM?

I was found in south town by a bar. I followed people if I thought they had food, I wanted some food, I was soooo hungry.  Like you know when your tummy is so mad it growls at you and you are like whoa tummy shut up, I am trying to find you some food, hush up, I am trying hard. A lady (now known as Foster Mommy) bought me a plain burger, I woulda ordered a cheese burger, but when you are beggin you can’t be choosin. I got in the car with that lady.

YOUR EARS ARE ADORABLE, WHAT BREED ARE YOU?

Foster Mommy says my tiny ears indicated I might be part Sharpei. You can rub my ears if you want to. And my tail curls like a Chow and I am fluffy.  But this creamy off white egg shell color usually means there is some Labrador in the gene pool. I am a 43 pound, 3 year old mixed breed dog to sum it up. If you like Shiba Inus, you might find me appealing.

WHAT MAKES YOU SPECIAL?

Huge feet, huge appetite! And I am very sweet and attached to my Foster Mommy like glue. The only time I cause trouble and don’t let my special shine is when Foster Mommy feeds us.  I have to be fed separately, because I try to steal all the other doggie’s food.  Hey, I told you my appetite was HUGEEEEEE and I don’t want my tummy mad at me again.

WHAT DO YOU LIKE ABOUT YOUR FOSTER HOME?

I like the food.  I like the other dogs. I like food. I like the cats. I like food. I like Foster Mommy. My Kong toy that I just figured out. Did I mention, I like food?

DO YOU HAVE ANY SKILLS THAT HUMANS APPRECIATE?

I am potty and crate trained. I do know SIT and finally learning STAY. People will appreciate my ability to follow them from room to room like a sneaky ghost. And I try hard to learn the people words, you will know this by the way I cock my head from side to side to catch your words.

name: Grayson
description: Grayson is an incredibly handsome dog with some of the softest bunny fur you've ever felt, but this active pup prefers you not dwell on his good looks or how adorable he is - he's way too busy for all that. But if you're looking for a running sidekick or someone to help you stay active, Grayson's got you covered. This energetic pup can run fast and far, and he'd love to be your trail buddy! Grayson has boundless energy and he's not picky how he gets it out. Running, hiking, whatever he can do to keep moving, because this boy's got energy to burn. If you're looking for a fun playmate, Grayson is more than up for that, too. Grayson is really stoked that toys exist; he knows where the toy chest is and he can barely wait for you to pull one out. If he had to pick a favorite, he'd probably say anything he can fetch. He will sit and wait for you to throw the ball, or if you're the one sitting, he'll drop a toy in your lap until you get the picture that it's time to throw something. He also likes to play tug of war, but if playing with his human isn't an option, he'll pick out a toy to chew on and keep himself entertained. Grayson would love an active home with a yard and a maybe family with older children who can handle his rambunctious nature. He gets really excited to see kids and seems to know they'd make great playmates. If you think you can handle an adorable bundle of energy, come meet Grayson!

Rosie MMK9’s New Year’s Ruffsolutions

5.     Beat my previous record time on slurping out all of the yummy stuff in my Kong toy.

 

6.     Get adopted by a person who wants a side kick that is very clingy, of course the doggie definition of clingy applies here…clingy ruffly translates to…be the MOSTEST loving and loyal dog ever to the people that you love so much.

You should know that I am crate trained and house trained and know some people words and what to do when I hear them.  I am 30 lbs and 1-2 years old or so. I like other dogs and I am really treat muttivated and enjoy to learn new people words and do them for TREATS!

name: Toro
description:
Here we have a great family dog, so long as they don’t have cats. Toro came to ABR with pneumonia, obviously ill and underweight and just feeling crappy. Well, this 2 year old boy is now healthy, gaining weight and feeling well enough to play with the other 3 Boxers in his foster home. He’s not fully vetted yet because he’s just been too weak, but he will be in early November.

Toro has a light fawn coat on a medium to large male body with natural ears and docked tail. He is blind in his right eye but doesn’t seem to have any activity or behavioral issues from it. This medium energy guy is really sweet and loving. He has good manners with his people and with his pack. He is house, crate and leash trained.

Sometimes the ones that are not flashy, or outstanding or in-the-spotlight are the best. Just being kind, loyal, loving and even tempered fit so comfortably.

name: DIESEL
description: Meet Diesel! This sweet boy spent a month in a foster home who loved him dearly. They wanted his future adopters to know this  Diesel needed some time to warm up after spending almost 3 months in the shelter but he did so very quickly. We have two pups and the bond that they have created over the past month has been beautiful to watch. He is a gentle giant, a sweetheart, and will steal anyone's heart that he gets to spend enough time with. He requires some work and training but the investment you get back when you put in that time with him is indescribable. We opened our home to Diesel but now our hearts will always we be open to him as well. He loves to cuddle up with you on the couch and is perfectly happy being part of a dog pack. It will be one of the hardest decisions in our lives to bring him back after fostering him and if we had the space to keep 3 pups we would have absolutely adopted him ourselves. To the family who adopts Diesel:  Give him some time to warm up  He appreciates knowing boundaries and rules of the house  Make sure he has bones and toys to play with because eventually when he is ready it will light you up with joy to watch him play  He loves booty rubs and gives the sweetest kisses  If you give him your love, time, a warm place to sleep, and some food, you will receive love in abundance for years to come  We love Diesel and we are so heartbroken to see him leave our home but we are excited for the future adopter who will get to experience his love.  Learn more about Diesel by contacting his staff Champion at lorian.epstein@austintexas.gov. Or come down to the shelter and meet him at Austin Animal Center!

name: Sadie Lynn
description: They call her mellow yellow. Ok, maybe she's more of a tan than yellow, but Sadie Lynn is as mellow as they come. She has an easy-going personality and will make a wonderful companion for a like-minded couch potato or someone who works from home. Sadie Lynn gets very excited to go on walks, although she doesn't need long walks and tends to tire after a few blocks. She's also not a fan of stairs, so the less to go up and down, the better. But she definitely likes being outside and is eager to greet other people and dogs when she's out and about, her tail wagging when she sees them. While not particularly playful, all the houses around Sadie's foster home have dogs, and if all the dogs are out at once, they sing their song and run along the fence together. Other than those few bursts of excitement, Sadie Lynn prefers to sit back and relax, but she still gets excited when she sees that leash come out. Sadie Lynn has good manners in the home, she's house-trained and does well left alone. But she prefers you not do that and hang out and give her attention - she'll even gently nudge your hand if you mess up and stop petting her. She's like a little shadow and likes to be where you are, and one of her favorite places to be is laying next to your feet while you work on the computer or watch TV. And when you lay down on the couch, she'll put her head where yours is laying. She's a very sweet girl. Sadie Lynn also gets along well with the other dogs in her foster home and is so laid back that when one of her foster doggie siblings gets jealous or territorial, she pays them no mind. Sadie Lynn is ready to lounge the day away and keep you or that couch from getting too lonely. Come meet her today!

name: SAM
description: A letter from Sam's foster family:  'Sam's favorite thing, by far - is to give kisses! So much so that we have to say Okay, no more kisses for now! We have timed it - he will kiss you for over 2 minutes straight if you let him. He absolutely loves to cuddle and be by your side. He loves to sleep in the bed if allowed, but is just as happy on a dog bed next to you. He loves playing with his foster siblings- who are 15 and 30 lbs less than what he his. They like to play rough. And to be honest- he takes a minute to learn to love a new dog. But once they slowly meet he becomes the submissive one in the friendship. Our 1.5 year old pup loves to pull on his collar, although we don't allow it, he just sits there and takes it. He is the sweetest dog to humans too- sometimes he gets a bit excited and nibbles, so would do best with older kids or adults, but I have never met a more loving dog. He loves walks- but also loves his sleep- a lot. He wouldn't have any issues living in an apartment. He runs in our back yard at times but usually does his business and comes back in right away. He stays in a crate while we are at work during the day with no problems. He has no food aggression at all and LOVES his chew toys- which he kindly gives up if one of our bratty dogs takes it from him. We joke about trading in our 2 dogs for him. We are only allowed 3 dogs per our HOA, and we do not want stop fostering- otherwise we would claim him as our forever pup in a heartbeat. I am jealous of his future forever family, they will have one of the greatest dogs alive.'  If you think Sam is your next 'forever pup', email jacqueslagel@gmail.com to learn more about him!

name: Miss Pebbles
description: Pebbles is a cuddle bug that is always up for an adventure! Her tail never seems to stop wagging with glee and her expressive face will melt your heart. You can read all her emotions just in the adorable way she perks her ears. Her gorgeous eyes truly seem to convey how much she loves you. Although she prefers to be the only animal in the house, she absolutely adores children! She is very well behaved when she's left along, and usually just occupies her time with naps or with her toys. She's also house trained and knows sit! Pebbles loves to run around the backyard, but is also up for a nice jog around the block. Walks can be a pretty entertaining endeavor as she gets a bit distracted by moving objects, specifically squirrels. She thinks they should all be her toys. She loves toys, and when she's playing that is her only focus. She has the most enthusiastic energy and really just loves to play and have fun! This sweet girl is the affection queen! She is so devoted to her people, and prefers to be as close to them as she can be. She is the best napping buddy, and loves to lay her head in your lap. She'll even let you rest your head on her if you're sleepy! Her current foster says she tries to get work done, and if Pebbles jumps up beside her it's nearly impossible to resist putting work away and snuggling. Pebbles' ideal home would have a roomy backyard where she can really stretch those athletic legs. She would also love to have a family that is able to spend lots of time with her, and give her lots of attention. She is so full of love and loyalty and cannot wait to show her forever family just what an amazing companion she is. Come meet Pebbles! Her joy really is contagious!
label: not-adopted

name: Kyle
description: Kyle could be best described as a very stoic, but sweet, heating blanket. He likes to be as close to his person as possible, preferably laying his whole body across you to keep you warm and show you how much he loves you. He's a bit aloof when meeting new people, but seems happy to see you the next time you visit. You'll know you're in the club when he climbs up to show what a great lapdog he thinks he'd make. Chill and affectionate, Kyle seems to enjoy the simple things in life - having a blast eating his meals out of a kong wobbler, taking in the great outdoors on walks around the neighborhood, and of course cuddling with his person. He may have a serious face, but he's really just a big clown, enjoying a romp around the yard to get his ya-yas out, then flopping down on top of you for some well-earned leisure time. He's been an impressive house-guest on sleepovers, quickly figuring out that he needs to potty outside and sleeping quietly through the night. This handsome guy already knows 'sit' and is learning all kinds of new skills APA!'s Total Obedience Program. The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Kyle has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! He is learning skills like sit and down, walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'Place', which means he will go to a specific place in your home on command. Once Kyle successfully completes all the skills on his training plan, he will be considered TOP Dog Ready! Kyle is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with him after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 Low key but full of personality, Kyle is an easy dog to please as long as there are laps available. While he's pretty adaptable and would likely do well in an apartment, we think he'd love a home with a yard to call his own. Come meet this great pup!

name: Sally
description: This calm and loyal lady has been described as 'cat-like' by her foster mom in that she's very independent and is content to do her own thing. Sally always stays close to her person when out and about, and if another person comes up to them, she will sit and look to her person for reassurance. Sally is calm around other dogs and people, but isn't particularly interested in interacting with them. While she can be shy when meeting new people, after some time to warm up, she'll allows pets and gently accept treats. But once she knows you, Sally becomes a very loving and loyal companion. She shares her toys with her foster mom and likes to curl up on the couch next to her. Sally really adores her soft stuffed animals, which she does not and will not destroy. She likes to carry them around gently in her mouth and will bring them all up from downstairs so she has them in one place. Sally enjoys a little fetch from time to time, but with a ball, thank you, not her babies. Sally is great on walks (unless she sees a squirrel that's up to no good) and she seems to accommodate whatever speed the human holding the leash is walking at. She has a low to medium energy level and is good with a 20 to 40 minute walk. She'd also probably enjoy a secure backyard that had squirrel visitors for her to stalk. Sally does well left alone, is house and crate-trained and doesn't bark much in the house. She also has cute little ears, pretty brown eyes and comes in a nice, manageable size. If you're looking for a quiet, calm companion, you won't find a better match than Sally. Come meet her!

name: Muffin
description: Muffin is a beautiful young pup with one floppy ear to give him some character. But Muffin doesn't get caught up on his looks. Muffin's got things to do. You see, Muffin's one of those dogs that wants to play ALL OF THE TIME! He's so very excited to meet other playmates, and if there are other dogs around, he's gonna chase them until they play with him! Because of a learning disability, Muffin's attention is difficult to hold, and his vocabulary appears stuck at 'stop', 'no' and 'good boy', though he recently learned 'sit' if a treat's involved. Muffin has a lot of energy in all directions at once, and while he may not exactly have object-permanence down, he's an expert in playtime and looks for fun around every corner. Muffin's favorite toys can best be described as 'anything moving'. He will do zoomies with the resident dog in his foster home or on his own, he enjoys tug of war with stuffed animals and playing 'mouth' with his doggie friends. And hold onto those hollowed-out plush toys, because Muffin likes to throw them in the air and catch them. When Muffin finds a favorite plushie, he enjoys cuddling with it and occasionally grooming it. He also loves going on walks, is pretty good on leash and likes to stop a lot to look at stuff, especially if he can't figure out what it is. He's very alert to any weird sounds - if it's moving he should probably go try to play with it! When Muffin does stop moving, that means it's naptime, and he likes to lay on his human for that. He enjoys a good cuddle, but prefers sleeping separate and eats and sleeps overnight in his crate. He likes to kiss feet and hands very gently, and he's particularly fond of his foster's mother and melts into her whenever they interact. As much as he loves people, Muffin often has a difficult time focusing, as he's constantly distracted by the next bit of fun he can see and sometimes seems to be ignoring potential adopters. But out on walks, he introduces himself to everyone he walks past and has an interest in runners (he'd likely make a nice jogging buddy). Overall, Muffin's entire mission in life is playing and finding ways to amuse himself. He also makes adorable 'gremlin noises'. The ideal home for Muffin would have active people, a playful canine buddy to help burn off his energy, a yard to bound through and an unlimited supply of plushies and balls. If you're ready to be Muffin's forever playmate, come meet this great pup!
