name: Tom Hanks
description: Do you want a pup to burrow his big, wrinkled head into your lap for pets? Do you love the idea of a dog tapping his feet in excitement over a good game of fetch? Then look no further than Tom Hanks! Tom is a quiet, calm boy who just loves to spend time with people - whether it's walking the trail, playing outside, taking a dip in the water or binge watching a show, Tom is an easy guy to please. He loves the treats too and does an adorable little smack when he gets one, and he'll have you doling those out regularly just to hear it. And those jowls and slight pout are a thing of beauty. This boy wins friends quickly, and the volunteers who are lucky enough to know him have all fallen in love with him. Tom has been on sleepovers with APA volunteers where he was reported to be house-trained and extremely well-behaved in the home. He was calm and respectful while inside and gentle while playing. Tom Hanks has lots of opportunities to earn his beloved treats in APA!'s Total Obedience Program (TOP), which is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Tom has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! He is learning skills like sit and down, walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'Place,' which means he will go to a specific place in your home on command. Once he successfully completes all the skills on his training plan, Tom will be considered TOP Dog Ready! Tom is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with him after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 Swing by APA today and ask to meet the handsome, sweet Tom Hanks!

name: Hunk
description:
Hunk is about 3 years old and all legs, his owner sometimes wonders if they are all connected to the same dog. Hunk is coming to ABR to find a forever family without cats. Looks like he faked his cat test in order to get out of the shelter and into this great home, only to find more cats. Other than that little issue Hunk is a winner. He wears a classic fawn coat with a black mask, natural ears and cropped tail; the usual clown suit for a goofy, happy, lovable Boxer.

He is healthy, fully vetted, heartworm negative and attracted to laps. He is almost house trained but doesn’t have a dog door, and he shares his displeasure with being put in his crate and separated from all the fun by crying. He’s the usual nosey young Boxer who needs to see where everything is and perhaps taste it if he can. He loves attention, belly rubs, head scratches, bacon treats, you know, attention from his humans.

Hunk is still a hyper young Boxer boy trying to figure out how to make it all work, including his legs. He adores his humans and tries to do what they tell him to do. He is  good with other dogs but doesn’t yet understand he can’t swipe their food. With boundaries, guidance, patience, love and activity Hunk can easily become a life-long companion. He’d do well with a fur buddy but don’t let him fool you, no cats.

name: Clement
description:
This sweet fawn boy is on the small side for a male, but Clement makes up for it with his even temperament and good nature. He gets along with other dogs just fine, and even though he does not live with kids, he’s been good with those he’s met, even the grand kids. He’s a happy guy that likes to carry his toys around with him.

He is crate and leash trained with the cutest wiggle-butt that gets him doing the “C” dance. He might get more excited for his food than for his humans, but it’s a very close call. He does sit nicely before he eats, what great manners. Clement is heartworm positive but ABR helps explain the options and helps with treatment; and treatment  does not have to be difficult now.

Clement probably lived on concrete before coming to ABR, and likely spent far too much time alone in a kennel. He doesn’t mind going into his crate for a time, but he gets anxious and chews to calm down. When he has a fur buddy and/or a human around he is more comfortable. He is a sweet, easy going guy that really seems to appreciate having a family and buddies.

She runs regularly with Beau and her foster Dad. She is equally willing and equally happy to take a nice long nap - any time and anywhere! My foster human siblings are fun to run around and play with but I also enjoy laying around relaxing and watching what my humans do all day. My foster mom thinks I am making great progress in only using the potty outside- yay! I get along with dogs quite well but I like to sniff them first duh! name: Toto
description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.My name is Toto and no I am not related to that Dorothy person. I eat red shoes for breakfast. You see my home got blown away a long time ago. I was living on my own at a company in San Antonio when a nice lady rescued me. I have to admit, I wasn't really happy about it at the time, but wow. Being in a home is alot better than trying to avoid mean people on the streets.

The nice lady who rescued me wasn't able to keep me, so she took me to the ranch. And guess what? I get to sleep inside a real house. My favorite thing is snuggling on the couch and watching that big box that makes all kinds of sounds. I love snuggling up and getting to lay on a nice warm lap.

I do have to warn you, I need to know you before I will become your friend. I have met people in my life that hurt me before, and I need to trust you first. If you have alot of patience and will let me get to know you, I will give you the best kisses and my total devotion.

If you can't adopt me, but would like to help support me, you can hit to donate button. All donations are tax deductible and really help keep our operation going.

name: Buddy
description:
Up for adoption in Texas: Buddy.


Buddy is such a happy dog, with such a sad story! Can you imagine having a 13 year old dog and posting him on Craigslist to give him away? That's just what happened to Buddy!


One of our Lucky Lab amazing volunteers spotted the ad and was worried about Buddy's future so she came to his rescue!


Buddy is such a sweet boy, he is dog and people friendly. He's chill, housebroken, he is well behaved when he's "home alone" and he is a total love! He lived with children in his prior home, one had autism as well.


Buddy is easy going and we can't say enough good things about him, he even knows how to ring a bell when he needs to go potty! He loves to be "loved on" and get lots of hugs.


He has a bit of hip dysplasia and cataracts but he's 13 so that goes with the territory. Otherwise he appears to be doing quite well!


He is vaccinated and microchipped. He weighs about 70lbs. Apply at www.luckylabrescue.com

Characteristic Canines for Special People		
			
MY NAME IS:  Cedar
POSTED TO PETFINDER DATE:  Oct 17, 2018
BREED:  Mixed
GENDER:  Male
SPAYED/NEUTERED:  Yes
COLOR:  Black/White

For more information please call the HCHS at 512-793-5463.  We are open every day except Tuesdays and Wednesdays from 11am to 4pm.  You can see all our available animals at HillCountryHumaneSociety.org.
All our adoptable dogs receive a DHPPV and Bordatella vaccine.
Wormed - yes
When you adopt one of our animals it will be micro chipped and registered at the time of adoption.
While we do our best to determine the breeds of our dogs, the majority are strays, and we have only general appearance, coat type, size, ear type, tail, tongue color and coat color to base breed on.  It is always possible when adopting a puppy that it will change dramatically to look like another breed.
We highly recommend that you enroll your dog in training classes.

description: Sarah is a super-sweet and ultra-smart pup who loves to get out for long walks and hikes and would make a great running partner. She loves to play tug of war, chase, or running around with squeaky toys, but she'll also chill and chew on her bones or rawhides. She's a pretty tolerant pup and is good about being bathed and having her nails done. She is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with her after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Tinkerbelle hasn't gotten very much attention in her first home.  She is a smart and fast learner, eager to please and will quickly learn the routine of your home and family. True to her terrier bred, she becomes very attached to her human. She is a bit jealous and guards her human.  However, these are typical issues that can be corrected.  But the adopter will need to guide her behavior.

Although Tinkerbelle gets along with other dogs, and cats, she will do better in an environment with few other pets and we prefer older children over 12. 

Make her a part of your life and she will shine.

name: Mandy
description:
Quick Stats
* Spayed Female; Probably Purebred
* DOB estimated 2013
* House & Crate Trained
* Heartworm Negative; Current on Prevention
* Good with others dogs and children

Mandy is a sweet lady who wants to be by your side, while you gently pet her and lovingly talk to her. She’s a great alert dog; she’ll let you know when there are visitors arrives and greet them in a friendly, happy manner.  She likes Animal Planet and will howl with the wolves on TV. She loves to go for rides and is well-behaved in public. 

Mandy has some issues with her vision and joints. She can see shadows and gets around fine. Sometimes, she’s hesitant to jump out of the car because she can’t see the ground clearly, but will jump with encouragement.  

This sweetie has been through a lot of breeding and most likely a tough life before rescue, so she deserves a loving home. She’s easy to live with and fits into any routine. She would be a wonderful companion for a quieter home, but does play with younger dogs if they’re not too rowdy. She’s good with puppies, too.

name: Harley (referral)
description:
HARLEY (referral): CONTACT Ashley, ASHLEY.N.MALDONADO@GMAIL.COM, 
512-228-2833

Quick Stats
* Spayed Female; 7 years old as of October 2018
* Has AKC papers
* House & Crate Trained
* Heartworm Negative; Current on Prevention & Vaccinations; Microchipped 
* Good with dogs; probably no cats.

Harley is a sweet, 7-year-old female GSD who has lived with her family (including two kids) and one other dog (with whom she gets along well) since she was a puppy. She’s VERY active for her age and loves a mental challenge, so she needs a home that will make keeping her active mentally and physically a priority.

Harley is extremely loyal, loving, and SMART. Harley knows basic commands, including Sit, Stay, Down, and Place, but will test her commander if they are not a confident leader.

She gets along well with other dogs and is dominant on her own turf. Her energy level and excitement can at times be overwhelming for playmates, so that should be kept in mind when meeting new friends. She has not been around cats much, but from her reaction during walks she may view cats as squirrels (i.e., prey), so it is not recommended she be introduced to cats at this time.

She is crate-trained and is used to being an inside dog when not playing outside. Harley does have a fear of thunderstorms and fireworks; she can exhibit destructive behavior if her anxiety is not managed during these circumstances.  

Harley is seeking a home with a calm, confident leader and a large yard or even acreage.  She’ll respond best to someone who has time to consistently provide her with training and physical activity.

name: Captain America
description:
Captain America was once Kaiser, but then, things change. He’s coming home to ABR now there’s a new skin kid in the house, and he’s been kinda pushy with his fur sister about who gets to protect whom. So, rather than have a big mistake that no one wants, Captain America is looking for a new family. He’s a healthy 7 year old guy in a fawn coat with a docked tail and cropped ears. He is heartworm negative. He has a gorgeous Boxer face with a white t-bone on his forehead and a white chest. And those eyes!

Captain gets along with people just fine, and he usually gets along with his fur sister unless there’s something special involved like a new kid or food. He can eat by himself of course, but the kid moves around. He is house, crate and leash trained but he still has a bit too much puppy curiosity to be left to his own devices with no one home. 

Captain Ameria’s a typical Boxer boy who hates to get his feet wet or go out in the rain. He loves affection, attention, scratches, pets and snuggles. He needs slow introductions with other dogs, and may not choose to be friends with some. He may be most comfortable as an only dog who gets all the attention and affection and knows his role as companion and protector.

Captain America has  been in a foster home for a while as of mid March and he’s doing fine. He likes to play with his human or his toys, look out the window, announce visitors and intruders, snuggle up on the couch or in bed, and take naps. He likes his walks but this big, strong boy needs an experienced handler. He’ll do best without cats or kids, but he’s a big, handsome loving guy on his own.

His ideal foster or adoptive home is low-key, not super busy with kids and people coming and going, and probably has another dog friend for him to hang out with! name: Laila
description:
Please contact Jamesa (roxysrescue@yahoo.com), 713-882-2610 for more information about this pet.Hi Everyone, my name is Laila and as you can see I am a beautiful Brown Brindle Labrador Retriever 1.5 years old. I'm looking for a loving home who wants to have a loving dog to come home to or just hang out with.
My foster mom calls me amazing and sweet, I don't know what amazing is but I am sweet as a Hershey bar, just like chocolate and everyone loves chocolate and I am sure you will love me.
My foster mom thinks I'm amazing because my personality and demeanor is just sweet. You see I was adopted as a puppy from a shelter. The family thought I was cute (and I am still cute) but as I grew older they didn't have time to play with me and I was very lonely and hungry. I would cry for someone to please help me.
Well help came and I am so happy. My foster mom cries now because she can no longer keep me and fears I have to go back to the shelter. In San Antonio, Tx the shelter is a very high kill place and I will be scared to go there.
I get along with all dogs, men and women and I love kids. I like my chewbones and I will play with them for a long time. I have never met a cat but I'm so friendly I bet I could be their friend.
I am friendly with everyone I meet. I am healthy, no longer hungry. I am spayed, microchipped and all of my vaccinations are up to date.
Can you give me a home and a 2nd chance to love a family as my own. I will be a real good girl.
You can see more pictures of me on Facebook page: Roxy's K-9 Rescue
ADOPTION FEE & APPLICATION REQUIRED

Roxy's K-9 Rescue does not have a shelter, all of our dogs are raised in foster homes. Each dog comes spay/neutered (fixed), rabies shots appropriate for their age, and dewormed twice. The dogs are up to date on vaccinations according to their age at the time of adoption. They are microchipped, heartworm tested and on monthly flea/tick and heartworm preventative. ALL OF THIS IS INCLUDED IN THE ADOPTION FEE.
Medical records will come with each dog at the time of adoption.
Our organization is run by volunteers/foster parents, please be patient to give us time to respond to your emails and/or phone calls. We will reply to you. Thank you.

The vets do not feel like he can be safely altered. We are looking at alternatives now.

description: Buckbeak loves his snuggles and his people. He is a very good listener and super food motivated so if you have a treat he will do anything for it! But after his walks and a little playtime he'll go down for a nice, long nap. He loves naps. Buckbeak is the sweetest baby boy. If you love walks, cuddles and kisses he's your man. Oh and isn't he so handsome!?  Here are some notes from his short-term foster home:  He loves to be on the couch or bed and sometimes gets too comfy and doesn't realize he's on the edge. He's fallen off several pieces of furniture.  When he gets the zoomies you have to be careful if you're in his way. One time we were playing and he was chasing me but knocked me down. After he jumped over me he came back to see if I was OK and kiss my face.  When I first picked him up he immediately fell asleep. I have a seat cover that goes in my back seat and one of the buckles came undone so the sling fell as well as Buckbeak. I looked back to check on him and he was content, still laying down on the bottom of the car. He's a goofball!

name: Big Caesar
description: Big Caesar spent four years in a home full of people and proved to be a wonderful family dog. Affectionate, low energy and low maintenance, this sweet guy loves nothing more than hanging out with his people. Described as a very caring and affectionate teddy bear, Big Caesar has a human-like look in his eyes, he's really good at knowing when you're down and is always there to give kisses to make you feel better. Big Caesar will let you love on him anyway you wish and is up for cuddles whenever you are, laying his head in your lap to ask for pets. He thinks he's a big lap dog, but he's also happy just being by your side. He loves meeting people, but doesn't get jumpy about it, though he's usually playful right away and will bring them his rope toy to play with. While he's typically relaxed and lazy, he does like to play tug of war and fetch. When he want to play, he'll bring you his rope, then lay it down next to you and wait for you to pick it up. On top of being a total sweetheart, Big Caesar is also a very well-behaved pup to have around - he doesn't take food that isn't given to him, he doesn't whine, he's fully housebroken and is great being left home for extended periods of time. He doesn't need a crate, will only chew on his toys, and he'll spend most of the day just napping on his bed until you return. And this smart guy does just about anything on command: sit, lay down, stay, roll over, shake. He even plays dead. If treats are involved, you could probably get him to drive you to the store. Big Caesar is showing off his skills and learning more in APA!'s Total Obedience Program. The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Big Caesar has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him expand his skill set to become the best dog he be! Skills such as walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, and 'Place', which means he will go to a specific place in your home on command. Once he successfully completes all the skills on his training plan, Big Caesar will be considered TOP Dog Ready! He is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program, you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with him after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 As long as he has people to love on and a cozy bed to call is own, Big Caesar would be comfortable in any size home. Come meet this amazing pup!

name: Lakota
description: Lakota's foster reports that he's 'a sweetheart, a sweetie pie, a gentle giant.' We're still learning about Lakota, but he seems to be a good-natured pup who's calm and non-reactive when meeting other dogs, fully house-trained and a very quiet guy to have around. The only noises he makes are when he's excited when you get home or greet him in the morning. Otherwise he's very chill and will get up to go to a window or door that something has alerted him. But he doesn't make a peep, even watching half a dozen deer walk by in the yard. Lakota may have had some training in the past because he's always looking to his people as if he's waiting for instructions. His foster mom figured out that when she throws her arm to the right, Lakota will run, then stop and look back. He definitely seems to be up for some training. He likes to stay close to his people and will follow them around like a little shadow, but also does well left home alone. He enjoys having a yard to explore and sunbathe in and loves going for car rides. Lakota is kind and good to everyone he meets, and we think he'll make a wonderful addition to any number of loving homes. Come meet this great pup!

name: Vivi
description:
We know that Vivi came from the Palm Valley area, as many of our rescues do, at the end of October, 2018. We know she has had a difficult time finding a foster parent with enough patience and compassion to help her begin to find her way. Somewhere, somehow, someone shattered her trust in humans and the outside world. She is slowly, glacially, willing to trust her foster dad and let him take her for walks, give her treats, and gently, very gently, ask her to try the outside world again. Often the unseen injuries are the deepest.

Vivi is a beautiful, small, brindle girl with natural ears and tail. She is heartworm negative and has finished her course of preventive medication given to all our rescues from Palm Valley. She is fully vetted, healthy and has no problem eating. She is housetrained but only goes outside to do her business. She is good on leash and loves her walks, but is immediately submissive when other people or dogs come near. She is not destructive in the house, but she is most comfortable in her crate whether she needs to be there or not.  She shows very little interest in other dogs or cats so far. 

She is sweet and lovable with her foster dad now, and she did great at ABR’s Austin Adoption Day in February when volunteer after volunteer came to calmly greet her. This 2 year old has made tremendous progress in her foster home and is slowly, at her own pace, learning the outside world can be welcoming and warm. Vivi has taken the first few baby steps on her journey from forgotten to family. She may never be the life of the  party or gregarious greeter, but she will surely fill someone’s heart with joy as a loving, loyal, trusting companion.

name: Punkin JuM
description:
Punkin JuM

I have a PSA, Punkin Service Announcement.  Who invented the game of punkin chunkin’?  Throwing punkins is not nice, I know they aren’t really alive, but maybe they still had aspawrations to be a Jack o latern, or a pie, or a Cinderella carriage. Once you chunk that punkin, you have ended all their career options. So please next time you consider the Fall Festival activity of punkin chunkin, please think about this and the delish pie that you missed out on. Thank you, now onto the main epawsode…me…

My name is Punkin because I was saved right before Halloween and I am indeed the color of a pumpkin, even my eyeballs are…see….*bats her eye lashes*, hence the name Punkin, because I am from Texas, and we like to say stuff different to be cool. I also have a dollop of whippy cream on my face and chest. Speaking of whippy cream, I need some sprinkled on my kibble, because I am in dire need of a weight gain.

The cutest thing about me is not my name though, it is my nubby tail.  I think someone chopped it off when I was a puppy to make me look more like a Boxer dog, but I look like a Vizsla too- I have the sleek/athletic body of both breeds!!  I am furmiliar with walking on a leash, staying in a crate and just an all around good mid-aged dog at about 3 years of experience in being a good girl. 

I came from the city shelter, very skinny, like my rib cage was very noticeable. But the rescue ladies have been giving me extra yummies to help me put on the pounds, I weigh 40 lbs now, but should weigh closer to 50 and be a solid medium almost crossing to large gal.  I am currently living with other dogs, both my size and smaller and I made friends with all of them.

And even though I am very hungry and practically starving, I take treats ever so gently from you human hand. If you want a mellow dog that will wiggle and shake it like a pumpkin flavored milk shake as soon as you get home from work, then I am the punkin for you.

GOD'S DOGS Rescue, in San Antonio TX, does not have a shelter - Our dogs are raised in foster homes in the San Antonio area. Each dog comes spayed or neutered, up-to-date with age appropriate vaccinations, microchipped, heartworm tested and are current with monthly flea/tick and heartworm preventatives. 

ALL OF THIS IS INCLUDED IN THE Local ADOPTION FEE OF $250.00 FOR PUPPIES and $200.00 for ADULTS. (Local is in the state of Texas). Medical records will come with each dog at the time of adoption.

IF THIS IS AN OUT OF STATE ADOPTION, TRANSPORT TO YOU is included in the adoption fee of $500.00 for PUPPIES and $400.00 for ADULTS. We transport all over the country!!

Our dogs are socialized, and we try to provide you a good understanding of the dog’s personality. Please contact us at info@godsdogsrescue.org for more information about adopting one of our dogs and puppies or fill out an adoption application at http://www.godsdogsrescue.org/adopt/adoption-application/ 

Please visit our website http://godsdogsrescue.org/ for helpful information re: transport, our adoption process and application, volunteering and fostering, and photos of our dogs/pups looking for homes!!

Thank you for wanting to adopt a rescued dog, their LIVES depend on it!

name: Weezie
description:
Up for adoption in Texas and New England: Weezie.


This 70lb dog was able to type out a bit about herself, what a gem !! :) 


Take it away Weezie:





"Hello, my name is Weezie. I’m a 6 year old lab mix, and I’m looking for my forever home. 





I’m pretty laid back, and tend to go with the flow. My foster home has dogs of all sizes and cats and I get along with everyone. 





I enjoy walks, playing fetch, car rides and lounging by the pool or on the couch. My favorite thing is to have my back scratched and of course squeaky toys. 





I am house-trained but my house now has a doggie door (that I only use when my foster mom or dad or home) that I use so I might need a reminder.  





I don’t bark much and I don’t jump. I have however, stolen a sandwich, or two, from the kitchen counter. I’m not a fan of being crated and thunderstorms make me really scared. I do best eating my meals alone - separate from my fur siblings."





Weezie's foster mom tells us she is good with other dogs (just not sharing her food), she is not a fan of the crate. She is good on a leash and likes to play fetch. She may also want to sample what you leave on the counter. :) 





Weezie is spayed, vaccinated and microchipped. 





Apply a www.luckylabrescue.com

name: Levi Strauss
description: Levi Strauss is the full package - athletic, playful and devastatingly handsome. If you're looking for a the best of both worlds - a peaceful homebody and an adventurous trail buddy - this big, beautiful dog is for you! Levi's idea of the perfect date involves long walks or runs around Lady Bird Lake, where he can sniff the good scents and maybe even take a little dip in the water. Later on, he'd like to jump in the car (where he's always on his best behavior) for an ice cream date and then cap it off with nice long nap on the couch. Then after he gets his second wind, Levi's ready to play fetch in the play yard and lope around like a big, goofy horse! Although he's an outdoorsy boy, Levi is a peaceful companion in the home. He's content to lay by your feet while you tap away at the computer or, better yet, snuggle up with you on the couch for some movie watching! Levi's also working on his skills with his TOP (Total Obedience Program) trainer, who is working with him on a customized training plan. So far he's proving to be a quick study, probably because he'll do anything to please his humans, especially if they have treats! The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Levi has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! Levi is learning skills like sit and down, walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'place', which means he will go to a specific place in your home on command. Once Levi successfully completes all the skills on his training plan, he will be considered TOP Dog Ready! Levi is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with him after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 We should also note that Levi could potentially go home to a well-matched doggy sibling. So what do you say? Are you ready to bring home a new best friend who will stay by your side through thick and thin? Come meet Levi Strauss today and we promise you'll love him 100 times more than your most favorite pair of jeans! Follow Levi Strauss on Instagram @adopt_levi_strauss

name: Abigail Grace
description:
Welcome to the Wonderful World of Rescue Dachshunds. Look around and read their bios. Find a few whose personality seems to fit well. Consider one of our Well Seasoned Seniors who are truly wonderful and have so much to offer. Need help finding the best fit? We'll help with that too. Please fill out an application and let’s get you all matched up with a loving new “furever’ companion and friend. You’ll find the application on the “Available Dogs” page.
NOTE:

Adoptions to Texas residents only

.

Standard Adoption Fee Adult Dog: $250 ea. Puppy Adoption Fee: $300 ea. Reduced rates for Seniors dogs (10 and up). Reduced rates for pairs (when adopted together).

Email: ddrtxinfo@gmail.com Primary Website: www.DDRTX.org

Say Hello to Abigail Grace! This beautiful girl is a bit of a miracle child. She came to us from Animal Control paralyzed in her hind end and unable to walk. After visiting with several vets and therapists, it was said that it would be very unlikely she would walk again.

She got lots of exercise in a wheelchair to prepare her for a wonderful wheeled future. Foster mom made sure to provide extra therapy for her back legs, just to give Abigail the best chance possible. And, much to everyone's surprise, Abigail began to use her back legs. She grew stronger and stronger every day. So we did what we could to help, and we started her therapy. After several weeks of laser therapy, accupuncture, and water treadmill exercise, she was walking again!

While she may never regain full strength and use of her legs, Abigail gets around just fine now. She stands for dinner, walks around the house, uses the dog door and ramp, and even plays fetch! She tries very hard every day to keep up physically with her furry foster sisters and brother, and usually succeeds.

She still has a special way of walking, and occasionally her legs slide right out from under her. She wears a diaper around the house because her bladder is a little weak, and sometimes she has accidents. But she doesn't let these things stop her from being a healthy, happy girl.

Abigail would do wonderful in a home that is prepared to treat her as the special princess she is. She is a very high energy girl who absolutely loves toys, fetch, and "deading" all stuffed animals. She isn't a lap dog, and only submits to cuddles when she is dead tired. But she gives the sweetest kisses, and provides absolute joy to everyone she meets.

Love dachshunds and not ready to adopt or circumstances won't permit having a dog? How about being a sponsor or making a donation. Every one of our dachshunds receives excellent medical care along with day to day food, love and housing. Being non-profit, we rely on generous individuals like yourselves to help save these fur babies. You can do this specifically for one dog with the sponsor button on their webpage or a general donation on our “How To Help” page. Easy and quick through Pay Pal or your debit/credit card. You generosity is sincerely appreciated by all and is tax deductable. Need other ideas? You'll find tons of them on the How to Help tab. All contributions are tax deductable.

Diamond Dachshund Rescue of Texas is a non-profit 501(c)(3) volunteer organization with focus on rescue and adoption of pure breed Dachshunds. All dogs are fully vetted and housed on private property. Meetings are scheduled upon adoption approval. Thank you for your continued support to the rescue and shelter communities!
Opt to Adopt!

name: BENTLEY
description: A note from Bentley's foster mom:   Like his namesake, Bentley Motors, Bentley is a classic man.  He's a distinguished six year old gent.  He has character with a small bit of one ear missing and incredible coloring.  At approximately 50lbs, he could stand to indulge in some fine foods to put on a little more weight.  Like any refined gentleman, he enjoys delicacies such as jerky, chicken, bones, peanut butter....really any food.  Most of the time you can catch him enjoying a mid-day nap with his foster siblings.  He enjoys the company of other doggie chaps.  He really loves to get his daily exercise by walking and running.  He also loves bones, scratches and following his people around the house.  He would do best in a home with a fenced yard and who can walk him daily.  Bentley knows his manners and is potty trained, can use a dog door and knows the command sit.  He will occasionally bark.  Although he prefers not to go in his kennel or take a bath, he will begrudgingly oblige.  Bentley does not like rain or cats, so no outdoor living for him or kittie friends, please and thank you.  Bentley is a good dog and will make a great companion.

name: Tasha
description:
Quick Stats
* Spayed Female; DOB mid-2017
* 65-70 Pounds, small but very muscular
* House & Crate Trained
* Heartworm Negative; Current on Prevention & Vaccinations; Microchipped 
* Fine with new other dogs with proper introduction, but can be leash reactive
* Has lived with a cat
* Good with people, but has not been around children

Tasha is a sweet, lovely, lively lady seeking her forever home. Although she had a rough start in life, given love, socialization, and proper correction, she’s becoming a good dog!

This sweetie takes treats gently and walks nicely on a leash. She loves playing with her ball, playing with her foster brothers and sisters, and going for walks. She’s comfortable in her crate, goes inside of it easily and eats there. She already knows Sit.

Tasha can be a bit headstrong and needs a confident, capable leader, or she will take advantage. For example, if she’s inside of her crate and hears you, she can become loud, demanding to be released from the crate. Saying a firm “No” and covering her crate will stop that. Also, she’s strong and can try to take control on walks, unless she respects you. She’s fine as long as she respects you as a leader, and she cannot go to a home without structure and rules.

If you can provide the love, guidance, exercise, and structure she needs, please apply!

Link to Application:
http://www.gsdrescuectx.com/adoption-application.html

name: Wesley
description:
Please contact Jamesa (roxysrescue@yahoo.com), 713-882-2610 for more information about this pet.Hey ya'll my name is Wesley and I think I'm pretty special because I'm so sweet and somber. First let's get the most important thing out of the way, I am looking for a home where I can be a play buddy with another dog. It doesn't matter how big or what age they are because in my foster home I play with all kinds. I do not like being by myself or I get very sad, I even like to sleep with my best friend. At first I slept cuddled with my sister but she got adopted, then I became friends with another dog and he got adopted. So I had to sleep with a big Rottweiler but she didn't mind, now I have 3 little pups that I play and sleep with.
If you do not have a dog already looking for a companion I probably wouldn't do so good by myself. I love to play with toys all the time. I pay until I take a nap then I'm back up playing again. I follow all of the rules very well in my foster home, I am house-trained and house trusted worthy. It has been months since I slept in a crate but I guess I can do it again until you get comfortable with me.
I am happy everyday, I like to cuddle with my humans too and I'll wait until you tell me to give you a kiss.
So let's explain my breed, my mother was a Labrador Retriever/Basenji Mix and my father was a Hound/Labrador mix (I look like my dad except for the black spots on my face from my mom) There is a picture of my mom and dad so you can see how pretty they were. There are pictures of me too.
You can contact my foster mom for more videos and pictures and information about me. I am 5 months old and weigh 22 lbs. My litter was pretty small so they do not think we'll get as big as our mother and father.
Transportation across the United States is no problem.

name: Sable
description:
Please contact Jamesa (roxysrescue@yahoo.com), 713-882-2610 for more information about this pet.Hee Hee! Hi there, I'm me Sable and I am a giggling wiggle worm. I am happy everyday and I bet I can make you laugh, you would love me. I am almost 4 months old and on the little side, I only weigh 12 pounds so far. My mom only weighs 45 but I'll probably be smaller than that as an adult since my entire litter were all small. I love to eat but I stay slim and trim!!
I live in a foster home with a big female Rottweiler and a big Labrador Retriever, I play with them every day and they are so sweet, they let me get away with crawling all over them, eating their food and taking their toys. I would be a great companion pup if you have another dog.
My special training is that I live in an apartment so I know how to run up and down the stairs, I let my foster mom know when I have to go potty but she still puts those pee pads down on the floor in case I have an accident. And I am quiet, not a barker at all.
You know what else is good about me? I am a soft cuddlier, I cuddle like a baby and will go to sleep in your arms. My foster mom says that I am very low maintenance whatever that means. I love my crate, it's my private home and I got in there often.
Don't you want to meet me? I bet you'll fall in love with me!! My foster mom has lots more pictures of me if you want to see them and she can tell you all about me. Hope to see you soon!

name: Grace
description:
Please contact Jamesa (roxysrescue@yahoo.com), 713-882-2610 for more information about this pet.I'm A Super Star!!!Hello Everyone, you are looking at a Super Star! That's right I am a super star just like Kim Kardashian - I may not look like her but I am equally a super star and I can be a bit of a Diva sometimes.
My Diva tricks includes cuddling with you, playing with everyone I meet, I am very friendly and I like everyone and walking with a prance as if I am in a parade or something!!!
How many Diva's can you find that are sugary sweet? Well you are looking at one and you should adopt me!!! You would be getting a great dog at least that is what I hear people tell my foster mom every time someone visits. I hear them saying how sweet I am so that must be something good. I let them rub my head which I love.
So for the necessities, I am about 2.5 years old and I was found at a steel mill where I had 8 babies. I have had lots of babies because my previous parents did not do the birth control thing but I will never have any more babies, I'm all fixed up now. The vet says I have mostly Labrador Retriever in me but I am mixed with something, they are just not sure what it is, maybe pit bull but does it really matter? NO, not to me.
My foster home is an apartment and at first it was a little scary because I did not know what the stairs were. But now I run up and down the stairs for potty and walking time. I am not a barker, really the ideal apartment dog. I will let you know when I need to go out to potty and I do not bother you to go out that often. I am completely house-trained but I tell you the truth, it would be great to have some chew bones for me so I don't get bored.
I am crate trained and I love sleeping in my crate when you go to bed but I also love being around you and quietly hanging out. I am a nosy Diva too, always trying to look out the window and so happy when my foster mom comes home from work. She has a cat and me and that cat are friends. I am friends with big and little dogs, I play with then all. I really do like little dogs, I play make believe that they are my babies, so I am gentle.
Just email or call my foster mom and you can meet me and fall in love with me.

name: Trombone
description:
Please contact Jamesa (roxysrescue@yahoo.com), 713-882-2610 for more information about this pet.Trombone is 1 of 3 puppies being cared for by Roxxy's K-9 Rescue. They are exactly 3 months old today (11-18-2018). I know for sure that their mother is a blonde mini Labrador Retriever but I am not sure who their father is. Their mother was a stray and I have taken several litters from her. I took Trombone and his 2 sisters when they were 2 weeks old and bottle fed them.
They have grown, running up and down the stairs, all around the yard and playing with each other with all kinds of toys. His sisters names are Dakota and Flute and all 3 have different personalities.
Trombone is the most calm one of the bunch. He plays but he likes to watch the others play. He is very independent and easy to train. Their potty training has gone very well, they whine loudly when they need to go out and they know what the pee pads are for. They also sleep through the night which is a great thing.
Trombone is the biggest of the 3 because he eats the most! The foster home is filled with an older puppy that they share a room with and much bigger older dogs that they get along great.
So far barking is not an issue, I only hear them bark when they are wrestling each other.
Playtime is all the time around her but they are on a routine and very easy to train.

name: Frank
description: Sweet Frank is a Michael Phelps wannabe! He adores swimming and is fearless in the water. Next to swimming, Frank's favorite thing is going for walks and doing lots of sniffing and exploring with his volunteer friends at the shelter. Frank takes a while to warm up to new people, but once he's comfortable, that sweet and goofy personality comes out and he becomes very playful and just loads of fun to be around. He likes being close to his people (preferably in their laps), and he will rub his head affectionately on them (kinda like a cat!), and he also gives kisses. And when he gets really excited, he likes to do zoomies! Frank also has the BEST eyes. They're golden and go wonderfully with his dramatic facial expressions and adorable head tilts. Frank is also a very smart pup, and that big brain definitely thrives on physical mental stimulation. He picked up on this basic obedience skills quickly and has been a wonderful houseguest on sleepovers with volunteers: no begging for food, no getting on furniture and no accidents. And he's learning all kinds of new things in APA!'s Total Obedience Program (TOP), which is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Frank has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! Frank is learning skills like walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'place', which means he will go to a specific place in your home on command. Once Frank successfully completes all the skills on his training plan, he will be considered TOP Dog Ready! Frank is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with him after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 Fluffy, handsome, active, smart, silly and unique, Frank will make a wonderful companion to some very lucky person. Come on down and check out this handsome ball of fluff! Follow Frank on Instagram @frank_the_shepherd

name: Cooke
description:
Cooke is a happy go lucky & incredibly intelligent and active 8 year old Cavapoo that weighs 18 pounds. She has a ton of love to give, and loves to cuddle, but she also REALLY loves to play fetch! She needs and loves to be with her people. Cooke has had formal training and knows sit, down, go to bed, wait, she walks nicely on leash, and loves to train. She does have separation anxiety, so she would do best in a home without kids and where someone is always home. She does fine with other dogs, but doesn't really need them around because she loves to be the center of attention. 

One important behavioral trait to note is that Cooke does have some resource guarding habits that could escalate to aggression which we have been working with in foster care, but will likely come back at first during a transition to a new home. She needs a family that will patiently continue to work with her and keep her mentally stimulated daily. 

She is an adorable, fun loving dog with a lot of life and love to give. She’s Heartworm negative, fully up to date on vaccinations, spayed, and ready to find her forever home.

If you are interested in Cooke, please email info@texassweetiesdogrescue.org for a copy of our application. 

Cooke's adoption fee is $250 which includes shots, spay and microchip.

name: Chip
description: Sir Charles Pibbles III, or known as 'Chip' to his friends, is a true gentleman who knows how to conduct himself in good company. This beautiful pup is house and crate-trained, walks well on leash and knows 'sit'. And while he won't climb onto your furniture unless cordially invited, once he has received his invitation, he's delighted to climb up for a snuggle. Chip's polite manners don't mean he doesn't know how to cut loose and have fun. Chip loves a romp in the backyard, and he's a connoisseur of squeaky toys. He'll zoom all over the house with squeaky in mouth, and he does this adorable thing where he'll take a tennis ball from your hand in slow motion. Chip also enjoys playgroup with his canine friends at the shelter and could go home with a well-matched doggie sibling. While he can be shy with strangers, Chip loves his people and getting pets all over. He's also very intuitive, and on a recent sleepover with a volunteer, she was on the phone and raised her voice, so Chip crawled into her lap to calm her down. He definitely thinks he's a lap dog, so that's likely to happen anyway, but we're happy to give him credit for that one. Chip is in APA!'s Total Obedience Program (TOP), which is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, he has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! Chip is learning new skills like down, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'Place, which means he will go to a specific place in your home on command. Once he successfully completes all the skills on his training plan, Chip will be considered TOP Dog Ready! He is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with Chip after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 If you've got a nice big yard, plenty of toys to play with and you're looking for a handsome gentleman to escort you through life, come meet this great pup!

I asked the photographer to get my good side, then I remembered, heck, every side is my good side. Even my insides are good and sweet, they too have been patched together over the last 8 years and the result is the sweetest smartest guy you will ever come across.

They believe me to be mostly made of Australian Cattle Dog or Heeler.  My Papa was likely the bear from those Snuggle fabric softner commercials because I am told that my coat is SO SO SO SOFT…all cap letters indicating yelling about how soft I am.

I am equal parts brains and beauty and already house and crate trained.  I am about 50 pounds and really just looking for a retirement home after being left at the local pound.  I really just want a new family that understands the defurnition of furever because I don’t want to have to move again. I will make a great pawtner for strolling the streets or warming up the sheets. Are you that family?

name: Amma
description: Amma is wicked smart.' Beautiful and athletic, Amma is dog that that thrives on clear boundaries, love and exercise and likes to be challenged to keep that amazing mind stimulated. As much as Amma loves hanging out with her person, she is definitely not up for being a full-time couch potato. What she is up for is whatever you want to do and is just so happy to have you with her! Amma's a very happy pup and her tail is always wagging - she wiggles and wiggles when her friends come to get her out of the kennel, and she loves getting their pets and attention. While Amma can be wary with strangers, she becomes very devoted to her people and is so eager to do what is asked of her. Once she's completed a command, she looks at you for approval and is so thrilled when you are pleased! A medium to high energy pup, Amma likes running around the yard chasing squirrels and absolutely loves to go for walks. She follows your lead to know that new things are safe, and she also just started agility training, which is helping her build her confidence. Amma's also an amazing houseguest, is very house-trained and never had an accident on extended sleepovers with volunteers. She never counter-surfs and can be left home for long hours uncrated without any issues. Amma's volunteer trainer says Amma is one of the smartest, if not the smartest, dog she's ever known, so it should come as no surprise that she's thriving in APA's Total Obedience Program, so much so that she recently became TOP Dog Ready, which means Amma has already learned all the skills in her training plan. The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP Dog, Amma has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help her learn the skills to become the best dog she can be! Dogs in the program learn skills including sit and down, walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers, calmly walking past another dog, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called (Amma's recall is perfect) and 'place, which means Amma will go to a specific place in your home on command. Amma can easily generalize and find a new 'place' very quickly (She and her trainer practice doing this on rocks outside). Amma also knows 'walk away' for when she's too fixated on something, and she will walk away and leave it alone. And she can shake with both paws! Amma has worked hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with Amma after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 Amma is looking for a home with someone who is willing to continue her training, and she'd love one with a back yard for her to play in. If that sounds like yours, come meet this amazing pup!

name: Otto
description: Gentle and easy-going, Otto is a beautiful pup with soft white fur and the most adorable face. He's deaf and blind, but has the loveliest brown eyes and is so sweet-natured that he never barks or growls, preferring naps to trouble-making. He's very good with other dogs and is currently living with eight ranging from an Australian Shepherd to a Yorkie. In the first couple weeks in his foster home, Otto began to recognize the family members and prefers to be in the same room as them. He enjoys having his head rubbed and getting scratches behind the ears, and is becoming more affectionate and engaged with his humans every day. He's also good with the 8 year-old he lives with and enjoys being pet by him. Otto is learning how to get around the house and enjoys strolling around the garden, stopping to smell the fresh air. A favorite spot to stop and sniff is near the chicken coop. Otto isn't crazy about crates or leashes but has responded well to being allowed to move around freely. He appears to be fully house-trained with frequent potty breaks, although he manages to make it up to eight hours through the night. He always relieves himself whenever he is let outside, so trips out are generally quite quick. Otto would love a home with easy access to the outdoors and one with people who are around quite a bit. He deserves someone to love and look after him, and in return, he promises to be an easy-going and sweet companion who won't cause any trouble. If you think you can handle all that, come meet this sweet guy!

name: Nimbus
description: We gonna play or we gonna cuddle?!' Nimbus is a high energy guy who's always on the move and is a big fan of hiking and jogging. He loves tug of war and playing fetch most of all, but he's also happy to snuggle with his people when he sees its chill time. Nimbus is a huge cuddler, and every night on sleepovers, he HAS to be touching a part of his person. And if you're moving around the house, Nimbus is sure to be following like an adorable little shadow. Nimbus is a very vocal fellow, always making rumbly grumbly noises to let you know what he's feeling at all times. Usually he's feeling 'play time!' or 'I love you!' He has a particular fondness for underwear, so it's advisable to keep the special occasion variety off the floor. On the plus side, he can help with the laundry. We should also warn you about his eyes. They're so big and beautiful, and he makes great eye contact, so it's hard not to fall in love right away. Nimbus is working on politely meeting strangers and not seeing everyone and everything as a new toy. Even when you pet him, he thinks 'Oh look, your hand's a toy now!' But his manners are overall pretty good. He knows sit, down, shake, and he also waits for the 'free command before eating. The ideal home for Nimbus would be one with an active couple or single person who will give him plenty of exercise, and he'd love to have a yard to romp in. In return, he promises to love you forever. Come meet this fun pup!

name: Daisy Mae
description:
Up for adoption in Texas: Daisy Mae.





She is about 2-years-old and weighs about 62lbs. 





Daisy Mae is white with a few tan highlights, including a cute spot on her head that is almost heart-shaped. 





Daisy Mae loves being outside, just lying in the sun or shade, but is also happy inside supervising the making of her dinner or the scratching of her ears. And when she gives you that look – with her one eye outlined in black, and the other in pink, well, you just know she wants to play. 





Once Daisy Mae warms up to you she is a doll. 





We saved Daisy Mae from a shelter where she had a broken leg for at least two weeks. After working with one of our vets the break healed on its own and she's doing really well.  She has a slight limp from time to time but it doesn't slow her down... just ask the squirrels around her foster family's yard! She keeps them on the run.   Her leg will be considered healed by the end of the year. 





She also loves chasing and playing with the dogs in her foster home.





Daisy Mae also enjoys going for a walk, but needs a bit more leash training, and is sometimes suspicious of other dogs on a leash. 







She prefers not to have another dog bother her while she’s eating, and immediately goes to an available indoor x-pen to wait for her breakfast or dinner.





She has not had an accident in the house or attempted to chew anything she shouldn’t. She rides in a car like a pro.











Daisy's ideal home would be one with adults and or older children, she likes calm and chill. 





Daisy Mae is spayed, vaccinated, microchipped and housebroken. 





Apply at www.luckylabrescue.com

name: Jonni
description:
Jonni is a very carefree, joyful, super sweet, playful, and mischievous pixie. At just 18 months old, she has a lot to learn but she is clever and a quick study.? She is a purebred AKC registered bench girl, her parents are Champion & Grand Champion show dogs. 

She loves all dogs, animals & people. She is a joy to foster with a few idiosyncrasies. Jonni is affected by Addison’s disease and is currently stabilized on meds that cost $100 - $150 a month. She needs an adopter that has a strong, established relationship with their current Vet so if there are any concerns about her health she can get immediate medical attention. With this type of Vet partnership and attentiveness she will live a long and healthy life with her adoptive family.  

Jonni is active and curious, as an English Setter should be!? She would love a home with an active family and outdoor activities. Jonni is looking for a home with a secure fenced yard, she is not a candidate for no fence or an invisible fence. She really wants another playful dog friend that can run, play and keep her engaged and stimulated. 

Jonni is spayed, microchipped and up to date on all vaccinations. She is in a foster home in the Austin, Texas area. It is important to minimize the stress for dogs with Addisons so she is looking for an adopter that can come and meet her and drive her home.

We have tried a myriad of different medications, all to no avail. We respect Freya very much, and we are looking for someone who has specifically worked with special cases like this before. name: Jane
description: Update March 2018 It has been a year since Jane had a stroke to her spinal cord. She came to us a chained dog, days after giving birth to puppies, some dying in the cold. Jane showed us day one she was a survivor. See below for more history. It is now time to find Jane her home. Jane is an amazing dog and she needs an amazing home. She is a little spoiled and is a special needs adoption, requiring more time, patience and money than the average dog. Jane is not a dog that can be left on her all day. We will be happy to answer all questions about Jane's care. Jane chooses who she likes, but a treat in hand makes a huge difference. She has been in her own space for some time now, so introducing her to another dog and new humans will be taken slowly. Maintaining her quality of life and finding her the right home is our goal. She has been recently spayed and is doing quite well. She is getting even more attention, if that is possible. Team Jane continues to care for her 24\/7 and she is greatly loved by the volunteers. If you feel Jane is a dog that you can bring into your home-life-family, please go to our website and complete an adoption application. We will contact you to set up a meet and greet. Thank you. wimberleywagrescue.org History: Jane had a Fibrocartilaginous Embolism resulting in a stroke to her spinal cord March 2017 and was paralyzed from the waist down. She improved, getting mobility in one back leg, but we had to amputate the other back leg as it was not responding to therapy and interfering with her walking. After many months of therapy, she can stand and walk a short distance using her back leg, but she can move quite fast on those three legs when she wants to. She now has a wheel chair. ORIGINAL POST - March 14, 2017 We are absolutely devastated that our beautiful Jane had a mini stroke to her spinal cord. (FCE; Fibrocartilaginous Embolism). She is paralyzed from the waist down. Prognosis is good for recovery, but it will be weeks of therapy and rehab. Jane is at CTVSH receiving the best care possible. Her condition is good. As you can imagine her care is going to be very expensive. Please help us help Jane. We urgently need donations for her care. Thank you.

As a TOP dog, Bukowski has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help her learn the skills to become the best dog she can be! Bukowski is learning skills like sit and down, walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'place', which means she will go to a specific place in your home on command. Once Bukowski successfully completes all the skills on her training plan, she will be considered TOP Dog Ready! Bukowski is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with her after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193

name: Redford
description:
Redford is a high-energy 58 lb. 5 year old field English Setter who came to us from a hunting preserve up north. He has been a kennel dog and needs help adapting to home life, but he is almost fully housebroken and surprisingly quiet, only barking when he needs a potty break. He does very well in crates and kennels while his owner is away.  

Redford bonds very quickly with his people, and is very affectionate in that goofy setter way. He does guard resources like toys, (which he LOVES to de-squeak) food and even his humans. He would be best as an only dog and in a home with no children. Because of his hunting background, Redford needs lots of outdoor active time and a securely fenced space to explore. The beauty of watching this dog cover ground is only matched by the beauty of the trust and love in his eyes as he melts onto the floor and rolls over for a belly rub.

Redford is neutered, micro-chipped, up to date on vaccines, and heartworm negative. He is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX.
For an application to adopt or for more information about Southwest English Setter Rescue including our adoption requirements and transport availability, please go to http://www.swesr.org/. Please call us at 214-997-3885 if you have any questions.

name: Daisy
description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.
Hi puppy lovers! My name is Daisy. I am 10-1/2 months old. I was part of the Mother’s Day save last year by the rescue. Unfortunately my siblings and I were all very sick. I fought hard along with these nice people. It was a tough road not gonna lie, but I am a survivor! I am now healthy and beautiful if I do say so myself. I am full of life and love to play. I am spayed, current on all vaccinations, microchipped and on preventatives. I will need help with potty training but I

will work hard I promise. You must have time to work with me. I am a little to active for small children but older children and/or other doggies would be great. If you would like to fill out an application and see if we’re a match, I would love that. They said it’s on the website. www.adoggie4you.org. If you aren’t able to adopt right now but would like to sponsor me that would be great too.

name: Enzo
description:
Please give a big welcome to Enzo!  Enzo is an adorable miniature Piebald Dachshund that was found as a stray and ended up in the shelter.  When we found this little guy he was very skinny, had hookworms and was infested with fleas.  Enzo desperately needed a dental as well but we got that all taken care of for him:)

Enzo is currently being fostered in a home with dogs of all sizes and does great with them.  He loves to zip around the yard and chase after anything that dares to touch the fence or trees.  He is an escape artist so he can never be left outside unsupervised.  He can literally dig under a fence in 5 minutes.  Enzo also has a very strong hatred for cats so a home with no cats is necessary.  Enzo is crate trained but loves being able to stay out and mingle with everyone when you are not home.  He must have a bed to sleep in at night as he loves to burrow under the covers.  He does still like to lift that little leg every once in awhile but that is fixed with belly bands:)

Enzo is estimated to be around 5 to 7 years old and weighs 9 pounds.

If you would like to meet this handsome little guy please email info@texassweetiesdogrescue.org for a copy of our application.  If your application is approved one of our volunteers will be in touch with you for a meet & greet.

Enzo's adoption fee is $250 which includes shots, neuter, microchip and dental.

Sorry, no out of state adoptions.

name: Jenga
description: Jenga is a very affectionate and playful girl who loves hugs and cuddles and listening to Beyonce. She absolutely adores people and will immediately dive in for snuggles. She gets so excited sometimes that she needs to burn off some energy before returning for the pets, but after some heavy playing, she is super duper cuddly and loves getting butt scritches. This spunky pup LOVES to play and will happily chase after rope toys and squeaky toys, and greeting her in her kennel is always a blast because she gets so excited to get some attention. To go with those gorgeous eyes and great smile, Jenga also has one of the best curious faces. If you point and excitedly say 'what's that??' she will look in the direction with her eyebrows furrowed and ears perked up, and then go investigate and make sure there isn't some squirrel up to no good. Jenga loves to explore new spaces and is always on the hunt for 4-legged 'friends.' Jenga is also always up for an adventure and very quick to learn new things. You can tell that she is always thinking, and she definitely benefits from mental stimulation. She's very treat-motivated and eager to please her person, and training and agility have been great for her. She learned 'shake' in a matter of minutes, and after she does something well, she revels in the praise and affection from her trainer. So far, Jenga knows sit, come, place, and shake. Her leash skills are coming along and she gives fantastic eye contact and is thriving in her TOP dog classes. The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Jenga has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help her learn the skills to become the best dog she can be! Jenga is learning skills like walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'place,' which means Jenga will go to a specific place in your home on command. Once Jenga successfully completes all the skills on her training plan, she will be considered TOP Dog Ready! Jenga is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with her after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 Spunky, sassy, smart, loving, athletic, curious and gorgeous, Jenga will make a wonderful companion to any number of loving homes. She'd love a yard to burn off some energy, but if but as long as she can go on long hikes or runs, she should be one happy camper. She also may be able to go home with a well-matched doggie sibling. Come meet this great pup!

name: Almond
description: Quiet and reserved and so very loving, Almond is a low maintenance senior and a total cuddle bug. He may not have many teeth left, but he does has irresistibly soft fur, which is perfectly suited to Almond because he's a big fan of back scratches. Almond lives with three little doggie foster siblings and does great with all of them. Even though he loves taking naps, he prefers to stay close to where the action is, hanging out with his people and doggie pals. But his favorite place in the world is definitely snuggled in your lap. Almond is fully house-trained and does great left home alone in his crate after a few minutes of protesting that he can't go with you. Not wanting to cause too much trouble, he quickly curls up and goes to sleep until you're home again. Almond will make a wonderful low key companion to a home with people who will give him plenty of attention. In return, he promises to keep your lap warm and love you forever. Come meet this sweet guy!

name: Pandora 2 JuM
description:
Pandora 2 JuM

My offurcial name is Pandora, but I have earned the nickname of Surfer, not for my beach blonde hair, but for my curiosity with packages on counter tops.  Just how my name sake Pandora’s curiosity got the best of her and she opened up the furbidden box, I too bounce my two front paws right up on the granite and streeettttcccchhhh my snooter really far as I can to find the BEST smellin’ treats.  This perhaps is a NO NO NO, but really you should consider keeping your goodies in the cabinet, you should!

I am a 1 year old 40 poundish light reddish yellowy Labrador Retriever mix.  I have a darker red almost Vizsla colored sister named Venus.  We were locked up at the local pound on a trumped up charge of being homeless….okay it wasn’t trumped up, we were indeed actually homeless…but how is that a crime??? We were shy and not good on a leash.  I litterally freeze up when leash goes on me, so I had to be carried out by my rescuer. I still have a long way to go and could benefit from more leash walking training.

Since coming to rescue camp, I have made LOTS of new doggie friends and I am really really good at making friends of the furry variety, big small, young old, all of them.  On the other paw, people are not quite as scary as I thought, so I follow volunteer Theresa around the pasture and show her my belly for pats, I like that.

Also, as a secret….all us dogs call Theresa, not by her human name, we call her The HotDog Queen, she always has some in her pockets, always.  So if you don’t mind teaching me the leash adopt me! Or if you don’t mind carrying around a 1 year old 40 pound doggie, adopt me! I am crate trained and will make a great doggie for someone who has a weeee bit of patience.

GOD'S DOGS Rescue, in San Antonio TX, does not have a shelter - Our dogs are raised in foster homes in the San Antonio area. Each dog comes spayed or neutered, up-to-date with age appropriate vaccinations, microchipped, heartworm tested and are current with monthly flea/tick and heartworm preventatives. 

ALL OF THIS IS INCLUDED IN THE Local ADOPTION FEE OF $250.00 FOR PUPPIES and $200.00 for ADULTS. (Local is in the state of Texas). Medical records will come with each dog at the time of adoption.

IF THIS IS AN OUT OF STATE ADOPTION, TRANSPORT TO YOU is included in the adoption fee of $500.00 for PUPPIES and $400.00 for ADULTS. We transport all over the country!!

Our dogs are socialized, and we try to provide you a good understanding of the dog’s personality. Please contact us at info@godsdogsrescue.org for more information about adopting one of our dogs and puppies or fill out an adoption application at http://www.godsdogsrescue.org/adopt/adoption-application/ 

Please visit our website http://godsdogsrescue.org/ for helpful information re: transport, our adoption process and application, volunteering and fostering, and photos of our dogs/pups looking for homes!!

Thank you for wanting to adopt a rescued dog, their LIVES depend on it!

name: Juniper (8 pounds)
description:
Get ready to fall in love with Juniper. Juniper is an older poodle looking for a home to spend her golden years in. She is the perfect size (around 8 pounds) and does great with other dogs. She has yet to meet a person that she doesn’t like and will want to be near you, especially if you have some soft snacks for her to munch on. 

Juniper prefers to roam and not be confined to a kennel and has done great when she is provided with an area that is hers (with a bed and a blanket to stay cozy with). Juniper has limited vision and will do best in a well-lit environment. Even with limited vision, she quickly learned her way around the yard and house at her foster home and she will happily greet you when you call her name. 

Juniper is on medication for heart disease and it makes her have to potty a little more frequently so her foster mom recommends putting a potty pad for her to use just in case. Juniper is quickly becoming a favorite and we can’t imagine that she will be without a forever home long. Juniper can’t wait to meet you so fill out an application today!To have your home considered for adoption, read about our adoption process or fees, and find out about interstate transport, please visit our website, www.LongWayHomeAdoptables.org and click the adopt tab!

nd tied up in an abandoned shed with her brother, who sadly has passed away. Minka is a little shy and hesitant when meeting new people but offer her a yummy treat and she will follow you anywhere. Please note that visual breed identification in rescue dogs is unreliable so for most of our dogs we are only GUESSING at predominant breed or breed mix. We get to know each dog as an individual and will do our best to describe each of our dogs based on personality, not by breed label.

While we do our best to determine the breeds of our dogs, the majority are strays, and we have only general appearance, coat type, size, ear type, tail, tongue color and coat color to base breed on.  It is always possible when adopting a puppy that it will change dramatically to look like another breed.
We highly recommend that you enroll your dog in training classes.

name: BRAXTON
description: Braxton is a super playful dog who loves to play with balls. He\u2019s very energetic, funny, and a very good looking dog! As much as he likes to play, he just as much enjoys laying on the couch with you. As far as physical health goes, Braxton has it all. He loves to run, fetch, play tag (he doesn\u2019t want to be tagged, so he\u2019s VERY good at this game). Braxton is an athlete extraordinaire!  On the other hand, Braxton remains incredibly loving and gentle, and even accepting to some strangers. Not sure if this behavior is attributed to the theory that dogs only live in the \u201chere and now\u201d or if he truly has a resilient spirit, but the Shelter and his Foster Family admire him for it nonetheless. Braxton enjoys human interaction and attention.  Braxton\u2019s humor may be unintentional, but it is priceless. Some of the looks he gets on his face, especially if he\u2019s guilty of something, like drinking out of the toilet, are remarkable. Once he gets his mouth on a tennis ball, he\u2019ll often start frolicking with it, batting it around and pouncing on it like a puppy. That is his ball. It\u2019s like his security blanket. Braxton does have a preference to balls, but any other toys or ropes he can chew on, he\u2019s a happy dog. He is strong and prefers to carry a ball everywhere he goes. Everywhere.  Braxton seems to do well with other dogs. We currently have Braxton with our dog, Kodah, who is about his size, a little smaller. Braxton doesn\u2019t seem to be too bothered by another dog around. He doesn\u2019t particularly enjoy Kodah running up to him to play (Kodah LOVES to play, and it can come off a little attack-like), but Braxton just lets Kodah know he\u2019s \u201cnot in the mood\u201d and they both calm down and go about their business.   If anyone is interested in meeting Braxton, I would love to show him off!

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.

Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and a 30-day trial of 24PetWatch Pet Insurance. Adopters will also receive a Petco Pet Parent Savings Books that contain:• $100s in savings plus a coupon for a free 6 lb. bag of WholeHearted dog food.• Thoughtful care tips.• Online resources and support.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved and you are traveling from out-of-town, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time.

We do try to schedule bi-monthly meet-and-greets in Austin as interested is generated.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/
