name: Tommy 18-08-015b
description: TOMMY Tommy is listed as a 2+ year old terrier\/pit bull mix that was found stray. He is up to date on immunizations, neutered, heartworm negative, and microchipped. Tommy currently weighs 60 pounds. He is tall and lean, and a stunning black and chocolate brindle boy, with a white pattern on his chest. Tommy is a volunteer and staff favorite at Bastrop County Animal Shelter in Bastrop, TX! He is calm and sweet, and loves to be loved on. While he enjoys being outside, he really prefers lying on the couch next to his loving companion while receiving lots of pets! He is very laid back in a quiet environment. Tommy appears to be housetrained and crate trained, gets along well with small children, is dog friendly, and comes when his name is called. If he doesn't come when called initially, squat down and call his name again, and he will usually come. He has not appeared food aggressive nor does he guard toys, bones, or anything else. Tommy mostly naps during car rides. Occasionally he will try to go to the passenger front seat, but responds favorably to "get in the back when told a time or two. Currently, Tommy enjoys mile long walks in the morning and at night time. He is gentle on the leash until the last few feet before returning home. I believe this is because he knows there will be several cats near the house. He is learning the command "leave it in relation to cats and often responds well when on the leash. Tommy is also learning commands to "sit, "down, "shake, "roll over, "beg, and "speak. He is definitely treat motivated and is very smart! Tommy is a GREAT companion for someone who would like to be interactive with their dog, and he will also want to be his companion's snuggle buddy! Please contact the shelter or Terri Mueller via FB messenger or (cell) 512-332-1746 if you are interested in meeting Tommy!!!!

name: Sadie
description: Hello...my name is Sadie. I was living on the streets of San Antonio. It was hard living out there trying to raise my puppies on my own. I was really scared but I was finally caught with my pups and we ended up in the city shelter. My pups have all found homes except for me. I'm scared and luckily found a foster family to help me relax, enjoy the good life and is patient with me. I'm starting to come around. I got on the sofa and sat with my foster family on the other side. I love to be petted but just unsure of everything, still. My foster mom tells me I'm beautiful everyday and how special I am. Hoping to maybe find my forever home and can bond with them too. I'm going to be a loyal\/loving girl, I just need a little time. It still amazes me watching the other dogs interact with my human foster mom....not something I have ever seen. I'm not too big at 40 lbs. I'm all legs really. Hoping there's someone out there who will fall in love with my sweet face and give me a chance. I am living in a San Antonio Pets Alive! foster home. By adopting me, you not only give me a new leash on life; you also save the life of an additional pet who can be rescued from euthanasia and placed in foster care. If you are interested in adopting me, please email adopt@sanantoniopetsalive.org with my name and ID#. Please allow up to 24 hours to respond, as all fosters work on a volunteer basis. To find out how you can get involved and help turn San Antonio into a no-kill city, please visit www.sanantoniopetsalive.org

name: Tex
description: Available in Texas and New England: Tex here! \n\nI am a one-year-old, 65-pound lab mix whose foster mom keeps telling me that I am the complete package & when my future family hears my story, they will know right away that I\u2019m their dog! My story started on the streets of Texas where I was a stray and then one day, everything changed. These days, I know what it is to be loved and cared for while making friends with every person and dog I met. I also discovered the most wonderful thing in the world- SNUGGLING!! My favorite days are filled with car rides, walks, playing with toys in the yards, and horsing around with my foster siblings. I would love to have a yard of my own and a family that is somewhat active so we could go on adventures together! My foster mom says she is blown away at how quickly I adjusted to becoming a house dog after being a stray for so long and that I am a smart boy who is eager to learn (super eager if there are treats involved!) and please. I am house trained, crate trained, and am working hard to perfect walking on my leash. I hope my new owner will understand that sometimes new things make me nervous, but I overcome that quickly with some reassurance and patience. Here is a secret though, I am super food motivated, so I would thrive with a family who will continue to teach me new things! My foster mom tells me that because I get so excited meeting new people and dogs, I\u2019d do best in a home with older children and without cats. I am up to date on my vaccines, neutered, and microchipped. I know my story is just beginning and if you think that you are my happy ending, please visit www.luckylabrescue.com to adopt me!

name: Jax
description:
Dear Texas, We have the MOST special boy up for adoption: JAX.





He was on death's door after he was hit by a car, but he is so kind, loving and sweet the animal control officer who found him, and the shelter staff could not euthanize him. 





So they thought, "What can we do?  Oh, I know, call Lucky Lab Rescue and Adoption! They're suckers for labs in need!"  :) 





The shelter said, "We have some video to show you and we are praying you can save Jax. Everyone who meets him just sees the joy in his eyes and his will to live, even when he's in pain.  This is the video they sent us:





https://www.facebook.com/luckylabrescueadoption/videos/2361442240750542/?t=6





Yup, we saw it and we were like, "Um, holy moly! Okay, we'll give him a try."   Lucky Lab worked with a great orthopedic surgeon in Austin and Jax had surgery to help fix him up.   He's been in an amazing foster home and he is adored.  Now it's time for Jax to get his own family and keep up his rehab and grow. 





Jax is a 1-year old, 50 lb., black lab mix.  He is a joyful and affectionate dog who enjoys playing with other dogs.  





Jax would do better with older children as he's still a young lab himself. He still has some of the young lab likes to chew on things phase in him but that can be worked on.   He does best crated home alone. 





He is house trained, neutered and vaccinated. 





Jax had a severe break on his right front leg and paralysis on the left front leg.  In three months, he’s made an amazing start in his recovery.  He has gained full use of his right leg and full function of his left leg.  





He has some remaining loss of feeling on the left side of his left paw.  He is currently walking on his left knuckle instead of using the full paw.  He will use that paw to play and hold treats.





Jax needs help in the next phase of his recovery.  His right leg needs more activity to continue to stimulate bone growth around his repair.  This activity need to be on grass and soft surfaces to avoid injury to his left knuckle.  Water therapy or swimming would also be great for Jax!  As his leg is still healing, he needs to be careful to not jump down from furniture and avoid rough play with other dogs.





He is seeking a foster or foster to adopt home that can focus on increased activity for his recover.





We'd love to talk to you more about Jax! Just apply at www.luckylabrescue.com

name: Skittles
description:
Please contact Anne (abaumgartner2008@yahoo.com) for more information about this pet.Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

** This dog is living in a foster home in San Antonio, Texas. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. **
Meet Skittles! Skittles is a 10-month-old Terrier and Cocker Spaniel blend. She weighs approximately 19 pounds.Skittles is a happy girl and loves meeting new people! She also enjoys playing with other dogs in her foster home.Please understand you are commiting to providing a good home for her entire life (up to 15+ years or more) - not just until her puppy cuteness wears off. You must also be committed to housebreaking, age-appropiate enrichment and exercise, leash training, grooming needs, and positive socialization. Her adoption fee is $175. This includes her spay surgery, DhPPv vaccination, bordetella vaccination, rabies vaccination, deworming, one month of flea and heartworm preventative, microchip, leash and collar, Petco coupon book, and 30-days of pet health insurance. Please be aware that puppies, small breeds, and pure breeds do get adopted quickly so interested parties are encouraged to apply online at www.saspca.org Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m. Additional questions may be directed to abaumgartner2008@yahoo.com.

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.

Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and a 30-day trial of 24PetWatch Pet Insurance. Adopters will also receive a Petco Pet Parent Savings Books that contain:• $100s in savings plus a coupon for a free 6 lb. bag of WholeHearted dog food.• Thoughtful care tips.• Online resources and support.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved and you are traveling from out-of-town, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time.

We do try to schedule bi-monthly meet-and-greets in Austin as interested is generated.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

name: Minnie
description: Hi! My name is Minnie and I'm a 10-year-old Terrier mix and weigh about 20 lbs. Despite having a tough start on life, I still love everybody! I am a sweet and calm girl who loves to cuddle and get my belly rubbed. I'm very gentle with children and I get along with dogs of all sizes! I LOVE to give kisses and sit on your lap and cuddle, but I will lay down and wait patiently by your side if you're busy. I am a mature lady who does not require much - just some love! I am fully house-trained and crate trained and NEVER chew anything up. I'm a couch potato, so I don't require long walks or lots of exercise - I'd rather just lounge around with you. You'll never meet a dog that's happier to be with her people, so let me know if you're looking for a cuddle buddy to give you unconditional love!

name: KitKat
description: KitKat is a 1-year-old lowrider, shepherd mix who weighs about 35 lbs. She is well-behaved and is house- and crate-trained. She is OK with cats and LOVES other dogs, however, she is a little skittish around people. She is very smart and follows a few commands. She is a sweet girl and does like attention and affection, but on her own terms--she does not like to be reached for, but she will approach people on her own for pets. She happily greets her foster parents at the door when they come home and she likes to sit next to them on the couch for scratches. She will need an understanding and patient adopter who will allow her time to trust on her own terms. KitKat takes comfort and gains confidence in the presence of other dogs, so her ideal home will have at least one other dog. She does not walk well on a leash and will need a home with an attached, enclosed yard. She would do best sharing a home with older children and adults only.

He absolutely adores his foster dog siblings and gets along great with all of them. He is potty trained and crate trained and sleeps well in his crate overnight. He knows sit and learns quick so I am sure he could learn so much more! Bandit is a special little guy and will make any family complete with his charm and playful personality!

name: Chakra (slaughter survivor)
description:
Chakra is one of our LWHA dogs that came to us from China. They were rescued off the meat trucks headed to the slaughterhouse to be turned into soup meat. Our wonderful rescuers on the ground in Harbin saved them in time, and now they are ready for their forever homes here in the United States. Chakra has some issues in his back that give him a little "cha cha" to his walk. When he first came to us, he had issues controlling his urine and bowels. Luckily, this problem has greatly improved since he has been here. He's very, very smart and is super loving. His favorite place is where ever his foster mom is. The best bonus you'll get with this little guy is that he "smiles". Ask him if he is happy and he'll grin. He is absolutely adorable!!To have your home considered for adoption, read about our adoption process or fees, and find out about interstate transport, please visit our website, www.LongWayHomeAdoptables.org and click the adopt tab!

Our adoption fee is $200, and it includes spay/neuter, all vaccines, heartworm testing, fecal testing, deworming, flea/heartworm prevention, and a microchip. 

NATIONWIDE TRANSPORT AVAILABLE. See our website for more info!

name: Q & M
description:
ADOPTION PENDING.

These two Great Danes are Q and M.  They are named after James Bond characters.  They need a new home because their family has to sell their home and move into an apartment.

Q is 18-months-old harlequin and M is 2-years-old merle.   They are very sweet and definitely live up to the gentle giant stereotype.  They are house broken, kennel trained, and love being around other dogs.  They are often go to Camp Bow Wow to play with their doggy friends.  They are both very good with kids but have never been around cats.

We would like to adopt Q & M together, but will consider adopting them to separate homes. 

If you would like to give M & Q a new loving home, please fill out the adoption application on our website.

name: Papaya
description:
Papaya is a beautiful soul who is looking for her best friend. She loves car rides, long walks around the 'hood, and chasing squirrels in the yard. She is an easy, chill little dog. (25 pounds) She needs someone who can take her hiking, and maybe to the lake. She loves to go... She would be a great office dog because nothing phases her. She just about never barks here. Gets along well with all of my dogs. She doesn't care for cats much so no cats. She is kennel trained and potty trained. 

Papaya is an athletic little girl who can easily jump a shorter fence or climb a chain link fence. She needs a good 6 foot wood fence.

My adoption fee is $190 and includes spay, microchip, shots and vetting. To meet this sweetheart, please apply.
She is available through Bastrop Animal Rescue. Apply here: www.bastropanimalrescue.orgInterested in adopting a pet from Bastrop Animal Rescue? To start the adoption process, please go to www.BastropAnimalRescue.org/adopt to complete an adoption application. Thank you!

name: Bessie
description: You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.My name is Bessie. I am six months old. I weigh 13 pounds now and won't get much bigger. My max is probably 15 pounds. I sit on command, sit at door before going outside and I lay down on my bed when my foster mommy asks. I am also learning drop it and leave it because I love to pick up everything. I love all the toys they give me to play with. She is teaching me to play bite my toys and not people. Who knew they didn't like that. I give kisses now instead. I love to go out on my harness and leash. However my favorite thing to do is run and play in the backyard. I have a lot of puppy energy and I can run and run. I can fetch my ball too! She tells me inside and I run to the door and wait for her. I am doing so good on potty training. I POTTY OUTSIDE all the time now. Of course she takes me out every couple of hours right now. I bark when I know I have to go. She gets so excited when I do, gives me treats and hugs me. That is worth it!! Apparently I DON\u2019T SHED (yay) and I am super soft! My foster mom said those are great things! I love other dogs and want to play with everyone. My foster mom said there are pets called cats too but I never met one. I could be scary to small children since I am so excitable, so I need some kiddos a little older, but I do love them!! I NEED A FENCED YARD because well like I said above running is my thing. I am great cuddler too. I am CRATE TRAINED when my foster mommy can't take me to the store with her. I just take a little nap patiently waiting for her to hurry up and get home. I sleep in my crate too. I don't like to be alone for several hours though. That's no fun. Let me know if you would like to meet me!!! I want to live indoors only of course and then have fun with the family in the backyard and parks!! Please fill out an application if you are interested! Please hurry I can't wait to find my forever home!\n\n

description: An absolutely gorgeous dog, MAKENZIE is a 2 year old 73 lb. red merle catahoula. High energy, a sweet nature, and a desire to be with people are some of Mak's traits. She's a well trained inside girl, but also needs lots of outside time. This is a dog for a young energetic owner with lots of time to spend with this wonderful girl. description:

Bailey James is bonded with his brother Beau DandyBailey James and Beau Dandy are the sweetest most handsome brothers around. Bailey is a chocolate dapple who could stand to lose a few pounds and Beau is a black/silver and tan dapple who could put on a few pounds! They follow each other everywhere and are very bonded.

Both boys are very sweet and love to cuddle. They like to sleep in the big bed but are comfortable sleeping on a doggy bed too. Bailey likes to play with toys but Beau is a little shy. They like laying in the sun or beside you on the couch.

If you would like to meet a couple of loveable cuddlebugs, fill out your application today!
Love dachshunds and not ready to adopt or circumstances won't permit having a dog? How about being a sponsor or making a donation. Every one of our dachshunds receives excellent medical care along with day to day food, love and housing. Being non-profit, we rely on generous individuals like yourselves to help save these fur babies. You can do this specifically for one dog with the sponsor button on their webpage or a general donation on our “How To Help” page. Easy and quick through Pay Pal or your debit/credit card. You generosity is sincerely appreciated by all and is tax deductable. Need other ideas? You'll find tons of them on the How to Help tab. All contributions are tax deductable.

All dogs are fully vetted and housed on private property. Meetings are scheduled upon adoption approval. Thank you for your continued support to the rescue and shelter communities!

description: My name is Davina, I'm a 6 year old typical Chihuahua. I protect my humans my food and my house. Strangers are a little scary so I have to bark, but I eventually will warm up to them. I like to sleep a lot but I also like to go for walks. I have a kennel I don't like that much but the cat does lol . name: Luna
description:
Meet Luna. She was pulled from the shelter almost a year ago and was adopted. However she had issues in the home with one of the other dogs, so she was returned.

She is about 40 pounds and around two and a half years old. She is a pocket terrier mix. Holly is a sweet, sweet cuddlebug that loves being around humans. She’s never met a stranger!

She is fully vetted, potty trained, and crate trained. She did have a fatty tumor removed from her face, but there is no further medical required. Luna loves meal times, snacks, and treats. She enjoys laying on the couch. She loves rubber toys and balls to chew on as well as stuffed toys and ropes to shred.

She rides well in the car, but does PULL on the leash so some basic obedience training could be beneficial. She does not bark a lot, but has had issues with black dogs and feral cats. She obeys commands very well.

Needs to be an ONLY pet. No cats. No dogs because she gets very over-stimulated.

She has been in a foster home so long and is really really pining for her forever home.

name: Dakota
description:
Up for adoption in Texas: Dakota.





She is a sweet and happy pup that is about one-year-old and weighs about 23 pounds. She is a small dog with a big dog personality... and perhaps there's some lab in there somewhere. :)  






She is potty trained and only chews on her toys or an occasional sock if you leave it laying around. 





She is crate trained, but as of late has wormed her way into her foster's bed at night.  She loves to play hard (by herself if no other dog or human is willing to join in) and then jumps in your lap to snuggle and recover.  





She is still skittish around strangers (tends to bark and hide) but just loves people once she feels comfortable. We think some positive reinforcement training in a loving home would be great for her. 





She's very alert and aware of her surroundings. You won’t need a door bell to know when the UPS driver is dropping off a package.  





She loves other dogs both big and little. In the evening she will lay by your side (or on your lap if you let her) while you are reading or watching TV. She will be a very loyal and loving companion. She has been around teenagers in her foster home.  We don't think she'd do well in a home with young kids running around-- she's just a little shy.





Dakota is spayed, vaccinated, microchipped and house trained. 





Apply at www.luckylabrescue.com
label: not-adopted

name: Sherman JuM
description:
Sherman JuM

Dawgs invented the smellfie, that is when you take a sniff of your own body parts to check out the odor, sometimes humans do it too to make sure their pits aren’t stinky.  Yes, we know you do. Since humans stole the smellfie from us dawgs, I thought I would give this front camera human selfie thingy a try.  Nailed it. Nailed it every time.  It is an easy feat when you have the good looks of the two most desirable steeds of dawgs, the German Shepherd and the Labrador Retriever.

My ombre shaded hair fades from dark at the roots down to a creamy yellow at the bottoms.  This is natural though, I didn’t go to the salon. To top off this hunk sandwich, I have what are reportedly THE cutest wittle ears ever seen on any dawg ever. But enuff about looks, I know the mostest impawtant thing about a dawg is their personality. I have that too.

I am THE guy to do sofa selfies with #chillin. Or the guy to brag about how we just hiked the mountain and take a sweaty selfie/smellfie combo. I was chosen to be rescued from the city pound because my friendly nature out friendlied every other dawg there.

I weigh a great large-ish size of 50-55 pounds and at about 2 years old I won’t grow much more in height, but I am hoping for some belly growth from all the chicken nuggets and sirloin steaks you will be tossing my way at those dawg friendly outdoor patio restaurants. I hope to meet you soon so we can start our smellfies and selfies twogether as a family. 

GOD'S DOGS Rescue, in San Antonio TX, does not have a shelter - Our dogs are raised in foster homes in the San Antonio area. Each dog comes spayed or neutered, up-to-date with age appropriate vaccinations, microchipped, heartworm tested and are current with monthly flea/tick and heartworm preventatives. 

ALL OF THIS IS INCLUDED IN THE Local ADOPTION FEE OF $250.00 FOR PUPPIES and $200.00 for ADULTS. (Local is in the state of Texas). Medical records will come with each dog at the time of adoption.

IF THIS IS AN OUT OF STATE ADOPTION, TRANSPORT TO YOU is included in the adoption fee of $500.00 for PUPPIES and $400.00 for ADULTS. We transport all over the country!!

Our dogs are socialized, and we try to provide you a good understanding of the dog’s personality. Please contact us at info@godsdogsrescue.org for more information about adopting one of our dogs and puppies or fill out an adoption application at http://www.godsdogsrescue.org/adopt/adoption-application/ 

Please visit our website http://godsdogsrescue.org/ for helpful information re: transport, our adoption process and application, volunteering and fostering, and photos of our dogs/pups looking for homes!!

Thank you for wanting to adopt a rescued dog, their LIVES depend on it!

name: Jack - Courtesy Posting
description:
Hi, I'm Jack. My "sister" and I were running in a busy city street when our "Fairy Grandmother" saw us, tried to catch us but couldn't. She followed us home to where our owner was in a desperate financial bind, so bad that the family, my sister and I hadn't eaten all day. My owner loved us enough to let us go with the rescuer.

My sister has found a home but I'm still looking for my "furever" family. I'm five months old, half Chow and half unknown, but my Grandmother thinks there might be Collie in my ancestry. 

Grandmother says I'm very smart because I've learned to go potty outside, I behave quietly while in my crate, and sit and wait for my food. I haven't chewed on anything but my toys, which I enjoy, and I'm told that's a very good thing! However, remember, I'm five months old and love to play so if I had another young dog to play with and a fenced yard, I would be very happy.

It's estimated that I'll grow to about 40 pounds since I currently weigh a bit over 20 pounds. I look forward to your inquiries! Sincerely, Jack.

Jack is neutered and up to date on vaccinations. He is in a foster home near San Antonio, TX.

For an application to adopt or for more information about Southwest English Setter Rescue including our adoption requirements and transport availability, please go to http://www.swesr.org/. Please call us at 214-997-3885 if you have any questions.

description: Do I look terrified? That because I am. name: Marshall
description: In my picture, you can catch a glimpse of the scar down the middle of my back. Apparently, I was burned, probably by a chemical, before I got here. I don\u2019t like being this way and would like very much to trust someone, but it\u2019s going to take a long time. Children and men scare me so much, I just can\u2019t be near them. I love dogs and get quite playful around them. Someone did take me home for a while, and she thinks I have the potential to be a great dog, but I need someone with a lot of patience to let me grow out of my fear. If you think you\u2019re that person, please come see me.

name: Big Bear TC
description:
Name:

Hello!  My offurcial name on the website is Big Bear but my Foster Parents call me Sandy for short. I am not sure how Sandy is short for Big Bear, but there isn’t anything short about me, I am a Bull Mastiff blend, so I am very tall.

Favorite Quote:

Life is like a 93 pound bag of chocolates, you actually know what you are going to get.  Lemme explain.  I am a 7-8 year old fully grown up chocolate and caramel brindle striped dog. I am a grown up, so you will know exactly what you are getting, no crossing your fingers and your toes hoping that brand new puppy doesn’t grow up to be a jerkwad.

Temperament:

Friendly with people of all ages, sizes, and gender. I have done well with cats too.  I can be bossy to other dogs, so your dog will not have to mind that. I want to reiterate that I am gentle with kids, even the toddley kind.  I like to be pet, and will let you touch my paws, ears, belly and booty. If you want, I will even crawl into your lap and snuggle in your pets (on the floor, I don’t like to get on the furniture).

Exercise Sesh Level:

Extra fries? Of course!

Exer-cise NOT extra fries:

Ah….I see the diffurence there. I am easy on the short walks because of my arthritis. Doing the stairs is kinda hard too due to my arthritis.  I prefer to sprawl out on the floor (not on the furniture again that dern arthritis).

Behaviors:

I am house trained, crate trained (need treats for encouragement), walk well on leash, and come when called. I do not jump, I suppose the arthritis has a lot to do with that.  I am working on playing nicely with other dogs, and have grown to tolerate the resident dog. I know sit, shake, and lay down.

Theme Song:

Lean on Me! Or really…. Lean on You. I am a leaner, meaning I LoVE to be next to you, sit by your side, and put my muzzle in your lap. I am hoping to find a retirement home where I will have someone to lean on for the rest of my life

GOD'S DOGS Rescue, in San Antonio TX, does not have a shelter - Our dogs are raised in foster homes in the San Antonio area. Each dog comes spayed or neutered, up-to-date with age appropriate vaccinations, microchipped, heartworm tested and are current with monthly flea/tick and heartworm preventatives. 

ALL OF THIS IS INCLUDED IN THE Local ADOPTION FEE OF $250.00 FOR PUPPIES and $200.00 for ADULTS. (Local is in the state of Texas). Medical records will come with each dog at the time of adoption.

IF THIS IS AN OUT OF STATE ADOPTION, TRANSPORT TO YOU is included in the adoption fee of $500.00 for PUPPIES and $400.00 for ADULTS. We transport all over the country!!

Our dogs are socialized, and we try to provide you a good understanding of the dog’s personality. Please contact us at info@godsdogsrescue.org for more information about adopting one of our dogs and puppies or fill out an adoption application at http://www.godsdogsrescue.org/adopt/adoption-application/ 

Please visit our website http://godsdogsrescue.org/ for helpful information re: transport, our adoption process and application, volunteering and fostering, and photos of our dogs/pups looking for homes!!

Thank you for wanting to adopt a rescued dog, their LIVES depend on it!

description: You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.My name is Tyler. I came to the girls from the valley, where I was scheduled for euthanasia. My first parents had a young child that hit me with sticks, kicked me and hurt me. One day I decided to fight back, and I bit the child, so I ended up in the slammer. I am barely a year old, so my foster mom decided to give me a chance. She loves me. She lets me sleep with her, she treats me good and lets me play with toys and go for walks with her. It took me about a week to trust her, but I love her lots. Mommy says she is going to find me a special forever home that will be patient and give me the time I need to get to know you. I am a very loving dog if I know you won't hurt me. I sill follow you everywhere, snuggle with you in bed and give great kisses. Are you the special family mommy told me about? name: Ben Hoku
description: Ben enjoys learning new things and is in APA!'s Total Obedience Program. The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Ben has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! Ben is learning skills like sit and down, walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'place', which means he will go to a specific place in your home on command. Once he successfully completes all the skills on his training plan, he will be considered TOP Dog Ready! Ben is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with him after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193

name: Pringles
description: Pringles is a goofy, playful, loyal guy who adores his humans tremendously, and he can't wait to meet the ones that will love him forever! Pringles likes spending as much time with his people as possible and is constantly telling them how much he loves them by giving them kisses and snuggling them. He's full of adorable playful energy and bounces with joy as he runs around with his squeaky toys. When this goofy guy lays down, he stretches out as much as possible as if he's trying to taking up the whole room. He likes playing tug of war with both other dogs and humans and throws play bows all over the place. Pringles is so loving to all the people he meets and will greet and give kisses to anyone. While he's very excited to meet strangers, he's quick to chill and snuggle once he's met their acquaintance. Pringles could go home with a well-matched doggie sibling and has done wonderfully with the 8 year-old, 20 lb, female resident dog on sleepovers with a volunteer. They played chase around the house and tug of war, and he even lets her win sometimes! He was very respectful and gentle her since she's smaller than him - she will regularly provide corrections when she does not want to play, and Pringles listens very well. Pringles is great at sleeping through the night on his dog bed, then in the morning will come get cuddles once invited on the bed. Pringles has a pretty high energy level and would likely make a great running partner, but he's always chill on sleepovers with volunteers, and after a long walk, he loves to snuggle up and just hang out. He's fully house-trained and is making progress on his crate-training, though he's had the most success being left home with a canine friend to keep him company. Pringles walks pretty well on leash and always responds quickly when asked for a 'sit' or 'down'. He's very treat motivated and super smart and is learning all kinds new skills in APA!'s Total Obedience Program. The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Pringles has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! Pringles is learning skills like walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'place', which means he will go to a specific place in your home on command. Once Pringles successfully completes all the skills on his training plan, he will be considered TOP Dog Ready! Pringles is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with him after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 Sweet, loving, goofy, loyal, Pringles would make a wonderful companion to any number of loving homes. He'd love an active one where people are around a lot of the time and who will include him in their adventures, and a well-matched doggie sibling may go along way with this sweet boy. Above all, he just wants to provide a loving friendship to his people. Come meet this great pup!

name: Lincoln
description:
Up for adoption, or foster to adopt in Texas: Lincoln.  He is a TOTAL cutie pie! And oh so sweet and kind.

Lincoln is people, dog AND cat friendly! He's lived in a house with other dogs and cats and has done great. His favorite place is cuddled right up to his doggie foster brother, he's probably do best in a home with another chill dog to keep him company and make him feel more confident. 

He is one-year-old and 35 lbs. 

Lincoln is house trained and walks beautifully on leash and walks are about his #1 favorite thing to do, other than cuddle next to you! When you pick up his leash he dances up on his hind legs and spins in circles! He is simply adorable and you really have to meet him! 

Lincoln can still get very scared with sudden loud noises or movements from his humans so we suggest a home with calmer older children or adults. He absolutely needs a home with a securely fenced in yard-- apartment or condo living is not going to work for Lincoln. 
Sadly, Lincoln was hit by a car and he lost a toe after the accident. He's still healing up, but the rescue will work with a new foster or adopter to get him all fixed up. 
He really is a terrific, sweet and darling dog. Just a nice soul. 
He is neutered, vaccinated, housebroken and microchipped.

name: Daphne
description:
Please contact Anne (abaumgartner2008@yahoo.com) for more information about this pet.Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

** This dog is living in a foster home in San Antonio, Texas. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. **
Meet our beautiful Daphne! Daphne is a Labrador Retriever and Rottweiler blend and is 1-year-old.
Daphne was adopted as a puppy from a local shelter and raised by a family with children. At age 6-months-old, Daphne was surrendered to our rescue.
Daphne has matured into an obedient and loving dog who lives to please! She enjoys playtime with her foster brothers and sisters, splashing in her wading pool, walks around the neighborhood and area parks. Her prospective owner ideally would include Daphne in a similar active lifestyle. Daphne is house and crate trained, walks great on a leash, and sits on command. Her Labrador personality makes her super outgoing and friendly!Please understand you are commiting to providing a good home for her entire life (up to 15+ years or more) - not just until her puppy cuteness wears off. You must also be committed to housebreaking, age-appropiate enrichment and exercise, leash training, grooming needs, and positive socialization. Her adoption fee is $175. This includes her spay surgery, DhPPv vaccination, bordetella vaccination, rabies vaccination, deworming, one month of flea and heartworm preventative, microchip, leash and collar, Petco coupon book, and 30-days of pet health insurance. Please be aware that puppies, small breeds, and pure breed dogs do get adopted quickly so interested parties are encouraged to apply online at www.saspca.org. Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m. Additional questions may be directed to Anne at 210-887-8041 or abaumgartner2008@yahoo.com.

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and a 30-day trial of 24PetWatch Pet Insurance. Adopters will also receive a Petco Pet Parent Savings Books that contain:• $100s in savings plus a coupon for a free 6 lb. bag of WholeHearted dog food.• Thoughtful care tips.• Online resources and support.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time from the Austin area.

We do try to schedule bi-monthly meet-and-greets in Austin as interest is generated.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ 4/22/19 12:20 AM

name: TORA
description: Meet Tora! Tora is a darling, petite sweetheart, full of fun and personality. She\u2019s playful and affectionate, and she\u2019ll dole out her sweet hugs and kisses to anyone who gives her a moment of attention. Tora enjoys playing, and ball is her favorite game, but once playtime is over, she\u2019s all snuggles and cuddles, and she\u2019s ready to share them with her special person. This little lovebug is a smart toot, too! She does fairly well when walking on a leash, and she knows some basic commands. She\u2019s particularly skilled in utilizing her charisma to charm the socks right off you! And can you say cute! OMG, this diminutive delight is a total doll! Actually, she\u2019s the total package if you\u2019re looking for an entertaining companion. If you\u2019ve been searching for the perfect little girl to add to your family, then you need to adopt Tora!

name: French Fry
description: French Fry is an extremely affectionate pup who loves to snuggle with his people more than anything, and that smooshable face and soft coat make for the perfect cuddle buddy. While snuggle time is his favorite time, French Fry also loves to exercise and can run for miles and even catches frisbees in the air! He LOVES to play and is never without his chew toys. His rope and Kong are his favorites, he's a big fan of playing tug of war, but he's also content just keeping himself entertained with his chew toys. French Fry is very treat-motivated and eager to please and already knows sit and stay. He's house and crate-trained and does great in his crate when left alone. He walks well on leash and has been good about ignoring cats when he sees them. He's wonderful when meeting new women, and while he can take a minute or two before warming up to new men coming in the house, overall he's a genuine people-lover. Sweet, loyal, cuddly, athletic and adventurous, French Fry would love a home with outdoorsy, active people who will give him plenty of snuggle time. If that sounds like yours, come meet this great pup!

name: Dori
description:
Quick Stats
* Spayed Female; DOB estimated 2017
* House Trained
* Heartworm: Light positive, undergoing treated
* Current on Vaccinations
* Microchipped: will be microchipped by adoption
* Dogs: Cautious at first, but fine; no aggression
* Cats: Unknown
* Kids: Has been OK when meeting kids, unknown whether has lived with kids; recommend older kids.

When Dori was found, she was thin and scared. This sweetheart is now very loving with her people, but is insecure with strangers and stands back until she is sure they are friendly. She shows no aggression to humans or dogs. At a recent meet-and-greet, Dori wanted to be close to her person, but did well and was very cooperative when other people walked her on a leash. She was very gentle with small kids she met.

She is house-trained and lets you know when she needs to go outside. She is easy to correct — a simple no and she stops the behavior immediately.

Dori is seeking a gentle, kind home with a patient adopter who will help her build confidence. This beauty needs love and will be a wonderful companion for a lucky person. 

Link to Application:
http://www.gsdrescuectx.com/adoption-application.html
label: not-adopted

name: Delgado
description:
Quick Stats
* Neutered 86 pound Male; DOB estimated 2012
* House & Crate Trained
* Heartworm Negative; Current on Prevention & Vaccinations; Microchipped 
* Good with larger dogs; good with people; does not like cats or very small dogs
* Leash Trained

Delgado (which means “thin” in Spanish) was very skinny when rescued, but he now weighs 86 lbs. He is the perfect companion. His favorite thing is going on walks; he will walk right beside you without pulling on the leash. He will roll over at anytime for a belly rub. If you like cuddling, he will snuggle in bed with you, but will also sleep on the floor or a dog bed. This fast guy loves to play chase with balls, and enjoys riding in the car and sticking his head outside of the window to feel the air. He also loves to be indoors. He’s strong, but will gently take treats.

This smart guy is bilingual — he understands Spanish and English commands. He’s good with larger dogs. For the past 2 1/2 months, he has been fostered with two GSDs and one Chow, with no incidents from him. He does not care for cats or really small dogs. If he’s walking on leash he won’t pull towards them, but in his own yard he will chase them.

Delgado would make a great addition to a family with someone who will walk and play with him — but mostly who will give him love.  Please fill out the application if you are that family! 

Link to Application:
http://www.gsdrescuectx.com/adoption-application.html

name: Parker Lynne
description: When you enter the house, you can hear Parker's tail smacking against the inside of her crate because she's so excited that you're home, her entire lower half wiggling like crazy as she greets you! She's great with meeting new people, knows sit and shake, is making good progress on her leash manners and is already house and crate-trained. She also has an adorable way of crossing her legs in front of her when she's chilling on her bed. But don't let her sweet nature and those soulful eyes fool you. While Parker is a super affectionate snuggle bug who will try to cuddle with you any chance she gets, she's still a very active pup who likes to get plenty of exercise and get in as much playtime as she can. She has a very entertaining way of pouncing on her toys and is really good at fetch, always bringing the ball back so you can throw it again and again and again. She also enjoys playing with other dogs and could go home with a well-matched doggie sibling who likes to play as much as she does and can help her get her ya-yas out. Parker Lynne would make a wonderful addition to an active home who will give her plenty of exercise and attention, and she'd absolutely love a yard to romp in. In return, she promises to love you forever. Come meet this great pup!

name: Pigeon
description: With his unique coloring, big floppy ears and pretty eyes, Pigeon is one handsome pup. While he's not crazy about being at the shelter, once he's out of that environment, he's able to relax and becomes a whole different dog. When Pigeon is in his comfort zone, he's equal parts goofball and cuddle bug. He often gets a case of the zoomies, running around the yard with his ears and tongue flopping around. Then when he's all tuckered out, he just wants to hang out with his person, snuggling and giving sweet kisses. He loves being pet and makes the cutest happy face with his eyes closed and tongue hanging out. Pigeon gets very excited about ice and he LOVES big soft toys like teddy bears. He absolutely adores his stuffed animals, and he'll bring them to his person as if he's introducing his baby to them. He also goes to playgroup at the shelter with dogs that have a softer play style, and he's generally friendly when meeting new people. This good-natured pup is looking for a chill home where he can continue to blossom and show off what a sweetheart he is. In return, he promises to keep you laughing and love you forever. Come meet him!

description:
Thelma here to tell you a little about me. I’m an adult rat terrier (they think I’m about 5 years old) and I am looking for a special home. I found my way to LWHA after my human passed away. No one wanted us (I was with 6 of my rat terrier family members) and thankfully rescues stepped up to help us. I am a little shy right now and my foster mom is working to get me to trust her again. She has rat terriers of her own so I know that I will learn to trust her, it is just going to take me some time. I’m looking for a home that will be patient with me and will understand that I am worth the wait! I would love it if you had other dogs because they are helping me gain some confidence back. name: Bonnie and Clyde (bonded pair)
description:
That's right, we're Bonnie and Clyde, a couple of troublemakers that have arrived in this here town!  We're bonded for life, meaning if you take one of us... you're taking both of us!  We are still so shy as we are trying to find our footing, and it takes us a little bit to warm up to people and dogs.  The right person will be patient with us.  
Bonnie has a hernia but the Vet has reassured us that there is nothing to worry about. Being  typical puppies, Clyde likes to chew the insides out of toys and Bonnie will chew books, shoes and electrical cords if left out. Bonnie piddles when she gets scared and Clyde gets car sick. However, both use the doggy dog at their foster home with no problem.

The best news is that we are looking for a human family that can take us in and care for us.   Bonnie and Clyde are ready to find their forever home - can we meet up soon to see if we would be a match?  



Visit pugrescueaustin.com/adopt to learn more.

name: Bella Rose
description:
Hey there, fine folks of Austin.  I'm Bella Rose, but you can call me Bella for short. At 12 years old, I am officially a super senior and loving it! I'm wise, relaxed, and great with other animals.  Though I'm diabetic and my vision isn't what it once was, this does not get me down. In fact, it often means more time for you to scoop me up and let me spend an afternoon on a nice, soft lap snoozing away!
 
Are you the angel I've been looking for to give me a warm home in my golden years?  Let the Pug Rescue of Austin know.  Until then, I'll be taking a nap in my foster home.

Visit pugrescueaustin.com/adopt to learn more.

label: Peter Parker
column26: Heartworm Prevention is given on the 24th of each month Meet Peter Parker. This handsome, playful boy was an owner surrender to a local shelter and CTDR was contacted and asked to bring him into Rescue. He has received all of his vaccinations and has been neutered and microchipped. He is nearly finished with his heartworm treatment and has done really well with no complications or adverse reactions. He has learned his name and eagerly comes when he's called. His two favorite things to do are play with his Kong ball and nap on your lap. He gets along with his foster sisters and has learned to sit and catch treats tossed to him.\nHe really wants a forever home and will make an loving companion for the right person or family. Would you be ready to bring this little guy into your home? If so, please complete an application at ctdr.org.

name: Stella Rose
description: Stella Rose is sweet senior cuddle bug. Whether at home or out and about, she loves to lean in for cuddles and pets, and she makes wonderful eye contact, giving her people the most loving looks. Stella Rose is very treat-motivated, which is good because she could use some fattening up. While she's a beautiful dog and pulls off the 'supermodel skinny' quite well, we'd like to see a few more pounds on her. Stella has a nice energy level, especially for an older gal. While she loves to snuggle, she can also be quite playful, enjoys her walks and does pretty well on leash. That is unless she sees a pesky squirrel that's up to go good (and they're always up to no good), but she quickly comes back when you call her name. She's also quite friendly when meeting new people. She's house-trained and well-behaved when left home, happy to find a blanket to nap on while you're away. Stella Rose has nothing but love to give, and she wants nothing more than to share this love with her forever people. If you could use some of that in your life, come meet this sweet girl!

name: CHUCK
description: Check out Chuck with his one pointy ear and one floppy ear! We're already in love.  Chuck is a classy, calm, well-mannered gentlemen with his trademark pointed ears, model-like dimples, and scrunched face, he makes heads turn with these stunning characteristics. As if those wrinkles didn't distinguish him enough, he makes the cutest strange little noises to help let you know just what he's thinking rather than barking. Chuck is very observant of his surroundings and loves to watch the world go by without displaying any reactive behavior. We did not test him with another canine companion but could imagine his low-key demeanor would carry over in those situations but would recommend a meet-and-greet as with any addition to a new squad. He would make for an excellent apartment roommate to a human given there are skyline views or a nice porch to roam. Chuck can be your well-behaved restaurant patio companion for happy hour drinks or Taco Tuesdays as long as you're willing to share because he LOVES tacos but not so much P Terry's french fries (I told you he was unique, right?!). On weekends, he's down to get a bit adventurous and stick his toes in the waters of the Greenbelt and catch a tan sunbathing by Lady Bird Lake. Chuck is still getting used to the idea of someone leading him thru life instead of roaming the streets alone so he takes a bit of time to gain trust and will need a confident owner willing to help him build up his own. He may not walk perfectly on a leash just yet but he will not pull and can be trusted. If you're able to provide Chuck with an urban lifestyle he so greatly deserves, he'll reward you with the luxury of loyal companionship for life.   Come down and meet Chuck at Austin Animal Center today!

description: Forest needs YOUR help RIGHT NOW. He is a bit of a loud mouth in his kennel, because he feels safe in it. But he is scared to death getting out. name: Fred
description: Fred is a big love bug, a sweet and happy guy who wants nothing more than to cuddle with his people. This handsome fella has the most soulful eyes to go with that big head, and his foster mom says he reminds her of Eeyore, but with the opposite personality. He loves getting attention and being pet, and he'll put his paw on your leg if you stop and nudge you to keep going. Mostly mellow but with a bit of active side, Fred walks well on leash - unless he sees another dog, at which point he really wants to go say hi and starts breaking into play bows. We think he'd love another playful dog to romp around with, but he's pretty chill otherwise. Fred can be shy with new men coming into the home, but out and about he's fine with everybody petting him. Fred does great when left home alone and is happy to sleep on the couch until you return. He's not a big fan of the crate, but he'll go in after a treat and settles down just fine. He sleeps in his crate through the night, and when you wake him up in the morning, he gives you his belly so he can get some belly rubs in before starting the day. Although he's house-trained, Fred doesn't seem to have much training otherwise, though he does know the word 'no' and will bow his head as soon as you say it. He doesn't bark very often unless he needs to let you know something about the outside world. Handsome, loving and loyal, Fred would make a wonderful addition to a loving home with people who will give him plenty of snuggle time. If you think you can handle all that, come meet this sweet pup!

name: RIDDICK in TX
description:
Col. Potter Cairn Terrier Rescue
www.cairnrescue.comHi future Mom/Dad! My name is Riddick and I'm ready for you to take me home with you. I'm 62.5% Chihuahua, 12.5% Shih Tzu and 25% mix. Even though I'm not a Cairn the Colonel Potter group took me and have nursed me back to health. I had demodectic mange, but I'm all better now and have almost all my hair back. I love relaxing on the couch with my foster mom or playing in the back yard with my toys. I have two Cairn foster brothers and I love playing tug-o-war with them. Sometimes you have to watch me because I'm sneaky and think anything on the floor is a toy. I love kids, especially when they let me lick them! I like meeting new people, but sometimes I'm shy and I may bark at them initially. I would love to be your new family addition!FOR LOTS MORE INFORMATION ON RIDDICK ENTER OR COPY THIS LINK ONTO YOUR WEB BROWSER:https://www.cairnrescue.com/store/dogs/
Riddick is being fostered in San Antonio, TX in a PRIVATE FOSTER HOME but we allow our dogs to be adopted out all over the United States and Canada!LEARN OUR 'ADOPTION FAQS': Any questions that you may have about our adoption process, fees, transporting a dog, and our policy not to adopt to families with small children, can be answered at our main website or going directly to this link:
https://www.cairnrescue.com/service/faq/
IT IS RECOMMENDED THAT YOU READ THE FAQ'S BEFORE COMPLETING AN APPLICATION. ADOPTION APPLICATION LINK: https://www.cairnrescue.com/adoption-application/
MEET ALL OF OUR AVAILABLE CAIRNS : https://www.cairnrescue.com/store/dogs/
**** FOSTER HOMES NEEDED! ****
YOU can make a huge difference by fostering just one dog. ONE dog, ONE time a year = ONE life that could be saved! Each and everyday we have the opportunity to save more Cairns in need, but we can't do it if we don't have the Foster Homes to place them in. Would you like to learn more on how you can help? 'Saving just one dog won't change the world, but it surely will change the world for that one dog.' 4/17/19 4:47 PM

name: Kratos JuM
description:
Kratos JuM

*Lemme set the scene* I am sitting patiently on a leash in a cozy bookstore staring at the shelves of Doggie Self Help books.  I spot one labeled “100 Ways To Make Your Owner Feel Guilty” and another page turner “How To Make Their Bed Your Bed”. I am gonna read these and dog ear all the impawtant pages and tips. I cannot wait to try out these tips on YOU!

My name is quite the misnomer. Do not google it, you might not choose me if you do.  Kratos is a fairly mean brute in Greek mythology, and I am not mean at all. My tail will tell ya that I am quite a happy guy, especially when humans sweet talk me. I am mild mannered for my age, accept treats ever so gently and already have some leash skills. Plus I know how to do a SIT.

I am labeled as a German Shepherd mix because of my black saddle and tan undermarkings, but this black and yellow combo often comes from Labrador genes as well. I have the blocky head and draped ears of a Lab. I am 1-2 years old and 50 pounds of handsome sauce. The volunteer lady said my fur is ultra soft and you will want to snuggle me.

I am a young guy and would be ideal for outings to go explore the great outdoors and then take it easy later in the great indoors. Please consider me as your new dog, I need to see how many crumbs I can guilt you out of with my pretty amber peepers. GOD'S DOGS Rescue, in San Antonio TX, does not have a shelter - Our dogs are raised in foster homes in the San Antonio area. Each dog comes spayed or neutered, up-to-date with age appropriate vaccinations, microchipped, heartworm tested and are current with monthly flea/tick and heartworm preventatives. 


ALL OF THIS IS INCLUDED IN THE Local ADOPTION FEE OF $250.00 FOR PUPPIES and $200.00 for ADULTS. (Local is in the state of Texas). Medical records will come with each dog at the time of adoption.

IF THIS IS AN OUT OF STATE ADOPTION, TRANSPORT TO YOU is included in the adoption fee of $500.00 for PUPPIES and $400.00 for ADULTS. We transport all over the country!!

Our dogs are socialized, and we try to provide you a good understanding of the dog’s personality. Please contact us at info@godsdogsrescue.org for more information about adopting one of our dogs and puppies or fill out an adoption application at http://www.godsdogsrescue.org/adopt/adoption-application/ 

Please visit our website http://godsdogsrescue.org/ for helpful information re: transport, our adoption process and application, volunteering and fostering, and photos of our dogs/pups looking for homes!!

Thank you for wanting to adopt a rescued dog, their LIVES depend on it!

name: Caesar
description:
Quick Stats
* Neutered 75-80 pound Male; DOB estimated 2017
* House Trained
* Heartworm Negative; Current on Vaccinations; Microchipped
* Good with people, but probably too big for small children
* No cats
* Learning how to walk on a leash, as well as general manners and obedience

This big hunk of burning love is a work in progress. Caesar is extremely smart and willing to please, but he needs a strong leader whom he respects and who will take the time to work with him. Without boundaries and structure, he will take over, which is not good because of his size and strength. Ideally, his adopter should be experienced with the breed.

Caesar has already made great progress and is getting better every day. Regular walks are recommended, as well as ball playing. He loves toys and balls; he will carry one around and may try to train you to throw it for him. Caesar should probably not go to a home with small children because of his size and energy level.

If you can give this gorgeous boy the exercise, structure, and great home he needs, please apply!

http://www.gsdrescuectx.com/adoption-application.html

name: Gretchen (referral)
description:
GRETCHEN (referral): CONTACT JESSA MORENO 830.221.7826 JESSAMORENO127@GMAIL.COM

Quick Stats
* Spayed 80+ pound Female; DOB estimated 2018
* House Trained
* Heartworm Negative; Current on Prevention & Vaccinations; Microchipped 
* Good with dogs and people

Hello! I’m Gretchen! I am super sweet and love people. I will be your very best friend and follow you around constantly. I love toys and snacks. I will sit, shake, lay down, and stay for snacks. 

I DO NOT like to be alone. I will be the best dog ever if you don’t leave me alone. I will go into my crate and won’t destroy it trying to get out, but I will yelp and cry. When I’m alone, I cry a lot. That’s why mom and dad can’t keep me in our apartment. 

I really would love a big back yard to run and play in! I walk O.K. on a leash, but I’m a big girl and pull sometimes when something catches my attention. Mom uses a training collar and that helps a lot. Mom and Dad leave me loose at night and I don’t tear up or chew anything! I really would love a new best friend who can be home with me all day. I hope you pick me!

Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. **Meet our adorable Marsha!Marsha is a 3-year-old Schnauzer blend. She weighs approximately 12 pounds.Marsha was saved from a south Texas shelter where she was scheduled to be euthanized. She is a friendly girl that loves everyone she meets! She lives in a home with other foster dogs and enjoys playing with them. She is crate trained and housebreaking is progressing nicely.Marsha has been diagnosed with heartworm infection. Dogs acquire heartworm infections when they are bitten by a mosquito that was infected with heartworm larvae.Dogs with heartworm infection live happy, high quality lives as long as they are given appropriate care. Heartworm infection is relatively common in the United States, so we are in need of caring adopters like you that are willing to open their home to a dog with heartworm infection. We think that our heartworm dogs have just as much to offer their new adopters as any other dog and they deserve a chance at life.You are truly saving a life by adopting a heartworm positive dog! We provide all the medications to treat the heartworms to include 6-months of Advantage Multi® and 2-months of doxycycline.Her adoption fee is $200. This includes her spay surgery, DhPPv vaccination, rabies vaccination, deworming, 6-months of Advantage Multi®, microchip, leash and collar, Petco coupon book, and 30-days of pet health insurance.Please be aware that puppies and small breed do get adopted quickly so interested parties are encouraged to apply online at www.saspca.org.Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio TX 78232. Event hours are 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m. Additional questions may be directed to sagdinfo@aol.com.

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.

Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and a 30-day trial of 24PetWatch Pet Insurance. Adopters will also receive a Petco Pet Parent Savings Books that contain:• $100s in savings plus a coupon for a free 6 lb. bag of WholeHearted dog food.• Thoughtful care tips.• Online resources and support.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved and you are traveling from out-of-town, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time.

We do try to schedule bi-monthly meet-and-greets in Austin as interested is generated.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

name: Bebop
description: Bebop walks great on a leash. He likes hiking and is learning new tricks and can sit, shake, lay down, and stay. He also loves his cuddles and car rides. This handsome pup also enjoys learning new things and is in APA!'s Total Obedience Program. The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Bebop has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! Bebop is learning skills like sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'place', which means he will go to a specific place in your home on command. Once Bebop successfully completes all the skills on his training plan, he will be considered TOP Dog Ready! Bebop is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with him after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193

name: Fideo
description: Fideo is low energy gal and a lover of relaxing pastimes like naps and sunbathing, but she's still pretty spry for her age and isn't beyond a few zoomies around the house or a roll in the grass. But she's definitely up for napping anytime of the day and will try to nest in any spot that looks remotely soft, whether that be a pillow, a blanket or the laundry. Fideo doesn't demand a lot of attention, but expects it when she seeks it out. She will climb in your lap for pets and nudge you with her head to let you know you're not done. She's pretty independent and likes to be in the same room as you and sometimes nap next to you or on your lap. She seems curious with strangers, though she doesn't want any new person to touch her until she knows they're cool. But once she warms up, she'll greet you when you come home with a rapidly wagging tail and her adorable snaggle tooth smile. And she gives kisses! Fideo naps when left home alone and stays in an xpen with a puppy pad. She did figure out how to get out of the xpen on the first day (she just needed to scoot it over three feet and then she was out!), but she was well behaved for her few hours of freedom. She sleeps quietly through the night, is house-trained, hasn't shown any destructive behaviors and doesn't whine. Fideo goes on 'walks' in the backyard, and while she doesn't seem to know any commands, she's great on leash and loves exploring the yard. She also likes to sweep the kitchen floor for crumbs. Fideo has lived with multiple dogs in the past and should do well with smaller or older pups. She hasn't lived with cats but totally ignores the neighbors cat when he is hanging out in the yard. Laid back, smart and independent, Fideo is a low maintenance lady who's just looking for a home that's as chill as she is. Come meet her!

name: Jacob
description: I want all the pets from everyone!' Jacob is one of those dogs who's never met a stranger, and he melts into every person he meets. A total cuddle master, Jacob's favorite thing is to snuggle and get and give affection. This sweet guy just loves being with his humans and wants to be by their side at all times. He'll lay his head on your lap to let you know it's time for tummy scratches, and he'll also 'talk' to you when he wants you to pay attention to him or if you're not picking up on the cue for the belly rubs fast enough. name: Bentley
description: Heartworm Prevention is given on the 12th of each monthBentley is an adult Standard Longhaired Dachshund. He weighs about 27lbs, but his best weight would be about 22lbs. He is on a diet and not real happy about it. He is a beautiful Black and Tan boy. He loves attention and exploring house and yard. He gets along well with his other foster siblings. CTDR is not sure of Bentleys complete background. It seems he was rescued and put in boarding last year and after a few weeks the boarding facility could not reach his rescue contact. It seems he was abandoned again at boarding. This facility continued to care for Bentley and could not bring themselves to surrender him to the city shelter. They believed he would not survive. You see, Bentley is \u201cBlind\u201d. There is no obvious cause like Glaucoma, cataracts or trauma. After a few more weeks of non contact from Bentley\u2019s rescue CTDR was contacted. As is usual CTDR stepped up. Bentley was vetted and tested negative for heartworms. He is now living comfortably (Except for diet) in his foster home. But he would like his own \u201cForever Home\u201d. Bentley is a low energy boy, who is happy being loved on by his people and exploring his surrounding like most dachshunds. He does bump into things a little more often than others, but that does not slow him down any. Bentley has been good both in his kennel and about going outside to do his business. I will describe Bentley as \u201cSpecial Needs Dog\u201d , but he really is not. If you are interested in a really good looking and loving companion please contact CTDR with any questions.

name: Ruby Sue
description:
Up for adoption in Texas and New England: Ruby Sue.





Ruby Sue is about 1.5 years old and weighs 42 lbs. 


She is laid back but loves to play.

She is housebroken and crate trained. 





There are not children in her foster home, so we'd recommend a home with adults or older children. 





Ruby Sue will fetch a ball if you throw it. She loves just checking everything out and sniffing away!!





She walks well on a leash and knows the "sit" command. 


??

name: Ivy
description:
Up for adoption in Texas: Ivy.





Ivy is a beautiful black lab mix, about two years old, weighing 40 pounds.  She is house-broken and crate-trained, as well as up-to-date on her vaccinations and heart-worm negative.





Ivy is friendly and attentive to people.  She loves to cuddle and will climb up on your lap if you let her.  She is very treat-oriented, great for training! 


Her foster parents have already (nearly) trained her to wait by her dinner when told “sit” and “stay.” 





She is gentle, but has a habit of using her mouth when playing.  Her foster parents have worked to break her of that habit, but occasionally it still comes out.





Ivy also has a great sense of curiosity and is obviously an intelligent dog.  She’s a “prairie dogger,” standing on her hind legs to see what is in someone’s hands or on a table or counter.  Even though she sniffs, she has never taken any food she hasn’t been explicitly given.





If allowed, Ivy would be a stereotypical squirrel and car chaser, and is super interested in her foster parents’ cat.  Although she is not hostile to the cat, she would chase it if she could.  With time and an no-nonsense, stand-your-ground cat, she would learn to tolerate one. But every cat is different, so we can't guarantee purrrrfect placement. 





We think Ivy was kept alone and outside before she came to Lucky Lab Rescue.  She barks and growls at other dogs when on a leash, but has had good interactions at the dog park.  


She needs more socialization with dogs and would thrive in a home with a bigger, older dog who would be who can show her the ropes. We can arrange a meet and greet for her if an adopter currently owns a dog.

name: Hercules Bernard EC
description:
Hercules Bernard EC

I feel like I should be offuring you a pint of whiskey or bourbon from a barrel around my neck, but all I have to offur you is a swift drink out of the toilet bowl, is that something that would interest you? I guess I wouldn’t make a very good bartender after all if Toilet Water was always my cocktail of choice.

St. Bernards are known for our heroism and floofy coats, and movies like Beethoven. I would rather be known for my great manners and mastery at chasing cats but never actually attacking them, now that takes will power. I am a 1 year old, purebred St. Bernard at about 105lbs and a little underweight still.

I am great around many other large dogs, like a Lassie dog and an Irish Wolf Hound, it is like a story book of heroic giants around here. I seem to be house trained, good on leash and ride great in the car. My mutto is “always hope for the park, even if you know it will be the Vet.” Gotta have faith.

My social skills do need a bit of brushing up, almost as much as my rugged coat. I was found abandoned on a deer lease near Mexico. They are not sure of my history, but they think I was an outside dog mostly, because I prefer to be outside.  Note to self: ask me that question again in the 100 degree summer, but for right now in winter, outdoors are cool.

I am not well socialized in the city and seem to enjoy being a country bumpkin. Gun shots don’t phase me, but city sounds make be wary.  I will need a home that understands my personal space boundaries. I LOVE attention and rubs, but I get a little nervous if you grab my tail or squish my face.  I do give a warning growl when you have entered the NO RUB ZONES, so I am okay with kids that understand the NO RUB ZONES.  I do not like people who think they can rub all over me willy nilly like I am a bottle of coconut oil, so for best results, no young children or toddlers would be ideal and safest bet.

I am looking for a home that is well suited for a large fluffy young dog and will manage my idiosyncrasies, like boundaries and no rub zones. I really am hoping for a country cottage over a city condo and hope to have a BIG yard to romp in, hopefully with another large dog to pal around with. Do you fit my bill?

GOD'S DOGS Rescue, in San Antonio TX, does not have a shelter - Our dogs are raised in foster homes in the San Antonio area. Each dog comes spayed or neutered, up-to-date with age appropriate vaccinations, microchipped, heartworm tested and are current with monthly flea/tick and heartworm preventatives. 

ALL OF THIS IS INCLUDED IN THE Local ADOPTION FEE OF $500.00. (Local is in the state of Texas). Medical records will come with each dog at the time of adoption.

IF THIS IS AN OUT OF STATE ADOPTION, TRANSPORT TO YOU is included in the adoption fee of $700.00. We transport all over the country!!

Our dogs are socialized, and we try to provide you a good understanding of the dog’s personality. Please contact us at info@godsdogsrescue.org for more information about adopting one of our dogs and puppies or fill out an adoption application at http://www.godsdogsrescue.org/adopt/adoption-application/ 

Please visit our website http://godsdogsrescue.org/ for helpful information re: transport, our adoption process and application, volunteering and fostering, and photos of our dogs/pups looking for homes!!

Thank you for wanting to adopt a rescued dog, their LIVES depend on it!

name: Sooni
description:
Please contact Jamesa (roxysrescue@yahoo.com), 713-882-2610 for more information about this pet.Hi, my name is Sooni and I am a very loving and affectionate dog. I am always looking to please you. I will walk by if you are sitting and lick your hand or knee and rest my head in your lap looking for a pat on the head. I will also lay down and turn over for a belly rub.
I love daily walks and car rides. I get excited as soon as you get my leash. I am calm and tolerate but it may be better if there are any kids in the home they be over 8 years old.
I am very scared of fireworks, rain, and thunderstorms! I will hide under your bed even though I don't fit.
There are two other dogs in the home and I do get along with them and watch them but I don't play with them, I’m more into loving my human family. I also love to play around with my owners but I don't know how to play with toys even when my owners have tried to teach me. I was rescued when I was about 6 months old and just never knew what toys were because I was out alone trying to survive.
I loved to sleep in my favorite chair but now I sleep on my own large pillow on floor or in my kennel. You don’t have to close my kennel as I am trustworthy, obedient and not destructive to any personal items in the house. I do like a hard chew bone to play with and chew on all day,
I clown around on the floor and refuse to move while my humans are eating. I don’t beg but I plea with my big beautiful eyes.
I am a loyal dog and will protect your home and will give lots of barks to warn you until I see my owner is safe or if I “know” you.
This is me clowning around on floor and refusing to move while people eat.
Thank you for reading about me!
