Ace is a 1 year old 12 pound mix of 100% cuteness! Every time we look at him, we are intrigued as to what his parents look like. Whatever their breeds are,  Ace is one of a kind!  He is super sweet, a little shy sometimes at first meeting but a few treats, lots of love and he becomes your shadow.   He is definitely ready to bond with his own forever family.

Ace is very playful, loves toys, chew sticks and is very treat motivated.  He likes to run around the yard, happily exercising himself but would also be a great walking or running companion. He’s has a playful easy going personality with other dogs and the children he has met. He loves to snuggle and has no problem with couch time! 

He is working on potty training and is comfortable with crate training. Ace is micro chipped, neutered, fully vaccinated, heartworm negative and on prevention.


** Please note: Due to their size, our dogs are not suitable for homes with children under 5..

We do not have a facility, all dogs are fostered in the homes of our volunteers. If you are interested in adopting a dog from Lil' Paws Maltese Rescue and other Petite Paws, please visit our website at www.lilpaws-malteserescue.org and fill out an adoption application. This is the first step in our adoption process. Our goal is to place our dogs in safe, stable and loving homes in the Austin Metropolitan area. Thanks for looking!

Lil' Paws Maltese Rescue and other Petite Paws depends on donations to keep the dogs in our program healthy. Many health issues are taken care of before a dog leaves a rescue: spaying, neutering, immunizations, dental care, and in some cases major surgery. Because of the cost of this care, donations are essential to enable us to continue our work. If you would like to show appreciation for what we do and help us continue to do it please go to our website homepage and click the donate button. We thank you in advance for your support.

name: BUDDY
description: Buddy is the epitome of resilience. After his owner died and nobody in the family could care for him, he lost the only home he ever knew and was surrendered to the shelter. But then Buddy decided this wasn't such a bad place after all and we all finally got to meet the real Buddy! The confident, goofy, sweet Buddy. The very chatty Buddy! That's right\u2026 Buddy has all the gossip and he wants to tell you all about it.    Oh, you're looking for a housetrained dog? Check!     One who walks nicely on a leash? Check!   You're also looking for a dog who likes to go on hikes and explore? Check!  And you want a dog who is sweet and happy even after all he's been through? Check!    Buddy lived with a poodle in his last home, and we think with proper and slow intros, he could live with another dog again. More than anything, though, Buddy is looking for a human to come scoop him up and remind him that it's all gonna be okay. He'll return the kindness with sweet Buddy kisses.    As a member of the Orange Dot Crew, Buddy goes home with a harness, training voucher, and all the support and guidance you need. description: Named after a certain stud running back, Ezekiel (Zeke) A087402 is a handsome neutered male estimated to be 5 years old.  He appears to be a mix of border collie and possibly terrier.  He weighs 18 lbs. and is heartworm negative.  Zeke really enjoys being around other dogs and adores his humans.  He walks nicely on leash.  He is crate trained and seems to be house trained as well. label: not-adopted

name: Shatzi
description: Shatzi is a very sweet pup who loves giving kisses, rolling around in the grass and cuddling with her people. And she's already proven to be an excellent houseguest! Shatzi's fosters report that she's been a really easy dog to have around. When she first arrived in foster, it was clear she was used to getting up on furniture, but when she did get on the furniture and was told 'no', it took her no time for her to understand and it hasn't been an issue since. She does get to sleep in the their 17 year-old's bed with him and she loves that. She also asks to go out in the backyard by herself to relax in the grass or sun on the deck. Shatzi does very well left home alone in a crate, and when her people are getting ready to leave, she gets in her kennel on her own and waits for them to give her a treat and close the door. She has excellent leash skills, doesn't pull, and when she gets back from the walk, she stays in a 'sit' before being invited into the house. She also knows 'shake' and 'lay down'. She's non-reactive to dogs when out on her walks, and she's been great with the resident kitties! One of the cats likes to love on Shatzi, and they hang out around each other. The other cat is completely in control with Shatzi. They get along perfectly fine, but Shatzi certainly gives her her space because she doesn't want to be swatted at. This sweet girl would make a wonderful addition to any number of loving homes. Come meet her!
label: not-adopted

name: Rasta
description: Rasta has so much love to give, and she adores anyone who she thinks will give her attention. She's goes right up to new people, wagging her tail and hoping they'll pet her. She loves the attention and will try and cuddle on whoever will let her. When Rasta first got in the car with her foster mom, she was so excited that she hopped right on her lap and looked out the window, ready for whatever adventures awaited her. Then the first thing Rasta did when she got home was fall asleep on her foster mom's lap. This sweet girl LOVES to cuddle, and she will climb right up on the couch and lay on top of you. And if the lap's not an option, she insists on having at least some part of her body touching you. She even puts her paws on you and tries to pull you closer to her. While Rasta likes getting out for her walks, she is extremely calm and chill in the house. She pretty much just falls asleep whenever it's tv time, but then gets very excited to go outside. She already knows sit, shake and down, and she even sits on her own when the leash comes out, though her tail wags the entire time. Actually, Rasta's tail literally never stops wagging. She's just so happy to be doing anything with her people, whether that's inside doing nothing or outside in the sunshine. She follows her foster mom around like an adorable shadow - whether she's doing the dishes or just getting something out of the closet, Rasta is right there, laying at her feet wherever she stops. Rasta is house-trained, does very well left alone and doesn't bark or cry when you leave the house. She does great uncrated, just sleeping on the couch and never chews anything or gets into anything she's not supposed to. She listens when you call her and just a very obedient dog. Affectionate, loyal, adaptable, low maintenance and so well-behaved, Rasta would make a wonderful addition to any number of loving homes who will give her plenty of attention and include her in their activities. In return, she promises to love you forever. Come meet this sweet girl!
label: not-adopted

name: JJ
description: JJ is a true gentlemen through and through. He certainly looks like a regal elder statesmen with his silky coat and dignified little mustache. And he has a gentle and polite personality to match. Though his energy level is quite low, he is never grumpy or offended if other dogs or cats get in his space with their antics. He gives them a 'Good day to you sir!' and moves on with his day, no drama required. JJ's biggest joy in life is to mosey around and explore. He loves walks. They are more like extended sniff sessions. Do not expect to get miles in, but he loves them. He also loves to laze quietly in the backyard for hours and be pet and be near you. He enjoys soaking in all of the wonders life has to offer at a nice calm pace. If you are all about stopping to smell the roses, and the grass and the blue bonnets and that candy wrapper and that butterfly and that prickly pear and that tree and that rock and then the tree again, then you should definitely meet JJ!
label: not-adopted

name: Macy
description:
Adoption applications should be filled out to expedite the process:
http://www.lilpaws-malteserescue.org/joomla/adoption/adoption-application.html

Monthly Meet & Greets 
Petco (in Leander) every 1st Saturday of the month
Pet Supplies Plus (Parmer & Mopac) every third Saturday of the month

Macy is a female poodle mix and is about 8 years old.  She gets along well with the other dogs that live in her foster home.  She is very affectionate and likes to sit with her family in the evening but she also likes to run and play in the yard.  Macy has made great strides in housetraining and now uses a doggy door.  She is current on vaccinations, microchipped, and spayed.  She has had a dental and her teeth are in good condition. She has dry eyes that require that an ointment to be applied daily.  Macy weighs about 13 pounds.  Although she is shy with strangers, once she knows you are ok, she is very friendly.

Adoption Fee $350

** Please note: Due to their size, our dogs are not suitable for homes with children under 5..

We do not have a facility, all dogs are fostered in the homes of our volunteers. If you are interested in adopting a dog from Lil' Paws Maltese Rescue and other Petite Paws, please visit our website at www.lilpaws-malteserescue.org and fill out an adoption application. This is the first step in our adoption process. Our goal is to place our dogs in safe, stable and loving homes in the Austin Metropolitan area. Thanks for looking!

Lil' Paws Maltese Rescue and other Petite Paws depends on donations to keep the dogs in our program healthy. Many health issues are taken care of before a dog leaves a rescue: spaying, neutering, immunizations, dental care, and in some cases major surgery. Because of the cost of this care, donations are essential to enable us to continue our work. If you would like to show appreciation for what we do and help us continue to do it please go to our website homepage and click the donate button. We thank you in advance for your support.
organization: Lil Paws Maltese Rescue and other Petite Paws

name: Sugar
description:
Hi, my name is Sugar and you might ask how I got to be so sweet. After all, in my seven years in this world, I have changed homes at least six times! Starting out as a non-hunter just minutes from being listed on Craigslist by a Texas backyard breeder/hunter, I was saved by SWESR, but moved from foster to adopter to foster to adopter; you get the picture. The thing is it was through no fault of my own. Sadly, my persons met with unfortunate accidents, illnesses, and did the very best for me by recognizing they could no longer take care of an active young dog. The best part is that I was loved and respected on each stop. If it weren’t for all those persons being so nice to me, I just wouldn’t have become the sweet Setter I am today. My name definitely fits. But now I need a permanent furever home.

I am a happy, healthy, girl with sparkling brown eyes and a smile as big as the world. My coat is the softest white, and I sport one quite fetching apricot patch on my left ear. While I love snuggling on the couch with the best, I am certainly not a couch potato! I need daily walks and a large fenced yard with lots of room to run. If you are looking for a fabulous walking companion, I am your girl. And while I might be a little excited to start off, by some Setter miracle, I do not pull on my leash. And besides as a pocket-setter, I only weigh a slim and trim 35 pounds. I promise to be your best buddy, inside and out.

I am crate-trained and am happy to do all my business outside as long as you will go out with me regularly and not forget me outside. My current foster Mom is so impressed how well I fit in with her pack of dogs and cats so quickly. She thinks I will do best with another dog brother or sister who will join me in playing and being busy in the backyard, with you not too far away of course. And she thinks I need a person who will give me lots of singular attention and be with me most of the time. That’s because when I am left alone too much, I get a little worried and nervous that I’ll be shipped off yet again. I really want the chance to a part of a stable, active family who will enjoy being with me forever.

I get nervous in the car and then curl into a ball so I am not a candidate for a long volunteer transport to a new home and flying to a new home would be scary for me and I might cry the entire way. I’ll do ok in the car with my new person after I have some time to realize I am not going anywhere other than an outing.

I learned some really quick escape skills in a previous home where I was able to bolt out of the door and go for run-abouts. Sometimes I came back on my own, sometimes they had to come corral me back. My foster mom says I need a home with very secure doors and gates and a home with kids coming and going won’t be a good match for me because I am certain to take advantage of any open door or gate. And I won’t come back when you call me. After all I’ve been through she says a very secure home is a must for me.

When I arrived at my current foster home near Austin, TX, I was all decked out in pink: collar, leash, harness, and crate. And you guessed it, I am pretty in pink, but I really don’t care what color my leash is, just as long as there is a loving and lively person at the end of it.

Sugar is spayed, up-to-date on vaccinations and tests, on heartworm preventative and microchipped.


For an application to adopt or for more information about Southwest English Setter Rescue including our adoption requirements and transport availability, please go to http://www.swesr.org/. Please call us at 214-997-3885 if you have any questions.

name: Red
description:
Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

** This dog is living in a foster home in San Antonio, Texas. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. **
This cute little guy is Red! Red is an 8 pound, 5 month old terrier blend who is playful and sweet. He can often be found snuggled up with the other puppies at adoption events.
Please understand you are committing to providing a good home for his entire life (up to 15+ years or more) - not just until his puppy cuteness wears off.
You must also be committed to housebreaking, age-appropriate enrichment and exercise, leash training, grooming needs, and positive socialization.
His adoption fee is $175 and includes his neuter surgery, DhPPv vaccination, bordetella vaccination, rabies vaccination, deworming, one month of flea and heartworm preventative, microchip, leash and collar, Petco coupon book, and 30-days of pet health insurance. Please be aware that puppies, small breeds, and pure breeds do get adopted quickly so interested parties are encouraged to apply online at www.saspca.org.
Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m. Additional questions may be directed to sagdinfo@aol.com.

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and a 30-day trial of 24PetWatch Pet Insurance. Adopters will also receive a Petco Pet Parent Savings Books that contain:• $100s in savings plus a coupon for a free 6 lb. bag of WholeHearted dog food.• Thoughtful care tips.• Online resources and support.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time from the Austin area.

We do try to schedule bi-monthly meet-and-greets in Austin as interest is generated.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

name: Lilleth & Radar
description:
Lilleth and Radar are a bonded pair. She is about 8 and he is about 7; she is a beautiful white with fawn patches and he is a handsome fawn.  Lilleth figured out the dog door right away and then held it open while Radar figured it out. He defers to her.

Lilleth is great at crawling up in your lap and snuggling. She is smart as smart can be and looks after Radar. She is an excellent walker and a joy to live with. She learned where her bed was and the house rules very quickly. She is heartworm positive but ABR always helps with treatment and it does not have to be difficult now.

Radar’s a pretty good snuggler too and he is very polite. He listens and follows direction very well. He’s a bit more stocky than Lilleth. They both get along with other dogs but we don’t know about cats or kids. Radar is a good walker too. He is just a bit incontinent but ABR has seasoned fosters who can help you with that.

These two, Lilleth and Radar, are very special, very easy to live with Boxers. If your house just seems empty now, these two can fill it up with warmth and smiles right away.

name: Kit
description: Kit is a very distinguished gentleman. He has a regal look to him, but not so regal that he doesn't appreciate a good butt scratch! Kit is so overjoyed by a good butt scratch that he folds himself up into a fat furry donut of love and happiness when he gets them. Belly rubs too. It's not uncommon to look over and see Kit sitting nearby with a big smile on his face, waiting for you to give him some. This handsome guy is a huge fan of people and will follow you around the house and nudge you with his nose to let you know it's time for pets if it's been a while. And as long as Kit gets a healthy dose of affection, he's generally happy to lay by your feet while you work or watch tv. Kit really loves walking around with tennis balls in his mouth, and he'll even carefully select one out before he goes for a walk: 'Hmm, what are we in the mood for today, old chap? Perhaps a Penn 100? Smells like it was a good year.' Kit's also a pretty low maintenance pup to have around. He has wonderful manners in the home, he's house-trained and will tell you when he needs to go out. He walks great on leash as long as you keep an eye out for squirrels (this boy gets very excited about those darn squirrels), he knows 'sit' and is perfectly well-behaved when left home alone. Kit's one of those dogs who can't help but bring a smile to your face. And who doesn't need more of that in their life? Come meet this great pup!

name: Matthew
description:
Up for adoption in Texas and New England: Matthew.





Wow!! What a handsome boy! 





Matthew (or Mattie as we shorten it to) has it all! He is two years old and weighs about 60lbs. 





He is active and loves going on walks, playing with a ball and tug of war, but is also a snuggler!





Mattie is a happy go lucky, excited to meet you boy! 





He stayed briefly with a foster who had a cat and did ok, but we can't guarantee he's going to be friendly with every cat. Sometimes it also depends how dog savvy the cat is too. 





He is mostly good with other dogs, he has a dominant, alpha dog persona and will stand his ground to hold that spot. So he'd need a meet and greet if potential adopters have another dog in their home, their dog should be more submissive. 





Mattie is housebroken and crate trained. He is good home alone, he stays in his crate with a Kong with peanut butter inside. He will bark once then settles down. 





He has done well in his foster homes with adults and kids and even had fun during a sleep over. 





His favorite play activity: Kong’s with treats. balls. Ropes for tug of war. He walks really well on a leash.





He knows sit, stay and paw.





Cutest behavior: When he curls into a little ball on the couch to relax/sleep or when he crosses his paws when he gets on my bed while I get ready for work.





He tries to counter surf but will get down when you tell him to get down.





Mattie is neutered, vaccinated and microchipped.


Apply at www.luckylabrescue.com

name: Axel
description: Hi Hi Hi. What do you want to do? I'm up for anything!' Axel loves to play and is so adorable when he's doing it! He's like a big happy puppy - he loves all toys and is a big fan of playing fetch and tug of war. While he can be shy when meeting new men, once he warms up, he becomes a very affectionate guy who wants to be pet all over and will climb right up in your lap to smother you with kisses! Axel gets all happy and wiggly when he knows he's going for a walk - he's amazing on leash, loves to go for runs and stays right by your side, making great eye contact. Axel is so eager to please his people and is very treat-motivated, so training's a snap. He's also fully house and crate-trained, hasn't shown any destructive tendencies in the home, and he knows how to shake with both paws! As much as Axel loves to play and go on adventures, he has a medium energy level and settles in nicely at home, happy to snuggle in close for a night in. Axel is learning all kinds of new skills in APA!'s Total Obedience Program. The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Axel has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! Axel is learning skills like sit and down, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'place, which means he will go to a specific place in your home on command. Once Axel successfully completes all the skills on his training plan, he will be considered TOP Dog Ready! Axel is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with Axel after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 Fun-loving, gentle and so very sweet, Axel will make some lucky person very happy. When he looks at you with those adoring eyes, we think you'll be won over instantly. Come meet this great pup!

name: Brennan
description: Brennan is a sweet young lady who LOVES affection (giving and receiving!). Before she came to APA!, Brennan had a pretty rough life, but other than not understanding what to do with toys at first, you could hardly tell with how cuddly she is. Brennan revels in the amounts of affection lavished on her by her friends at the shelter, and her absolute favorite thing is being in their laps. She particularly loves when her friends hold her like a baby and rock her back and forth. And we hope you like dog kisses, because Brennan loves to love her people right back! Brennan has a moderate energy level but still enjoys her walks and does well on leash. She also does fine being left home alone in her crate, as long as she has her beloved chew toys to keep her company. She's very treat-motivated and eager to please her people, and she's learning all kinds of new skills in APA!'s Total Obedience Program (TOP), which is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Brennan has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help her learn the skills to become the best dog she can be! Brennan is learning skills like sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free', coming when called and 'place', which means she will go to a specific place in your home on command. Once Brennan successfully completes all the skills on her training plan, she will be considered TOP Dog Ready! Brennan is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with her after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 The ideal home for Brennan will be one with affectionate humans who can lavish her with the attention and love she deserves. If you think you can handle all that, come meet this sweet pup!

MISSYS HAVEN CANINE Rescue, in San Antonio TX- ALL of our dogs are raised in the San Antonio area. Each dog comes spayed or neutered, up-to-date on vaccinations that are appropriate for their age, microchipped, heartworm tested and on current on monthly flea/tick and heartworm preventative. 

ALL OF THIS IS INCLUDED IN THE ADOPTION FEE OF $200.00 FOR LOCAL DOGS AND $250.00 FOR PUPPIES. ( Local is in the state of Texas)! Medical records will come with each dog at the time of adoption.  Some dogs are part of our ambassador program and their adoption fee varies.

IF THIS IS AN OUT OF STATE ADOPTION, TRANSPORT TO YOU is included in the adoption fee of $400.00 for adult dogs and $500.00 for puppies. We transport all over the country!!

All our dogs are socialized and we try to provide you a good understanding of the dog’s personality. Please visit our website for more information about what we do; http://www.missyshavencr.org. You will also find helpful our adoption application and pictures of our all our dogs/pups looking for homes!!

Don’t forget to like and share us at http://Facebook.com/missyshavencr

If you are interested in adopting, please fill out an application, once submitted we will contact you for a meeting. Also, we only adopt young puppies out of area once they reach 10 weeks old. OUT OF STATE ADOPTIONS: We do allow out-of-state adoptions for dogs, however, the adopter MUST pay for all transportation fees. NOTE: As we believe proper healthcare of one's pet is a requirement of good ownership, MHCR only adopts out dogs that have been fully vetted and altered. Thanks!

Please apply http://www.missyshavencr.org if you are interested in adopting from Missy’s Haven Canine Rescue. More information available by contacting info@missyshavencr.org

name: Bradley Cooper
description: A STAR IS BORN!! Meet Bradley Cooper. This handsome fella shares a several traits to his famous name-sake. Most striking are his baby blue eyes. You truly can get lost in his puppy dog eyes! Pictures do not due him justice. He also has the best hair!!! So soft and silky. He's such a lush. He loves to be cuddled and snuggled. Also like his name-sake, Cooper is such a charmer. So loving and sweet, playful and silly. Unfortunately for being only 3 months old he's experienced some of the worst things in life already. There's a lot we don't know, but what we do know is that he has a spinal injury. Perhaps from being hit by a car? It's unclear. He was also dumped at a high killer shelter by his previous foster. Can you believe it? He deserves nothing but the best in life, but he's has a rough start and a long road ahead. He currently doesn't control over his hind legs. All he wants to do is run and play, like every other puppy, but has very limited mobility. He's doing GREAT given everything he's been through and incredibly resilient. Cooper is the perfect little gentleman. He's smart and picking up commands very quickly and highly motivated to please. The road to recovery is still unclear, and we'll keep you updated!!! So keep checking back on the journey. We are currently accepting donations and application from adoption.

name: Riley (referral)
description:
RILEY (referral): CONTACT CERA.THERRIEN@YAHOO.COM. 214-549-6389

Date of Birth: March 2016; Gender Male; Breed: short hair German Shepherd; House Trained? Yes; Crate Trained? No, high anxiety in crates; Heartworm Negative; Current on Heartworm Prevention; Neutered; Not microchipped; Good with other dogs; Don't know about cats; Good with children. 

Riley is literally one of the sweetest, most attention-loving dogs you will ever meet. He is good-natured, but very high energy and high anxiety. He is slightly small for a full grown male at 63 pounds. His coat is short and healthy with minimal shedding.  

Riley loves to play fetch and be petted, and is extremely patient with kids (my baby would pull and hit on him and he would just let her). Riley needs a lot of attention.  He would do very well in a home with someone that is there most of the day, or with several children or other dogs.

Riley has anxiety and does not liked to be locked up.  If you need to lock him in a crate or room he will relentlessly scratch and try to figure a way out.  In fact he knows how to open some unlocked doors, and once scraped his face & scratched his eye to escape from a crate, so he would not do well in a home that requires crating.

Riley also likes to roam, so he needs a new home with a backyard that has a completely fenced perimeter with 6' height. (He easily jumps over 4' fences). He is too smart about finding ways to escape, but always comes home and tries to open the front door to get back in.

description: \u201cStar has nothing but love to give and deserves to be spoiled!\u201d - Star\u2019s foster mom Star\u2019s foster mom believes Star would do best in a home with children as she seems to brighten up whenever children are in the room. In fact, Star sleeps with her 8-year-old foster brother.   Star LOVES toys, enjoys walks, and likes being outside, but she\u2019s also a superb couch cuddler. name: Cami
description:
Please contact JoEllen (sagdinfo@aol.com) for more information about this pet.Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

** This dog is living in a foster home in San Antonio, Texas. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. **

Meet our beautiful Cami, she is a spayed female Great Dane who is around 3 years old and fully grown weighing in around 100#. Cami is a sweet girl who gets along well with the other dogs in her foster home. Her ideal home would be one on the quieter side as she doesn't really love a ton of people in and out of the house, (the same frequent visitors are no problem for her) Cami is past the puppy shenanigans stage but will need some time and understanding while she settles into her new environment. Cami is VERY food motivated and has picked up her sit command quickly, she's very intelligent.

Please understand you are commiting to providing a good home for her entire life (up to 12+ years or more) - not just until her puppy cuteness wears off.

You must also be committed to housebreaking, age-appropiate enrichment and exercise, leash training, grooming needs, and positive socialization.

Her adoption fee is $300. This includes her spay surgery, DhPPv vaccination, bordetella vaccination, rabies vaccination, deworming, one month of flea and heartworm preventative, microchip, leash and collar, Petco coupon book, and 30-days of pet health insurance.

Please be aware that puppies, small breeds, and pure breeds do get adopted quickly so interested parties are encouraged to apply online at www.saspca.org.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m.

Additional questions may be directed to sagdinfo@gmail.com

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.

Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and a 30-day trial of 24PetWatch Pet Insurance. Adopters will also receive a Petco Pet Parent Savings Books that contain:• $100s in savings plus a coupon for a free 6 lb. bag of WholeHearted dog food.• Thoughtful care tips.• Online resources and support.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved and you are traveling from out-of-town, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time.

We do try to schedule bi-monthly meet-and-greets in Austin as interested is generated.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

name: Snickerdoodle
description: Hi, I\u2019m Snickerdoodle!\n\nMy life prior to SNIPSA had been a little ruff. I was found dumped at a local grocery store roaming around the parking lot begging for anyone to help me. It was 28 degrees outside and I was cold and hungry. Thankfully, some SNIPSA people happened to be the ones I chose to follow around that evening and they immediately took me in. After a warm bath, a belly full of food, and a nice welcome from their resident pup, I was finally happy and relaxed. They brought me to SNIPSA where I got everything I needed to be a healthy girl ready to find my very own forever home! I have to say I have fully embraced this pet life! I absolutely enjoy the company of my human and four-legged family members. I love to be loved on and am very submissive. I don\u2019t mind water when taking my baths\u2026it sort of reminds me of a relaxing spa day. I am quickly picking up house training and crate training and walk pretty well on a leash if I do say so myself. And if looks could score me a home, I am the whole package, with my cinnamon swirl coat and yellow-green eyes! Do I fit in with your family? I really hope so! Fill out an application today at www.snipsa.org

name: Minnie
description: My name is Minnie, I'm a beautiful soft and shiny black Labrador retriever. I'm a little shy but a very sweet little girl. I love to cuddle and watch movies, but I will also play a fun game of tug of war with you. I'm gentle around children and I do great around other dogs too. I'm not aggressive or overbearing. I love to go for car rides, and I even do great in a shopping cart or stroller. I'm already crate trained, and I don't even cry or bark when told it's bedtime. I do like my toys but I really just want to find my forever home. Will you adopt me? I am living in a San Antonio Pets Alive! foster home. By adopting me, you not only give me a new leash on life; you also save the life of an additional pet who can be rescued from euthanasia and placed in foster care. If you are interested in adopting me, please email adopt@sanantoniopetsalive.org with my name and ID#. Please allow up to 24 hours to respond, as all fosters work on a volunteer basis. To find out how you can get involved and help turn San Antonio into a no-kill city, please visit www.sanantoniopetsalive.org

name: Tiger
description: This HANDSOME boy is Tiger. He's a 80 lb. hunk of Love.... he loves other dogs, kids (we recommend they be 12 and older) and people! Everywhere he goes, people are drawn to his striking looks and sweet temperament. If you're looking for a love bug on the larger size, we have you covered! Tiger is very smart and observative. While at the refuge he has learned many commands as well as how to control his puppy ways in order to have manners. He's been on many social outings and would definitely make a wonderful "sidekick" for an individual or the whole family. While we haven't seen him in a home, we believe he'll be somewhat of a couch potato who will be happy to have a few play rounds, romps or walks a day. He doesn't tolerate extended heat too well so don't count on him being a running partner. Tiger would love a home with another dog or two he could play with...any size but the bigger the better! He would do well where there is an area big enough to get his romp on before he lounges in some shade. He loves children but, as with any dog of his size, needs supervision for now around the little ones because he's still a pup at heart and, in high excitement, still wants to jump. A stronger willed owner to give him consistent direction will ensure he blooms into the wonderful family companion we know he will be. To meet Tiger in person, fill out an adoption application on our website, wimberleywagrescue.org, and then we'll contact you. Thank you!

name: Scarlet
description: Scarlet is a peach, and waiting for that perfect home to call her own. Scarlet knows all the ropes when it comes to her house manners and even knows how to sit, stay, and kennel up. She is crate trained and loves to cuddle up in her crate with a warm fuzzy blanket. Scarlet gets along great with other dogs, cats, kids and specifically women who don't wear big scary hats! She can sometimes be a bit choosy when it comes to her male friends and will definitely want a meet and greet with everyone in the home to make sure personalities match! (She has never been mean, just scared). Scarlet is such an easy going girl and adored by so many. She loves tummy rubs and has a tickle on her belly. She loves a good face scratchy scrub too. Once she becomes your best friend, she wants nothing more than to follow you everywhere and be the best companion there is!

name: Maverick and Cotton
description:
They were both saved from different shelters, at different times, but ended up at the same foster home. That's when the magic happened.  Their foster is moving and can't keep them any longer and we'd love to find them a forever home together! 





Cotton is 11 months old and she weighs 40 lbs.





She loves to play with other dogs, and people. She is kid friendly with the ones she's met in her foster home. She walks on a leash. Is crate trained, loves her toys and snuggles on the couch. She is medium energy and really smart.





Cotton is spayed, microchipped, vaccinated and housebroken.





Maverick is about 1-2 years old.  He is SUCH a handsome boy! He loves people and is a big cuddle-bug





He's smart too! In a short time he has learned sit and is working on fetch. Maverick is house trained too!


Maverick is a gorgeous future diamond! He'd love to have a forever home. His happiness is so evident, look at his happy smiles in all his pictures.





He is pretty good with most dogs, he may have more of a dominant personality. 





He is neutered, vaccinated, microchipped.


If you'd like to adopt this duo just apply at www.luckylabrescue.com

She is about two years old, weighs 45lbs and is a beautiful blonde/red color.  CAT and DOG FRIENDLY! 





Molly loves to cuddle, it her favorite thing. She doesn't seem to mind cats, and loves to play with other dogs. 





She does well around the kids in her foster home. We'd recommend older kids for her.

ADOPTION PENDING.

Izzie is one of three Great Danes that were seized and taken to the Montgomery Co. shelter because owner was arrested.   The mantle was returned to the original breeder, because she was microchipped.  Black got adopted from the shelter and Izzie was picked up by a volunteer and brought to our rescue.

Izzie is a very sweet girl.   She is estimated to be 3 or 4 years old.    She is a small Dane weighing only 90 lbs.  Still a very large dog. Being that she is smaller built, she will probably not have hip issues and live longer.    She's been spayed and is current on all vaccinations and she is also microchipped.  

Since Izzie was in a home with two other dogs, it will probably be best if she goes to a home with other dogs.  

If you are looking to add a sweet dog to your family, please consider Izzie.  If you haven't filled out our adoption application  yet, please go to our website and fill it out.  Keep in mind, our system is outdated and we do not get applications if they are filled on the phone, so it's best if you use a PC when filling out the adoption application.

name: Sookie
description:
Meet our Sookie girl! This rescue has quite the story and we hope you take the time
to read it. Surrendered to SNIPSA several months ago from her owner of many
years, we thought Sookie’s biggest hurdle in finding her a home would be her age.
Yet we knew her breed and cute little face would wiggle its way into someone’s
heart. She received a flurry of interest in just days of her posting on our website and
landed herself an adoptive home. All seemed well until her adopter grew very ill and
returned Sookie to SNIPSA. We were faced with finding her yet another adoptive
family. And this is where her story get’s more colorful.

Sookie had a mild cough but just enough of a cough that we thought it may need
further attention. A battery of tests were performed which showed a primary lung
tumor. Bad news for our Sookie but good news we had some wonderful surgeons on
our side. She underwent another battery of tests including a CT scan, more
bloodwork, and additional x-rays (can you see the dollar signs adding up?) There
didn’t appear to be involvement in the adjacent lymph nodes or evidence of other
neoplasia. Tumors like this had a decent prognosis so we decided to give her the
benefit of the doubt with surgery. Dr. Israel and her team at Blue Pearl went to work
opening her chest and removed the diseased lung and tumor. She spent a few nights
in an oxygen cage with a chest tube – a dog ICU of sorts. Two days later, she was
ready to be discharged! Dogs have an incredible way of healing and she was no
different. And the best news yet…the biopsy revealed a low-grade malignancy with
complete excision of the tumor. We expect Sookie to live several more fruitful years.

Our sweet Sookie is back up for adoption and looking oh so fashionable in her pink
t-shirt. She wags her tail, eagerly waits for her foster mom, and lounges on her
favorite dog pillow. She can go on walks and be treated like any regular 10 year-old
dog. She is easy going, mild mannered, housebroken, devoted beyond measure, and
the perfect lady. She has had one noteworthy adoption story in her short time in our
care and we are ready to find her a lifelong home. Please give her a chance. Fill out an application for Sookie at www.snipsa.org!

name: Roadie
description:
Roadie: (noun) An individual who travels with a band and assists with setup and organization whose main goal is to ensure the show runs smoothly.

First off, I don’t have any strong musical preferences. My tail will keep time to whatever’s playing! And I’ll never change the station in the middle of your favorite song because that’s just rude.

For a while there, my life was like a sad country song. Somehow I ended up alone on the street during one of the coldest weeks in recent history. Thankfully, a lady took pity on me and brought me in out of the cold. I don’t usually brag, but I suspect my dashing good looks and charming personality sucked her in. Plus, it didn’t hurt that I know how to be a good houseguest.

Turns out, people are easily impressed. I mean, they’re all gushing about how smart I am just because I’m housetrained, crate trained, not destructive, love other dogs and kids, and I’ll sit and lie down on command. Cattle Dogs are known for their smarts, so little do they know, I’m capable of way more than what I’m currently letting on! I mean, the above qualities are good, but just wait till you start to train me and I’ll give you something to be impressed about. Plus, everyone knows it’s important to keep learning new things in life. Who knows, you might even learn a thing or two from me! For example, I can teach you how to be cool. It just seems to come naturally to me! Everyone who meets me says so anyway. Thanks, y’all! Back atcha!

Now, I could see how you might be thinking I sound like the perfect dog right about now, but because dogs are incapable of lying, I’m going to confess something I hope won’t be a deal breaker. There was one time when I was first rescued that they left me outside overnight and that’s when they learned two things about me:
1) I’d rather be inside with you – No brainer!
and
2) I have no problem scaling a 6’ fence
My current foster spends lots of time with me, plus they have other dogs to keep me company, so they’ve never seen any signs of me wanting to escape. I’m a fast learner, after all. I know a good thing when it’s right in front of me. But they’re not my forever home, I’m just crashing here till my own special person comes along! They’ve gotten to know me pretty well and they think I’d do great with another playful dog to hang out with. Or if you want me to be your only dog, that’s ok as long as you have time to spend with me.

So there it is. The good, the bad, and, well there is no ugly here! What do you say? If you make me your Roadie, I’ll worship you like a rock star and pretty soon you’ll be my biggest fan in return.

If you would like to meet me or just want to get more information on me just call 210-619-1980 or email info@homesforpets.org.

name: Puppy Lola
description:
Up for adoption in Texas and New England: Puppy Lola.
This sweet puppy is 10 weeks old and weighs 14 lbs. 
When you first meet Lola she is excited to greet you.  She will come running to you but then may run away until she has you figured out. 
She is great with other dogs and is medium on the energy scale.  Lola is nearly housebroken too! 
She is crate trained and stays in a crate with her brother. She can go five hours without an accident.  She will sleep all night without having to get up. She stays with her brother in a crate. 
Lola knows her name and responds to kennel, no and treats.  She also knows her schedule and will run to her crate for meals and treats.
She doesn’t really play fetch but she runs after her brother trying to steal the ball from him.
She loves to play with her brother and foster siblings.  She likes playing with her toys and stealing socks from you.  
She is not leash trained yet but is working on sit and down. 
Lola loves to walk on her hind legs and grab your leg with her front paws, like a toddler.  She waits to be picked up and cuddled.  She also puts herself to bed at night which is adorable!   
Lola is a very happy and energetic dog.  She isn’t afraid to let you know when she needs attention She loves playing with other dogs and would do best in a house with other dogs. After a few hours of playing she is ready to sprawl out and have a nap on the couch.  She is very gentle in her play but is a normal puppy and loves to chew. She enjoys stealing shoes and socks when she thinks you are not looking.  She happily gives them up when you redirect to a toy!    
Apply at www.luckylabrescue.com

description: Rosco has experience living in a home with a small child, a small dog and a large dog. He seems to be in great health, he's heartworm negative and fit at just under 60lbs. name: Gator
description: Gator is a 3-year old male weighing between 70-80 lbs. He is a big boy but super-gentle, friendly and loving with people. He is a very sweet dog who is learning to adapt to indoor life. He loves to go outside and hang out with his foster parents. He is potty trained and has had no accidents. He does well in a crate. We have not heard him bark once since he's been home and he doesn't mind the neighbor's dogs barking next door. He doesn't seem to pay any attention to them. He is very gentle with us and loves attention. It seems he will be good with another female dog but male dogs scare him a bit. I think he would do well with kids who are respectful of his space. He likes to play a bit in our backyard but not too much (maybe this will change as he gets more comfortable). He just likes to be wherever his foster parents are, and follows them everywhere. I am living in a San Antonio Pets Alive! foster home. By adopting me, you not only give me a new leash on life; you also save the life of an additional pet who can be rescued from euthanasia and placed in foster care. If you are interested in adopting me, please email adopt@sanantoniopetsalive.org with my name and ID#. Please allow up to 24 hours to respond, as all fosters work on a volunteer basis. To find out how you can get involved and help turn San Antonio into a no-kill city, please visit www.sanantoniopetsalive.org

name: Fred
description:
Up for foster or adoption in TEXAS: Fred. He is SO darn handsome! 





Fred is about one year old and weighs about 65 lbs. Overall Fred is the friendliest, kindest dog. He would make a great family dog or be an awesome companion for anyone who is a young adult.





Fred is a very sweet and loving dog. He absolutely loves people and gets very excited when you walk in the door.





Fred is always up for a walk and is great on a leash.





He likes his crate if food is associated with it so it's a happy place. He has been sleeping through the night in his crate, and we don't hear a peep from him. 





Fred does best when he has either an activity or a toy to play with. Give him a bone and Fred will entertain himself all day with it. 





He's never lived in a home with young kids, so we aren't sure how he would do, but overall he is incredibly sweet. 





Fred does well with overall dogs, he is friendly and happy. When we got Fred he wasn't neutered, but now he is. He has had a little residual, how do we say, "humpy-ness" just with dogs, but he's now getting better that his post neuter testosterone is dropping. 





LOL, so now he's neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, house trained and Fred deserves a great home! 





If you'd like to apply for this gorgeous boy please go to www.luckylabrescue.com
label: not-adopted

name: Alex
description:
Adoption applications should be filled out to expedite the process:
http://www.lilpaws-malteserescue.org/joomla/adoption/adoption-application.html

Monthly Meet & Greets 
Petco (in Leander) every 1st Saturday of the month
Pet Supplies Plus (Parmer & Mopac) every third Saturday of the month

Though Alex had a rough start in life, his disposition is such that he takes things in stride. Alex is a sweet, happy boy who loves to play. He is just as content to play with a toy by himself, tossing it in the air and shaking it, as he is having you throw it and running after it. Sometimes he even brings it back but he's working on it! He is a good mix of being very affectionate and independent. He has a quirky smile (a broken jaw that didn't get treated) but it doesn't seem to bother him and he can eat well and has no problem taking treats softly from your hand. It also doesn't bother him to have one good eye. He is a loveable, bouncy boy that would love to be in his furever home...are you that special person who could fulfill his wish?

** Please note: Due to their size, our dogs are not suitable for homes with children under 5..

We do not have a facility, all dogs are fostered in the homes of our volunteers. If you are interested in adopting a dog from Lil' Paws Maltese Rescue and other Petite Paws, please visit our website at www.lilpaws-malteserescue.org and fill out an adoption application. This is the first step in our adoption process. Our goal is to place our dogs in safe, stable and loving homes in the Austin Metropolitan area. Thanks for looking!

Lil' Paws Maltese Rescue and other Petite Paws depends on donations to keep the dogs in our program healthy. Many health issues are taken care of before a dog leaves a rescue: spaying, neutering, immunizations, dental care, and in some cases major surgery. Because of the cost of this care, donations are essential to enable us to continue our work. If you would like to show appreciation for what we do and help us continue to do it please go to our website homepage and click the donate button. We thank you in advance for your support.

name: XENA
description: Howdy! My name is Xena!  I was hit by a car prior to arriving at Austin Animal Center on January 5, 2019. My right front leg was badly broken and I had to undergo an emergency orthopedic surgery. The surgery went well, but I was crate-ridden and limited from physical activities for weeks while my leg healed. On Valentine's Day, I was taken in by my foster family, who wanted to help me recover and be the very best I can be. I was a little nervous at first, but I quickly settled in and learned that it was a great place! Now, I'm back to my happy and playful self, and while I love my foster family, I can't help but wonder where my forever family might be... I promise to continue being a good girl and to keep learning and growing! I love my canine foster brother, and I LOVE toys - you don't even have to play with me, I'll play by myself if you're tired!  If you want to ask about how to become my forever family, email my foster at btran.n@gmail.com

name: Blanche
description: Blanche is between 3 & 5 years old and weighs about 35 lbs. She is an easy-going girl with a low-key, lovable & friendly personality! She's beautiful, playful and great with children!! name: Trip
description:
Please contact JoEllen (sagdinfo@aol.com) for more information about this pet.Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

** This dog is living in a foster home in San Antonio, Texas. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. **
This fat and sassy boy is Trip! Lovingly assigned this name because he will trip you! If you've ever known labradors you know what we are talking about. He sticks VERY close to his people. Trip is approximately 5 years old and fully grown weighing in around 90#. Trip is heart worm positive, but we provide meds to assist in treating this at home with minimal impact to day to day life. Trip LOVES to play fetch and will retrieve til he drops!
Please understand you are commiting to providing a good home for his entire life (up to 15+ years or more) - not just until his cuteness wears off.
You must also be committed to housebreaking, age-appropiate enrichment and exercise, leash training, grooming needs, and positive socialization.
His adoption fee is $250. This includes his neuter surgery, DhPPv vaccination, bordetella vaccination, rabies vaccination, deworming, 6 months heart worm prevention, two months of doxycycline, microchip, leash and collar, Petco coupon book, and 30-days of pet health insurance.
Please be aware that puppies, small breeds, and pure breeds do get adopted quickly so interested parties are encouraged to apply online at www.saspca.org.
Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m.

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.

Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and a 30-day trial of 24PetWatch Pet Insurance. Adopters will also receive a Petco Pet Parent Savings Books that contain:• $100s in savings plus a coupon for a free 6 lb. bag of WholeHearted dog food.• Thoughtful care tips.• Online resources and support.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved and you are traveling from out-of-town, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time.

We do try to schedule bi-monthly meet-and-greets in Austin as interested is generated.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

name: JOE
description: Joe is not your regular Joe. Unlike his name, he\u2019s unique in so many ways. But Joe\u2019s a reserved guy, and he doesn\u2019t like to brag. He\u2019s not going to let you in on who he is right away. He\u2019ll make you work for it, and he\u2019s definitely worth the effort.  It\u2019s obvious Joe is handsome. And he will tell you he likes to explore. He also enjoys observing and take in the world around him. He\u2019s accommodating, though it\u2019s clear he has a mind of his own. He has the intelligence to use it. But he\u2019ll do as you ask because he is cooperative. His only request is that you listen to him on occasion.  Joe is a quiet dog. He doesn\u2019t bark or jump, and he\u2019s not one to do backflips in his kennel to get people to notice him. He\u2019s waiting for you to notice him. And once you do, you won\u2019t be able to look away. You\u2019ll want to take him home and make him a part of your family.

name: Kase JuM
description:
Kase JuM

Wow guys, I just googled the meaning of my name to see if Kase was actually a word.  Good news guys! Very insightful. Kase means cheese.  Do I need to explain any further why that is awesome???  It’s cheese. I love cheese. Or as an urban dictionary alternative it also means a young hot guy, so win win for me.

The only part that really confused me when googling my name origin is that the Rescue Lady said I am the color of honey and sweet as honey too, I guess she didn’t realize I was actually made of cheese, not honey. I am about 1 year old, so defurnitely a young guy and 50 pounds of hunky cheese muffin as well. Put some honey on it if you want to. I won’t stop you.

The Rescue Lady thinks my coloring comes from being a mash up of not just honey and cheese, but Shepherd and Shar Pei too. I am cool around other dogs. And even though I haven’t met any kids yet, the Rescue Lady thinks I would make a swell family adventure dog, because of my friendly and sweet nature. And not to sound too cheesy, but I am ready to solve the kase of the missing family and get adopted!

GOD'S DOGS Rescue, in San Antonio TX, does not have a shelter - Our dogs are raised in foster homes in the San Antonio area. Each dog comes spayed or neutered, up-to-date with age appropriate vaccinations, microchipped, heartworm tested and are current with monthly flea/tick and heartworm preventatives. 

ALL OF THIS IS INCLUDED IN THE Local ADOPTION FEE OF $250.00 FOR PUPPIES and $200.00 for ADULTS. (Local is in the state of Texas). Medical records will come with each dog at the time of adoption.

IF THIS IS AN OUT OF STATE ADOPTION, TRANSPORT TO YOU is included in the adoption fee of $500.00 for PUPPIES and $400.00 for ADULTS. We transport all over the country!!

Our dogs are socialized, and we try to provide you a good understanding of the dog’s personality. Please contact us at info@godsdogsrescue.org for more information about adopting one of our dogs and puppies or fill out an adoption application at http://www.godsdogsrescue.org/adopt/adoption-application/ 

Please visit our website http://godsdogsrescue.org/ for helpful information re: transport, our adoption process and application, volunteering and fostering, and photos of our dogs/pups looking for homes!!

Thank you for wanting to adopt a rescued dog, their LIVES depend on it!

name: Sam
description: Hi I'm Sam! I'm 8 years old and looking for a brand-new forever family. My last one didn't end up working out, but that's ok. I really love meeting new people and making friends! You may have noticed that I'm a little on the heavy side; the vet says that I need to lose some weight so I'm on a diet. Losing some weight will help me feel more comfortable and allow me to be more active and play! I would love a home where I can get nice leisurely morning and evening walks that are easy on my senior joints. We could spend the heat of the day hanging out inside and I would love to just follow you around and be your constant companion.

name: Emory
description: Hi I'm Emory! Around here they call me the "Helper Dog" because I love to meet the shy and scared dogs that come in and help teach them that it's okay to trust people. I get along with just about everyone and I LOVE to play in the play-yard with others dogs. I also love toys! If you let me walk past the toy-box I'll pick one out and carry it around in my mouth. My favorite game to play is Fetch, and if you come play with me I promise I'll be gentle and will try not to slobber all over the balls.  I love people, kids included! In fact I don't think there's a person I've met that I haven't gotten along with. I like to play and wrestle, so I might be a bit too much for some small dogs or cats, but other dogs my size would make great brothers or sisters! When I was younger I got hurt pretty badly, and even though I'm healed now I have some damage that will probably last the rest of my life; because of that I have accidents and can't control my bladder the way other dogs can. It's mostly a problem when I sleep, but I've been told there are some pretty cool pants-for-dogs that I can wear that could help with that! Because I'm such a special girl I'm available in our Foster-to-Adopt program; that means you can take me home and we can make sure it's a good fit for everyone before you finalize the adoption!

name: ADONIS
description: My Story  I am a gentleman who loves to go out on a walk, but I don\u2019t need to get anywhere too quickly. I love to have  a good time and play, but I\u2019m ok with just hanging out  if that\u2019s more of your thing. I have been at my current place for about 6 months now and I\u2019m really looking for a change of scenery. I know a couple of commands in Korean and I am very good at \u201csit\u201d. How many dogs do you know that are bilingual? Also, have you seen my eyebrows? Handsome huh?  My Perfect Match  My last relationship ended after 5 years so I am really looking for somewhere to call home again. A dog bed, a couple of toys and someone to show off my amazing qualities to would be ideal. Also, if you are up for it, I really enjoy a good back\/butt scratch.  My Ideal Date  I\u2019m a pretty laid back guy so I would love a quiet stroll through the national park while we enjoy the company of one another. We could keep it low key and go back home to watch the game and relax with a cold one afterwards, or we could stay out and see the sights and picnic. I will also say that ending the date with a few kisses is probably a given.  Send me a message if you\u2019d like to share your home with me. Of course I\u2019m up for a long-term place to call home, but if a short-term foster commitment is more your thing I can be flexible.  ***Want to learn more about this sweet boy? Email his volunteer champion at pegfikac@yahoo.com***

name: Blue Jeans
description: Well hello there. Foster mama wanted me to introduce myself. She says the world is ready for me, or maybe it\u2019s I\u2019m ready for the world... hmm. At any rate, not sure what to say. I guess I should start with my name. Mama named me BlueJeans. She keeps humming when she says my name and sometimes says \u201cforever in blue jeans.\u201d That mama. Silly lady. There\u2019s also a foster daddy and I love him so much. I get so excited for his pets that I make little squeaky sounds because I just can\u2019t hold in my excitement sometimes. There are also two younger humans and four other dogs here. I think they\u2019re all great. \n\nI\u2019m a bit embarrassed to share this, but when I first came to my foster family they said there were a few things that needed tending to. They immediately took me to the groomer who said I was just fantastic, a natural! Next up was a cherry eye repair, and a couple other things. I did need a dental cleaning (mama said my breath could clear a room!). Turns out I needed much more than that. I had extensive work done and the end result was getting to keep only two teeth. I don\u2019t want to complain because everyone has been so nice to me, but I was pretty sore. But I\u2019m starting to feel better and pretty soon I will be ready to meet my new family. A few more things. I am 8 years young. I love going on walks and foster mama says I am the best walker out of the bunch. I know exactly where to do my business, which foster daddy in particular really likes. Mama says that I like to \u201ctalk\u201d a lot so no apartments or homes with shared walls for me! I also am very skilled at begging for people food so she says my furever home needs to be disciplined in that area. I really adapt amazingly well. Mama also says I\u2019m a pretty and petite girl. Ta-ta for now

name: Gibbs
description:
Up for adoption in Texas and New England: Gibbs.





Gibbs is a total sweetie pie. He is about six months old and weighs 40lbs. 





Gibbs has never met a stranger! 





He is so excited to meet new people and dogs!  We don't know how he is with cats.  But with dogs he is 


great with pooches of all sizes, very submissive. 





He's pretty chill too. 





Gibbs is house trained, and we are working on ringing the bell when he needs to go out. 





As of now he will just go and sit by the front door, so we are working on making sure he is 'louder' or more assertive when he needs to go outside. 





Gibbs has shown major improvement in the crate area. He will go to the crate when he is told and does well sleeping in it at night; although, he prefers to sleep with his humans. 





Gibbs will stay in his crate during the day, although he does not like being left alone in it. 





Gibbs has never been left home alone out of his crate but does wonderfully when people are home.


This dog would do better going to dog daycare or being adopted by someone who works from home and can hang out with him. 





He has not been exposed to kids that we know of. 





Gibbs is not very interested in toys or fetching. However, every now and then he will lay down and chew on a toy/show it attention. He loves chew bones and toys.





While Gibbs does know how to walk on a leash and does not pull, he likes to do his business and go back inside. He is not fond of walking places he is unfamiliar with. 





He is more scared on leash than off; however, he has not yet mastered coming when called but he never strays far from his humans/fellow dog companion.  





Gibbs has mastered sit, shake, crate & drop it. We are still working on lay, come, and down. 





Cutest behavior: Gibbs is the biggest cuddler. This guy is one of the sweetest dogs his fosters have ever met which is hard for them to say considering their own bias towards their own dogs. He loves to lay around with his humans. 





Gibbs has gotten use to playing with his mouth while playing with other dogs and will sometimes grab your hand or arm for attention with his mouth. While it is never hard, it is a negative behavior we are working on. Since he still has some puppy play skills we'd recommend he only goes to a home with older kids or adults.  We just never want something misinterpreted or a young child getting scared. 





He is neutered, vaccinated and microchipped.

name: Miley
description:
Please contact JoEllen (sagdinfo@aol.com) for more information about this pet.Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

Meet sweet little Miley! She is an 18 month old spayed female terrier mix who is fully grown weighing in around 15#. Miley is kennel trained and also knows how to walk on leash. She is polite about taking a treat and knows her sit command.
You must also be committed to housebreaking, age-appropiate enrichment and exercise, leash training, grooming needs, and positive socialization. Like most young dogs, she will chew on anything within her reach to include but not limited to baseboards, shoes, socks, children's toys, electrical cords, etc. She is crate-trained and housebreaking is progressing nicely.
Her adoption fee is $175. This includes her spay surgery, DhPPv vaccination, bordetella vaccination, rabies vaccination, deworming, one month of flea and heartworm preventative, microchip, leash and collar, Petco coupon book, and 30-days of pet health insurance.

Please be aware that puppies and small breed do get adopted quickly so interested parties are encouraged to apply online at www.texasgreatdane.org.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio TX 78232. Event hours are 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m.

Additional questions may be directed to sagdinfo@gmail.com

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.

Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and a 30-day trial of 24PetWatch Pet Insurance. Adopters will also receive a Petco Pet Parent Savings Books that contain:• $100s in savings plus a coupon for a free 6 lb. bag of WholeHearted dog food.• Thoughtful care tips.• Online resources and support.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved and you are traveling from out-of-town, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time.

We do try to schedule bi-monthly meet-and-greets in Austin as interested is generated.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

By adopting me, you not only give me a new leash on life; you also save the life of an additional pet who can be rescued from euthanasia and placed in foster care. If you are interested in adopting me, please email adopt@sanantoniopetsalive.org with my name and ID#. Please allow up to 24 hours to respond, as all fosters work on a volunteer basis. To find out how you can get involved and help turn San Antonio into a no-kill city, please visit www.sanantoniopetsalive.org

name: Ace
description:
Please contact JoEllen (sagdinfo@aol.com) for more information about this pet.Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

** This dog is living in a foster home in San Antonio, Texas. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. ** Meet our handsome Ace! Ace is a 2-year-old Dachshund and Terrier blend.Ace was suffering from extreme neglect when we saved him. After receiving quality veterinarian care and a nutritious diet, he is now a healthy pup!Ace is such a friendly boy! He enjoys playing with other dogs in her foster home. Ace loves toys, balls, elk horn antlers, and killing bed slippers and socks. Ace is very energetic so his ideal home would enjoy an active lifestyle to include daily exercise and canine stimulation activities. Ace is crate-trained and housebreaking is progressing nicely.Please understand you are commiting to providing a good home for his entire life (up to 15+ years or more) - not just until his puppy cuteness wears off. You must also be committed to housebreaking, age-appropiate enrichment and exercise, leash training, grooming needs, and positive socialization. His adoption fee is $200. This includes his neuter surgery, DhPPv vaccination, bordetella vaccination, rabies vaccination, deworming, one month of flea and heartworm preventative, microchip, leash and collar, Petco coupon book, and 30-days of pet health insurance. Please be aware that puppies, small breeds, and pure breeds do get adopted quickly so interested parties are encouraged to apply online at www.saspca.org. Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m. Additional questions may be directed to sagdinfo@aol.com.

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.

Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and a 30-day trial of 24PetWatch Pet Insurance. Adopters will also receive a Petco Pet Parent Savings Books that contain:• $100s in savings plus a coupon for a free 6 lb. bag of WholeHearted dog food.• Thoughtful care tips.• Online resources and support.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved and you are traveling from out-of-town, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time.

We do try to schedule bi-monthly meet-and-greets in Austin as interested is generated.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

name: Mondo
description: This handsome pup is in APA!'s Total Obedience Program (TOP), which is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Mondo has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! Mondo is learning skills like sit and down, walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'place', which means he will go to a specific place in your home on command. Once Mondo successfully completes all the skills on his training plan, he will be considered TOP Dog Ready! Mondo is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with him after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. name: Diane
description: Diane is a sweet young lady who enjoys being pet and will paw at you if you stop. Other than looking for a bit of attention, Diane really doesn't ask for much and makes for a very low key companion. She just seems so appreciative having a soft bed and regular meals, and she was the perfect houseguest on an extended sleepover with her virtual foster, spending most of the time napping. In fact she was so quiet, her foster almost forgot she was there! Diane is pretty shy at first and likes to take her time with new people and places. When she first arrived at her foster's apartment, she took her time exploring the space, and then seemed to enjoy having a quiet place to stay out of the shelter. When she saw things were safe, she hopped up on the bed, then let out a long sigh before conking out and snoring contently. She'd occasionally come check on her person and wag her tail and get some pets, then ventured into the kitchen to see what was happening in there and was excited to find that's where they kept the string cheese! Diane is fully house-trained and is great about letting you know when she needs to go out. Out on walks, she doesn't pull on the leash and looks to her person for guidance as to what she's supposed to do. She also bravely hops right in and out of the car, even if she's a bit unsure of the destination. Low maintenance and so appreciative of her people, Diane would make a wonderful addition to any number of loving homes and maybe one with a well-matched doggie sibling to show her the ropes and help build her confidence. If that sounds like yours, come meet this sweet girl!
