name: Amy Lee
description: Amy Lee is as sweet as she is adorable - she has soft fur, one ear that's always up and one that's always down, and she doesn't even shed! She loves belly rubs and butt scratches and gives very gentle kisses. She also gives her foster mom hugs every time she gets home from work - she walks right up and lays her head on her chest, waiting for the embrace. Amy can be shy with strangers, but she warms up quickly, and once she's comfortable, her eyes are filled with love and affection whenever she looks at her people. Amy's preferred mode of play is to chase or be chased. Her favorite thing is to get a ball and then wait for someone to try to get it from her. Then she runs around the yard and stops, waits for you to try to get it, then she's off again: repeat until you're tired. When you're all chased out, Amy's happy to go practice on the squirrels. As much as she loves her walks and playtime, Amy overall has a pretty moderate energy level and is content to spend a lot of time just snoozing around the house. Amy is also an excellent houseguest - she's house-trained, and while she enjoys being in her crate, she behaves perfectly when left home alone outside of one, and she sleeps quietly through the night. She walks well on leash and is even up for a jog if you are. She's super smart too and already knows sit, down, roll over, stay and come. Feisty, well-trained, playful and and so very sweet, Amy Lee is a dog who's impossible not to fall in love with. She'd make a wonderful addition to any number of loving homes, but we think she'd prefer one with a yard full of squirrels. If that sounds like yours, come meet this great pup!

name: Oli Sykes
description: Oli Sykes is a handsome young pup who is very tune in with his person and will happily follow their lead. This smart fella learns tricks and routines quickly, has excellent manners in the home and is very eager to please. Oli is shy with new men and seems to favor women, but he can warm up to anyone and has a sweet and obedient disposition with the people he trusts. Oli loves to cuddle on the couch, but enjoys playing just as much. He adores his toys, especially tennis balls, and has also lived with a pittie in the past and got all well with her. They did like to play rough so he'd likely do well with a well-matched doggie sibling who likes to mix it up as much as he does. He's also house and crate-trained, though he prefers to sleep with his person at night. Smart, sweet, loyal and playful, Oli will make a wonderful addition to a family who will give him plenty of attention and guidance and ideally a yard to romp in. In return, Oli promises to be the best dog he can be. Come meet him!

name: Edison
description: Let's go hiking!' This resilient pup is recovering from paralysis of his back legs, and now that he's getting back to normal, Edison is taking full advantage of his hard-earned mobility. When he gets outside, his silly, playful personality takes over, and he loves to run around the yard playing fetch and even tosses toys in the air to himself. He has an adventurous spirit and likes to go exploring, taking leisurely walks in the neighborhood to check out what's going on, and even likes to jog a little now that he's getting his muscle tone back. As long as he gets some exercise, Edison is relaxed and chill in the home and loves to sit in laps and get pets or a nice massage, but he's also good at keeping himself entertained with his toys or chewing on his bones. He's house-trained and does well left home alone outside of a crate, staying quiet and not getting into any trouble. Edison also super smart and will be easy to teach new things. He is currently in APA!'s Total Obedience Program (TOP), which is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, he has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week learning skills like sit and down, walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'Place, which means he will go to a specific place in your home on command. Once he successfully completes all the skills on his training plan, Edison will be considered TOP Dog Ready! He is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with him after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 Loyal and loving, Edison is very devoted to his favorite humans. He isn't crazy about meeting strangers, and it takes him some time to warm up to new people, but once you're in the club, he'll love you forever! Edison would love to be your loyal sidekick on your outdoorsy adventures, and a yard to play in would be a plus. Come meet this amazing pup!
label: not-adopted

name: Princess
description: Princess is a rare, soulful and sensitive lady. Her foster mom says she's human-like in her displays of affection and that she has never met a dog so soft and sweet. Princess is one of those rare dogs that gives hugs and will even say thank you - when you put her harness on, she kisses and nudges you, and looks into your eyes in very appreciate way. Same with when you give her food, or put her bed down. She also loves to give kisses and will follow you from room to room like an adorable shadow. Princess is also extremely playful, but isn't pushy about it. She enjoys playing tug of war and loves moving her toys from room to room, getting them organized. Her favorite stuffed animal is a Scooby Dog and she uses him as a pillow or cuddles him in between her paws as she sleeps. She's also really into bones and pig ears. She likes to bury them outside or inside in blankets and boxes. Her other favorite 'toys' are shoes, which her foster parents allow her to play with as she doesn't really chew them and likes to gingerly hold them in her mouth. She really loves sandals and bringing assorted ones to you. She also loves being outside where she sprints and jumps like a deer, and she also likes to go swimming. Princes is house-broken and is making great progress on her leash skills. She does great left home alone outside of her crate. She loves her bed, and even found a box with blankets to make herself a second bed, much like a cat. We think Princess would likely do well with a well-matched doggie sibling. She's a little shy with new people and dogs and doesn't seem to know what to make of them. She barks, but with a wagging tail, and just seems so uncertain whether these are potential friends or not. But she's is extremely sweet and loving with people once she's familiar with them and the same might go for other pups. Kind, intelligent, empathetic and so much fun, Princess is truly one of a kind. She'd love a home with people who will included her in their activities and hopefully a yard to romp in. Come meet this amazing pup!
label: adopted

name: Mr Marbles
description: Mr Marbles is one of those chill dogs who just seems so grateful for a soft bed to lie in. He's a low maintenance guy who likes nothing more than hanging out with his people. He has a serious expression on his face most of the time, but that's just to hide what a gentle goofball he is. Mr Marbles has a quiet and calm nature and is the perfect gentleman in the home - he's house-trained and does great in a crate or left to roam free. He loves being on the couch with you, but won't get up unless invited and will sit politely nearby if that's not allowed. As much as he loves to cuddle, Mr Marbles is still pretty independent and prefers to sleep on the dog bed even if his person's bed is an option. He walks nicely on leash, is non-reactive to critters when out and about, and is great with meeting new people. He has a moderate energy level, and while he can be playful and enjoys his walks, he mostly likes napping and chewing on his toys, which he absolutely adores. Mr Marbles has also done well in APA!'s Total Obedience Program. The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Mr Marbles has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! Mr Marbles is learning skills like sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'place', which means he will go to a specific place in your home on command. Once he successfully completes all the skills on his training plan, Mr Marbles will be considered TOP Dog Ready! Mr Marbles is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with him after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 Sweet, playful and so well-mannered, Mr Marbles is the perfect match for someone looking for an easy-going companion. Come meet this great pup!

name: Frisco
description: Frisco is one of those dogs that always seems to be happy. He's super-excited to see his people, wagging his tail and saying hello with a kiss or two. Frisco is a bit of a wild child - he likes to find the noisiest squeaky toys, pounce on them, toss them around and wrestle their squeaker from them. He hasn't mastered fetch yet, but will definitely chase a toy that's thrown. He still has a lot of puppy energy and is like a toddler who doesn't want to take a nap. He'll wear himself out rather than laying down on his own. He's also a super-smart pup and eager to please, so training should come come easy. He's already crate-trained and is making good progress on his house-training. And he's been friendly with everybody he's met. name: Glendale
description: Glendale is a very cuddly and affectionate young pup who's looking to be someone's forever shadow. Glendale likes to be with his favorite people wherever they are in the house. He will seek out pets by leaning his body on you or by placing his head near your hand. He'll also try to lie on you to trick you into giving him belly rubs! And don't be fooled by his initial shyness when meeting new people. Glendale warms up quickly, and after he know a stranger is safe, he will go up and ask for pets. Glendale is a pretty chill guy and definitely has lower energy levels than the average dog of his age. He likes to play and get in some exercise, but he's also content to spend a lot of time lounging. He enjoys going for walks and does well on leash, but what he really loves is hanging out with his people and spending quality time with his toys, especially cloth toys that squeak. He's also a big fan of tennis balls, and will play some light fetch inside the house. He will come immediately to the sound of a squeaky toy or put his toy near you to let you know it's time to throw it. Because Glendale has abnormalities in his back legs that affect his mobility, his playtime is kept to a minimum, but he's a lower energy pup anyway, so he's fine with doing a lot of relaxing. The ideal home for Glendale would have few or no stairs as it is difficult for him to move up or down them (He can be carried and is really receptive to that). Glendale is house-trained and a really quiet pup to have around. He walks pretty well on leash, and he sits when his leash comes out or when you put out food. He doesn't seem to actually know the command sit, but he sits anyway when he knows he's supposed to. He's pretty calm whenever he gets bathed, he takes medication easily and is willing to do whatever you need him to do. His foster parents experimented by putting a raincoat on him and he was like 'Yeah, I guess that's fine, go ahead.' Glendale also wants to go say hi whenever he sees other calm dogs and could go home with a well-matched doggie sibling. This sweet guy is full of love and he's sure to make some lucky family very happy. Come meet him!

name: Dodge
description:
Looking for a companion dog to chill near you while you are working in the yard, reading or watching TV? Our Dodge is that very mellow guy! He loves walking on a leash and is easily handled by our Junior Volunteers. Impressive because he's so big. 81 pounds big. He's seven years old and over the puppy crazies. Dodge isn't treat driven, and a tickle behind the ear works just as well for a reward. So far he's been non-reactive to all the other animals at the shelter. And he's housebroken!

Dodge is neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, tested heartworm-negative and is on monthly heartworm protection. All our animals must be indoor pets. Dogs are very social animals; there's really no such thing as a "good outdoor dog".

If Dodge would be the second dog in your family, give us a call and schedule a Meet and Greet under supervision at our shelter with your spayed or neutered dog. 830-980-2247 or BAHShelter@yahoo.com.

You can visit with Dodge and all of the adoptable animals at BAHS on Tues/Thurs/Sat from 10A to 1P or during "Special Adoption" hours on Sunday from 1P to 4P. For driving directions to Bulverde Area Humane Society see our webpage at http://www.bulverdeareahumanesociety.com/contact.html

name: Lyra (referral)
description:
LYRA (referral): CONTACT EMILY FENNER at 817-937-7541 or EMILYJFENNER@GMAIL.COM. Dog is located in north Ft Worth, but foster is willing to drive the dog where needed. 

Sweet and loving 7-year-old German Shepherd looking for a new forever family. Lyra is playful and loyal. She grew up with a small child, and loves him very much. Never hurt a fly, and wants to play with everyone. She’s never hurt anyone, but is protective and not used to being around people. Lyra deserves a stable and loving home.

She’s not used to other animals or walking on a leash, but is smart and needs someone to work with her. We have had her since she was 6 weeks old, but she has not received much training. She’s a pure breed, and we have her family history.

Lyra is an amazing dog who needs to find a loving home. 

* Good with dogs; ok with our cat; good with children
* People: if she knows you, she does great, if she doesn’t, it takes an adjustment period before she stops barking and is comfortable
* 95 pounds; not micro-chipped; crate trained; house trained. 
* Current on all shots and heartworm prevention; spayed; no health problems

name: Van Gogh
description:
"Starry starry night
Paint your palette blue and gray
Look out on a summer's day"

 Oh, yeah, sing it Don McLean!!  Vincent Van Gogh's famous painting is eulogized in this popular 80's song by Don McClean!!  Starry, starry night perfectly describes my beautiful coat which shows similar swirls, textures, and color palette to the famous painting.  Hence, my namesake!!

I am a hybrid of two amazing working dog breeds; Australian Cattle Dog and a guarding breed that results in double dew claws on my back legs.  But, as a hybrid,  I don't run on petrol and electric, I run on milk bones, hot dogs, and snuggles!!  With this hairytage of brainiac working dawgs, just imagine the smarts in my noggin!!   My luxurious "Starry Night" coat has the merle effect 
associated with my Heeler Hariytage, but I am taller and have double dew  claws on my back feet (Livestock Guardian breeding!)  I will probably top out at a lean 50 pounds when at my ideal weight.

Foster Mum calls me an absolute "DOLL"!!  I don't want to embarrass my nice Foster Mum, but I am a walking breathing canine, not a DOLL!!

I am a loyal, confident and trustworthy four legged family dog that loves being inside and outside with his family.  I am equally happy lounging on the couch, going on action adventure hikes, or leisurely strolls to the coffee house.  I am very respectful of my hooman and walk gently on the leash without pulling too much. I walk best in a no pull harness.

I am eager to please my hooman and strive not to cause any discomfort, frustration, or extra work.  I am crate trained and will only bark when crated if I have to "go".

I am playful and athletic and do well with other social dogs.  Foster mum even introduced me to her most fearful foster and I wagged my tail, licked his nose and went about my business.

My favorite thing is belly rubs...wait, no, my favorite thing has to be going on walks...or maybe it's treat time?  Can I possibly have three favorite things?  I will have to ask Foster mum about that!!  Let me also add, I love to give kissess!!  I could probably make a good living working at a kissing booth...and love every minute of it!

Foster mum calls me a "quick study" (Hoomans and their crazy  sayings...Sheesh!!)  Sometimes, it is hard to remember which is my  actual name!! As previously mentioned, I am eager to please learn very quickly.

I REALLY enjoy being a part of the family and being included in activities.  At 45
pounds, I am the perfect size to be able to tag along with you anywhere you go, and my striking good looks are an artist's dream :)

Another chorus of Don McLean's ditty describes my life with my original owners who
had to give me up; (please excuse my literary license with the lyrics)

"For they could not love me
But still my love was true
And when no hope was left inside"............ I found YOU!! Please fill 
out the online application and adopt me today!!

name: Momma
description: Momma is one of those dogs who's super easy to please, a mellow young lady who is going to make some lucky person very happy. Momma loves car rides and going on walks, and she absolutely adores peanut butter. She has a great smile and looks so happy taking nice quiet walks with her person. Momma is the perfect houseguest too - she's fully house-trained, does great left home alone uncrated, and she rarely gets up on the furniture, even if she's invited. Momma's happy just hanging out on a nice cushy dog bed, and if you get down on the floor with her, she'll happily snuggle up and even gives hugs and kisses. While Momma can be shy around new people, you can tell she wants to trust them and it isn't long before she's accepting pets. Once she's warmed up to you, she's ready to cuddle and keep a close eye on wherever you are. Gentle, easy-going and low maintenance, Momma really doesn't ask for much - just a home that's as chill as she is and someone who will take her on adventures and give her plenty of cuddle time. In return, she promises to love you forever. Come meet this sweet girl!

name: Estelle
description: Estelle is a sweet and curious young mama with adoring eyes and a gentle demeanor. She's just getting used to how this whole beloved family dog thing works, but she definitely likes the sleeping indoors on a soft bed part of the deal. She's still figuring out how to walk on leash and doesn't quite know what to do with toys, but she's already developed an affinity for Kongs and rawhides and most of all, treats. Although Estelle is shy around people, treats are the way to her heart. She'll approach you when she wants some attention, and she seems to like the 8 and 10 year-old girls in her foster home. She's done wonderfully with the resident senior Jack Russell mix - the first time her foster parents saw her tail wag was when she met her new doggie foster brother. She's also been fine with the resident kitty, not paying him any mind. Estelle is a very chill houseguest, happy to lounge around and keep an eye on what everyone's up to. She's perfect when left home alone (just keep those treats up high somewhere), she never barks at strangers or when someone knocks on the door. And she likes being in her crate, especially if there's a big soft pillow for her to chill on. And we should mention those glorious and scratchable ears that are truly a sight to behold! Gentle, beautiful and quiet, Estelle would make a wonderful addition to any number of loving homes, ideally one another dog to help show her the ropes. Before long we know she'll blossom into the adoring companion she's destined to be. Come meet this sweet girl!

name: Wilder
description:
What can be said about Wilder?   This young boy came to TGPR because a very nice Good Samaritan couple saw this skeletal, sad, mostly bald dog, wander into their neighborhood.  He was so very sweet, but clearly desperately in need of help.  This wonderful young couple did not just call rescue - they put Wilder in their car and took him to the vet, starting his treatment for significant skin infections, fleas, ticks and ear infections.  Thus, when TGPR took him in, Wilder was already starting his road to recovery.   Wilder is currently in a foster home, and is being fed wholesome food, snacks and receiving baths every other day for his skin.   Want to know how Wilder responded to being saved?  Within twenty four hours, this poor guy, so thin every rib and spinal vertebrae were visible, stood on his hind legs and gifted his foster family with the brightest smile.  It was truly a gift and epitomizes his personality.

Wilder is not an LGD.  While he loves to go outside, sniff, walk the fence line, like any other member of his breed, he prefers to live inside, with his human present and close.  Wilder gives delicate kisses, and pushes his body against you - his favorite spot is standing right behind your knees and leaning.    

Wilder gets along very well with other dogs, and is very playful - he is a puppy.  He has nice dog/dog manners, and appears to have been socialized in his early weeks of life.  Wilder has not responded negatively to cats walking through the yard or in the veterinarian's office.  He met children in the vet's office and was very excited to see them, did not jump.  Basically, everyone is Wilder's friend.

Are you looking for a Pyr family member?  Well, then look no further than Wilder.   However, since he is still just a puppy - albeit a huge puppy - Wilder needs continued socialization and training.  His foster family has already started his training, including basic commands and leash work.

Texas Great Pyrenees Rescue, Inc. is a 501(c)(3) organization dedicated to Great Pyrenees. We have the best selection of Pyrs in Texas and we do home checks and vet checks before placement. We start with adoption applications (no cost/obligation) and we make placements on a first submitted-first approved basis. If you are interested in giving this dog a new home, please complete an adoption form found at http://www.txpyrs.org

name: Pacific
description:
When you hear the word “Pacific”, do you envision a long, palm covered stretch of beach with tranquil turquoise waters lapping at the shoreline? Can you feel the calmness and "Zen" of this scene? That is exactly the soothing and calm energy that I emote.

According to Wikipedia, the definition of the word Pacific means "peaceful in nature or intent, nonviolent, mild, gentle, and equable". All of these adjectives describe me perfectly!!

My hairytage is the working breed dawg of Anatolian Shepard and
America's most popular Labrador Retriever…imagine the smarts in my noggin’!This unique mix is a wonderful hybrid that takes many positive personality traits from both its parents.I inherited the calm, nurturing, caretaker vibe from the Livestock Guardian Anatolian Shepard and the sweet and loyal nature from my Labrador genetics.

I am an adorably sweet, 10-month-old spayed female pup. I currently weigh 73 pounds, so will probably top out as an adult around 80-85
pounds or so. I am trim and athletic and LOVE water sports and action/adventure hikes...but, I also love lounging on the couch in front of a blazing fire to spend some snuggle time with my hooman(s)! Walks around the park or to the local coffee shop are also on my "to do list"!! As long as I am with you :)

I am medium energy, gorgeous gal with a sunny disposition and a positive outlook on life ?I am a soft-furred, genteel lady who takes treats gently, knows sit, come, wait and down.I walk nicely on a leash without tugging (Foster Mum walks me in an "Easy Walker" harness!!). My original owner had me in classes with a professional trainer; the trainer's comment was that I was very "focused on and connected with my person; eager to please with a lot of potential."

Speaking of my original owner, I was surrendered by them because the family's other dog started aggressively attaching me. The other dog and I were ok when I was a small pup, but, as I grew up, the other dog became more and more aggressive. When an attack on me resulted in a
puncture wound so deep it required a vet visit and a drain, my original owner brought me to Foster Mum's ranch for my own safety. There were a lot of tears and much sadness for all of us. Through tears, my original Dad said that I was the best dog that he ever had.

With my gentle, submissive nature, I get along well with all other dogs (large and small), hoomans, and kidlings.I am playful with the doggies, but also love to snuggle on the couch for some down time. Tug of war is my favorite game! :)I love people and try hard to be a good girl and please my hooman….you just have to let me know what you want me to do!!(I really try to be a good girl!)

With my “glass is half full approach” to life, I am ready to find the furever family that I deserve whom I can take care of and share love and adventures!

He is such a sweet boy. Happy, playful, and loves everyone. Very smart. He plays well with other dogs, but has more of an alpha disposition. He would do well with an active family. 

Neutered, fully vaccinated, house-trained, fully vetted and microchipped. Carl is ready for his forever home.

She is an amazing mother. Attentive and caring. Such a sweet girl. She loves treats and loves. She has a playful side and genuinely loves being with people. She'd do great in just about any household.

name: Fawny (aka Clara)
description: Clara is a 3-year old Australian Cattle Dog blend. You know the pretty girl that doesn't have a lot of friends and doesn't date? That's Clara, beautiful but awkward and anxious. So if you want to meet her, you'll need patience, understanding and a big heart. Initially frightened of every movement and sound, she is still quite ambivalent of strangers and new situations. She's never been aggressive, just vocal and what some would call skittish. Clara is smart as a whip; she knows sit, lay down, no, this way and right here. She walks great on a leash, until there are people or animals in view. Walks are always an opportunity for training. Clara is house and crate trained...in fact her crate is her safe place, she easily goes in. She loves a comfy dog bed and taking naps. While she plays with the neighbor dogs through the fence on each side, super slow intros face to face are strongly recommended. Her prey drive is high; she is ready to pounce and chase cats, birds and squirrels. Her favorite things are green beans, bully sticks and playing with her toys. I am living in a San Antonio Pets Alive! foster home. name: Justice
description: Justice came to us from a Euthanasia list, this sweet stoic young lady didn't look like the "prettiest" dog in the shelter due to her missing hair. You see she had previously been in a fight with another dog, and that cause injuries all over her body. Despite looking a bit unkempt she had the sweetest personality and attentiveness. Once she landed safely at our shelter we soon realized something else about Justice. She is Deaf! Now before you start worrying about her, or what that means for her, let us tell you she has no idea she is different. Deaf dogs live completely regular lives, you just never have to worry about the music being too loud or those pesky firework phobias! Deaf dogs can even be trained just the same as other animals, they just need visual signals with your hands instead of vocal commands. Speaking of training, we won't fib, Justice probably hasn't had much of any training so far in her life. She loves to play with toys, or anything you may be holding she thinks is a toy, and for this reason we are looking for a home with older kids, but are definitely open to meet and greets with all the member so the family to make sure it would be a good fit. She is super sweet, just needs some basic obedience! Come stop by and meet this gem of a dog, her intelligence and attentiveness is sure to sweep you off your feet!

name: T-Bone
description:
THIS IS A COURTESY LISTING. ADR is not responsible for the health, temperament, behavior or placement of this dog. Listings are done at the request of the dog's owner and as an outreach and community service in hopes of finding these dogs a loving, stable forever home. Placement decisions are made solely at the discretion of the owner and not Austin Dog Rescue. Owners are required to ask for an adoption fee from adopters.

***Please do not contact ADR. Contact person listed below via e-mail***

This is the information that we received from T-Bone's current owner:

T-Bone is a 3.5-year-old, male, Bloodhound mix who weighs around 90 pounds.

He was my boyfriend's dog, and during a recent breakup, my boyfriend left the dog with me. Unfortunately, we were living in a home with a fence, and he is not leash-trained.

I am chronically ill - I have had two spine surgeries, and have a neuromuscular disease - and am finding it impossible to safely control him in our new apartment.

I tried intense day training with Sit Means Sit, but they caused horrible collar sores, and I had to pull him from training.

He’s incredibly sweet and good with other dogs and children, but would thrive in a home with a yard. 

T-Bone is fully vaccinated, neutered and on flea, tick and heart worm preventative.

He does currently take Apoquel daily, but is healthy otherwise. He just had a full exam with fecal and blood work.

***If you are interested in meeting this handsome boy, please contact Jennifer Lake at: jrl5363@gmail.com***

name: Henshaw AG
description:
My name is Henshaw!

I am a young guy, about 45 lbs, with loads of energy for all the playtime and activities in the world. I am named after Hank Henshaw aka Cyborg Superman. I know it's a reach, but foster mom says my fur and eyes make it look like I am made of many different parts, like a cyborg. I think she should just call me Hank Handsome, but she buys the kibbles around here, so I let it slide.

My weird colors are due to the fact that I am a Catahoula and Aus Cattle Dog/Blue Heeler mix. I'm not sure if that makes me a CataCattle Dog, or maybe a Heelahoula? Man, Chiweenies have it easy.

I came to God's Dogs after someone found me running loose in San Antonio with a hurt leg. I was taken in, treated, and HEELED (haha, get it?) very quickly. I can't be out of commission very long with all the stuff there is for me to do! Anywho, with as much great work as the people did in finding me, they weren't able to find my family and needed help in getting me a new one. Maybe that's where you come in. *wink*

Back to playtime!! I love to bounce bounce bounce bounce, just like the tennis balls I play fetch with. Foster mom says bounce for ball is ok, bounce on people is.....good? Bad? Oh I forget. (He needs some training help but learns quickly.)

In true Heeler fashion, I am extremely loyal and loving, chock full of energy for lots of activities, but protective over the things that are mine. My food, my toys, my family. I am ok with other dogs, but on top of being protective, I am also a herding dog. I herd EVERYTHING. Tennis balls, bugs, my hair floating in the sun (I shed A LOT). I also love to herd my foster mom's puppies when they run around the yard. They think I'm being rough, but I'm really just trying to teach them how to act like big boys like me.

Inside the house, I do ok, but try to mark here and there. I don't go potty inside of my crate, but I am still getting used to the concept. Sometimes I cry when I am in there, but not for long because, like I said, I'm a big boy. Foster mom says that I still need to be "noodled" (neutered) or something, too. After I get my noodle, I should not have the urge to mark, and my not be so rambunctious or dominant over the other pups at home.

I am a very smart, sweet, and oh so handsome guy that would love to be your partner in crime....I mean life. Won't you make me furrever yours?

name: Mary Pitt
description: Mary is a beautiful young lady who is happy to go with the flow and do whatever you want to do. She loves to cuddle and lie with you for hours watching tv, but she also enjoys going for walks and loves to play. She adores her rope toy and Kong, and is a big fan of anything filled with peanut butter. Mary gets incredibly happy whenever she sees her person, and on the occasions she's being lazy, she will stare at you and move her face as if she was talking to you just by looking at you! Every morning when she hears you wake up, she'll come running to the bedroom door, super-excited and playful and just so happy that you made it! While Mary can be nervous with new people, once she warms up, she'll be your best friend forever. Mary is so well-behaved in the home, her fosters say she's almost human. She'll follow you around the house while you do your chores, but without getting in your way, just making great company and being an adorable shadow. On top of being crate and house-trained, Mary knows commands like sit, down, stay, pop up and low five. And if you tell her to wait, she will wait in front of her food until you tell her it's ok to eat. She also previously lived with a pair of kitties and did fine with them. She rides great in the car, sheds very little and comes in the perfect size - not too big, not too little. A great mix of joyful playmate and cuddly couch potato, Mary would do well in a house or apartment and will make a loving and loyal companion to some very lucky person. Come meet this sweet pup!

name: Wonder RE
description:
Wonder RE

Name:

My name is Wonder, like the bread. I am not a pure bread doggie, but I am wholesome and honey drizzled. I will enrich your life and I am the next best thing to sliced bread. Stop. That is actually all a fib. My name is Wonder, because it is a “wonder” that I am walking after being paralyzed by an altercation with an automobile. Boo hoo right? It is much more fun to pretend I am named after bread. Bread is the backbone of society and deserves a standing ovation.

History:

After being bunged up by a car, my back-end refused to coopawrate with my front-end and I had to drag my back legs. The City of San Antonio Animal Care services started my rehabuttlitation to get my booty back in business. I went to a God’s Dogs Rescue Foster Home to continue to work on my coordination. Now I walk, but kinda like a drunk uncle, not too straight, a little crooked, but in a cute way.

Breed/Age/Weight:

I am about 1.5 years old and a girl doggie.  I am a mostly white colored with a few toasted spots Terrier mix weighing in at 40 pounds.

Problem:

I had 99 problems but being sad ain’t one. Once my back end was rehabuttlitated and I could wag my tooshy again, I had a new problem. I was suffering from Happy Tail Syndrome. It’s like a thing.  And my tail was knocking into stuff real hard, thump THUMP, kerthud, whack, ouch. During a surgery to remove a fluid filled tumor from my left booty cheek, the Vet also removed my tail so I couldn’t hurt it anymore either. Now I have a nub tail to add to my cute factor.

Temperament:

I love to play with other dogs and having a crooked back-end does not stop my roll. My crooked gait isn’t even something other dogs notice. After playing I like to cuddle in the doggie pile and snooze until it is time to play again.  I am described as “delightful”. I like to be in the same room as my human, but I don’t have to be directly underfoot all the time.

Skills:

I am house and crate trained.  Foster Mom has a small door just for doggies and I use it to go outside when I need to relieve myself.

Final Ask:

I am a really good dog and don’t even bork, except that one time the other dogs were going litterally nuts over a squirell, of course I joined in and said “bork, bork” just to fit in due to peer pressure.  Otherwise I am quiet and sweet and you will be happy to know me, but not as happy as me, I set the bar the Happy meter. Adopt me!

name: Molly TW
description:
Molly TW,

Hi girls, I edited Molly TW’s bio a little bit, because she is already brindle and kind of Pitbull looking and needs slow intros with dogs, so I wanted to highlight some of her better qualities to improve her chances of getting adopted, because she is actually a really fun girl. I am including a photo of her with the small dog that lives there, so people can see she is fine with small dogs.

Molly TW

“On the road again. Just can’t wait to get on the road again. Making music with my friends” Bowooooo wooo woo. Car karaoke on the road is so much fun. I’ve been road doggin with my Foster Mom while she travels for work. Turns out I’m an AMAZING copilot because I have energy when we are out and about on a grassy break, but settle down like a sloth when it is time to roll on.

I am about 1 year old and they call me a Plott Hound mix and that is how I got this dreamy striped pattern coat. I’m about 40 pounds or so and I’m as big as I’m going to get. I love people and even kid people, all people. I know how to SIT on command. Foster Mom says I would be an ideal pawtner for a trucker or police officer or fireman or encyclopedia salesman, because I make the best ride along bud.

But if you live in a house a lot, I am good with that too. Foster Mom says I’m doing great learning all the rules to being in a house. I am potty trained and will wake you up at night if nature calls, so that I don’t make any uh-ohs in the house. I don’t chew up your stuff, just my toys annnnd sometimes a water bottle, crinkle crinkle, that plastic cronchy is music to my ears.

I live here at my Foster Mom’s house with two little Chihuahuas, oops, I meant Yorkie Pies, or some other big eared small creature.  One of them is called Lil Shyt, because she has pooped more than a few times out of spite. Lucky for you, Lil Shyt already has a permanent home that has loved her for 12 years. I hope I find a home too that will love me for 12 years even if I pooped in their shoe! I won’t do that.  I promise.

I love to go on sniffathons and smell everything.  When I meet new dogs, I like to sniff them too, properly with doggie manners, not jump right into playing. Ironically, even though I LOVE riding in trucks, about the only thing that I am not a fan of is things on wheels like bikes and skateboards. Hey if it hasn't got legs it shouldn’t be moving. Speaking of moving I’m all ready to move in with you so come get me please.

GOD'S DOGS Rescue, in San Antonio TX, does not have a shelter - Our dogs are raised in foster homes in the San Antonio area. Each dog comes spayed or neutered, up-to-date with age appropriate vaccinations, microchipped, heartworm tested and are current with monthly flea/tick and heartworm preventatives. 

ALL OF THIS IS INCLUDED IN THE Local ADOPTION FEE OF $250.00 FOR PUPPIES and $200.00 for ADULTS. (Local is in the state of Texas). Medical records will come with each dog at the time of adoption.

IF THIS IS AN OUT OF STATE ADOPTION, TRANSPORT TO YOU is included in the adoption fee of $500.00 for PUPPIES and $400.00 for ADULTS. We transport all over the country!!

Our dogs are socialized, and we try to provide you a good understanding of the dog’s personality. Please contact us at info@godsdogsrescue.org for more information about adopting one of our dogs and puppies or fill out an adoption application at http://www.godsdogsrescue.org/adopt/adoption-application/ 

Please visit our website http://godsdogsrescue.org/ for helpful information re: transport, our adoption process and application, volunteering and fostering, and photos of our dogs/pups looking for homes!!

Thank you for wanting to adopt a rescued dog, their LIVES depend on it!

name: Athena (referral)
description:
ATHENA (referral): CONTACT Jaime Whitten 360-628 6166 or email WHITTEN263@HOTMAIL.COM

Quick Stats
* Female German shepherd husky; est. birthdate November 2013
* House & crate trained
* On heartworm prevention and another test due in July; so far she's been clear
* Spayed; Microchipped
* Good with other dogs not on her property, can be protective of owner, she's more fear/anxiety based
* Good with our cat; Good with all ages of children. 

We are rehoming Athena. After trying professional training to help her adjust to farm animals, the trainer recommended we find a more suitable home. We have too much stimulus here that triggers her to chase anything and any animal on the farm. She can and does jump 4 foot fences. After chasing the neighbors cows again, we have decided not to risk Athena's safety or risk injury to the other animals and find her a less stimulating environment.

She is sweet and athletic and might do well in tracking or agility.  Please contact me so she can have another loving home.

name: Sasha
description: Sasha has a sense of calm and ease that comes with experience. She knows how this whole 'dog' thing works. She will sit, she will be polite in the home, she will go outside to potty, she'll bark when there are people lurking around outside but she will stop when asked. In return, you will pet her, give her something nice and soft to lay on, cuddle her during thunderstorms and take her for walks. This is the contract. She knows the score. Sasha has been a dream of a houseguest in her foster home, a highly affectionate dog with impeccable manners - she will wiggle with happiness when you get home and then go back to being her calm self. She is very intelligent and eager to please - she will bark when someone comes close to the apartment, but stops as soon as her foster mom tells her it's okay. She hasn't yet shown any interest in toys, but she loves her walks and also does her business quickly on brief outings. Sasha is complete house-trained and does great left home alone without getting into any trouble. She has never attempted to reach the kitchen counters or any form of food sneaking. She's well-behaved on walks and will sit when you pick up her leash. She loves to cuddles and to be petted, but isn't pushy about it and understands when that time is over and is happy to go chill on her bed. She is courteous with strangers and happy to get their pets. Sasha would make a wonderful addition to any number of loving homes with people who will give her plenty of attention and ideally one with a yard to romp in. In return she promises to love you forever. Come meet this perfect pup!

name: Conch
description:
Please contact JoEllen (sagdinfo@aol.com) for more information about this pet.Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

This handsome little man is Conch. He is an 6 month old neutered male chi mix probably with terrier who is fully grown weighing in around 12#.
Conch is a happy little guy who gets along well with all the other dogs in his play group.
You must be committed to housebreaking, age-appropiate enrichment and exercise, leash training, grooming needs, and positive socialization. Like most young dogs, he will chew on anything within his reach to include but not limited to baseboards, shoes, socks, children's toys, electrical cords, etc. She is crate-trained and housebreaking is progressing nicely.
His adoption fee is $175. This includes his neuter surgery, DhPPv vaccination, bordetella vaccination, rabies vaccination, deworming, negative heart worm test, one month of flea and heartworm preventative, microchip, leash and collar, Petco coupon book, and 30-days of pet health insurance.
Please be aware that puppies and small breed do get adopted quickly so interested parties are encouraged to apply online at www.texasgreatdane.org.
Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio TX 78232. Event hours are 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m.
Additional questions may be directed to sagdinfo@gmail.com

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.

Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and a 30-day trial of 24PetWatch Pet Insurance. Adopters will also receive a Petco Pet Parent Savings Books that contain:• $100s in savings plus a coupon for a free 6 lb. bag of WholeHearted dog food.• Thoughtful care tips.• Online resources and support.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved and you are traveling from out-of-town, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time.

We do try to schedule bi-monthly meet-and-greets in Austin as interested is generated.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.

Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and a 30-day trial of 24PetWatch Pet Insurance. Adopters will also receive a Petco Pet Parent Savings Books that contain:• $100s in savings plus a coupon for a free 6 lb. bag of WholeHearted dog food.• Thoughtful care tips.• Online resources and support.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

description:
Please contact JoEllen (sagdinfo@aol.com) for more information about this pet.Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

This handsome little man is Norman. He is an 18 month old neutered male Shih Tzu mix probably with terrier who is fully grown weighing in around 15#.
Norman is a happy lil fellow who survived distemper and as a result he has been left with a minor twitch that is permanent.

You must be committed to housebreaking, age-appropiate enrichment and exercise, leash training, grooming needs, and positive socialization. Like most young dogs, he will chew on anything within his reach to include but not limited to baseboards, shoes, socks, children's toys, electrical cords, etc. She is crate-trained and housebreaking is progressing nicely.
His adoption fee is $175. This includes his neuter surgery, DhPPv vaccination, bordetella vaccination, rabies vaccination, deworming, negative heart worm test, one month of flea and heartworm preventative, microchip, leash and collar, Petco coupon book, and 30-days of pet health insurance.

description: You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Our Great Dane Momma and puppies will be ready for adoption the first week of April, 19\n\nWhisper and her children, Twig, Snowball and Pip were found at an RV park in San Antonio. They were living in a wooded area behind the park inside an old, broken television set. Lucky for them one of the visitors decided to go hiking. We were called and agreed to take them. Momma was very skinny when they came in, but she still weighed 94 pounds. These puppies were feral when they came in, but the young adults that rescued them came and stayed by our facility so they could work on socializing the pups. They are doing great and love everyone.

name: Darla
description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.We were contacted and asked to help a son who's mother had died after a long illness. The son is having to shut down the house, while dealing with his own health issues. He was desperately trying to find placement for the 7 dogs his mom had. He was able to find homes for two and we agreed to take the remaining five.

Darla is the social butterfly of the group. She is constantly following you and wants your attention. She appears to be in good health and under two. She tends to be the leader of the pack. She will do good in a family.

name: Chip
description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Peaches and her puppies were a surprise from the streets of San Antonio. Our San Antonio Network of trappers were trying to catch several dogs that had been running loose for many months. We agreed to take the small pregnant one, who was one of the last dogs caught. She was missing for several days and we all hoped she had found a great home.

About a week later there was another sighting of the dog. Only this time she looked different....she had delivered her pups on the street. They were able to trap her and find her puppies. In addition, they found another dog that was protecting momma and her puppies. They brought her to the ranch too.

We named the momma dog Peaches. She is probably a doxy mix of some kind. The pictures are deceiving. She is not very big and her puppies are all under 3 pounds. The big girl with her is Lightning, named after the white streak on her back.

They were feral when they came in. Momma would try to bite us every time we got near the puppies, now she is a love bug. Lightning is leary of new people, but she warms up fast.

Lightning is already fixed and ready for the right new home. You will have to have plenty of patience, because she is shy. But she walks great on a leash and LOVES kids.

Peaches will be fixed the first week in April, 2019, then she will be ready for adoptions. The children just got their first shot today. They will be ready for adoption Early May, 2019. Send in your applications now. They will go fast.

Chip is the largest puppy. He is a male. Shivers and Vanilla (who we can Nilla) are females. They are all incredibly social and love people.

name: Meghan (slaughter survivor)
description:
Meghan is the sweetest senior who came to LWHA from China! She loves naps and to curl up close. She is perfectly kennel trained and loves to just snooze in it. With her soft thick fur, she definitely needs a brushing every now and then but no fear because she absolutely loves to be brushed! Meghan is working on leash walking and using a doggie door. She has done fine in her foster home with other dogs and cats when a proper introduction has been done. Because she’s a little on the older side, she would do best with an owner that had a quieter home and where her person was with her more than being gone. She just wants to be around her person! She does fine being kenneled but would prefer to be with her people. Meghan will make a great companion!To have your home considered for adoption, read about our adoption process or fees, and find out about interstate transport, please visit our website, www.LongWayHomeAdoptables.org and click the adopt tab!

Our adoption fee is $200, and it includes spay/neuter, all vaccines, heartworm testing, fecal testing, deworming, flea/heartworm prevention, and a microchip. 

NATIONWIDE TRANSPORT AVAILABLE. See our website for more info!

name: Kate (slaughter survivor)
description:
Kate is an older pug (around 7 years old) who came from China. She is crate trained, sleeps great in her crate at night and LOVES food and treats with a passion, like all pugs. Kate does have limited vision and she is a little slow (unless belly rubs are involved…which she loves). She gets along with the other dogs in her foster home and is learning how to use the doggy door. If you are a pug lover, this sweet girl is for you.To have your home considered for adoption, read about our adoption process or fees, and find out about interstate transport, please visit our website, www.LongWayHomeAdoptables.org and click the adopt tab!

name: Agnes
description: Agnes is like the BFF you have always wanted, the perfect blend of active and chill. One of Agnes' favorite things is to hang out with volunteers who are standing around talking. She just wants to be a part of the group and will lay down and listen, soaking up the latest gossip. And if she gets bored with the chit chat, she'll ask for some belly rubs while she patiently waits to hit the trail. Agnes loves going on walks and has the cutest little swagger. She really enjoys being outdoors and would love a home with a yard. If you're looking for a dog that could join you on movie night or a slumber party (she loves to be brushed), or a long walk to watch the sunset, Agnes could be the perfect fit. Come meet this sweet pup!
label: adopted

name: Turkey
description: Despite his goofy name, Turkey is actually quite mysterious and aloof. His piercing hazel eyes and gray tuxedo markings does give him the air of an enigmatic stranger sipping drinks along the perimeter of a fancy party. Does he notice me? Is he interested? Does he know where secret treasure is buried? But as we've gotten to know Turkey, we've seen his regular old dog self come through. He loves to play with stuffed animals and run on the trails. And don't tell anyone, but he even loves to give kisses. Turkey has also proven to be an excellent student in APA!'s Total Obedience Program. The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Turkey has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! Turkey is learning skills like sit and down, walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'place', which means he\/she will go to a specific place in your home on command. Once Turkey successfully completes all the skills on his training plan, he will be considered TOP Dog Ready! Turkey is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with Turkey after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 Turkey will make an elegant, but still very lovable addition to your family. Come meet him!
label: not-adopted

name: Angel Jack
description: Angel Jack truly lives up to his name. He loves meeting new people and hasn't met anyone he didn't instantly take a liking too. He wants nothing more than to be close to his human and give them snuggles, and he literally gives hugs! When you prompt him, he will put his paws on your shoulder and put his head on top of your head and it is just the sweetest thing. Angel Jack is a perfect gentleman on walks. He doesn't pull, and he's gotten to the point where he can be within 5 feet of a passing leashed dog and not even care (as long as you have treats!). As much as he enjoys his walks, he gets tired out pretty quickly and is happy mostly being a couch potato and watching some Netflix with you. Teddy is such a quick learner with new tricks and agility courses and he'll do just about anything for a treat. Come meet this sweet pup!

name: Sparrow
description: null
label: adopted

name: Maple
description: Maple is a calm and sweet lady who's still working out this beloved family pet thing. And stairs. Maple can walk up the stairs to the second floor of her foster home, but she's still trying to figure out the going down part. But she's got the squirrel thing down already. Maple has a hilarious obsession with squirrel watching, and she likes nothing more than being out in the backyard, keeping an eye on them and chasing them when they're up to no good. After five days in her foster home, Maple figured out what toys are for, and now her favorite pastime (besides squirrel-hunting) is throwing her purple squeaky bunny in the air and play bowing to it. She also likes to be where the people are and will follow them around the house like an adorable shadow. She loves back and ear scratches and mostly prefers to lay in her bed next to where you are sitting, but will occasionally rub her face and body against you like a cat. Maple has been great with with the 4 and 8 year-olds kid in her foster home and is very gentle with them, though she seems to prefer the chiller energy of the older one. She's also calm around the resident kitties, mostly ignoring them. While she likes her walks and chasing squirrels in the back yard, she has a low to medium energy level and takes several long naps during the day. Maple is house-trained and fantastic on her leash. She responds well to 'leave it and comes when you call her. She is crated during the day, and while she's not crazy about it, she settles down after a bit. She does fine being left out at night and will happily sleep in her dog bed next to her foster parents. Maple would thrive in a loving home with people who will help her build her confidence as she continues to blossom into her playful and happy self. She loves walks and loves her people, and as long as she has that and a good squirrel-watching spot, Maple will be one happy camper. Come meet this sweet girl!
label: not-adopted

name: Pumpkin
description: The first thing you should know about Pumpkin is that she's one of those dogs who gives hugs. She will literally give you a little squeeze and lay her head on your shoulder, and it's just as sweet as you could imagine. With her regal beauty and gorgeous coat, Pumpkin is truly a one-of-a-kind dog. She's highly intelligent, eager to learn and always wants to please her people. She's house and crate-trained, walks well on leash, is very well-behaved in the home and knows a ton of commands. While she's a total cuddle bug who likes to give kisses and definitely thinks she's a lap dog, she also respectful her person's space. Pumpkin is a pretty active pup and loves to go jogging with her foster's teenage son. She enjoys hiking and jumps in the lake, but can also chill and watch a basketball game with you. And you cannot throw the ball enough with Pumpkin. She LOVES playing fetch, and when your arm is finally tired, she'll keep it going by tossing her toys to herself! She's also great with dogs and lives with two in her foster home, a senior and a younger pittie who she loves to play with. She's also great with cats and is BFF with the resident kitty. Silly, affectionate, well-behaved and just a delight to have around the house, Pumpkin would make a wonderful addition to any number of loving homes. She'd love a yard or at least an outdoorsy family who can take her on long walks or hikes and include her in their adventures. And of course someone who likes to get lots of hugs and kisses. If that sounds like yours, come meet Pumpkin!

name: KATIE
description: This is Katie! Katie is 9 years old. She was owner surrendered to the shelter through no fault of her own. She is an older gal who doesn\u2019t require much, except attention. Her favorite activities are going for short walks and getting pet and pet and pet! She is very food and treat motivated, and is also house trained. All Katie wants these days is love. She would do best in a home where she is the only animal. She may start off very timid at first, but forms a very strong bond to her people. It would be great if she were adopted by someone who just wants a couch potato to hang out with. Small children may also be a bit too much for her. Katie deserves the best at this stage in her life. She deserves love and a home to call hers forever. Are you that special person that can make this gal\u2019s dreams come true? Please contact caring@classiccanines.org to meet her!

name: Nick
description: My name is Nick and I'm a big boy at 65 lbs. If I were a human my foster mom says I would probably be a 2-4 year old as I can be mischievous. I love toys and balls. Love to tear the stuffing out of stuffed animals. I am crate trained and pretty good at potty trained. I love other dogs but not sure about cats yet. I love food! Especially hotdogs! Toss me a treat and I will catch it! I love cuddling with my foster mom and especially sleeping on the couch with my buddies. I pull a little on the leash but if you tell me no I will stop. I love riding in the car, will jump right in. I like people and the pets I get from them. I am living in a San Antonio Pets Alive! foster home. By adopting me, you not only give me a new leash on life; you also save the life of an additional pet who can be rescued from euthanasia and placed in foster care. If you are interested in adopting me, please email adopt@sanantoniopetsalive.org with my name and ID#. Please allow up to 24 hours to respond, as all fosters work on a volunteer basis. To find out how you can get involved and help turn San Antonio into a no-kill city, please visit www.sanantoniopetsalive.org

All other toys and treasures are gathered in his bed. He loves socks and will squirrel away any he finds on the floor. He loves his crate,and walks well on a leash. His house training is coming along and with persistence he has improved.<br><br>Although he is a work in progress, Enrico is ready for his own home. He must have a fenced yard in which to run and would love a playmate. Enrico is a clown and is a lot of fun so any new family must have a sense of humor.<p>If you are interested in Enrico, please use <a href='http:\/\/www.paphaven.org\/cgi-bin\/docs\/AdoptApp.pl?id=2110' target='_new'>Adoption Application<\/a>

We will keep you updated on this sweet little girl's progress. Thank you!

name: Major Tom Bowie
description:
Welcome to the Wonderful World of Rescue Dachshunds. Look around and read their bios. Find a few whose personality seems to fit well. Consider one of our Well Seasoned Seniors who are truly wonderful and have so much to offer. Need help finding the best fit? We'll help with that too. Please fill out an application and let’s get you all matched up with a loving new “furever’ companion and friend. You’ll find the application on the “Available Dogs” page.
NOTE:

Adoptions to Texas residents only

.

Standard Adoption Fee Adult Dog: $250 ea. Puppy Adoption Fee: $300 ea. Reduced rates for Seniors dogs (10 and up). Reduced rates for pairs (when adopted together).

Email: ddrtxinfo@gmail.com Primary Website: www.DDRTX.org
Born in Rescue to Layla Clapton. Major Tom Bowie is sibling to Sharona Knack, Miss Molly Richard, Bennie Jet John, Peggy Sue Holly, Cuban Pete Ricardo, Louie Louie Kingsman, and Mustang Sally PickettMajor Tom Bowie is one of eight puppies born to Layla Clapton on January 23rd of this year in DDRTX's care. While mother Layla Clapton is a dachshund mix, we do not have any idea who the father of the puppies is.

Major Tom Bowie is a sweet, gentle boy with a crazy streak. When he is not cuddling, he's bouncing around!

Major Tom is available and ready for adoption under Puppy Provisions!
Love dachshunds and not ready to adopt or circumstances won't permit having a dog? How about being a sponsor or making a donation. Every one of our dachshunds receives excellent medical care along with day to day food, love and housing. Being non-profit, we rely on generous individuals like yourselves to help save these fur babies. You can do this specifically for one dog with the sponsor button on their webpage or a general donation on our “How To Help” page. Easy and quick through Pay Pal or your debit/credit card. You generosity is sincerely appreciated by all and is tax deductable. Need other ideas? You'll find tons of them on the How to Help tab. All contributions are tax deductable.

Diamond Dachshund Rescue of Texas is a non-profit 501(c)(3) volunteer organization with focus on rescue and adoption of pure breed Dachshunds. All dogs are fully vetted and housed on private property. Meetings are scheduled upon adoption approval. Thank you for your continued support to the rescue and shelter communities!

name: Greta
description:
Please give a big welcome to Greta!  Greta was a stray that came in to the shelter in terrible condition.  She had bad matting all over her body and her teeth were all rotted.  Even though it seems like Greta has had a hard life she is still one of the sweetest dogs around.  Her foster dad says she is doing great with house training and has figured out the doggie door as well.  She is currently being fostered with another small dog and does great with him.  Greta would love to find a home that will let her snuggle in bed with the humans and also on the couch while watching tv.

Greta is a miniature schnauzer that is estimated to be 5 years old and weighs 12 pounds.  She is being spayed this week and then we will be getting her dental done in a couple of week.  This sweet girl will be available to leave for her forever home after May 1st.

If you would like to meet sweet Greta please go to www.texassweetiesdogrescue.org to read our adoption requirements.  If you agree with the requirements please fill out an adoption application.  If your application is approved one of our volunteers will be in touch with you for a meet & greet.

Greta's adoption fee is $250 which includes spay, shots, microchip and dental.

Sorry, no out of state adoptions.

description:

Hi- My name is Chuck E and I am in need of a human to be in love, love, love with !

I am a 6 year old boy that lived not such a great life in a barn with a big group of dogs. I get along really well with everyone I have met, dogs big or small, cats and all humans. I just had my teeth cleaned, I lost a few that were really hurting me, now I am starting to feel much better. I absolutely love nothing more than a comfy bed, a blanket to burrow under and to be near my humans. I discovered the big bed and don’t ever want to leave it, its so soft and warm !

I am very quiet, a little bit shy and reserved, quite inquisitive and a huge love bug. My foster Mom says I look into your soul. I am learning how to live in a home and am loving every minute of it. I am still recovering from my dental work and am learning to be a part of a small pack. They are teaching me to be a regular dog that does dog things.

I would be so happy to have my own family that could be patient with me as I learn and grow into a very special boy.

Chuck Es in loooove, he’s in love, he’s in love… won’t you love him back and give him a forever home ?

name: Sabrina
description:
SABRINA 

Don't let Sabrina's scars and shy behavior scare you away from looking deep into her eyes and seeing the gem that she truly is. 
Sabrina is a beautiful 3-year-old terrier mix who wants nothing more than to be a part of your family. We don't know her back story but we do know she is sweet and timid. A very polite girl and when nervous or unsure she will check in with her human and try to avoid the thing that is making her uncomfortable. Once she is comfortable with you she solicits pets and leans in for all the extra loving. We would suggest a family with older children. She's lived with big dogs in a previous foster home but we would still suggest a meet and greet with any other dogs. She's a bit unsure about cats. Slow introductions all around.
She is crate trained, food motivated, takes treats with a soft mouth, working on house training and rides well in the car. Sabrina walks beautifully on a leash, UTD on shots, spayed and working on heartworm treatment. Extra loving is all she needs. 
Would you like to meet her? Message us for more info or fill out an application here: https://georgetownanimaloutreach.org/adoption-application/

name: Moon
description:
Meet Moon!  Moon is the Mary Poppins of dogs, practically perfect in every way.  She is house-broken, knows basic commands, is excellent on lead, is kennel trained, has amazing recall, and is GREAT with kids, cats, and .... MOST dogs.

Moon is a girl who wants to run the house her way.  If dogs are submissive and playful, they are her favorite and she will shower them with kisses.

Moon loves to snuggle.  If her people aren't available she will find her favorite dog, if no one is available, she will find the warmest most comfortable blanket and lull herself to sleep.  In her foster mom's opinion, she also loves to have the song You Are My Moon Beam sung to her to the tune of You Are My Sunshine.

She LOVES to play tug as well as to toss her bones around and play keep away with herself.  Bones are her favorite and she will often be found quietly chewing one or skidding around on the floor with her favorite find of the day.  

Moon has the best smile.  She loves to ham it up for attention and will greet you daily with the wiggliest of butts and warmest of smiles.  She is a girl you cannot imagine living without.

Moon is looking for her forever home where she can be loved and spoiled for the rest of her days, are you the one for Moon?

name: Mike Jonze
description: With his striking good looks, you're sure to hear a lot of compliments when you're out and about with Mike Jonze. And you're likely to be out and about quite a bit, because this handsome guy has a lot of energy to burn, and he'll make a wonderful adventure buddy to some lucky person. Mike walks well on leash and is super smart. He already knows sit, paw and down, and waits for the 'ok before eats. He also sits and wait at the door before before going outside. He's house-trained, loves his crate and does really well left alone with a Kong filled with peanut butter. He will be quiet when you leave him and very happy when you come home. Mike can take some time to warm up to new people, but it goes a lot faster if treats are involved. Once he's decided you're okay, his sweet, silly and playful personality comes out. Mike loves to play with ice cubes and his braided rope toy and will toss his toys up in the air and catch them. He also loves playing with other dogs, so a similarly energetic playmate will go a long way to keep him occupied. As energetic as he is, Mike is also a champion cuddler and is happy to settle down for the night with his person Mike Jonze is such a sweet guy, and he wants nothing more than a home with an active person who will give him plenty of love and attention. If that sounds like yours, come meet this great pup!
label: not-adopted

name: Lucio
description: Lucio is basically a pocket Great Dane. All the looks but not all the size! He's still a big dog, but not massive, and he's such the polite gentleman. After getting to know you a bit he's so excited to see you and heads right in for kisses! Not by jumping however. Lucio is too polite for all that. This handsome guy has enough energy for walks, fetch, and fun, but not overwhelming so. Lucio is the perfect fetch machine. He brings the ball right back to you, dropping it at your feet and sometimes dropping it right in your hand. Even when engaged in his favorite activity, he's still very much a gentleman. Lucio can be a bit shy, but after your first walk with him, he warms up and to start giving kisses. As much as he enjoys his playtime, he's quite content to settle down for snuggles with his humans. Lucio is also thriving in APA!'s Total Obedience Program (TOP), which is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Lucio has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! He is learning skills like down, walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'Place', which means he will go to a specific place in your home on command. Lucio is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with him after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 Lucio is hoping for a home with someone who will play with him and take him for walks, but also make time for those snuggles. A yard where he can play fetch would be ideal. Come meet this perfect pup!

name: Bertram
description: Bertram will come up for the occasional scratch behind the ears, but he's really quite an independent old chap who likes to nap and enjoy his meals. Eat, potty, nap and repeat - and he's very appreciative of you sticking to that schedule, thank you, specifically the eating three times a day with snacks thrown in as well. Bertram would make a wonderful Hobbit. He loves being outdoors, wandering around and happily sniffing the yard and garden. But only food seems to get Bertram truly excited, and he always gives a little jump when he senses his food bowl is coming. As independent as he is, Bertram is attentive to where his person is and follows them from room to room, hoping to find a dog bed in each one. He's fine with all dogs and wags his tail when a new one comes on the scene. He's lived with two chihuahuas and has had lots of doggie visitors in the yard - Bertram likes to sniff them and wag his tail, but after he's said his hellos, he's happy to get back to exploring the garden. Bertram is deaf and sort of blind, but he learned his way around his foster's home fairly quickly. He's crate-trained and is perfectly content to sleep in his crate through the night and also when left home alone. He's a quiet fella to have around and doesn't get into any trouble. In fact, he's only ever barked once and that was to greet another dog. Dignified and plucky, Bertram wants nothing more than to be loved and kept on a predictable routine. An outdoor space to explore would be wonderful, and in return he promises to be quiet and non-demanding, a low-key companion just looking to celebrate his retirement. Come meet him!

name: Ace
description:
Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

** This dog is living in a foster home in San Antonio, Texas. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. ** Meet our handsome Ace! Ace is a 2-year-old Dachshund and Terrier blend.Ace is such a friendly boy! He enjoys playing with other dogs in her foster home. Ace loves toys, balls, elk horn antlers, and killing bed slippers and socks. Ace is very energetic so his ideal home would enjoy an active lifestyle to include daily exercise and canine stimulation activities. Ace is crate-trained and housebreaking is progressing nicely.Please understand you are committing to providing a good home for his entire life (up to 15+ years or more) - not just until his puppy cuteness wears off. You must also be committed to housebreaking, age-appropiate enrichment and exercise, leash training, grooming needs, and positive socialization. His adoption fee is $200. This includes his neuter surgery, DhPPv vaccination, bordetella vaccination, rabies vaccination, deworming, one month of flea and heartworm preventative, microchip, leash and collar, Petco coupon book, and 30-days of pet health insurance. Please be aware that puppies, small breeds, and pure breeds do get adopted quickly so interested parties are encouraged to apply online at www.saspca.org. Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m. Additional questions may be directed to sagdinfo@aol.com.

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and a 30-day trial of 24PetWatch Pet Insurance. Adopters will also receive a Petco Pet Parent Savings Books that contain:• $100s in savings plus a coupon for a free 6 lb. bag of WholeHearted dog food.• Thoughtful care tips.• Online resources and support.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time from the Austin area.

We do try to schedule bi-monthly meet-and-greets in Austin as interest is generated.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/
