** This dog is living in a foster home in San Antonio, Texas. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. **

Champ was surrendered after being left with another dog alone except for twice daily checking on/feeding for almost a year. He really loves being with his people and craves socialization and love. After coming into foster care, Champ remembered he is house trained and with a little reminding, he obeys on the leash so he can get the walks and companionship he wants. Champ is very comfortable in his crate and will put himself to bed if his door is left open. Champ does well with other dogs, but due to his size and potential roughness, smaller dogs are not recommended. He loves children, but again, he is not really aware of his size so more mature children would be best. Champ just wants to bond to his person and be treated like a family member! He is healthy except for bad knees: he had a knee replacement and the vet said odds are his other back knee will need replacing so no rowdy running and jumping for Champ. He enjoys playing, but luckily he is not excessively rowdy. Leashed exercise walks are highly recommended.

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and a 30-day trial of 24PetWatch Pet Insurance. Adopters will also receive a Petco Pet Parent Savings Books that contain:• $100s in savings plus a coupon for a free 6 lb. bag of WholeHearted dog food.• Thoughtful care tips.• Online resources and support.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time from the Austin area.

We do try to schedule bi-monthly meet-and-greets in Austin as interest is generated.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

name: Lily
description:
Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

** This dog is living in a foster home in San Antonio, Texas. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. **

Lily (70 lbs, 3 yrs) is a super sweet bully who came up to a rescuer trapping another and asked to come home. All she wants is to be a house dog and part of the family. It's evident Lily was hit, so raised arms or swiping motions make her duck and freeze. Lily needs a good mommy or daddy to let her be their lap dog with plenty of belly rubs and hugs given. Lily is crate and house trained and knows the sit and shake commands. Lily does fine with dogs that don't over-react to her out-going, in your face attitude; she does well with tiny to huge dogs, but is too excitable for cats. Lily runs errands and goes to the park and pet stores, but is still working on her leash skills when she gets excited. Her sweet personality is definitely worth it! For more information, please contact her foster mom, Anne. 210-887-8041 or abaumgartner2008@yahoo.com

name: Trip
description:
Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

** This dog is living in a foster home in San Antonio, Texas. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. **
This fat and sassy boy is Trip! Lovingly assigned this name because he will trip you! If you've ever known labradors you know what we are talking about. He sticks VERY close to his people. Trip is approximately 5 years old and fully grown weighing in around 90#. Trip is heart worm positive, but we provide meds to assist in treating this at home with minimal impact to day to day life. Trip LOVES to play fetch and will retrieve til he drops!
Please understand you are commiting to providing a good home for his entire life (up to 15+ years or more) - not just until his cuteness wears off.
You must also be committed to housebreaking, age-appropiate enrichment and exercise, leash training, grooming needs, and positive socialization.
His adoption fee is $250. This includes his neuter surgery, DhPPv vaccination, bordetella vaccination, rabies vaccination, deworming, 6 months heart worm prevention, two months of doxycycline, microchip, leash and collar, Petco coupon book, and 30-days of pet health insurance.
Please be aware that puppies, small breeds, and pure breeds do get adopted quickly so interested parties are encouraged to apply online at www.saspca.org.
Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m.

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and a 30-day trial of 24PetWatch Pet Insurance. Adopters will also receive a Petco Pet Parent Savings Books that contain:• $100s in savings plus a coupon for a free 6 lb. bag of WholeHearted dog food.• Thoughtful care tips.• Online resources and support.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time from the Austin area.

We do try to schedule bi-monthly meet-and-greets in Austin as interest is generated.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

name: Shrugs
description: It's been said that the only thing happier than a three-legged dog is a four-legged dog, though we think Shrugs is definitely the exception. Shrugs recently lost one of his legs, but even just a few days after surgery, he treated it like a minor inconvenience. He's got too many dogs and people to meet to worry about all that! Shrugs gets so excited to see new people that he breaks out in a big smile and his tail goes absolutely crazy. He's still figuring out his balance with the three legs, so he sometimes gets so excited that he almost falls over. But when he sees an unattended sandwich on the table, he might as well have six legs... Whoosh! There goes Shrugs! Shrugs loves to be loved on and leans into you for pets. He nudges your hand if you stop, and he also gives kisses and hugs. He's great with dogs and was so excited to meet the resident Lab in his foster home. He walks wonderfully on leash and loves all the dogs he passes on the street. While he stays calm, that tail just starts wagging whenever he sees one coming. He also loves to watch TV and his tail wags when he sees people on the screen. Shrugs is overall a pretty chill dog to have around. He's house-trained and listens well, doesn't jump on people and takes treats very gently. He is a smart boy who quickly picked up on the rules of the house, and he's food-motivated so training should be easy. He likes to follow his people around the house, but will happily go lay on his bed if you have people things to do. Shrugs would make a wonderful addition to any number of loving homes, and he's going to make some lucky family very happy. Come meet him!

name: Caesar
description:
Caesar is a 6-year-old Great Dane.  Although he is mostly white, he is NOT deaf.   He's been well taken care of all his life, but unfortunately, due to financial hardship, his owner needs to move, so Caesar needs a new home.    

Caesar is a very healthy dog. He is neutered, up to date on all vaccines and on heartworm prev.   His birthday is October 6. He has nearly always lived with another dog, which suits him, because he does have some separation anxiety.   He is fully house trained, knows basic commands and is really a wonderful dog.  

If you would like to give Caesar a new loving home, please fill out the adoption application on our website.   If you already filled out the application, please send us an email to request a meet-n-greet.

Keep in mind, our website is having some issues with the on-line application and for some reason we do not receive applications if they are filled out on the smart phone, so please fill out the application on your PC.

name: Molly Ilene
description:
Welcome to the Wonderful World of Rescue Dachshunds. Look around and read their bios. Find a few whose personality seems to fit well. Consider one of our Well Seasoned Seniors who are truly wonderful and have so much to offer. Need help finding the best fit? We'll help with that too. Please fill out an application and let’s get you all matched up with a loving new “furever’ companion and friend. You’ll find the application on the “Available Dogs” page.
NOTE:

Adoptions to Texas residents only

.

Standard Adoption Fee Adult Dog: $250 ea. Puppy Adoption Fee: $300 ea. Reduced rates for Seniors dogs (10 and up). Reduced rates for pairs (when adopted together).

Email: ddrtxinfo@gmail.com Primary Website: www.DDRTX.org
Molly Ilene is a red short-haired girl with a white chest and white “socked” front paws. She also only has 3 legs. Her rear right leg was amputated early March. We don't know what happened to cause her to need this amputation. She is getting around great and can run and keep up with her foster brothers and sisters. She is very sweet and loves to cuddle on the couch and bed. She loves sleeping under the covers.

If you would like to meet this happy-go-lucky little girl, put in your application today!
Love dachshunds and not ready to adopt or circumstances won't permit having a dog? How about being a sponsor or making a donation. Every one of our dachshunds receives excellent medical care along with day to day food, love and housing. Being non-profit, we rely on generous individuals like yourselves to help save these fur babies. You can do this specifically for one dog with the sponsor button on their webpage or a general donation on our “How To Help” page. Easy and quick through Pay Pal or your debit/credit card. You generosity is sincerely appreciated by all and is tax deductable. Need other ideas? You'll find tons of them on the How to Help tab. All contributions are tax deductable.

Diamond Dachshund Rescue of Texas is a non-profit 501(c)(3) volunteer organization with focus on rescue and adoption of pure breed Dachshunds. All dogs are fully vetted and housed on private property. Meetings are scheduled upon adoption approval. Thank you for your continued support to the rescue and shelter communities!
Opt to Adopt!

name: Edna
description: Edna is a shy and skeptical young lady, but she loves to be held and will adorably tuck her head under your chin. While she's unsure of her world, she has a lot of love to give to her special person - she wags her tail when you talk to her in a sweet voice, and she loves to be pet. Her eyes are so expressive and they're always telling you how much you are loved. Edna is a chill and low energy pup, so she doesn't mind being on bed rest while she heals from a broken back leg and waits to find her forever home. She's been a wonderful houseguest and makes no noise whatsoever - even when the resident dogs in her foster home bark, Enda has no interest in all guff and just keeps a watchful eye on whatever's happening. She does very well being left alone, patiently awaiting your return so she can get back to snuggling. Shy, sweet, calm and quiet, if you're looking for a loyal little lady who wants nothing more than to be your forever cuddle buddy, come meet Edna!

Meet Fabio! 

Fabio is part of a recent group that was just rescued from a testing facility in Mexico. He is being transported to Austin, TX area but we desperately need to find a foster home or his forever home! Fabio has shown us that he is an overall sweet guy. He does well with other dogs and people! We hope someone will open their home and hearts to this guy, especially after what he has been through. He deserves to live a life outside of cruelty and fear! 

If you're interested in fostering or adoption Fabio, please email us at adopt@rescuefreedomproject.org or fill out an application on our website at www.rescuefreedomproject.org.

name: Brady (referral)
description:
BRADY (referral): CONTACT Kim Newsome at 713-825-1411 or complete application at www.WhoRescuedWho.com . Dog is at The Woodlands Dog Suites (north of Houston)

Brady is 3 to 4 years old, fully vetted, neutered, heartworm negative, 80 pounds.  He is loyal and obedient. Brady will let you know when he wants to go out, and come back in. He knows “sit”, “stay”, "no", and shakes with both paws. 

Brady is high energy, active and athletic, and outside, his nose is always to the ground. His athletic abilities include running top speed to catch a squirrel. In the mornings, he greets us, wagging his huge tail from side to side, with a big smile on his face. Part of his greeting includes brushing up against us, like an 80-pound cat. 

Brady is unaware of his own strength, but he never jumps on us, and oddly enough, we've never heard him bark.  Brady is extremely light on a leash in familiar surroundings. He’s great off the leash in our yard, but is never left unattended due to his adventurous spirit. He must also have a securely fenced yard. 

He has a "soft" mouth, which means he accepts treats very gently from your hand. He is housetrained, but not crate trained. As long as he has someone to keep him company, he’s a happy camper. He’ll always whine to let you know when he’s feeling anxious. 

More than anything, this boy needs a stable home, where he can be a part of a family who can give him the love, attention, and activity, he so desperately needs. His personal requests include lots of exercise, a cozy bed by the fire place, and milk bone dog biscuits.

DISCLAIMERS: 
• German Shepherd Rescue of Central Texas claims no responsibility for the descriptions or temperaments of any dogs listed as a referral. 
• We have not met these dogs, evaluated them, or verified claims made by owner or contact person.  
• We do not own or take responsibility or liability for any completed adoption or transaction made regarding these dogs.
• Potential adopters are expected to seek out any and all information on health, temperament, and past behaviors prior to adopting.

description: A note from Red's foster family:  Red is a fantastic boy and has been a great foster dog. His two favorite things are cuddles and toys. He is still a bit of a puppy and does some jumping up, chewing and mouthing hands, etc but has improved a lot just in the time I have had him.  His other great attributes are that he is not a barker and is VERY people friendly. He loves getting pets and belly rubs and will give you lots of licks in return if you let him. He will make his new owners very to happy to have such a loving guy in the home.

name: Peanut
description:
Please contact Jamesa (roxysrescue@yahoo.com), 713-882-2610 for more information about this pet.Look at me, my name is Peanut and I am so cool and I know I am pretty, so that makes me pretty cool!!!!! My foster mom says I like to have to run around in a yard, it doesn't have to be a big yard but I like to roam around outside. I don't really play with toys but there may be 1 or 2 that I like, a stuffed animal or a squeaky toy.
I get along great with other dogs and cats and I would do great as a companion pet, I did have a sister but they separated us and I long to have another playmate, I am crate trained for up to 8 hours, please do not leave me longer than that,
I can be shy at first but you can pet me and then we can become friends. I about 25 lbs and sturdy and have reached my adult weight and height. I currently live in an apartment with some foster siblings but I would love a home with a yard.
Once I get over my shyness and get comfortable, I am a great snugger, especially if you call me Peanutbutter and I will snuggle and my tail wags like crazy. I am independent and sometimes put myself in my crate just to chill out. I also have my meals in my kennels. I walk well on a leash but I am mostly an off leash dog and I stay right by your side like a pro.
Please email my foster mom so you can meet me.

description: Spotty is a world class sweetheart! He gives lots of kisses and his fur is so soft that it feels like a bunny. He loves affection and neck scratches, is house-trained, crate-trained, and walks well on a leash. He was clearly trained at some point in his past, but is now looking for a forever home with someone who wants to cuddle on the couch. He has cute little brown spots on his white ear and down his back. He is a fairly calm and mellow boy and can be a little shy at first until he knows he is safe. With slow introductions, he has been excellent in meeting his foster mom's two medium sized dogs. He is very friendly, and once he overcomes his shyness, he lets his full playful personality come out. He really is a 'turn-key' pup as he already has great life skills and a loving, sweet nature. Come meet him!

name: Nikki
description: This beautiful brindle is 18 month old Nikki, a Plott Hound mix. She weighs around 55lbs. Nikki loves to cuddle with you, always placing her head in your lap and will follow you wherever you go.  We are working with her on basic manners and crate training. This girl is smart and has already learned \u201csit\u201d. Being very treat motivated will help with her training. Nikki does great with other dogs, is wonderful with kids of all ages, but has not been cat tested (she does chase squirrels). She would love to find a family that enjoys walks, hikes, or runs. If you want a loyal loving companion, Nikki is your girl!\n\nAdoption fee covers the cost of spay, microchip, all vaccines, heartworm test and dewormer.

name: Athena Bella
description:
Welcome to the Wonderful World of Rescue Dachshunds. Look around and read their bios. Find a few whose personality seems to fit well. Consider one of our Well Seasoned Seniors who are truly wonderful and have so much to offer. Need help finding the best fit? We'll help with that too. Please fill out an application and let’s get you all matched up with a loving new “furever’ companion and friend. You’ll find the application on the “Available Dogs” page.
NOTE:

Adoptions to Texas residents only

.

Standard Adoption Fee Adult Dog: $250 ea. Puppy Adoption Fee: $300 ea. Reduced rates for Seniors dogs (10 and up). Reduced rates for pairs (when adopted together).

Email: ddrtxinfo@gmail.com Primary Website: www.DDRTX.org
I’m spunky and I know it! My name is Athena and I am a one year old female dachshund mix with the longest legs you will ever find! I am back with Diamond Dachshund Rescue through no fault of my own. My adopter worked too many hours and in my best interest decided to do what’s best for me and bring me back to Diamond Dachshund.

I LOVE TO PLAY! With you or with other dogs. Sitting in one place for too long is boring.

I am energetic and love to run and play with your or with other dogs. The smaller dogs don't seem to enjoy my company because they think I am in their personal space... which I can be but only because I want to PLAY!!! My foster mom and I are working on that. The older dogs tend to find me a little annoying because I'm a little too playful for them.

But, I am crate trained, potty trained, I know the command ‘sit’ and I can use the doggy door. I am a really good girl! I just like to play!

If you or your pet is interested in having a loving and well behaved (but energetic) pup join the family then make your way over to the application and fill that sucker out!
Love dachshunds and not ready to adopt or circumstances won't permit having a dog? How about being a sponsor or making a donation. Every one of our dachshunds receives excellent medical care along with day to day food, love and housing. Being non-profit, we rely on generous individuals like yourselves to help save these fur babies. You can do this specifically for one dog with the sponsor button on their webpage or a general donation on our “How To Help” page. Easy and quick through Pay Pal or your debit/credit card. You generosity is sincerely appreciated by all and is tax deductable. Need other ideas? You'll find tons of them on the How to Help tab. All contributions are tax deductable.

Diamond Dachshund Rescue of Texas is a non-profit 501(c)(3) volunteer organization with focus on rescue and adoption of pure breed Dachshunds. All dogs are fully vetted and housed on private property. Meetings are scheduled upon adoption approval. Thank you for your continued support to the rescue and shelter communities!

Hi,
My name is Bear and I am a handsome Red Doxie. I am really enjoying my new life now that I have had all my dental work done! At first, I was very timid and scared of my own shadow, but I have warmed up to my new foster home and I greet everyone with a wagging tail.

My foster parents have a cat, he likes to pick on me, but I just ignore him, but I get along great the other dogs in the house. I am potty trained, and
love having a yard to run around in. I love to cuddle. I will sit with you on your bed, couch, or any other place that I can be next to you while you read or binge watch Netflix. I don’t understand the leash and harness thing very well, but I am sure given time I can learn to walk well on it.

I can’t wait to find that perfect family to call home, and if you have children, I am ok with that as long as they give me their laps to sit in too! I look forward to meeting you and licking your face!

Love,
Bear

Hi-Ho, Kermit The Dawg here!!!

It’s not so easy being a double dapple hoping for a forever family. I have so many wonderful qualities to offer if you can get past the fact that I can’t hear you and can’t see very well. I am completely potty trained, I am an expert at napping, I get along with all my foster dog family and I will follow you to the end of the rainbow ! Do you have feet that need to be napped on? Have you always dreamed about what you will find at the end of the rainbow?? I’m here waiting to meet you, come see me and I’ll be your forever Kermie…

I am a complete snuggle bug, I love my humans very much but I love sleeping more!

The Diamond Dachshund Connection

(In the tune of “The Rainbow Connection” as sung by Kermit the Frog)

Soon I’ll meet my famileeeeee…………….

Some day I will find it………..

The Diamond connection……..

name: Sheba
description: Sheba is an elder stateswoman with a puppy's spirit and a gentle, affectionate nature. She's calm indoors and out and is about as low maintenance a pup as you could hope for. Sheba loves hugs and kisses, and if she had her way, she'd spend all day sitting next to you being pet. She will seek your hand and place her head near it, just so that you know it's there and that she's ready for pets when you are. And when you stop petting her, she makes sure to let you know that it's okay to continue, gazing lovingly into your eyes and showering with you with kisses if she has to. Though she's loyal to her person, Sheba isn't picky who she gets affection from and is really happy when there are house guests over - she cannot wait to kiss them and see if they're offering pets too! Sheba is a very smart pup and understands what she can or cannot do. She has wonderful manners in the home, lets you know when she needs to go out and does great left alone uncrated. She enjoys napping throughout the day, and while she doesn't need a great deal of activity, she does like going on short walks, taking in the fresh air and feeling the breeze. She's great on leash and non-reactive to the dogs she sees. Sheba would make a wonderful addition to any number of homes looking for a laidback and loving companion. If you're looking for a mellow pup with nothing but love to give, come meet this sweet girl!

name: Marty
description:
Please contact JoEllen (sagdinfo@aol.com) for more information about this pet.Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

** This dog is living in a foster home in San Antonio, Texas. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. **

This handsome boy is Marty, he is a 3 year old neutered male schnauzer who came to us with a broken pelvis and rear leg. After careful consideration our vet elected to amputate his rear leg because it was not able to be repaired. He doesn't really seem to notice it's missing and runs and plays with the best of them. Marty is in desperate need of a loving home because clearly the first home didn't provide proper vet care and as a result he is heart worm positive. We will include medications to help treat his heart worms with his adoption fee.

Please understand you are commiting to providing a good home for his entire life (up to 15+ years or more) - not just until his cuteness wears off.

You must also be committed to housebreaking, age-appropiate enrichment and exercise, leash training, grooming needs, and positive socialization.

His adoption fee is $250. This includes his neuter surgery, DhPPv vaccination, bordetella vaccination, rabies vaccination, deworming, 6 months of advantage multi and 2 months of doxycycline, microchip, leash and collar, Petco coupon book, and 30-days of pet health insurance.

Please be aware that puppies, small breeds, and pure breeds do get adopted quickly so interested parties are encouraged to apply online at www.saspca.org.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m.

Additional questions may be directed to sagdinfo@gmail.com

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.

Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and a 30-day trial of 24PetWatch Pet Insurance. Adopters will also receive a Petco Pet Parent Savings Books that contain:• $100s in savings plus a coupon for a free 6 lb. bag of WholeHearted dog food.• Thoughtful care tips.• Online resources and support.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved and you are traveling from out-of-town, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time.

We do try to schedule bi-monthly meet-and-greets in Austin as interested is generated.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

description:
***COURTESY LISTING***
For more info about this dog, please contact person listed below.

Sweet Annie girl was found wandering an apartment complex. Despite being dumped, she knew to ask for help from a human. So quick to forgive!! 
She is around 2 years and weighing in at 49 pounds. Absolutely loves going for long walks to sniff and explore. Car rides are the best, or is it toys and chew bones? It’s her mission in life to say hi to every human out there. Dogs too, seems to prefer males over females. Cats and squirrels are boring!! 

Politely will ask to go outside to go potty. Doesn’t mind going into a crate for safe keeping while nobody is home. She still has a little bit of puppy tendencies with collecting and chewing things. Ms. Annie is looking for a human(s) who are kind, caring, loving, fun and firm. Pssssst....she can be on the stubborn side at times. Will it be you to give her, her furever home?  

Annie is spayed and vaccinated. Her adoption fee is $75. For more info, contact birdbrain27@msn.com.

name: Felix
description: Felix is in APA!'s Total Obedience Program (TOP), which is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, he has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! Felix is learning skills like sit and down, walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'Place, which means he will go to a specific place in your home on command. Once he successfully completes all the skills on his training plan, he\/she will be considered TOP Dog Ready! Felix is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with him after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193

Characteristic Canines for Special People		
			
MY NAME IS:  Low Rider
POSTED TO PETFINDER DATE:  April 10, 2019
SIZE: 37 1/2 pounds
APPROXIMATE AGE:  1 1/2 years
SHELTER STAFF SAYS:  Low Rider is the cutest little guy.  He rarely barks, he keeps his cage clean, he gets along with other dogs and he walks pretty good on a leash.  When he came in he was very scared and now he is very loving.  He is very inquisitive and will sniff and explore everything.  He will need someone who is willing to take it slow with him but in a very short time he will be your best buddy.

Heartworm:  Not tested yet
For more information please call the HCHS at 512-793-5463.  We are open Thursday through Sunday from noon to 4pm and on Monday, Tuesday and Wednesday by appointment only.  You can see all our available animals at HillCountryHumaneSociety.org.
All our adoptable dogs receive a Cap Star for fleas, DHPPV and Bordatella vaccine and are de-wormed.  
When you adopt one of our animals it will be micro chipped and registered at the time of adoption.
While we do our best to determine the breeds of our dogs, the majority are strays, and we have only general appearance, coat type, size, ear type, tail, tongue color and coat color to base breed on.  It is always possible when adopting a puppy that it will change dramatically to look like another breed.
We highly recommend that you enroll your dog in training classes.

name: Stubbie
description:
Named after the American Hero Sgt. Stubby!  I like to think that I am a dream of a dog. I am young, and love love love to give kisses.

I have foster brothers and they are teaching me all about balls and toys. I can't decide if I want to chase, chew or snuggle them. We share dinner and play time and we get to sleep in the big bed together until the lights go out then I get to sleep where-ever I want. 

 I haven't been around too many kiddos but I think I like them. The little girl at the groomers was cute and gave me some loving. 

My foster mom was bragging that I haven't had one accident in the house and I will even “knock” on the door when I am ready to come back in from my potty break.

 I really like my new foster home but mom says not to worry, she won't let me go unless I'm a perfect fit.

name: Dede
description:
Characteristic Canines for Special People		
			
MY NAME IS:  Dede
POSTED TO PETFINDER DATE:  April 11, 2019
SIZE: 99 pounds
APPROXIMATE AGE: 8 years
SHELTER STAFF SAYS:  DeDe is a very sweet dog.  She loves to be around people, but also likes her alone time just laying around relaxing.
She is good with other dogs, loves to go on walks and she is good on a leash. She needs to be in a home with no children. She is house trained and loves to go for rides in the car.

Heartworm:  Negative
For more information please call the HCHS at 512-793-5463.  We are open Thursday through Sunday from noon to 4pm and on Monday, Tuesday and Wednesday by appointment only.  You can see all our available animals at HillCountryHumaneSociety.org.
All our adoptable dogs receive a Cap Star for fleas, DHPPV and Bordatella vaccine and are de-wormed.  
When you adopt one of our animals it will be micro chipped and registered at the time of adoption.
While we do our best to determine the breeds of our dogs, the majority are strays, and we have only general appearance, coat type, size, ear type, tail, tongue color and coat color to base breed on.  It is always possible when adopting a puppy that it will change dramatically to look like another breed.
We highly recommend that you enroll your dog in training classes.

name: Merlot
description: With ears that flop this way and that way, Merlot is the sweetest thing. She loves to cuddle up right next to you and lay her head right on your lap as she noses at your hand until she gets her favorite thing every- a relaxing head scratch! When she isn\u2019t snuggling up on the couch enjoying your favorite show with you, she is running around the house collecting every toy as she learns how fun they can be. Merlot loves to run around outside so if you\u2019re looking for a running partner, this girl can keep up with you! Merlot walks well on a leash, and is picking up house training quickly. Be the best part of Merlot\u2019s rescue story and fill out an application today at www.snipsa.org

name: Amelia
description:
Little Amelia what she lacks in size, she makes up with her character! 
She is energetic and adventurous. She enjoys exploring outside, chasing the ball, barking at unfamiliar objects, playing with toys and gnawing on chewies. 

When she gets excited, she can walk upright! 

Besides being outgoing, Amelia is also very loving, gives lots of tiny kisses and can give hugs with her front legs! She is intelligent, observant and very eager to learn!

Amelia will thrive with an active family who can take her for daily walks. Ideally, she needs a family with time to engage her in vigorous play because this sweet girl has lots of energy!

name: Jenifurr
description:
****PLEASE DO NOT CONTACT ADR ABOUT THIS DOG. INSTEAD, PLEASE CONTACT THE DOG'S FOSTER @ THE E-MAIL ADDRESS LISTED BELOW***

THIS IS A COURTESY LISTING. ADR is not responsible for the health, temperament, behavior or placement of this dog. Listings are done at the request of the dog's owner and as an outreach and community service in hopes of finding these dogs a loving, stable forever home. Placement decisions are made solely at the discretion of the owner and not Austin Dog Rescue. Owners are required to ask for an adoption fee from adopters.

This is the information that we received from Jenifurr's current foster:

We saved a pregnant stray dog off the streets of Houston in November, and provided her a safe place in which to have her puppies in Austin with us. Jenifurr's puppies are finding homes easily, and now she's ready. She's a 40-pound Heeler mix, spayed, has all of her shots, and has been through her first training classes. She is lovable, and loves the outdoors. She is walking well, but needs a little more work and a yard. She does bond to certain other dogs, and loves her toys. We love her and wish we could keep her, but we have so many dogs and want to leave a place for more fosters. 

If you are interested in meeting this gorgeous girl, please contact Beth at: beth@titosvodka.com

10 years old

Poodle

name: Frijoles
description: Frijoles is a beautiful young pup with big, expressive eyes and an even bigger personality. He has so much love to give and wants to play with everyone and everything! Frijoles is currently recovering from a wound on belly, but he doesn't seem bothered at all by his cone. He was a champ during all the treatments and being crated a lot, so some long walks will do him good! His foster parents have been taking it easy with him while he heals. but Frijoles will play with ANYTHING given the chance (toys by himself, other dogs, people). He has so much energy, as he is still a puppy at heart with 100% of his mind dedicated to squeaky balls, ropes, etc. He's still working on his manners as he's just so excited when he gets to meet new people, and his whole butt wiggles as he knocks stuff over. It's hard to really cuddle Frijoles at the moment because of the cone, but he will push that smooshable face right into yours and he loves having his ears scratched. He currently lives with a couple of Saint Bernards and a pittie, and he gets along with all of them. He also walks great on a leash, is house and crate-trained and will go in his crate on command. Playful, sweet, energetic and resilient, Frijoles is looking for a home with a yard and an active family who will include him their adventures and give him plenty of attention. If you're looking for a lovable playmate with personality to spare, come meet this great pup!

name: Orphie
description:
Welcome to the Wonderful World of Rescue Dachshunds. Look around and read their bios. Find a few whose personality seems to fit well. Consider one of our Well Seasoned Seniors who are truly wonderful and have so much to offer. Need help finding the best fit? We'll help with that too. Please fill out an application and let’s get you all matched up with a loving new “furever’ companion and friend. You’ll find the application on the “Available Dogs” page.
NOTE:

Adoptions to Texas residents only

.

Standard Adoption Fee Adult Dog: $250 ea. Puppy Adoption Fee: $300 ea. Reduced rates for Seniors dogs (10 and up). Reduced rates for pairs (when adopted together).

Email: ddrtxinfo@gmail.com Primary Website: www.DDRTX.org
Meet Orphie. He was adopted from DDRTX almost a decade ago. His family had to move and needed our help to take care of him. We have taken him back in to help him find a home.

Orphie gets along with other fur friends. He is a sweet furry love bug. He does like to explore so a harness and leash are always a great thing to have and he is good on the harness and leash.

Orphie has had his dental and is now ready for adoption.
Love dachshunds and not ready to adopt or circumstances won't permit having a dog? How about being a sponsor or making a donation. Every one of our dachshunds receives excellent medical care along with day to day food, love and housing. Being non-profit, we rely on generous individuals like yourselves to help save these fur babies. You can do this specifically for one dog with the sponsor button on their webpage or a general donation on our “How To Help” page. Easy and quick through Pay Pal or your debit/credit card. You generosity is sincerely appreciated by all and is tax deductable. Need other ideas? You'll find tons of them on the How to Help tab. All contributions are tax deductable.

Diamond Dachshund Rescue of Texas is a non-profit 501(c)(3) volunteer organization with focus on rescue and adoption of pure breed Dachshunds. All dogs are fully vetted and housed on private property. Meetings are scheduled upon adoption approval. Thank you for your continued support to the rescue and shelter communities!
Opt to Adopt!

name: Nellie
description: Nellie is 3 years old. She is a rescue that has had a hard life. She has overcome abuse and health issues and is a big cuddle bug! She is a tripod, but that doesn't slow her down. She loves to play with tennis balls, steal all the blankets, and snuggle her person. She needs to be in an only pet home (NO cats or other dogs) where she will be primarily kept indoors due to her scarring on her back, as it has sun sensitivity. She is very affectionate and loves to go for walks, go to Petsmart and Petco, or to get treats from Starbucks. She does need to be in a home where the owner is able to lift more than 40 pounds as sometimes she does need assistance getting on\/off furniture or out of vehicles due to her amputation when she gets tired. She has a lot of love to give and needs to be in a home where she can be loved on and love on her people. She is up to date on all shots and preventatives. name: Pablo
description:
Welcome to the Wonderful World of Rescue Dachshunds. Look around and read their bios. Find a few whose personality seems to fit well. Consider one of our Well Seasoned Seniors who are truly wonderful and have so much to offer. Need help finding the best fit? We'll help with that too. Please fill out an application and let’s get you all matched up with a loving new “furever’ companion and friend. You’ll find the application on the “Available Dogs” page.
NOTE:

Adoptions to Texas residents only

.

Standard Adoption Fee Adult Dog: $250 ea. Puppy Adoption Fee: $300 ea. Reduced rates for Seniors dogs (10 and up). Reduced rates for pairs (when adopted together).

Email: ddrtxinfo@gmail.com Primary Website: www.DDRTX.org
Light Heartworm Positive ContractPablo is a young 13.1/2 lb. dapple, although he appears more like a red dachshund. He has a light dusting of beige hair on his sides and almost a black strip down his back. He has one beautiful white spot on the side of his neck. But while his muted markings do not make a huge fashion statement his unusually calm and gentle nature makes him truly unique at his young age.

Pablo is still growing his personality and his foster family is making new discoveries every day. He loves to be pet, and when you stop he will nudge for more. He likes being in a lap or lying near his human. He likes toys and has a gentle way of playing. He loves lying in the sun or adventuring outside chasing squirrels with the other foster dogs in the house. He will take treats in a very sweet mannerly way.

He is housetrained and has accepted being in a kennel but prefers to sleep in the bed with the other foster dogs.

He gets along well with all adults and the other dogs in the house but may need to be around only older children. He can be a little protective of his food at feeding time, but his Foster mom is working on his trust through this and he is showing signs of improvement.

Pablo is most definitely very sweet, gentle and quiet with an angelic look out his eyes. The right family will need to give him time to adjust to yet another change in his life, but we are confident he will accept new surroundings in the same way he has in the foster’s home. There is a future lifetime of love to have from this little guy.

PUPDATE: Pablo has tested light heartworm positive. He is available for adoption under a heartworm positive contract.
Love dachshunds and not ready to adopt or circumstances won't permit having a dog? How about being a sponsor or making a donation. Every one of our dachshunds receives excellent medical care along with day to day food, love and housing. Being non-profit, we rely on generous individuals like yourselves to help save these fur babies. You can do this specifically for one dog with the sponsor button on their webpage or a general donation on our “How To Help” page. Easy and quick through Pay Pal or your debit/credit card. You generosity is sincerely appreciated by all and is tax deductable. Need other ideas? You'll find tons of them on the How to Help tab. All contributions are tax deductable.

Diamond Dachshund Rescue of Texas is a non-profit 501(c)(3) volunteer organization with focus on rescue and adoption of pure breed Dachshunds. All dogs are fully vetted and housed on private property. Meetings are scheduled upon adoption approval. Thank you for your continued support to the rescue and shelter communities!
Opt to Adopt!

name: Grace
description:
Grace is an approximately 10-11 year old Boston Terrier. She weighs about 17 pounds. Grace appears to have had a rough life and has been dealt some difficult cards. Despite this, she is the sweetest little girl in search of her perfect furever.

She came to us from a shelter — she was microchipped but the owner did not come for her. She has a very wobbly/strange gait but gets around pretty well. She can’t do stairs or jump on/off furniture, but she can run around, and she loves to roll in the grass. She definitely has a sense of humor.

We aren’t sure what causes her gait issue, one thought was maybe a disc issue in her past but we have no true diagnosis for this — but she did not give the vet any indication of it being an active injury or painful. We think due to her very shortened toenails (from rubbing the ground) & confidence in her walk (even with the sometimes falls) that she has had this gait for quite a while as well. What we do know from her labs and abdominal ultrasound is that sweet Grace has been living with liver tumors for probably quite awhile. One is very large. Without surgical intervention/biopsy, the guess is that they are likely benign or low malignancy because they are not fluid filled or interesting in appearance, and if they were anything very aggressive then Grace would likely not be near as happy and functional as she is.  We will definitely provide her lab work and radiologist report to an adopter should they want to go further with exploring diagnostics for her liver.

We have no way of knowing how long Grace has left, and if she doesn’t have long then we want to prioritize her happiness and comfort over diagnostics and surgeries while she’s in foster care. Our vet has reassured us that this is a valid route to pursue since we know nothing about her history other than she is an older gal with some big struggles going on BUT she is happy and not in pain and LOVES to eat, so we want to focus on that. She could very well be a hospice adoption, but we don’t know that for sure. 

She has had a very generous donor sponsor her adoption fee in hopes that we can find her the perfect home for her golden age. We ask that an adopter be prepared of course that Grace may not have a lot of time left although we really hope that she does! Also, she has some other minor things that could need to be addressed down the line should she have a bit of time left. These include a possibly a dental at some point and a very minor BB size mammary tumor removed (and monitored for growth in the meantime). We don’t want to anesthetize her unless it’s urgent due to her compromised liver, but we want to make an adopter aware of these things. She also is on proin for sleep (pee) Incontinence and hasn’t been having any more accidents since she started this medicine! This would be something an adopter will likely want to continue — it’s not an expensive medicine and very commonly prescribed to seniors.

Grace is dog & cat friendly. She is potty trained but she needs to go out for pee breaks pretty often or she will have an accident. This is because she drinks a bit of water due to her liver. She does know how to use a doggy door to let herself out to pee.

We know it seems like a lot to take on, but we really believe that Grace’s guardian angel is out there. If you think you are that home for her, please read the adoption requirements and apply to meet her at www.texassweetiesdogrescue.org . She is spayed, up to date on vaccines, heartworm negative, and microchipped.
label: adopted

name: Roux
description:
Roux is a sweet, loving and playful 2-year-old doodle mix that’s roughly 12 lbs.  He’s super gentle and loves to cuddle and be with people, he’s basically your shadow.  He’s very timid and has separation anxiety, so he would do best in a home where someone is always home.  

He’s potty trained and knows his basic commands like sit, down, come and learning shake and wait.  He loves to play fetch, be outdoors and go on walks.  Roux does amazing on the leash — he will bark and whine when you go to get the leash (because he gets super excited).  He does well with other dogs but wants all the attention (he’s learning personal space).  

Roux does not like to be confined or kept behind closed doors (bedroom), he tends to chew on the door trim trying to escape.  However, he does well roaming freely at home alone, he’ll just lay on the sofa and wait for his human(s) to come home.  He tends to bark and whine when he gets excited but you can calm  him down by saying “quiet”.

Roux’s adoption fee is $250; he’s neutered, up to date on vaccines, microchipped, and heartworm negative. If you are interested in meeting Roux, please fill out the application at www.texassweetiesdogrescue.org

To find out how you can get involved and help turn San Antonio into a no-kill city, please visit www.sanantoniopetsalive.org

description: You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.My name is Winston and I am very high energy but oh so loveable. name: Mamma
description:
Mamma is a very sweet and calm dog. She loves to cuddle and chew on antlers. Her favorite things include playing outside, eating and taking naps. She can be very shy at first but once she warms up she will beg you for attention and love you forever. 

She is house trained and crate trained. She walks well on leash but can be hesitant in new environments. She plays well with other dogs and does well with kids, too.

Mamma is about 5 years old. She got that name because she was rescued with puppies. Those pups have been adopted and now it's her turn! She is spayed, vaccinated and microchipped. When first rescued, she tested positive for heartworms. However she's been treated and is now heartworm free and taking prevention.

Thanks for considering a dog from Texas Cattle Dog Rescue! We place heelers all over the state of Texas.

If you're interested in one of our dogs, please first complete our adoption application. You can download it at www.texascattledogrescue.com/adopt.html. Our standard adoption fee is $250 for adult dogs, $300 for puppies. Our dogs will be spayed or neutered, vaccinated and heartworm tested before going to a new home. We conduct a home visit to help match up the right dog with the right owner. For more information, visit our website www.texascattledogrescue.com.  Email adopt@texascattledogrescue.com if you have questions.

name: Secret
description:
That's why, darling, it's incredible

That someone so unforgettable

Thinks that I am

Unforgettable, too......

My Secret Dog has come so far socially! I toy with keeping her but she deserves her own family that will have soooooo much more time and love to shower her with! She’s such a good girl, but she’s not the life of the party yet, she’s just now feeling like she has a life and is starting to enjoy it! I want her to have a special home where she will totally forget about me, and her being ”the Secret Dog” who hid under the cat tree for a month, scared to show her face. name: T-BONE
description: T-Bone was recently surrendered to PAWS when his owner became chronically ill. Here's what T-Bone's mom had to say about him!: "This is T-Bone - a 4.5 year old Bloodhound\/Rottweiler mix, who weighs approx. 95 pounds. Like most dogs, his favorite things include playing with the same toy for hours (a black rubber Kong), going for rides, playing fetch until he simply can't anymore, and carrying his favorite stuffies around the house gingerly. T-Bone is also obsessed with cardboard boxes and likes to carry them around and shred them. (He even opens his own Christmas gifts.) He's also a big fan of the dog park (even without other dogs in it) and hanging out at the brewery with people, kids, and dogs to meet. T-Bone also loves baths and will even ask you for one! He is very smart and trainable and while he knows sit, stay, and down, he was also trained to open the refrigerator (with a pull rope) and to retrieve medications for his chronically ill owner. He is eager to learn and loves to show off. I joke that T-Bone is on his first pass at Earth - he's never lived any other lives and so everything is a new experience to him. He's always excited, happy, and full of joy. I've actually never met a more loving dog. Despite being a big guy, he loves to cuddle. He is great with other dogs and isn't cat aggressive but hasn't spent much time with them. He also loves children but is big and all muscle so maybe not the best choice for tiny children. He is crate trained and sleeps in his crate at night but would love nothing more than to be in bed with you."

name: Xena
description: Xena is a true warrior princess. She's been through some tough times in her past life, which resulted in a leg amputation, but after being showered with love and attention in her foster home, she's become a whole new dog. That missing leg doesn't slow her down at all, she really enjoys her walks through the neighborhood, and she can jump up on the couch all by herself! When you come through the door, Xena gets so excited to see you that her whole body wiggles, then she runs to get her favorite toy to show it to you. Xena LOVES her squeaky toys. She has a favorite that's a squeaky avocado, and when she hears it squeak, she will wake from a dead sleep with ears fully perked. True to her name, Xena has been an absolute princess in her foster home, and her affectionate morning nuzzles are a wonderful start to the day. She gets super excited to see you wake up and does a nuzzling thing in your face while pressing her body on top of you with her butt sticking up in the air. Those eyes will melt your soul and that tail will tell you everything you need to know. There's so much love in her eyes that her foster mom says she can hardly stand it. Xena is protective of those that she loves and will let you know if she hears something outside, but she warms up quickly to new people once she knows they're supposed to be there. After initially meeting someone and they sit down, Xena's ready to be their best friend and snuggle. She also does wonderfully with her foster's 7 year-old male boxer and may be able to live with a well-matched doggie sibling who will let her be the boss. She loves to play and tries to get the resident pup dog to rough house with her, but he's never been into all that. Despite her impressive strength, Xena is an incredibly gentle girl. She is very careful when taking treats and giving kisses, and even though she is so excited about walks, she patiently waits for her harness to be put on at the door. She does well left home alone and waits to get up for food until it's put down and you call for her. An absolute gem of a dog, Xena would make a wonderful addition to any number of loving homes. Come meet this sweet girl!
label: not-adopted

name: Maggie Mae
description: Is it possible to cuddle with humans all the time all day? Maggie Mae doesn't know for sure, but she's trying to find out! This beautiful girl's foster dad says she's incredibly sweet and would cuddle all day if she could. But she's also just as happy playing fetch. She's a real pro who especially loves catching tennis balls, but isn't picky about toys. She'll fetch anything you're willing to throw. A smart pup, Maggie's learning to obey basic commands and walk well on leash. Because she has so much energy, a home with a big back yard, or even a ranch with a pasture to run, would be a bonus. But Maggie Mae is really just hoping for a home with humans she will love (because she loves all people) and who will love her back, and of course someone who will keep throwing those tennis balls.

MY NAME IS:  Rodney
POSTED TO PETFINDER DATE:  April 16, 2019
SIZE: 42 pounds

All our adoptable dogs receive a Cap Star for fleas, DHPPV and Bordatella vaccine and are de-wormed.  
When you adopt one of our animals it will be micro chipped and registered at the time of adoption.
While we do our best to determine the breeds of our dogs, the majority are strays, and we have only general appearance, coat type, size, ear type, tail, tongue color and coat color to base breed on.  It is always possible when adopting a puppy that it will change dramatically to look like another breed.
We highly recommend that you enroll your dog in training classes.

description:
Meet our little Blossom!


As soon as she sees you, Blossom’s tail slowly wags back and forth. And once you get down to her level and give  a loving pat on the head and tell her what a good girl she is, her tail moves so fast, you can almost feel a breeze! Blossom loves to be the center of attention and to her, you are the whole world. On a relaxing day at home, Blossom turns into quite the cuddle bug and will snuggle up right next to you as you read a great book. If you’re looking for a pup to be your shadow, Blossom is your gal. She loves nothing more than being by your side and the pitter patter of her tiny paws following you all around the kitchen will always put a smile on your face. Blossom loves to go for walks and happily trots beside you the entire time. Blossom seems to be house trained, crate trained, and leash trained! What’s not to love with this sweet and smart girl?! Fill out an application for Blossom today at www.snipsa.org

When she isn\u2019t snuggling up on the couch enjoying your favorite show with you, she is running around the house investigating every room and curiously sniffing at the toys. We think that once she understands how fun they are, Buttercup won\u2019t want to put them down! Buttercup seems to be house trained, crate trained, and leash trained! With her fun and quirky personality and little stub tail, how could you not fall in love with this happy girl? Fill out an application for Buttercup today at www.snipsa.org!

Bubbles is crate trained and house trained and is working on her leash training, but as long as you are by her side, she can take on the world. name: Sarabi
description:
Up for adoption in Texas: Sarabi.
She is SO BEAUTIFUL!
This gentle dog is a friend to the whole animal kingdom - you name it, people, dogs, cats, livestock. From all observations she peacefully coexists with them all.
She is about 3-years-old and weighs about 65lbs.
She was born with a malformed front paw. It doesn’t hurt her or slow her down at all.
She is great with dogs of all sizes including puppies.
Although Lucky Lab found her as an outdoor dog, she has settled into the indoor life and much prefers it now. She does love to be out in the yard, but she is happy to go back to her spot on the couch afterward.
Sarabi is playful and submissive. Although a gentle girl all around, she does love to go rough and tumble with other dogs. She is a bit shy around new people, but she adores her foster family and is quite the cuddler with those she knows well.
She has had an amazing foster home and they've taught her how to walk on a leash, go for car rides, she's becoming the lady about town. 
She would do best in a home with a backyard. 
She is spayed, vaccinated and microchipped.
Apply at www.luckylabrescue.com

This smart boy easily learned to use the doggie door so he can go outside with his chewie or play with a toy. (Ben has an old pelvic fracture & weak back end...that has gotten a lot stronger. He could barely walk when we first got him. He does well with a potty schedule. \nBen gets along great with other dogs. (He hasn\u2019t caused one problem!)He immediately fit in! Super easy going...soul mate. Ben likes cooked green beans and carrots for a snack. \nHe can be a bit scared and nervous at first, so He needs someone who is gentle and encouraging. He is heartworm positive and will be treated at CSRA expense! Ben fosters in the San Antonio area.

name: SHAYE
description: Hello! My name is Shaye. Unfortunately, I will have a chronic problem of my left front shoulder popping in and out of place for my whole life. What this means, is I will have to be on medication on and off as needed for pain management.  If some special person wanted to take me to an animal orthopedic specialist, they may be able to come up with treatment options for my shoulder.  I am a happy dog, and I love to play!
label: adopted

name: Paislee
description:
Up for foster or adoption in Texas: Paislee.  We want nothing more in the world than for Paislee to have an amazing, loving home, because she's such a loving dog.





Paislee is gorgeous and adores people. She is about 2-3 years old and weighs about 75lbs. 





People who meet her instantly fall in love. She loves to play and loves to retrieve.





We saved Paislee and her brother from a high kill shelter and they lived together for a couple of years-- now they're gone their separate ways and we are looking for a foster or adopter for her. 





We'd recommend at this point, a home without other pets for Paislee. But she would love, love, love to love you! 





She is spayed, vaccinated and microchipped. Housebroken too! 






Apply at www.luckylabrescue.com
label: not-adopted

name: Courage
description:
We have a beautiful girl up for adoption in Texas with the most incredible story. Meet Courage! 
Courage is about 7 months old and weighs 50lbs. With her brindle colored coat and amber eyes-- she is simply gorgeous.
This pup was found living under a bulldozer with her mom and siblings in South Texas.
Men in the neighborhood were abusing them all! Hitting them, throwing rocks at them! It was awful.
Someone contacted a Lucky Lab volunteer and we brought them all into a fantastic foster home. 
When they first arrived they were very scared but with time they blossomed in their foster home. We think with more positive reinforcement training she will really bloom! 
If you've ever been to a puppy training class with your pup it's so much fun. 
We'd recommend a home with adults, older kids would be okay, and a fenced in yard. She would LOVE having another dog or two in her forever home! She loves playing with other dogs so much!! 
She is spayed, vaccinated and microchipped. Housebroken too.
Apply at www.luckylabrescue.com or send us a message on Facebook!

name: Meg
description: My what big ears you have! Meet the amazing Meg! She is a 5 month old Belgian Malinois mix. Even though she is not pure breed, she sure has many of those amazing traits of a Malinois. She is super smart, very active and loves to please her owner! Oh and did I mention she LOVES food and treats!! Honestly between this girl's drive to please her owner and her love of food, she should be at the top of her class with training in no time. Over the past two weeks in a foster home, she is already accident free in the house and knows sit. She gets along with other dogs, hasn't shown any interest in cats, although her exposure to them has been super limited. In her foster home she has an 11 year old human brother whom she loves. Her energy level may be too much for small children. Meg will likely do best in a home with an owner who will provide daily exercise although she sure loves to cuddle up to you at the end of the day. If you are looking for a smart, fun loving girl, give Meg a shot. No apartments or rentals! Malinios experience is required! She sure would love to meet you today!

name: Han Solo
description:
A long time ago in a galaxy far, far away…

There were a litter of adorably cute puppies lost and looking for their furever families. With eyes full of love and and tails full of energy, we knew that they would have their best chance of finding them here at SNIPSA!

You’ll find Han Solo playing with his foster siblings all day long! He loves to wrestle and is constantly wiggling his butt with excitement as he tackles his pup pals! When he is all played out, Han Solo likes to snuggle up with his big foster brothers..unless you pick him up of course. Then he’ll nap right on your lap! Han Solo is still a young Jedi and will need training to be the perfect pup but with a great Jedi Master, he will learn quickly! Is the force strong with this pup? Fill out an application for Han Solo today at www.snipsa.org!

name: Bailey
description:
Birthday boy Bailey here! Foster mom says we celebrate in style! 

My other mom went to heaven so I landed with CSRA, I gotta say they are pretty awesome!

I have foster dog sisters but I really like my foster mom best, life is good when I have a dog bed to lay in and someone to scratch my belly.

 At my other home they liked to feel me from their plate so I'm just a tad bit "fluffy". Foster mom says we will work on that but I say more of me to love! 

She thinks I'm a really good boy, she puts this thing called a belly band around my waist, I don't mind, it's like a being hugged all the time. 

I can't wait for my next home where I can chill out, get a belly scratch and nap with my human.

name: Sammy
description: Sammy arrived at APA! with an unknown injury to his back legs, which causes him to walk a little funny, but he exhibits no pain and gets around just fine. He even handles the stairs well. Sammy also has some incontinence issues, and it is unknown if it is related to his legs, but in the meantime a belly band has solved this issue for his foster mom, and he does not mind them at all! Sammy is great with dogs and people so far, and the vets were impressed with how well he handled being examined. He is a very happy, well-behaved puppy, he understands 'no' and respects the space of his grumpy foster sisters. Sammy is also great in the car - he lays in a dog bed in the car and passes out for most of the ride. Sammy loves to carry around a tennis ball in his mouth and is content to play with the ball by himself, though he is also not opposed to you throwing it for him every now and then. Sammy also loves his kennel and happily sleeps in it on a nice soft bed. Sammy loves belly rubs, your undivided attention and laying next to his foster mom wherever she is in the house. Come meet this sweet pup!

We highly recommend that you enroll your dog in training classes.

name: Maya
description:
Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

** Maya is a new intake who will be available around May 4th after she gets her spay, gastropexy, and vaccinations. We are accepting applications now so if you are interested please submit one! **

This super friendly, 8 month old fawn great dane is Maya! Maya earns her foster's award for record time in winning over all the other dogs in the foster pack. She has such a goofy and sweet personality that the four of them were playing soon after she arrived and they haven't stopped playing since. And Maya is always in the middle of it! She is good with dogs of all sizes, though like most young danes she doesn't know how big she is and will sometimes knock little ones over! She came to us as an owner surrender and her previous owners taught her good house manners. She is house trained and does not chew things up. She tends to pull on the leash in excitement but she is a quick study and already improving her walking skills!

Her adoption fee includes her spay surgery, DhPPv vaccination, rabies vaccination, deworming, heartworm prevention, microchip, leash and collar, Petco coupon book, and 30-days of pet health insurance.
Please be aware that puppies and small breed do get adopted quickly so interested parties are encouraged to apply online at www.saspca.org.Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio TX 78232. Event hours are 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m. Additional questions may be directed to sagdinfo@aol.com

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.

Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and a 30-day trial of 24PetWatch Pet Insurance. Adopters will also receive a Petco Pet Parent Savings Books that contain:• $100s in savings plus a coupon for a free 6 lb. bag of WholeHearted dog food.• Thoughtful care tips.• Online resources and support.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved and you are traveling from out-of-town, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time.

We do try to schedule bi-monthly meet-and-greets in Austin as interested is generated.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/
label: not-adopted

name: Baloo
description: Yup, that\u2019s me. Just like the big \u2018ol bear in The Jungle Book, I\u2019m playful, good-natured, easy-going, fun-loving, gentle, caring and a whole lot more. Here they call me a silly, big teddy bear. My size isn\u2019t a problem because I\u2019m so chill and well-behaved. I\u2019d love to show you my sit-shake skills when you visit. And when you take me home, I\u2019ll lie quietly by your side and you can read me The Jungle Book so I can learn about that other Baloo.
label: not-adopted

name: Caramel
description: I\u2019m as sweet as my name. I live up to every expectation you have of a little dog that looks like me \u2013 get me anywhere near your face and you\u2019ll end up getting lots of kisses. Just the thought of getting some affection makes me happy and excited. But then, just the thought of getting to go on a walk to explore my surroundings has the same effect. I guess I\u2019m just a happy, excited girl! The only thing that would make me happier is to find a forever home with you.
label: not-adopted

name: Gladys
description: Oh my, my hair is all messed up! That\u2019s probably because I love rubbing against people. Good thing I really don\u2019t care about my hair. I care more about sharing my love. I\u2019m mostly calm, but I also have a goofy side that loves to play. The folks here say I\u2019m easily teachable too. I\u2019m already good on the leash. Wouldn\u2019t you love to teach me more and play with me and give me a forever home? I would like that so much!
label: adopted

name: Thorton
description: I don\u2019t mean to look so serious. I was a little nervous about having my picture taken. You should have seen me afterward! I really love people and it takes just a few minutes to warm up and then I show my true personality. I do look quite handsome, don\u2019t you think? I do prefer to be an only pet in a home with just adults and older kids. I\u2019m sorry to be picky, but we\u2019d all be a lot happier that way. We could bring each other great happiness.
label: not-adopted

name: Voldebork
description: Where do I begin to explain myself? I\u2019m a strong, active, loving dog with a kind heart who gets along with most dogs and people. I was found on a college campus, obviously a stray but soaking up all the attention I could get. A kind lady took me home and tried to find my owner but had no luck. With a house full of family and dogs, she couldn\u2019t keep me though everyone there had fallen in love with me, so they brought me here. She left a letter all about me for the lucky family that adopts me. I hope it says good things! I have a feeling it does, because I\u2019ve seen people cry when they read it. Take me home and you can read it too.

name: Howard
description: Howard is an intelligent, lovable pooch with the cutest, most perky ears! He is so full of affection and can't wait to meet his forever family! Howard is an energy matcher - if you're excited, he's excited, if you're relaxed, he is too. He absolutely loves to romp around the yard and get you outside to play with him, but if it's time to chill, he's down for that too. Howard is a bit shy when he first meets new people, but once you've won him over, you have a friend for life! This well-behaved pup is house-trained, crate-trained, and has learned 'sit' and 'down'. He walks wonderfully on leash and is a big fan of trails! This quick learner and really aims to please his people and has excelled in APA!'s Total Obedience Program. The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP Dog, Howard has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! Howard is now TOP Dog Ready, which means he has already learned all the skills in his training plan, including walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers, calmly walking past another dog, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' and coming when called. Howard has worked hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with Howard after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 Howard would love to be a part of a home that loves activity! He has lots of energy and loves long walks and getting plenty of exercise. He mostly just wants lots of love and can't wait to meet his forever family! Come meet Howard, he promises to be the best pal he can be! Follow Howard on Instagram @howard.needs.a.home_apa
label: not-adopted

name: Keke
description: OMG we're friends! BEST friends! We just met but I love you!!' This silly and adorable lady is up for anything. And me mean anything. Keke is a real party animal and she comes with a super high energy level. She loves playing fetch more than anything, but she'd also make a great hiking or running partner. Keke is very dog-social and a playgroup rockstar. She's actually recommended to go home with another energetic dog, since she loves having another pup to mix it up with, and you'll appreciate the assist in helping get her ya-yas out. She's also a big fan of squeaky toys, so make sure you stock up on those. This sweet girl has never met a stranger and isn't shy about letting them know how excited she is to meet them. On top of being house and crate-trained, she's also a very smart girl and is coming a long way in APA!'s Total Obedience Program, which is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Keke has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help her learn the skills to become the best dog she can be! Keke is learning skills like sit and down, walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'place', which means she will go to a specific place in your home on command. Once Keke successfully completes all the skills on her training plan, she will be considered TOP Dog Ready! Keke is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with her after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https:\/\/vimeo.com\/89434193 Keke would love a home with another pup who can help her burn off all that energy along with active people who will get her out for adventures. A backyard to romp in would be lovely too. Come meet this fun pup!
