name: Rafe
description:
This is Rafe.  He is a 3 1/2 years old Great Dane.   He needs a new home because his previous family has 5 kids and when # 6 was due to arrive, they decided that there was not enough room in their small home for Rafe.  

Rafe is a very sweet dog.  He loves everyone.  Obviously he is good with kids.  He is also OK with other dogs. Never been around cats.  He has not had any training or vet care, but we will provide that and also get him neutered prior to adoption.

If you would like to give Rafe a good loving home, please go to our website and fill out the adoption application.  Please fill out the application on a PC or a laptop, but it will not submit if you do it on your smart phone.
label: not-adopted

name: Sarah
description:
Sarah is an absolute delight. She is housetrained but needs support to find the door at first since her vision is limited. Her peripheral vision is better but mature cataracts prevent her from seeing directly in front. She appreciated a well lighted environment. She knows how to use a doggie door. 

She loves to dance in the mornings to celebrate every new day, loves men, loves napping in the sun. Her hearing was damaged by untreated ear infections (in her previous life) so she sleeps that wonderful, uninterrupted and deep sleep we all wish we could experience. While her ears are better now, she will need some veterinary oversight to ensure continued improvement. 

Sarah would love to chase a cat, if they would just stand still! Otherwise, she will cuddle up with them. She enjoys the company of her foster sisters, Emmy Lou and Flossie, and loves evenings when her people settle to watch a movie. 

Sarah is about 10 years old and is a perfect companion.

name: Mugsy
description: With those gorgeous eyes and happy smile, it\u2019s hard not to smile back when you meet Mugsy. And what\u2019s not to smile about? This sweet girl loves people of all ages and gets along well with other dogs and cats too. Taking a road trip? Mugsy would love to join. Riding in the car is always a good time to Mugsy! Mugsy loves to go out with you when she can no matter where you\u2019re going. Whether it\u2019s running an errand or joining you on the family summer vacation, Mugsy is always enjoying life with you. name: Nala

Whatever trauma she endured - she is always looking forward, always looking for love. She isn't ashamed of the scars that life has left her. name: Duck
description:
Please contact JoEllen (sagdinfo@aol.com) for more information about this pet.Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

** This dog is living in a foster home in San Antonio, Texas. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. **

This handsome boy is Duck, he is a 3 year old neutered male Great Dane mix. He is fully grown weighing in around 110#. Duck is a good natured gentle boy who gets along with everyone he has met so far.

Duck has tested positive for heart worms, we will include medications for the slow kill protocol with his adoption fee. He will get 2 months of oral medications, as well as 6 months of advantage multi. We will retest him for heart worms in 6 months as well.

Please understand you are commiting to providing a good home for his entire life (up to 12+ years or more) - not just until his cuteness wears off.

You must also be committed to housebreaking, age-appropiate enrichment and exercise, leash training, grooming needs, and positive socialization.

His adoption fee is $350. This includes his neuter surgery, DhPPv vaccination, bordetella vaccination, rabies vaccination, deworming, microchip, leash and collar, Petco coupon book, and 30-days of pet health insurance.

Please be aware that puppies, small breeds, and pure breeds do get adopted quickly so interested parties are encouraged to apply online at www.saspca.org.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m.

Additional questions may be directed to sagdinfo@gmail.com

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.

Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and a 30-day trial of 24PetWatch Pet Insurance. Adopters will also receive a Petco Pet Parent Savings Books that contain:• $100s in savings plus a coupon for a free 6 lb. bag of WholeHearted dog food.• Thoughtful care tips.• Online resources and support.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved and you are traveling from out-of-town, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time.

We do try to schedule bi-monthly meet-and-greets in Austin as interested is generated.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

name: ELLA
description:
Hi there, my name is Ella. I like to think its short for Umbrella because I block metafurically rainy days with my wide happy spirit. I know my face has your typical Boxer look of concern, but that's just my face, I'm happy happy. My mutto is "I do zoomies to chase away the gloomies".

I am 12 weeks and 22 lbs, so I'm on my way to be a med/large girl. My fur Mom is Boxer, this we know. We have no clue on dad, but my paperwork says Lab mix, but let's face it, some people are gonna also identify me as a Pitbull mix too. So really, I'm a mix of the top 3 goofiest dogs on the planet. Triple non threat. A banana split, a win win win.

I do have a few questions for you, my pawtential adopter. Do you drool? Do you snore? I like to sleep next to my Humans face at sleepy time and it's non-goatsbull (Note: she means nonnegotiable). Snores and drools aren't deal breakers, I just want to know ahead of time because you know so much about me now.

I'm a great multi tasker. I can hold a toy in my mouth while running the zooms in the room. Equal to a human chewing gum and walking, now that takes talent! I am good with all dogs, working on potty training, and spayed, got my shots, blah, blah, blah boring stuff people want to know. Final ask, I don't like to dine alone, so will you sit with me while I gobble my vittles? It's also like non-goatsbull and stuff. Love you already!

Ella is available for adoption with Saving Grace Dog Rescue of San Antonio. The adoption fee is $150.00. An adoption application, home visit and adoption contract are all required. All dogs are spayed/neutered, up to date on vaccinations appropriate for their age, microchipped, and wormed for internal and external parasites. If you would like more information or an adoption application, please email us at sgdrsa@outlook.com.

Please note that visual breed identification in rescue dogs is unreliable so for most of our dogs we are only GUESSING at predominant breed or breed mix. We get to know each dog as an individual and will do our best to describe each of our dogs based on personality, not by breed label.
organization: Saving Grace Dog Rescue of San Antonio

name: Kenai
description:
We have a beautiful boy up for adoption in Texas with the most incredible story. Meet Kenai!





Kenai is about 7 months old and weighs 50lbs. With his brindle colored coat and amber eyes-- he is simply gorgeous.





This pup was found living under a bulldozer with his mom and siblings in South Texas.





Men in the neighborhood were abusing them all! Hitting them, throwing rocks at them! It was awful.





Someone contacted a Lucky Lab volunteer and we brought them all into a fantastic foster home.





When they first arrived they were very scared but with time they blossomed in their foster home. We think with more positive reinforcement training she will really bloom!





If you've ever been to a puppy training class with your pup it's so much fun.


We'd recommend a home with older kids, adults and a fenced in yard. He would LOVE having another dog or two in his forever home! Kenia loves other dogs! 





He is neutered, vaccinated and microchipped. Housebroken too.





Apply at www.luckylabrescue.com
label: not-adopted

name: Dominic
description:
Can you say CUTE , GORGEOUS, PUP who needs a home... in Texas? 


Meet Dominick, he's up for adoption in Texas. 


Dom is about 7 months old and weighs 50lbs. He is simply gorgeous. 


He has the saddest story! This puppy was found living under a bulldozer with his mom and siblings in South Texas. Men in the neighborhood were abusing them all! Hitting them, throwing rocks at them! It was awful. 


Someone contacted a Lucky Lab volunteer and we brought them all into a fantastic foster home. They were all scared to death at first but their amazing foster parents have been helping them work through that. They are blossoming.


We think with more positive reinforcement training Dominick will bloom even more. 


Dominick loves to come sleep next to his foster parents, he is so at peace then. He gets along super well with all the dogs in his foster home, he loves playing with them. He'd love to have a dog in his forever home to play with. 
We'd recommend a home with adults, adults with older kids and a fenced in yard. 


He is neutered, vaccinated and microchipped. Housebroken too.  


Apply at www.luckylabrescue.com
label: not-adopted

name: Argus
description:
Up for adoption in Texas: Argus. 





What a cute boy, check out those white socks, just adorable! Argus is so loving with people-- and he's smart too! He typed up this bio so you can read all about him. 





"Hi, my name is Argus. They say I’m about four or five years old and weigh about 60 pounds.





Somehow I ended up alone in a small high-kill Texas shelter. Just when the shelter was deciding to put me on death row, Lucky Lab noticed me, and I made the trip up to north Texas to be with my foster family. 





I have a little more floof than the average Lab, possibly some fluffy dog gene in there somewhere. 





I love being cuddled by my foster mom, and especially like to snuggle with her at night or if she’s sitting around reading a book or watching TV.  





I’m also happy just sleeping on the floor, and I only bark if I see a suspicious character.  I’ve grown to love the rest of my foster family but I mostly play by myself or stick with the humans if they want to play with me. 





I have a lean graceful physique, with the softest, silkiest fur and ears for petting. I am fine staying in the house when my family is gone with some fun toys, but wow, am I glad to see them when they come home!





Over the months I’ve had lots of four-legged foster brothers and sisters that are labs, and a corgi that lives here too. I don't always like to share everything with them, and I'd probably want to meet your dog too and make sure we're a love connection. :)





I hope I can find my forever home soon, so I can share lots of quiet and fun times with those very special humans who love me for who I am."





Argus is neutered, vaccinated and microchipped, housebroken too! We'd recommend a home with adults, adults and older kids and if you have another dog, a meet and greet. 





Apply at www.luckylabrescue.com

name: Diamond
description:
Hello! My name is Diamond and my personality is as sweet and spunky as my ears, which are as big as Texas! And it just so happens that I'm up for adoption in the Lone Star State. 
I’m approximately 5 months old and weigh 26 lbs. I survived a probable coyote attack and now my wounds are healed and gone! 
I live with three other dogs and get along great with them. I also have a 7 year old human foster brother who I love snuggling with on the couch. 
My favorite pastimes are playing with other dogs, finding sticks, chewing on my toys, and snuggling with my foster family. I know how to use a doggie door, sit for treats, and I’m crate trained. I’m almost done with potty training, too. My foster mommy says I will make a great family member.
Apply for me at www.luckylabrescue.com

name: Kahlua
description:
***PLEASE DO NOT CONTACT AUSTIN DOG RESCUE ABOUT THIS DOG. IF INTERESTED, PLEASE CONTACT THE PERSON LISTED BELOW VIA E-MAIL***

THIS IS A COURTESY LISTING. ADR is not responsible for the health, temperament, behavior or placement of this dog. Listings are done at the request of the dog's owner and as an outreach and community service in hopes of finding these dogs a loving, stable forever home. Placement decisions are made solely at the discretion of the owner and not Austin Dog Rescue. Owners are required to ask for an adoption fee from adopters.

This is the information that we received from Kahlua's current owner:

Kahlua is almost 2 years old, She is a Morkie (Maltese/Yorkie) that is moderately active. We have been through dog training sessions. She needs a home with a fenced-in backyard so that she can run and play. She is shy around big dogs, but loves small dogs (she weighs around 12 lbs). She is very shy around children, so a household with small children would not work for her. She is tan with highlighted hair that is soft to the to the touch. She is a a gentle snuggler. On the other hand, she can play hard too.. I work from home, and don't have a fenced-in backyard. I am rehoming her because I believe she deserves a home with more activity, which would look like a home with 2-4 people/pets. Kahlua has been spayed, chipped and her vaccinations are all up-to-date. I also keep her on monthly heartworm and flea treatments.

If you are interested in meeting this sweet little girl, please contact Carrie at: cevl@yahoo.com

description:
The Fairy Litter

Iridessa, Terence, Silvermist, Fawn, Vidia, Rosetta 

This is quite the fairy tale! All of these mystical lab mix cuties in this brother and sister family are looking for their permanent homes. These pups are bursting at the seams with lots of love and are more than ready to share it with you. They have quite playful personalities while also having an incredible demeanor. A love for sticks is a mutual occurrence in this litter as they all enjoy romping around in the outdoors. Following an afternoon of play, you can find these cuties curled up for a little snooze! Their fur is almost as soft as their little puppy hearts. If you are looking for a snuggly, adventurous companion, you will not go wrong with any of these fairy friends. Fill out an application for your favorite one(s) today at www.snipsa.org!

name: Luna
description:
Luna is an approximately 2 year old Husky mix. Luna got all the best features of the Husky breed, with none of the ones that make that breed a challenge. She is smart, playful, and a happy girl, but she isn’t hyper or an escape artist or a constant talker.

Luna loves to play, either amusing herself with toys, or running and playing with other dogs—she gets along with all manner of dogs. She is house trained and crate trained. She is working on her leash training.

Luna is fully vetted and up to date on all vaccinations and preventatives. She tested positive for heartworms and received injections, plus the 30 day course of Doxycycline and prescribed crate rest. That was about 2 months ago. She isn’t yet testing negative, but we know that is a function of time.

Luna was found wandering the streets in a really bad neighborhood in Houston—she was very thin and had an injury on her back. After a lot of TLC (and her HW injections to get her completely healthy), she is ready to join a really lucky human family.

name: Rosana Dana
description: Rosana Dana and her 7 puppies were picked up on the streets of Pleasanton, and a good samaritan found them and took them to the animal facility there. They did not have the abilities to keep them, so APA! came to the rescue. Rosana was very protective of the babies when they were being moved around, but once she realized she was in a safe place, she was happy for her foster mom and others to love on and play with her and the puppies. The puppies have gone on to their forever homes, and now Rosie is looking for one of her own. Rosana has the long body and short legs of a Dachshund and the face, ears and coloring of a Cattle dog. While she can be shy when meeting new people, she warms up quickly. She loves to cuddle and put her head in her foster mom's lap and follows her around the house like an adorable shadow. She is such a love bug and truly wants to be close all the time, gazing at her person with those beautiful, expressive eyes. Rosana loves playing with her doggie foster sibling and adorably carries around her favorite pink horseshoe toy all day. She has obviously lived in a home, as she is house-trained, good on the leash and loves to ride in the car. She has a medium energy level, excellent house manners when left home alone and is very treat-motivated. And she already knows how to use a doggie door. Rosie would do well in any number of loving homes, but she'd love to have another dog to play with. Come meet this perfect pup!

name: Lola
description:
Heartworm Prevention is given on the 1st of each month
Lola was found February 13, 2012, as a puppy, happily wandering the streets of Northeast Houston. I brought her home and she immediately started sleeping in the bed with me. She was perfect as an apartment dog and quickly became my best friend. She went everywhere with me. She loved walking, but was never a fan of dog parks. She is intimidated by other dogs and although she wants to play, it doesn’t take long for her to show fear aggression. I don’t know her history before my home, but she was a stray in an area that was home to many large “aggressive breed” strays. Lola is gluten sensitive, so she eats grain free food and treats. If she gets wheat or gluten in her diet she begins to scratch her belly and undercarriage until she bleeds. Lola has back trouble sometimes. We manage it by making sure she doesn’t go up and down a lot of stairs or jump off of high furniture. On two separate incidents she had to be medicated and rest her back. In April of 2018 my wife and I were blessed with triplet infants. We weren’t expecting so many babies but we figured 3 dogs and 3 babies- what could go wrong? well we quickly saw that once the babies were moving around, Lola and her back issues were not ready for triplets.
Lola would be happiest in a home with no other dogs or small children. She would do well with older children who understand to be gentle. She is a great best friend and companion. She is accustomed to a life where she is the best friend and priority, and she deserves a life where she isn’t afraid all the new little people will stand or fall on her. Lola is still very active and playful and would love to live somewhere that she can be taken for walks. She loves to play with dog toys or play fetch. Lola is a loyal best friend and is very affectionate to her person

name: Cotton
description:
Adoption applications should be filled out to expedite the process:
http://www.lilpaws-malteserescue.org/joomla/adoption/adoption-application.html

Monthly Meet & Greets 
Petco (in Leander) every 1st Saturday of the month
Pet Supplies Plus (Parmer & Mopac) every third Saturday of the month

This is Cotton, a Malti-poo Male, 16lbs.  He has been fixed, micro-chipped and is about 5 years old.  He was picked up as a stray.  Cotton is Very friendly & gets along with other dogs & children.  He loves to play & go for walks, is potty trained & crate trained.  He is real good about sleeping in a dog bed at night.  Available soon, he is having eye surgery on the 22nd.  He will be at adoption day at Pet Supply Plus, Parmer & Mopac on the 20th, 12-2pm if you would like to meet him.

Adoption fee $400


** Please note: Due to their size, our dogs are not suitable for homes with children under 5..

We do not have a facility, all dogs are fostered in the homes of our volunteers. If you are interested in adopting a dog from Lil' Paws Maltese Rescue and other Petite Paws, please visit our website at www.lilpaws-malteserescue.org and fill out an adoption application. This is the first step in our adoption process. Our goal is to place our dogs in safe, stable and loving homes in the Austin Metropolitan area. Thanks for looking!

Lil' Paws Maltese Rescue and other Petite Paws depends on donations to keep the dogs in our program healthy. Many health issues are taken care of before a dog leaves a rescue: spaying, neutering, immunizations, dental care, and in some cases major surgery. Because of the cost of this care, donations are essential to enable us to continue our work. If you would like to show appreciation for what we do and help us continue to do it please go to our website homepage and click the donate button. We thank you in advance for your support.
organization: Lil Paws Maltese Rescue and other Petite Paws

name: Cooper
description: Cooper is a sweetheart and such a character, he is a typical playful puppy. Eat , sleep play, repeat. That's my normal mantra. Cooper and his siblings love to play. They play before they will eat in the mornings, have a quick breakfast, and play again. Cooper and his siblings are around 9 weeks old. They are developing personalities of their own. They love to explore, and hide under the furniture from one another. They love to play and wrestle. They have lots of toys but of course they like to all play with the same one. Running and chasing each other around. Watching three pups all trying to hold a tennis ball is quite hilarious. Cooper likes to snuggle in your lap after he's worn out from playing. And he sleeps through the night like a champ. The pups are too young to go outside potty, they need to complete their puppy vaccines first. We have been working on paper training. Cooper is doing very well, he will even get back into their playpen to go potty on the paper. Of course, he is still a baby . Accidents will happen. Carrots and Golden delicious apple wedges are his favorite treats. They are great for pups to munch , healthy and cold from the fridge can help with teething discomfort. Young puppies like to chew, a carrot is a great alternative. The pups are up to date for age on vaccinations and preventables. They still need to be neutered and micro chipped, which will be done before they leave my care. Cooper is looking for a family to call his own. Is that you? I am living in a San Antonio Pets Alive! foster home. By adopting me, you not only give me a new leash on life; you also save the life of an additional pet who can be rescued from euthanasia and placed in foster care. If you are interested in adopting me, please email adopt@sanantoniopetsalive.org with my name and ID#. Please allow up to 24 hours to respond, as all fosters work on a volunteer basis. To find out how you can get involved and help turn San Antonio into a no-kill city, please visit www.sanantoniopetsalive.org
label: adopted

name: Trapper
description: Trapper is an awesome little pup, full of energy. He loves to run and run, it seems he is always in a hurry. He is such a character. He loves to run around chasing and playing with his brothers. Trapper is a great explorer , trying to fit into every nook and cranny. He races around the house exploring . Trapper was the first to master the stairs, both going up , and coming down. Coming down can often be a little scary for them. Now the pups love to play on the stairs, I have had to put a barrier up so they are safe . They get a little over excited on the landing. They have lots of toys, Trapper loves balls and loves to play tug of war with his siblings. It seems though, just like kids, the pups always want the same toy. They are always wrestling one another for a toy, and can get quite vocal with each other. They can play for hours, then flake out for a long nap. Trapper sleeps through the night. Trapper is just a pup and is still getting teeth in, so he loves to chew. Did I mention Trapper loves to chew ? He prefers cold carrot sticks and golden delicious apples over any of their many chew toys.. Trapper is still young , around 9 weeks old. He is learning to use pee pads and newspaper to go potty. He is really is doing very well, and seeks out the newspaper, but still misses sometimes. Trapper is up to date for his age on vaccinations and preventables. He will be micro chipped and neutered prior to adoption. He is an energetic little sweetheart looking for a family to call his own. Is that you? I am living in a San Antonio Pets Alive! foster home. By adopting me, you not only give me a new leash on life; you also save the life of an additional pet who can be rescued from euthanasia and placed in foster care. If you are interested in adopting me, please email adopt@sanantoniopetsalive.org with my name and ID#. Please allow up to 24 hours to respond, as all fosters work on a volunteer basis. name: Chance
description:
Chance is completely blind, and while only two years old, unfortunately Golden Retrievers are prone to a genetic disorder called pigmentary uveitis. We are going to try some special eye drops, just in case there is a chance of restoring his eyesight, but unfortunately the odds are very low.

On top of all that, Chance is also HIGH heartworm positive, after bloodwork and X-Rays we know we are going to have to take it slow.

All this combined means Chance will not be available for adoption anytime soon, and will be with us for a few months while we get his health straightedge out, including adding some much needed weight. However chance is available to foster for those residing in Kerr or Gillespie County that can commit to bringing him to frequent Veterinary visits.

Dachshund/Cocker Mix (typical now-really-sure-what-the-mix-is dog)

Toby was surrendered along with Disney to a local municipal shelter because they were too much to handle. During the first couple of days, his foster mom thought "something is just not right". Toby seemed to be very calm for a puppy. He was following Disney and the other dogs around and played but seemed to be hesitant sometimes. Puppies really don't have brakes, but Toby was never really making the first step and was following everybody or was just by his foster mom's feet. He did run around being all puppy playful but every once in a while would run into something. 

Toby's foster mom voiced her concern to the vet and it seems that Toby is either blind or has some sort of vision disability.
 
In order to help him thrive better, Disney and Toby were separated. Toby has a hard time being crated alone, he is confused without another puppy around. He will learn soon that he is safe and cared for. 

His other senses seem to be fine, he will follow hearing footsteps and smelling the other dogs. He will probably do well in a home with a playmate, but will also do well as a single dog in a home where there isn't a lot of furniture moving.

Toby's adoption fee of $350.00 includes his vet exam, age appropriate vaccinations, worming, monthly heartworm prevention, flea treatment, neuter, and microchip.

If you live in the Austin Area and are interested in adopting please go to www.forgottenfriendstx.org and fill out an application.

Adoption decisions are based on the best overall match and not done on a first-come-first-serve basis.

name: Beber
description:
My name is Beber. I am a 9 month old Aussie mix, but my personality is all Aussie! I traveled a rough rode these past 9 months and as a result I am very timid. My foster mom says I have come along way in trusting people, but what I need is a home of my very own. One who will love me, work with me, and be patient as I build up trust. I would do best in a home without small children. I get very scared with fast and loud movement, especially when coming near me. I really need someone who has some experience with dogs, because of my fears I really need someone who understands me. But I promise you, once I trust you, I will give you all the love and cuddles you could ever want. I would love a Home with another fur brother or sister, even if it’s a cat. I love all things furry! My foster mom tells me I walk amazingly on leash, and I always go to my crate when I’m told. She says I’m a good boy!

If you think I am a good fit for your family,please fill out the application:

https://www.australianshepherdsfurever.org/adoption-application

name: Cary
description: Look, I know my pictures make me look like I am a big doofus. Am I big? yes. Am I a doofus? Ok, also yes.  But I'm a very very SWEET doofus.   \n\nCary (Carrot Top aka Care Bear)  is a young  guy. He's probably maybe only a year and a half old with the energy and vigor of a much younger pup. He loves to play, he loves to bark, he loves to jump up on your face and smother you with drooly kisses. He is NOT a delicate flower, to put it mildly. He would make an AWFUL apartment dog--his bark can be heard several states over. He has the will to climb up on countertops but all the grace and skill of a drunken walrus. If you're looking for a calm companion, we can direct you to several other wonderful, deserving dogs. But if you're looking for a lotta fun and a lotta love and heart of gold, Cary's your guy.   This loveable mug is fostering in the Austin area.
organization: Cocker Spaniel Rescue of Austin\/San Antonio
label: not-adopted

name: Heidi
description: Meet Heidi!  She is an adorable collie\/mini aussie mix.  Heidi is 9 months old, house trained, kennel trained, and knows how to use a doggy door.   Heidi is a typical playful puppy, she is very sweet, loveable and a smart girl.  She gets along great with other dogs and is in a foster home with dogs of all sizes.  She is anxious about car rides but can overcome that with patience and training.  While she waits for her forever family, she will just be playing her days away while she waits for her forever family.  If you are interested in meeting Heidi, please let us know!  Please send your application to myhapytail@yahoo.com.  Applications are found under the How to adopt menu on our website at www.myhappytail.org.
organization: APAC - Association for a Pet Adoption Center

name: Spec
description:
Spec here! Say, you ever been to Spec's? I'm dying to go! I hear the ad on the radio while they clean my cage: "Spec's Wines, Spirits, and Finer Foods...with thousands of gourmet goods and accessories." First off, named after ME! Plus, they've got spirits and I DO, TOO! People here say I'm super spirited. Not to mention, HELLO, I'm all about finer foods! I'm all about any food, really. The similarities are downright uncanny! I've got my heart set on this place, people. All I want is a forever family to take me there and maybe buy me a roll of gourmet PUPPERONI. I'm ready for my field trip!

Come see me at the City Of Taylor, Texas Animal Shelter or call 512-352-5483 for more information.

name: Bailey
description: I'm Bailey. Yup, like an Irish cream coffee. I'm smooth, sweet, and ready in under a minute. In fact, I've already got my bags packed. It didn't take long. Come see me at the City Of Taylor, Texas Animal Shelter or call 512-352-5483 for more information.

description: I'm Astro! I'm an athletic pup with lots of team spirit. Baseball is my fave! GO ASTROS! I know we'll hit it outta the park, you and me. All I'm looking for is a HOME run! Come see me at the City Of Taylor, Texas Animal Shelter or call 512-352-5483 for more information.

name: Faith
description:
Faith is a super sweet, 22lb Lab mix. She loves to cuddle and is a people pleaser. This girl loves to snuggle on the couch while chewing on her special bone and enjoys going for a walk. Really she is just happy to be by your side. Her foster has her trained to use the doggy door and she does well in her crate. Faith can be a little vocal when meeting new dogs, but that’s just her way of saying she wants to play. Being incredibly food motivated will help with training, she already knows “sit”.

Faith had a rough start to life, she was found in a garbage bag on the freeway with her sisters. But she still loves humans so very much. 

Adoption fee covers the cost of all vaccines, spay, microchip, deworming, and preventative meds.

name: Hope
description: Hope is a sweet little momma dog whose favorite things are snuggling and snoozing. She is a very pretty girl with a calm, laid back demeanor. She has a wonderful temperament and is very treat and attention-motivated, so training her is easy. She's been learning commands like sit, down and shake. She walks really well on leash and only needs a few reminders not to pull. Hope is always appreciative of pets and cuddles, she plays gently and is not mouthy at all. She will 'talk' and play growl with her toys and likes to hide her chewies in the couch cushions and then arranges the couch blankets over the hiding spot. She rarely barks, and she's been very polite when meeting new people. Hope is ok with being crated, but doesn't really need it as she is fine when home alone. She's also not an early riser and is happy to sleep in with you. Hope is a just the easiest dog to have around. She's so well-behaved and sweet, and she's going to make some lucky family very happy. If you're looking for a low maintenance cuddle bug, Hope is your gal!
label: not-adopted

name: Tyson
description: I don't want to disappoint you, I want you to be happy with me and snuggle me. Also, can I have more treats?' This soulful and sweet boy is ready to give you all of his snuggles and love and he can't wait to find his forever home so he can show off all his great skills! Tyson is currently living a foster family and loves playing, wrestling and running with his doggie foster sibling and would love to have a similarly energetic pup to mix it up with. Tyson tires out before his doggie pal, but he stubbornly keeps going and will try to play forever. He's no long distance runner, but he will chase a tennis ball to the end of the earth! He's great at playing fetch and will hunt the ball out even after it's put away. Tyson is an amazing cuddle bug who couldn't be happier snuggled up next to you, making sure his head is rested close to you or on your leg. He will stare at you with his deep, sweet eyes to ask to snuggle and loves being kissed on his nose. At home Tyson is very gentle and responsive to commands and he knows a lot of them. He knows to 'back away' from food and 'stop playing' when him and his doggie buddy get too rough. He paws the door or bumps the doorknob to go potty, and knows sit, lay down, 'watch me' and 'give paw'. He even goes to bed on command (which is the perfect time to listen to his cute little snore!). He isn't crazy about his crate, but he'll stay in it quietly while his foster parents are at work. Tyson loves hearing his name called, and looks heartbroken when he is scolded and is quick to stop doing bad things. He is always eager to please and doesn't want you to be disappointed in him. If all that wasn't impressive enough, Tyson has a very soft coat and the most adorable freckles all over his nose, chest and belly. He even has an amazing 'happy run where his paws clop up and down like a horse while his lips flap up and down with delight! Tyson wants nothing more than to love and be loved by you. He learns SO quickly and will be incredibly loyal to his forever home! Come meet this great pup!

name: Hoss (referral)
description:
HOSS (referral): CONTACT DONNA MCKEE AT YOGIMCKEE@YAHOO.COM
Dog is in PARADISE, TX.

Hoss is 75-80 lbs, neutered, 3 to 4 years old, GS or Belgian Shepherd mix; up-to-date shots and HW Positive (funds for treatment available); working on House training; not social with other dogs and not sure about cats; great with older kids and livestock. 

Hoss was rescued from a negligent and abusive situation. The owners did not take the time to socialize him, let him out of his small, unsheltered pen, or feed him adequate food for his size. Hoss was being cared for by neighbors because they became concerned when he was under weight and sickly. The local police and animal control could not do anything to help unfortunately because it "looked like" he was cared for once the neighbors stepped in. He was in a filthy pen for 3-4 yrs. He was so thin you could see his ribs and hip bones, and his hair was falling out.  Eventually, he was rescued from his situation, but he has some behavioral issue from his abuse.

I need to place this dog because I do not know how to train him properly so he can live a happy stress-free life that he so deserves. He is gaining weight and slowly working on bonding with people. I have been walking him daily, and he looks forward to going on his walks and seeing me. Hoss is making great progress with more walks and socializing with my other dogs, but he is not to be trusted around small dogs or off leash. He has no people aggression and is not bothered by children; he just takes some time to like them, but that will improve too with love.  His aggression issues are much better. I believe the neuter, along with the walks and the love he is getting are contributing to the improvement. Please contact me to give him a loving home. 

DISCLAIMERS: 
• German Shepherd Rescue of Central Texas claims no responsibility for the descriptions or temperaments of any dogs listed as a referral. 
• We have not met these dogs, evaluated them, or verified claims made by owner or contact person.  
• We do not own or take responsibility or liability for any completed adoption or transaction made regarding these dogs.
• Potential adopters are expected to seek out any and all information on health, temperament, and past behaviors prior to adopting.

name: Sasha (referral)
description:
SASHA (referral): CONTACT CONTACT JENNIFER WARKENTINE@HOTMAIL.COM
Dog is in SAN ANTONIO, TX.

My name is Sasha. I am approximately 10 years old. My current owner got me from a German Shepherd rescue in Texas when I was about a year old; I have been with her ever since then. I am up to date on my vaccinations and receive monthly heartworm preventative meds and have never had any issues with that. Other than yearly allergies which seem to occur every April, I am in good health. I just visited my vet last week and got my yearly allergy shot, so I should be good for a while. 

Temperament wise I am fairly calm. I tend to get hyper when cooped up too long, but as long as I get my daily walk I am fine. I like to play with other dogs just fine, but I DO NOT like cats at all. I am somewhat nervous around new people, but as long as they are friendly and calm towards me I don’t have any problem. As far as children go, I think I would do much better living in a house with older kids who will play with me. I don’t do as well with little toddlers who like to pull on my ears and tail. 

I am potty trained and don't have any problems with that. I am a very good guard dog and will protect my owner. I deserve a good home with lots of love and attention.

name: Tom
description:
Imagine after 6 years, you and your buddy Jerry are taken by your owner to the bet and BANG - the vet is told to kill you ... because your owner is moving from Houston to NJ.
That is our story.
Jerry, the Daschund and I have stayed together with the family - seen two f his daughters grow up and when he relocated he wanted us killed. 
Luckily Ramesh Anand and his family saved us and we are in Houston Looking for a home anywhere in US or Canada.
I am extremely sweet and friendly and love showering people with kisses.
I walk reasonably well on a leash and eager to please.
Jerry and I are bonded and would like to go to a home together - the nice part is that when you adopt us, we give each other company too.
I am choosy about other animals and would prefer a home without another pet.
I am HW-ve and upto date on shots.
Check out this videoclip about Jerry and me. https://youtu.be/8sal6psVmZc

name: Suki
description:
Please contact Anne (abaumgartner2008@yahoo.com) for more information about this pet.Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

5 yr perfect 30 lb house dog and jogging partnerSuki has been a family dog all her life, but her energy level requires regular exercise. So, she lost her home when her family downsized yards and got too busy for her. Suki is doing great in her foster home. She just needs her regular interactions and walks and she has settled right in. She is crate and house trained, is a pleasure to walk, and is great with children and dogs. She was indifferent to her first cat meeting, but should be further tested, For more information on Suki, please contact her foster mom, Anne. 210-887-8041 or abaumgartner2008@yahoo.com.
Suki's adoption fee if is $175. She is spayed, her microchip will be registered with her adopter, she is up to date on all her vaccines, dewormed, heart worm negative and will go to her new home with her next month's heartworm and flea prevention and collar/leash set. We meet at the Petco on 281/1604 Saturday's 11-3pm.

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.

Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and a 30-day trial of 24PetWatch Pet Insurance. Adopters will also receive a Petco Pet Parent Savings Books that contain:• $100s in savings plus a coupon for a free 6 lb. bag of WholeHearted dog food.• Thoughtful care tips.• Online resources and support.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved and you are traveling from out-of-town, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time.

We do try to schedule bi-monthly meet-and-greets in Austin as interested is generated.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

name: RORIC
description: Roric is very uncomfortable at the shelter. All the noises frighten him, and he\u2019s not sure how to handle his current situation.  Being afraid makes him aloof, but beneath the fear, Roric is a very sweet boy. He\u2019s amazingly good looking, and given time, he\u2019ll come out of this experience and become an incredible companion.  He does seem to know how to walk on a leash. He is too fearful to demonstrate if he knows commands. He\u2019ll take treats in his kennel, which right now is his safe place. Inside, he\u2019s yappy and tries to keep everyone at bay.  Outside is overwhelming for this handsome boy. While he tries to avoid people, he will relax enough to allow you to touch him briefly which suggests he\u2019ll like to be petted once he\u2019s in a more favorable situation.  Roric needs an adopter or foster who is experienced in working with scared dogs. He\u2019ll require time and patience, and lots of love will make a world of difference to him.

name: Horace
description: Horace is very dog-like. If you were to just think of a random dog, you would probably think of a dog like Horace. Playful, goofy, affectionate, loyal and always just a tad confused, he is all dog all the time, and his demeanor reminds his foster mom of Dante the dog from Coco. Horace is house-trained, polite in the home and gets along great with other dogs of all shapes and sizes and wrestles with his foster doggie siblings every chance he gets. He prefers to be around people at all times, but can entertain himself with a toy or Kong if needed. He's super affectionate and likes to snuggle in close, and he will not think twice about climbing into your lap or anyone else's. He's a bit of a gangly sort. Some of his parts, like his feet and ears, seem a bit too big for the rest of him. It just makes him extra cute. Horace has a moderately high energy level, he loves fetch and is amazing at it - so much so, that if he can't get someone to throw the ball for him, he will kick it all over the yard with his big paws so he can chase it! Horace is for the true dog lovers out there, and he'd love an active home where he'll get plenty of exercise and be included in the family's adventures. Come meet him!
label: not-adopted

name: Bubba
description: Bubba is one of the sweetest dogs you'll ever meet, and he wants to do is to be next to you, no matter what youre doing. He absolutely loves cuddling, especially when its on the couch. He is well-mannered and is excited to meet everyone. When he greets you when you get home, he'll give you so many kisses! When he's outside, he loves to smell everything and chase squirrels if you let him. He can also be a total clown! Bubba knows commands like sit, shake and is working on lay down, but he's a quick learner. He wants to make you happy because that makes him happy. Bubba is such a great dog and will be happy with playing all day to laying down with you when youre sick. Bubba is the total package. Come meet him!
label: not-adopted

name: Churchill
description: Churchill, much like his namesake, is quite the crowd-pleaser. He may not be able to give speeches, but those loving eyes have a lot to say. Gentle, sweet and stately, get Churchill some spectacles and a pipe and he would wear them well! He is a dog of the people and is super friendly when meeting strangers, giving gentle kisses and hoping he'll get some belly rubs in trade. There is something really special about this wise old-soul. Churchill trusted his foster family immediately and has so much gratitude toward them. Whatever his life was before, it's miles away for this super sweet and gentle pup. He is always thumping his tail when someone comes into view and has been known to make a piggy snorting noise when he is excited. He also has the best bark - putting the accent of the FFFF in WOOOFFFF. Even though he snores like a freight train, you can't help but smile when you hear him napping. Churchill is house-trained and has free reign of the house when left alone. Due to some mobility issues we're still trying to get to the bottom of, he hasn't been out on many walks. And in lieu of zoomies, he does adorable rapid-speed tippy-taps to show how happy he is. He's also done wonderfully with his foster doggie sibling, a 7 year-old Rottie mix, and he'd love a home with a doggie friend or two. Churchill is a truly amazing dog with so much love to give and he will make some lucky family very happy. Come meet this perfect pup!

description: If you’re looking for a fun playful puppy, you absolutely have to meet Maki! He loves to run around, pounce, and play all day long! Whether it’s on top of all of his hoarded toys or in a nearby basket-if he can lay on it, he will nap on it! Think this cutie fits in with your family? description: Jasmine is named after a lovely sweet flower and she is just as sweet as it is. Former owner says she is housetrained, good with adults and kids of all ages, and she's been friendly with other dogs. She enjoys toys, treats, and all kinds of fun activities. Jasmine is just a wonderful dog all around and she's looking forward to being part of a new forever family.\n
label: not-adopted

name: Lucky
description: Lucky is a stunning young dog who appears to be an Alaskan Husky. This breed has a very loving temperament, equally affectionate towards humans and other dogs, and famous for their love of cuddling. The Alaskan Husky needs to be given constant mental stimulation, or else he will find creative ways to pass time. For example, he will come up with more and more creative ways to escape from the yard when you try to keep him from doing so. In the past, this has been true for Lucky, so he needs a new forever home with a confident owner who's willing to invest some time, patience and training to help Lucky find the happiness he deserves. You will be rewarded with a loving and loyal companion for many years to come. P.S. We've discovered that Lucky LOVES to be brushed!\n
label: not-adopted

name: Cooper
description: Cooper is a handsome young dog who hasn't been around many people, so he's a bit shy and fearful. Former owner says if you are patient and go slow, he will be sweet and friendly once he gets to know you. Cooper lived with a smaller dog and a cat and was friendly with both of them, as well a teen-age child. He lost his home through no fault of his own, so now he's wishing and hoping for a new forever home with kind and understanding people who will help him find the happiness he deserves.\n

name: Gus
description: Boy oh boy, you\u2019ll be so excited to meet Gus! \n\nGus is full of love and energy! As soon as he sees you, Gus\u2019 tail does not stop wagging! With his big brown eyes and floppy little ears, Gus already steals your heart with his cuteness. But once you get to know his personality, there\u2019s no way you won\u2019t fall absolutely in love with him! Gus loves to be the center of attention and to him, you are his whole world. He loves to play with other dogs and cats who are willing to play too but will also leave them alone if they don\u2019t feel like being bothered. Gus is working on his house training and crate training and loves to go on walks on the leash. What more could you ask for?! Fill out an application for Gus today at www.snipsa.org!

Juice does take a minute to get used to you but after that initial meeting, he is as sweet as can be! name: Rosetta
description: This is quite the fairy tale! All of these mystical lab mix cuties in this brother and sister family are looking for their permanent homes. These pups are bursting at the seams with lots of love and are more than ready to share it with you. They have quite playful personalities while also having an incredible demeanor. A love for sticks is a mutual occurrence in this litter as they all enjoy romping around in the outdoors. Following an afternoon of play, you can find these cuties curled up for a little snooze! Their fur is almost as soft as their little puppy hearts. If you are looking for a snuggly, adventurous companion, you will not go wrong with any of these fairy friends. name: HARLEY
description: A handsome little 11 lb chihuahua mix, Harley is three main things: cute, fast, and fun! At 9 months, he\u2019s almost full grown, but don\u2019t let his small size fool you - he struts like a big dog! Harley is a healthy little guy with a soft full coat, gorgeous white markings and flashing white socks. He\u2019s quick and loves to run and retrieve; he\u2019ll walk and play as long as you\u2019ll go! Harley is neither yappy nor snappy - he\u2019s a happy little dog that will do well with other dogs, well-behaved gentle children, and adults alike. He\u2019ll also do well with cats when properly introduced. We work by appointment only, so please contact Highland Lakes SPCA at (830) 693-0569 for more information or to set up an interview with one of our dogs.  Our adoption fee includes up-to-date parvo\/distemper series (up to series of three immunizations, depending on the length of time we have had the pet), worming, flea treatment, heartworm test and\/or heartworm preventative treatment, spay\/neuter and rabies immunization.  In compliance with Texas law, this animal has been microchipped. name: OLLIE
description: If you like unique, then Ollie is your guy! A 2 year old brindle corgi\/dachshund mix, he\u2019s a good looking dog with a nice personality to complete the package. Ollie has a sweet personality - he\u2019s not a barky or fussy in any way. He can be a little shy, but loves to be held, petted, walked, played with and is just a great hang out with you guy. Ollie is a strong healthy little guy weighing in at 16 lbs.  He does well with other dogs and will get along with properly introduced cats. He likes to ride in the car and is fantastic on a leash. If you like the look with a special twist, Ollie would love to have a furever home with you. description: With his glorious wealth of hair, intelligence, and energy, Toby is a dog to behold! A 4.5 year old 28 lb Spitz, he\u2019s gorgeous, glamorous, and fun. Spitz are high energy and Toby is no exception; they need boundaries in a caring home. But Toby is outgoing and eager to bond with his new family and will thrive in a loving environment. He\u2019s a happy little guy who enjoys being groomed, loves treats, walks great on a leash and is easy in a car. Toby will do well with older children and well-mannered dogs. Great for an active family that enjoys canine companionship on outings, Toby is just waiting for his family to find him. name: RIO
description: *read\/sing to the tune of Rio Rio by Duran Duran  His name is Rio And he sits, high-fives, and shakes. Just like the goodest boy he shows his love for you And when he shines he really shows you all he can  Oh Rio, Rio wishes for his forever friend! Oh Rio\u2019s family come and let\u2019s go hike the Rio Grande!  Rio has been an absolute doll of an office dog for the last few months with the Animal Protection Officers. He was always excited to have anyone walk into the office and insisted on greeting each and everyone. He never chewed on anything that wasn't explicitly given to him, and even then he wasn't much of a chewer. He does love a well stuffed kong or treats though! The only notable time he took something that wasn't his was when he took a staff member's zip-up hoodie to his bed to sleep with. He didn't do anything but snuggle it, and that is doawn right heart-warming and endearing. He loves to walk and could be a great running\/hiking buddy. We hope a public kennel will help him find his furever home or a lovely foster until that certain someone(s) come along.   For further information and inquires please come to the shelter and meet this sweet boy. His Champion is Hilary, she works here and is the owner of previously mention hoodie, so just ask if she is in and she would be more than happy to come help you get to know this chocolate dream boy! You can also reach out via email to: hilary.shurtleff@americanpetsalive.org.   He would do best in a home with no cats, but a doggy friend could be nice!!

name: Bruce Baryshnikov
description: Bruce Baryshnikov is a lovebug looking for a furever home where he can cuddle in your lap. He is a dog that loves his humans dearly and will happily follow and be by them all day long. Part Basenji, Bruce very rarely barks, and his primary modes of communication are to perk up his head and ears when he hears something of interest (which makes him look like a little fawn) or to make a cute whimper sound. On a scale of 1 to 10 for cuteness, sweetness, and elegance, he's definitely an 11. Bruce's name includes Baryshnikov because he is known to elegantly prance around, leap, and stand on his legs like a ballet dancer. He loves to chew on empty toilet paper rolls, chase balls and play with other pups his size, and he enjoys going on long walks to explore the neighborhood and nature. He's sweetheart with kids, cats, and other dogs, although he can be shy with the bigger ones. Bruce still has some puppy in him and is making good progress on his house-training and does pretty well in a crate. Bruce is nice combination of cuddly and playful and would make a wonderful addition to any number of loving homes. Come meet him!

name: Shelby
description: Meet Shelby!  This girl is so amazingly sweet and her true loving personality has only grown since she was rescued from the shelter with her \u201csister\u201d, Mia, after their owner passed away.  She went from being sad and scared to happy and loving in no time!  If you are looking for two great sweethearts, they may be the ones for you! Shelby is a gorgeous 8 yr old chihuahua\/min pin mix.  Shelby is a little more reserved at first than her \u201csister\u201d, Mia, but once you have gained her trust she will be your best friend!  Most days you will find her relaxing on the top of the couch just waiting for someone to sit down so she can beat the crowd to her favorite spot on their lap.  With her small build, she will be best in a home without really young or very active children though.  She is housebroken and will let you know when she needs to go outside.  She is fully vaccinated, spayed and heartworm positive (nothing to worry about though....her slow kill treatment plan is sponsored and with it we would expect a negative result in 18 months).  Her adoption fee is $90 and includes her shots, spay and balance of slow kill treatment.  If you are interested in this wonderful girl, please visit our website at www.myhappytail.org and download an application.  Please send your application and any questions to myhappytail@yahoo.com.

name: Chloe
description: Happy tail! Whether you're petting her, feeding her, leashing her up for a walk, or introducing her to new human friends and dog friends, Chloe's tail never stops wagging. When she's really excited, she may jump up on you, but she's what we call a "soft jumper", you'll barely notice she's leaning on you. Chloe is healing up from an illness, and as her energy level increases, her easy going nature remains the same. If you need her to spend some time in a crate, she'll go right in, especially for food. However, she's been nothing but perfect outside of her crate when left home alone, so it's probably not even necessary. She adores all people and dogs she meets. She's still a little unsure on cats, but with a proper introduction, she'd probably do just fine. If you're looking for a girl to follow you everywhere and wait patiently for your attention, Chloe's the one! Fill out an application at www.snipsa.org!
label: not-adopted

name: Lilac
description: This precious little girl will bring a smile to your face every day.  She is very fond of giving kisses and having her belly rubbed.  She enjoys playing with a variety of stuffed and chew toys and loves to play new \u2018games\u2019.  She is particularly enjoying fetch and tug of war these days.  She loves her food and treats and is absolutely darling when she is taking her daily naps. She is a quick learner (she sleeps in her crate every night and uses pee pads almost 100% of the time) so continued puppy training will be easy for her new family.  This loving and outgoing puppy will make a wonderful addition to a home with children at least 8 years old.
label: not-adopted

name: Romeo & Lucy
description:
This cute couple are Romeo and Lucy.  As you can see from the pictures, they are a bonded pair.  Romeo is the black Great Dane who is estimated to be about 7 months old, and the little one is Lucy, a buff color female Chihuahua weighing only 8 lbs. 

 These two dogs were dropped off at the Austin Humane Society.  The AHS took the dogs to the Austin Animal shelter and we pulled them to make sure they stay together.

Romeo and Lucy are current on all vaccinations, they are on HW & flea prev., microchipped  and they were also spayed/neutered.   All they need now is a good loving home. 

If you would like to adopt these two adorable dogs, please go to our website and fill out the adoption application.   Keep in mind, our website is having some issues with the on-line application and for some reason we do not receive applications if they are filled out on the smart phone, so please fill out the application on your PC.

He enjoys the company of other dogs, kids and adults.  Rocky is vaccinated, neutered, house trained, heartworm negative and current on flea and heartworm preventative. description:
Characteristic Canines for Special People		
			
MY NAME IS:  Tater
POSTED TO PETFINDER DATE:  April 23, 2019
SIZE: 13 pounds
APPROXIMATE AGE: 1 year
SHELTER STAFF SAYS:  Tator is a very loving do, he loves to be held and petted. . He needs a quiet home with a nice warm lap to lay on .  He rarely barks and walks great on a leash.

Heartworm:  Negative
For more information please call the HCHS at 512-793-5463.  We are open Thursday through Sunday from noon to 4pm and on Monday, Tuesday and Wednesday by appointment only.  You can see all our available animals at HillCountryHumaneSociety.org.
All our adoptable dogs receive a Cap Star for fleas, DHPPV and Bordatella vaccine and are de-wormed.  
When you adopt one of our animals it will be micro chipped and registered at the time of adoption.
While we do our best to determine the breeds of our dogs, the majority are strays, and we have only general appearance, coat type, size, ear type, tail, tongue color and coat color to base breed on.  It is always possible when adopting a puppy that it will change dramatically to look like another breed.
We highly recommend that you enroll your dog in training classes.

name: Mia
description: Meet Mia!  This gorgeous jewel is learning to love again after her owner passed away leaving her and her \u201csister\u201d, Shelby, to find their next forever home!  She is so sweet and loves all the attention she can get!!  If you are looking for two great sweethearts, they may be the ones for you!  Mia is a beautiful 5 yr old chihuahua mix.  While waiting for her perfect forever family, her foster home has lots of playmates her own size to make the days go by faster and cozy laps to curl up in.  With her small build, she will be best in a home without really young or very active children.  She loves warm blankets, lots of love and has learned how to give big hugs to show her appreciation for saving her from the hardship of waiting in the shelter.  She is housebroken and learned how to use the doggie door the first day (although with everyone's small size, is only open during the day when their people are home and can make sure nothing happens while they are outside).  She is fully vaccinated and heartworm negative. Her adoption fee is $90 and includes her shots, spay and a box of heartgard.  If you are interested in this beautiful girl, please visit our website at www.myhappytail.org and download an application.  Please send your application and any questions to myhappytail@yahoo.com.

name: Crystal
description: If you\u2019re looking for the crown jewel of a pup, you have to meet Crystal!\nThis gorgeous lab mix is playful, rambunctious, and happy as can be! Crystal oves to run around and play with any and everyone! As fun-loving as ever, this cutie would make a terrific family dog. She is gentle with others and eager to please so training should be a breeze! After a full day of play, you\u2019ll find Crystal loves nothing more than ending the night snuggling up in your lap. Crystal has been working on her house training and crate training, and this smart girl is making waves! Don\u2019t miss out on these jewel-fill out an application for Crystal today at www.snipsa.org

name: Daisy
description:
Est. DOB: 6/1/05
Hello, we are Daisy & Bailey and are identical twins!  It's pretty hard to tell us apart until you get to know us.  We are sisters and were born in Seguin after our  Mom was dumped in the country. We also have a brother named Max.
The family who owned the property where we were dumped was kind enough to take us in and care for us until we were old enough to start wandering off.  Unfortunately, they didn't have a fence to keep us safe at home so that's when they asked the shelter to take us in and we've been here ever since waiting for our forever homes to find us!
We are really sweet and loving and will be great dogs for kids or anyone who is willing to love us back!
Daisy and Bailey are spayed and current on vaccinations and heartworm prevention.
Click here to complete the adoption questionnaire (link at the top of the page) and email it to: kim@dogsrus.org
Visit our Website for more information about our shelter, adoption policies, and procedures.
 

BAILEY WAS ADOPTED
